    '{"id":"01KFBHZKF154TW56YATE5D2SXF","title":"iCorps + New North Weekly","summary":{"notes":"## **Account-Based Marketing (ABM) Performance and Lead Nurturing**\n\nThe ABM campaign is generating increasing engagement, primarily driven by strong content offers that attract qualified leads.\n\n- **The highly engaged lead list grew to 263**, with new leads coming from the Legal Services campaign and LinkedIn PDF downloads, including two leads who downloaded the \"AI Safety for Law Firms\" guide last week (03:50)  \n    - Ruby confirmed she has begun follow-ups via engaging emails to these leads, maintaining active nurturing despite no immediate conversions  \n    - Nathalie emphasized that content offers, especially PDFs, are the main driver for lead capture, reinforcing the need for strong offers in future campaigns  \n    - Ruby is testing reconversion tactics by sending a quick quiz scorecard as a next step to deepen engagement and encourage meeting bookings  \n    - This nurture strategy aims to convert warm leads over time, building pipeline momentum from initial content interest\n\n- **A key financial services lead, Brandon Lepke, requested outreach in Q1 for IT scaling**, flagged for follow-up now as the quarter begins (05:30)  \n    - This timing aligns with the prospect’s buying cycle, presenting a timely opportunity for targeted outreach  \n    - Ruby will schedule outreach to capitalize on this window, increasing chances of conversion from a warm lead  \n    - This practice exemplifies strategic lead timing to improve sales efficiency and pipeline quality\n\n- **ABM reporting now consolidates LinkedIn messaging, Smart Lead email stats, and paid media campaign metrics**, providing a comprehensive view of lead generation and engagement (06:20)  \n    - Metrics include connection acceptance rates, message reply rates, email sends, opens, replies, and paid campaign performance  \n    - Ruby plans to present these integrated metrics to her team, supporting data-driven decision-making and campaign adjustments  \n    - The unified dashboard aids in pinpointing strong channels and optimizing resource allocation\n\n## **SEO and Organic Growth Progress**\n\nSEO efforts are delivering rapid improvements in keyword rankings, boosting organic visibility and traffic.\n\n- **The New York location page reached 4th place and the real estate page jumped from 6th to 3rd in search rankings within about two weeks** (07:55)  \n    - This fast ranking increase shows effective targeting of localized keywords and content relevance  \n    - Ruby will share these quick wins with Jeff and Mike to demonstrate SEO’s tangible impact on site authority  \n    - Nathalie highlighted monthly search volume data to prioritize keyword focus and content development  \n    - These gains support broader organic growth goals and improve lead inflows from search\n\n- **SEO content updates are underway including new AI assessment pages and Microsoft Copilot consulting edits**, expanding topical coverage to support emerging service lines (08:45)  \n    - Nathalie sent preview pages with visual highlights for feedback, speeding review and iteration  \n    - This content expansion aligns with product evolution and market demand around AI readiness and technology consulting\n\n- **Monthly keyword tracking faces API limitations, so manual CSV exports will provide rising/falling keyword data for ongoing optimization** (17:45)  \n    - Monthly CSV reports will help identify topic trends and guide blog and campaign planning  \n    - Ruby emphasized the need for updated keyword lists to refresh existing blogs and plan new content for the year  \n    - This approach balances new content creation with targeted updates to maintain SEO relevance\n\n## **Marketing Dashboard Development and Data Insights**\n\nA draft executive dashboard consolidates key marketing metrics, with planned enhancements to improve lead qualification visibility.\n\n- **The dashboard currently shows total MQLs for last year, current SQL counts, conversion rates, and top marketing lead sources from HubSpot** (09:45)  \n    - Ruby requested filtering by custom lead source to isolate marketing-attributed leads like content, SEO, paid, and email channels  \n    - Nathalie confirmed this customization is feasible and will implement it to sharpen performance insights  \n    - This granularity helps track the true impact of marketing efforts on pipeline generation\n\n- **Ruby proposed adding a block showing detailed reasons why leads are unqualified, such as out of country, spam, or timing issues, to clarify lead quality** (13:00)  \n    - Nathalie agreed to present unqualified lead reasons alongside counts of qualified leads to improve conversion rate accuracy  \n    - This will help the team better understand lead funnel health and refine qualification criteria  \n    - Including lead status and detail fields provides actionable insights into lead disposition\n\n- **Access to the dashboard will be via a simple link without requiring login to Pulse, ensuring ease of use for stakeholders** (20:30)  \n    - Ruby noted that leadership is unlikely to access dashboards independently, so centralized, meeting-based reviews remain key  \n    - Flexibility in date filtering allows for tailored reporting over different timeframes, supporting regular performance check-ins\n\n## **Branding and Account Management Updates**\n\nThe company is transitioning branding and HubSpot account usage to align with the Marketers in Demand identity.\n\n- **The HubSpot account used for partnership will shift from productionewnorth.com to production at Marketers in Demand, managed by Colin** (22:00)  \n    - Nathalie clarified that Marketers in Demand is the overarching brand for client engagements, while New North remains a recognized agency name for growth marketing searches (23:00)  \n    - This dual-brand strategy balances market recognition and internal consistency  \n    - Ruby and Samuel will coordinate with Colin if any system changes are required during the transition\n\n- **The rebranding effort reflects a strategic positioning to differentiate service offerings by channel and audience while unifying client experience under one umbrella** (23:15)  \n    - This clarity helps streamline marketing messages and internal team alignment  \n    - It supports long-term brand equity building and client trust\n\n## **Content Planning and Campaign Alignment**\n\nContent strategy will emphasize AI readiness and targeted topics, leveraging keyword research and campaign integration.\n\n- **Keyword research for AI and other content buckets will be completed and shared by end of day to support Ruby’s presentation and campaign planning** (19:30)  \n    - Nathalie will deliver updated keyword lists to guide blog topics and content refresh priorities  \n    - This supports coordinated marketing efforts to capitalize on trending themes and improve SEO relevance  \n    - Ruby’s plan includes aligning blogs with ABM campaigns for consistent messaging and lead nurturing\n\n- **The team recognizes that updating existing blogs is as important as creating new ones to maintain topical authority and SEO performance** (19:50)  \n    - This approach maximizes resource efficiency and leverages past content investments  \n    - It helps keep the content library fresh and aligned with evolving market interests\n\n- **Preview pages for AI assessment and development content have been circulated for feedback, accelerating content deployment timelines** (08:50)  \n    - Visual cues in previews help streamline review cycles  \n    - Rapid iteration ensures timely support for emerging business priorities in AI consulting and assessments","outline":null,"keywords":["ABM Campaign","SEO Performance","Executive Dashboard","Lead Nurturing","Keyword Research","HubSpot Integration"],"overview":"- **ABM Performance**: Lead list grew to 263; strong content offers drive engagement, with follow-ups ongoing.\n\n- **Targeted Outreach**: Financial lead Brandon Lepke flagged for Q1 follow-up, aligning with buying cycle for better conversion chances.\n\n- **SEO Success**: New York page up to 4th and real estate page to 3rd; rapid keyword ranking improvements enhance organic traffic.\n\n- **Marketing Dashboard**: Draft dashboard includes MQLs and SQL counts; custom filtering planned for better lead source tracking.\n\n- **Rebranding Transition**: HubSpot account shifting to Marketers in Demand brand, aiming for unified client experience and clear service differentiation.\n\n- **Content Strategy**: Focus on AI readiness and updating existing blogs; keyword research to support aligned messaging in campaigns.","action_items":"\n**Nathalie Mintjens**\nSend note and contact details for Brandon Lepke for Q1 Financial Services follow-up (06:20)\nShare ABM reports including LinkedIn, email, and paid media campaign stats with Ruby for team presentations (06:20)\nImplement Microsoft Copilot consulting page edits as received from Jeff (07:25)\nProvide keyword research data and CSV keyword status reports for blog planning and AI content campaigns by the end of the day (19:00)\nFinalize and send the draft executive dashboard to Ruby, incorporating custom lead source filters and including lead detail blocks for unqualified reasons (09:20)\nConfirm dashboard access method and send relevant links to Ruby and team (20:30)\nFollow up with Colin Costigan on HubSpot account change process for Marketers in Demand branding (22:00)\nSend all related links and keyword research files after meeting (23:40)\n\n**Ruby Pontbriand**\nPresent ABM campaign metrics and updates to internal team and meetings with Mike, Jeff, and Cook (07:26)\nProvide feedback on draft executive dashboard and requested data fields for lead details and conversion insights (12:30)\nIncorporate keyword data into blog and campaign planning for the year, focusing on AI readiness and updating older blog content (18:50)\n"},"duration":24.610000610351562,"speakers":[{"id":0,"name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"id":1,"name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"id":2,"name":"Samuel Bagnall"}],"sentences":[{"text":"Sam.","index":0,"end_time":51.07,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":25.77,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Hello, Natalie.","index":1,"end_time":70.38,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":69.38,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"How you doing?","index":2,"end_time":70.98,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":70.38,"speaker_name":"Samuel Bagnall"},{"text":"Good.","index":3,"end_time":72.14,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":71.78,"speaker_name":"Samuel Bagnall"},{"text":"How are you doing?","index":4,"end_time":73.82,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":72.14,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Good.","index":5,"end_time":74.18,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":73.82,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"How''s the week going?","index":6,"end_time":78.59,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":77.71,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Did you guys have Monday off?","index":7,"end_time":81.87,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":79.47,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"It''s a floating holiday for us.","index":8,"end_time":85.19,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":83.63,"speaker_name":"Samuel Bagnall"},{"text":"So we can choose.","index":9,"end_time":86.03,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":85.19,"speaker_name":"Samuel Bagnall"},{"text":"So some people had it off.","index":10,"end_time":88.03,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":86.99,"speaker_name":"Samuel Bagnall"},{"text":"Me and Ruby did not.","index":11,"end_time":89.15,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":88.03,"speaker_name":"Samuel Bagnall"},{"text":"Oh, okay.","index":12,"end_time":90.59,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":89.79,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":13,"end_time":91.27,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":90.83,"speaker_name":"Samuel Bagnall"},{"text":"So we can choose between.","index":14,"end_time":92.27,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":91.27,"speaker_name":"Samuel Bagnall"},{"text":"Was it MLK Day?","index":15,"end_time":94.99,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":93.39,"speaker_name":"Samuel Bagnall"},{"text":"President Stay and Juneteenth.","index":16,"end_time":96.51,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":94.99,"speaker_name":"Samuel Bagnall"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":17,"end_time":98.15,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":97.79,"speaker_name":"Samuel Bagnall"},{"text":"What about you?","index":18,"end_time":98.63,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":98.15,"speaker_name":"Samuel Bagnall"},{"text":"Do you have it off?","index":19,"end_time":99.39,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":98.63,"speaker_name":"Samuel Bagnall"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":20,"end_time":100.27,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":99.79,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Okay.","index":21,"end_time":101.39,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":100.75,"speaker_name":"Samuel Bagnall"},{"text":"I actually didn''t realize until like the Friday before.","index":22,"end_time":105.48,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":102.44,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Do anything fun or just hang out or.","index":23,"end_time":109.96,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":108.12,"speaker_name":"Samuel Bagnall"},{"text":"No, it was just a Monday reset kind of day.","index":24,"end_time":114.84,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":110.92,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Just cleaning and stuff.","index":25,"end_time":116.44,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":115,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":26,"end_time":118.6,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":118.12,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"That''S all right.","index":27,"end_time":121.48,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":120.68,"speaker_name":"Samuel Bagnall"},{"text":"Always good.","index":28,"end_time":122.6,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":121.88,"speaker_name":"Samuel Bagnall"},{"text":"Oh, that''s.","index":29,"end_time":123.56,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":122.76,"speaker_name":"Samuel Bagnall"},{"text":"Oh, sorry.","index":30,"end_time":125.84,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":124.92,"speaker_name":"Samuel Bagnall"},{"text":"I think I emailed you.","index":31,"end_time":127,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":125.84,"speaker_name":"Samuel Bagnall"},{"text":"I didn''t realize you were off on Monday.","index":32,"end_time":128.36,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":127,"speaker_name":"Samuel Bagnall"},{"text":"So I emailed you and said, hey, did you get this?","index":33,"end_time":130.56,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":128.44,"speaker_name":"Samuel Bagnall"},{"text":"I think and you were like, yeah, I got it.","index":34,"end_time":132.83,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":130.56,"speaker_name":"Samuel Bagnall"},{"text":"Was that.","index":35,"end_time":133.51,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":133.07,"speaker_name":"Samuel Bagnall"},{"text":"No, no.","index":36,"end_time":133.95,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":133.51,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Okay.","index":37,"end_time":135.31,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":134.83,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Sorry.","index":38,"end_time":135.63,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":135.31,"speaker_name":"Samuel Bagnall"},{"text":"I don''t know if that was Monday.","index":39,"end_time":136.55,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":135.63,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"I don''t know.","index":40,"end_time":137.23,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":136.55,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Okay.","index":41,"end_time":138.27,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":137.87,"speaker_name":"Samuel Bagnall"},{"text":"I thought, I thought it was like Monday and I was like, oh, I think I pay attention.","index":42,"end_time":142.03,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":138.27,"speaker_name":"Samuel Bagnall"},{"text":"Didn''t realize it was.","index":43,"end_time":143.07,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":142.03,"speaker_name":"Samuel Bagnall"},{"text":"Some people had it off.","index":44,"end_time":144.51,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":143.39,"speaker_name":"Samuel Bagnall"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":45,"end_time":145.23,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":144.75,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Hey guys.","index":46,"end_time":148.83,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":148.11,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"Good morning.","index":47,"end_time":149.31,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":148.83,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"Hey, how are you?","index":48,"end_time":151.87,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":149.63,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Good, how are you?","index":49,"end_time":153.07,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":152.19,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"Good, Excellent.","index":50,"end_time":155.87,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":153.79,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Just grabbing a cup of coffee and then I''ll be switching onto my laptop.","index":51,"end_time":160.82,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":157.3,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"Okay, no worries.","index":52,"end_time":163.86,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":161.62,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"I''ll pull up the deck.","index":53,"end_time":167.14,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":165.62,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"So just looking at our points so far for the month, still have 59 more in working.","index":54,"end_time":177.3,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":171.3,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"So these are just the monthly management tasks which will all close out on the 31st.","index":55,"end_time":183.3,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":177.38,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"That''ll be 59 points and then for ABM.","index":56,"end_time":189.71,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":184.63,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"So our highly engaged lead list has jumped up to 263.","index":57,"end_time":194.31,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":189.71,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"I went into it to look.","index":58,"end_time":196.15,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":194.63,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"So it looks like we''re getting our first few ones from the Legal Services campaign and then also others that are coming in from some of the PDF downloads from LinkedIn.","index":59,"end_time":206.95,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":196.15,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"And then I saw that we got two additional leads in this past week for Legal Services and both of them downloaded that AI Safety for Law Firms guide on LinkedIn.","index":60,"end_time":219.62,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":207.99,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"And then I saw Ruby that you already did follow up with them with the emails.","index":61,"end_time":223.98,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":219.62,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"I think that the, the emails are really good.","index":62,"end_time":225.98,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":223.98,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"It''s engaging.","index":63,"end_time":228.3,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":227.34,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"And then yeah, we did see that one that ended up going to the Contact Us page or the meeting age.","index":64,"end_time":235.99,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":228.38,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Yeah, no conversion yet, but I think we just keep nurturing and getting in front of them.","index":65,"end_time":242.31,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":237.83,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"They''ll start to convert.","index":66,"end_time":244.31,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":243.03,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Yeah, I got a couple in also this morning too that I still need to do follow ups on.","index":67,"end_time":252.39,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":245.59,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"But yeah, it''s looking good.","index":68,"end_time":254.19,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":252.47,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"I''m glad we''re getting some.","index":69,"end_time":255.27,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":254.19,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"Yeah, awesome.","index":70,"end_time":257.91,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":255.83,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"It looks like.","index":71,"end_time":259.87,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":259.27,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Yeah, there.","index":72,"end_time":260.39,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":259.87,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"It''s definitely the content that''s drawing them in like pretty much all of them that we''ve got is from some sort of PDF or some sort of offer that we''ve given them.","index":73,"end_time":270.04,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":260.63,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"So yeah, I think that''s what we''ve learned from last past campaigns too is we have, we need a strong offer in order to get them through the door and then continue nurturing.","index":74,"end_time":278.2,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":270.12,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Yeah, what I''m doing in some of.","index":75,"end_time":282.76,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":278.92,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"My follow ups like for the AI.","index":76,"end_time":284.36,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":282.76,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Readiness ones are like cool you downloaded the tool or hey, thanks for downloading like the AI safety for law firms.","index":77,"end_time":292.36,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":284.84,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"But also like here''s that like a next cool step is like take this super quick quiz to get your scorecard and I like send them the scorecard link so that in hopes of like it''s a reconversion and that they do the scorecard we get more info from them and maybe book the meeting too.","index":78,"end_time":314.72,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":294.08,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"Yeah, I think that''s great.","index":79,"end_time":317.44,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":315.28,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Awesome.","index":80,"end_time":319.13,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":318.73,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"And then I did see.","index":81,"end_time":321.29,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":319.61,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Sorry, that''s my cat.","index":82,"end_time":323.45,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":322.49,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"There''s so many cats.","index":83,"end_time":324.41,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":323.45,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"I did make a note a while ago, so while we were doing the financial services on.","index":84,"end_time":331.61,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":326.81,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Oh, am I lagging?","index":85,"end_time":336.89,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":335.45,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Sorry, I was probably breaking up for a second.","index":86,"end_time":342.01,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":340.33,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"Okay.","index":87,"end_time":344.26,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":343.86,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"For the financial services campaign, I did make a note a while ago that there was someone called Brandon Lepke.","index":88,"end_time":354.66,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":346.74,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"We had sent one of the first few messages to him and he asked us to reach back out in Q1 of this year saying that that''s likely when his company is going to be looking at scaling up their IT solutions.","index":89,"end_time":367.38,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":354.82,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"So just wanted to flag this one.","index":90,"end_time":369.62,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":367.7,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"I can send the note or the name to you after as well, that maybe now would be a good time to reach back out to him.","index":91,"end_time":376.01,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":369.94,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Okay, awesome.","index":92,"end_time":380.89,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":380.01,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"Thank you.","index":93,"end_time":381.37,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":380.89,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":94,"end_time":382.97,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":382.49,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"And then so last week we did talk about the ABM report as well for you.","index":95,"end_time":391.01,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":385.21,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"So we put pulled everything together here, I''ll send this sheet over to you.","index":96,"end_time":395.05,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":391.01,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"So we have hey, reach so LinkedIn messages looking at construction and financial services.","index":97,"end_time":402.18,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":395.85,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"So we looked at the total number of leads, the connection accepted acceptance rates, the message reply rate, and then the actual numbers here.","index":98,"end_time":413.78,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":402.5,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"And then we did the same thing for Smart Lead, which is our email stats.","index":99,"end_time":418.74,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":414.82,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"So for all of the campaigns, the number of emails that were sent, opened, replied, and then we also broke it down by each individual email.","index":100,"end_time":429.51,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":418.74,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"And then for paid media as well, we just pulled in all the stats for every campaign that we had running.","index":101,"end_time":437.83,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":432.87,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"So I know you said that you''re going to be presenting to your team, so hopefully these numbers are helpful.","index":102,"end_time":443.67,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":437.91,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Yeah, this is awesome.","index":103,"end_time":447.51,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":446.47,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"Thank you.","index":104,"end_time":448.07,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":447.51,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Sure.","index":105,"end_time":449.35,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":448.95,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"All right.","index":106,"end_time":452.96,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":452.56,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"And then for SEO, so I received the edits from Jeff again yesterday for this Microsoft Copilot consulting page.","index":107,"end_time":461.84,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":452.96,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"So we''ll work on making those updates.","index":108,"end_time":466,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":463.2,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"And then also yesterday I was looking at the rank tracker, something really cool.","index":109,"end_time":472.84,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":467.6,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"The location page that we published, the New York one, we''re now ranking fourth for that, for this keyword.","index":110,"end_time":479.43,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":472.84,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"So that was pretty quick.","index":111,"end_time":481.91,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":480.79,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"I like that.","index":112,"end_time":483.75,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":482.95,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"Yeah, that was like two weeks ago or something.","index":113,"end_time":487.35,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":484.87,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"But we''re already ranking, which is cool.","index":114,"end_time":489.35,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":487.43,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"And then for this, for the real estate page as well, we were sixth place and now it jumped up to third place.","index":115,"end_time":498.87,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":491.67,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"That''s really good.","index":116,"end_time":503.04,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":502.16,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"I want to share that with Jeff or I''ll share it with Jeff and Mike to bring that full circle because we talked a lot about SEO and about the keywords and how does this work and how does it really benefit us?","index":117,"end_time":519.68,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":503.04,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"So this will be a great example of a quick win, right?","index":118,"end_time":524.08,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":519.68,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":119,"end_time":524.64,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":524.16,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"And then this is the monthly search volume.","index":120,"end_time":526.96,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":524.8,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"So how many searches the they each of these keywords get per month.","index":121,"end_time":530.67,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":526.96,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Awesome.","index":122,"end_time":535.07,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":534.43,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"And then for our additional projects, so I sent over those preview pages, the assessment page and the development and AI page that now includes like information about the AI assessments.","index":123,"end_time":550.23,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":536.75,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"And then I send it over with like images that have it circled in red so you can see what was newly added.","index":124,"end_time":556.48,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":550.23,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"So just let me know if you guys have any feedback on that.","index":125,"end_time":561.28,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":557.04,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Awesome.","index":126,"end_time":562.72,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":562.08,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"Thank you.","index":127,"end_time":564.08,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":563.44,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"And then I.","index":128,"end_time":567.04,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":565.84,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"So I didn''t receive the email or the information from Jeff on the specific stats that he wanted to see that we talked about last week.","index":129,"end_time":574.4,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":567.2,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"But we just put this first like draft executive dashboard together which includes like what we think they''d want to see.","index":130,"end_time":583.47,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":575.52,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"So this first slide is just a complete overview.","index":131,"end_time":586.79,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":583.47,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"So this is the total.","index":132,"end_time":588.55,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":587.59,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"You can change the dates for all of these.","index":133,"end_time":591.27,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":589.03,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Total number of MQLs for last year.","index":134,"end_time":594.79,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":592.15,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"This is the current number of contacts with the SQL lifecycle stage.","index":135,"end_time":601.99,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":597.59,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"And then here we showed SQLs and opportunities specifically that have marketing sources in Hubson.","index":136,"end_time":609.6,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":602.39,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"So not counting other things like from sales and stuff like that.","index":137,"end_time":613.12,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":610.08,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"And then for the date range, the conversion rate from MQL to SQL and then our top lead sources, I''m thinking for this one might be more helpful.","index":138,"end_time":626.76,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":615.28,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"If we use the custom lead source in HubSpot, is that correct?","index":139,"end_time":629.84,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":626.76,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"And that''s where it will show like LinkedIn specifically or.","index":140,"end_time":633.44,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":629.84,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Okay, yeah, yeah, that would be great.","index":141,"end_time":635.88,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":633.44,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"And then if it''s possible to.","index":142,"end_time":638,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":635.88,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"Yeah, do custom lead source and then if it''s possible to include or like not include certain ones, is that possible on the back end of it?","index":143,"end_time":648.72,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":640.32,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"Yeah, I think it should be okay.","index":144,"end_time":650.88,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":649.04,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"It would be great if we could do custom lead source is any of the ones that we are for marketing.","index":145,"end_time":662.09,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":651.68,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"Just.","index":146,"end_time":662.73,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":662.33,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Just marketing.","index":147,"end_time":663.85,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":662.89,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":148,"end_time":664.61,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":664.17,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"Okay.","index":149,"end_time":665.21,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":664.61,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"So like content SEO, any of the paid email.","index":150,"end_time":672.25,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":665.53,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"Okay.","index":151,"end_time":674.33,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":673.77,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Okay.","index":152,"end_time":679.61,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":678.97,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"That might also awesome.","index":153,"end_time":682.25,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":680.97,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"That also might.","index":154,"end_time":683.45,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":682.41,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"Helpful.","index":155,"end_time":687.14,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":686.66,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"I think on that block to the left there total current opportunities and then SQLs for those sources.","index":156,"end_time":696.22,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":687.22,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"If we could do custom lead source, that would be really good.","index":157,"end_time":698.98,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":696.22,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"Okay.","index":158,"end_time":700.66,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":700.02,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"And see.","index":159,"end_time":707.06,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":704.82,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"Perfect.","index":160,"end_time":710.1,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":709.62,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"I do have one other thing.","index":161,"end_time":714.51,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":713.31,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"It''s a wish like a.","index":162,"end_time":717.63,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":715.95,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"If I could ask for one more little block would be.","index":163,"end_time":721.23,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":718.03,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"Total something.","index":164,"end_time":726.43,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":725.55,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"Right.","index":165,"end_time":727.07,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":726.67,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"But with the ability to show the lead detail.","index":166,"end_time":734.19,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":728.43,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"Because lead detail shows like where it ended up or like where it.","index":167,"end_time":742.12,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":738.04,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"It''s kind of like.","index":168,"end_time":744.2,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":743.32,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"Kind of like lead status.","index":169,"end_time":745.48,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":744.2,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"But it''s like in the event that lead status were unqualified, then lead detail would say why?","index":170,"end_time":752.76,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":746.76,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"For like it would say like out of the country spam procurement vendor.","index":171,"end_time":760.44,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":755.4,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"Like all the, you know, because I think out of that, like the 1800, like the 1800 MQLs.","index":172,"end_time":768.69,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":760.44,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"That''s cool number.","index":173,"end_time":773.25,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":771.81,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"But that''s all in which is fine because we do need like that benchmark.","index":174,"end_time":778.93,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":773.89,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"But I think they''re going to want to know is like they know for sure.","index":175,"end_time":782.85,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":779.73,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"Oh God.","index":176,"end_time":783.53,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":782.93,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":177,"end_time":783.93,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":783.53,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"Like 1800 MQLs definitely did not like not all those MQLs were, you know, hand raisers that were ready to talk to sales.","index":178,"end_time":793.92,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":783.93,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":179,"end_time":795.36,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":794.88,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"And the way that top reasons why they''re unqualified is what.","index":180,"end_time":800.76,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":795.68,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"What you''d want to see.","index":181,"end_time":801.76,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":800.76,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Yeah, maybe.","index":182,"end_time":803.76,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":802.56,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"And then the number of ones that actually were legit.","index":183,"end_time":808.8,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":804.799,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"Right.","index":184,"end_time":809.36,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":809.04,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"Like the ones that don''t have that were basically do like lead detail is none of.","index":185,"end_time":816.08,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":809.36,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"Or.","index":186,"end_time":817.5,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":817.26,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Sorry, hold on my brain.","index":187,"end_time":821.26,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":819.9,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"I know it''s hard to visualize lead.","index":188,"end_time":824.94,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":822.86,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Does lead detail only get added if they''re unqualified?","index":189,"end_time":830.06,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":824.94,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"No.","index":190,"end_time":832.06,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":831.66,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"Okay.","index":191,"end_time":834.06,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":833.42,"speaker_name":"Samuel Bagnall"},{"text":"So yeah, so like lead detail is usually like where they''re at or if they''re.","index":192,"end_time":847.83,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":843.19,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"All right, sorry, let me slow this down.","index":193,"end_time":851.03,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":849.03,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"Custom lead status is the property that shows where they are in the lifecycle stage process.","index":194,"end_time":866.87,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":852.39,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"For example, how like if we followed up, how many times have we contacted them?","index":195,"end_time":875.84,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":869.44,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"Did a meeting get booked?","index":196,"end_time":877.28,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":875.84,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"Was a meeting held?","index":197,"end_time":878.48,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":877.28,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"Are they unqualified?","index":198,"end_time":880.24,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":879.04,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"And then if they''re unqualified, that''s when we would do like lead detail is either not a fit for timing or they went dark or it was spam or they were out of the country or whatever reason it is that they''re not moving forward through the pipeline.","index":199,"end_time":900.38,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":881.12,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"Okay.","index":200,"end_time":901.82,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":901.18,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"And I guess what I''m saying for that for like this dashboard is.","index":201,"end_time":910.54,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":906.14,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"It could be presented like a list like this.","index":202,"end_time":917.98,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":915.34,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":203,"end_time":919.1,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":918.7,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"Because they''re not.","index":204,"end_time":920.46,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":919.1,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"It''s not a free form.","index":205,"end_time":922.26,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":921.02,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Right.","index":206,"end_time":922.54,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":922.26,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"You have to select one.","index":207,"end_time":923.82,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":922.54,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"You have to select.","index":208,"end_time":924.78,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":923.98,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":209,"end_time":926.59,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":926.27,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"So it could just be presented like this.","index":210,"end_time":928.15,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":926.59,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"And then the total number.","index":211,"end_time":929.23,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":928.15,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Okay, yeah, that would be cool.","index":212,"end_time":933.87,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":930.03,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"We could just do those.","index":213,"end_time":934.83,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":933.87,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"So custom lead status and then lead detail would be cool to put it.","index":214,"end_time":940.67,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":934.83,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"Okay.","index":215,"end_time":943.95,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":943.39,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"And then maybe a block that just shows all of the MQLs that were not unqualified.","index":216,"end_time":950.27,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":944.59,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"Okay.","index":217,"end_time":954.2,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":953.72,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Because that I think impacts the conversion rate and all that stuff too.","index":218,"end_time":970.32,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":964.12,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"Right?","index":219,"end_time":970.68,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":970.32,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":220,"end_time":974.36,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":973.88,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Okay, we''ll get that updated.","index":221,"end_time":984.37,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":979.89,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"And then we have SEO and organic performance on the second slide.","index":222,"end_time":991.49,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":987.09,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"So this is the amount of organic traffic that came to the website.","index":223,"end_time":995.41,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":991.65,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"And then the top organic pages.","index":224,"end_time":997.89,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":995.97,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Yep.","index":225,"end_time":999.57,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":998.93,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"Over here.","index":226,"end_time":1000.29,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":999.57,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"And then we were also able to pull in AI search as well.","index":227,"end_time":1006.13,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1001.97,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"So these are the top pages that are bringing in visitors from AI tools.","index":228,"end_time":1012.9,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1008.18,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Very cool.","index":229,"end_time":1014.02,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1013.3,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"Yeah, like that.","index":230,"end_time":1015.46,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1014.34,"speaker_name":"Samuel Bagnall"},{"text":"Right.","index":231,"end_time":1018.98,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1018.58,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"And then paid media as well.","index":232,"end_time":1022.58,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1020.02,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"So we kept this very high level.","index":233,"end_time":1024.34,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1022.66,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Like if.","index":234,"end_time":1026.82,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1026.18,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Or Cook.","index":235,"end_time":1029.78,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1029.22,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"Yeah, yeah, Cook.","index":236,"end_time":1031.94,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1030.66,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"Or Cook.","index":237,"end_time":1032.42,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1031.94,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"I always get Kirk, Chris, Cook.","index":238,"end_time":1034.58,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1032.42,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"It''s so confusing.","index":239,"end_time":1035.78,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1034.66,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"If Cook were coming in, you just want to see like these top.","index":240,"end_time":1041.01,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1037.41,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"These top numbers, but if he wants to see anything else, we can add it in as well.","index":241,"end_time":1044.85,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1041.65,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Oh, and then only thing for SEO, we couldn''t add in the.","index":242,"end_time":1053.41,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1049.33,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"The rising and falling keywords for some reason, like the.","index":243,"end_time":1057.89,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1053.73,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"The API between Data box and Ahrefs just doesn''t allow us to do that.","index":244,"end_time":1062.77,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1058.45,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"But what we can do is like on a monthly basis, just pull a CSV file for you and show you the status of all keywords.","index":245,"end_time":1070.78,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1063.33,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Yeah, that''d be really helpful.","index":246,"end_time":1072.94,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1071.58,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"I was also going to ask about keywords just because we''re wanting to do like, get some blogs planned out for the year.","index":247,"end_time":1082.7,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1073.98,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"Not necessarily like a ton of like, new north blogs, but just like our, like, you know, usual blog content that we do and wanting them to be.","index":248,"end_time":1090.7,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1083.66,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"We have like a chunk of them that are around AI readiness that are already kind of like in the works to support the ABM campaign.","index":249,"end_time":1099.11,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1090.78,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"But we also wanted to do have like that updated list of keywords to see what''s, you know, what''s popular, what should we be writing blogs about?","index":250,"end_time":1111.39,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1100.31,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"You know, or if there are.","index":251,"end_time":1113.67,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1111.39,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"Because we also have like a lot of older blogs and if those blogs are on content or topics that are surrounding those really popular keywords, that''s how we could identify which blogs to update and like bring into the current present day.","index":252,"end_time":1136.04,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1115.43,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"Because some of them are old.","index":253,"end_time":1137.2,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1136.04,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"Yeah, I mean, they''re old.","index":254,"end_time":1140.2,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1138.48,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"The minute they get two days after they''re published, they''re old.","index":255,"end_time":1142.48,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1140.2,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"But you know what I mean?","index":256,"end_time":1144.32,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1142.48,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"And then also Just planning like, you know, chunks of topics for the year, like, oh, we know this is a really hot.","index":257,"end_time":1151.6,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1145.52,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"Or also planning campaigns for the year.","index":258,"end_time":1153.84,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1151.6,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"So yeah, if you could send that Ahrefs thing, CSV at some point, maybe even today, if you could, maybe by the end of the day, that''d be really cool.","index":259,"end_time":1168,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1158.8,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"I''d like to include it for what I''m presenting for tomorrow.","index":260,"end_time":1174.16,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1169.2,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"Okay.","index":261,"end_time":1175.94,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1175.46,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Yes, I''ll do as much as I can today.","index":262,"end_time":1179.54,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1177.38,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":263,"end_time":1182.1,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1181.78,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"And I think when we also went to that, that online webinar, they did mention that like, updating blogs you already have is just as important as creating new ones.","index":264,"end_time":1192.82,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1182.1,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"So yeah, I''ll do some keyword research.","index":265,"end_time":1195.82,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1193.7,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"I''ll send you a list of like, of ones that are popular for AI.","index":266,"end_time":1199.9,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1195.82,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"And then also the other, the other buckets that we have in our content plan.","index":267,"end_time":1204.61,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1199.9,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Okay, perfect.","index":268,"end_time":1206.13,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1205.09,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"All right, so I''ll send this dashboard to you.","index":269,"end_time":1211.65,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1208.61,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Over to you for now anyway.","index":270,"end_time":1213.21,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1211.65,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"And then we''ll also work on making those updates.","index":271,"end_time":1215.17,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1213.21,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"All right.","index":272,"end_time":1216.29,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1215.81,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"And then in terms of accessing the dashboard down the line, I know it''s like obviously they''re still in draft or whatever, but you know, say we get this all finalized and they''re like, yep, we love it.","index":273,"end_time":1227.97,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1217.25,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"How do they get access them?","index":274,"end_time":1230.35,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1228.37,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"So just to this dashboard.","index":275,"end_time":1233.63,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1232.11,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":276,"end_time":1234.99,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1234.59,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Or.","index":277,"end_time":1235.31,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1234.99,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Yeah, this one.","index":278,"end_time":1236.59,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1235.31,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"Yeah, it''s just with this link.","index":279,"end_time":1238.75,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1237.15,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Okay.","index":280,"end_time":1239.63,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1239.07,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"So there''s no like, you don''t have to like log into Pulse or.","index":281,"end_time":1243.95,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1239.63,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"No, but we can add it there if that''s easier as well.","index":282,"end_time":1248.79,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1245.389,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Or they could like literally just bookmark the link and it''ll.","index":283,"end_time":1251.59,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1248.79,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Yeah, whatever is easiest.","index":284,"end_time":1252.91,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1251.59,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"I just didn''t want them to have to like log into Pulse and then do this.","index":285,"end_time":1256.33,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1252.91,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"They''ll never do that.","index":286,"end_time":1257.37,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1256.49,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"And honestly, they''re probably not going to look at these dashboards on their own as often as it even really matters to talk about.","index":287,"end_time":1266.01,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1257.45,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"It''s just, it was just a question.","index":288,"end_time":1268.33,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1266.89,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"It''s a.","index":289,"end_time":1269.41,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1268.81,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"It.","index":290,"end_time":1269.77,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1269.41,"speaker_name":"Samuel Bagnall"},{"text":"Ultimately it will be me meeting with Mike and Jeff and Cook on our off weeks of like, you know, they.","index":291,"end_time":1279.33,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1271.53,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"They''re.","index":292,"end_time":1279.85,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1279.33,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"Mike and Jeff will come to our meeting next week.","index":293,"end_time":1282.25,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1280.09,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"Next, like Wednesday.","index":294,"end_time":1284.04,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1283.32,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"And then the following Wednesday when they don''t come is when I would meet with Mike and Cook and Jeff and review like where things are at.","index":295,"end_time":1291.72,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1284.12,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"Yeah, but this is good, like high level stuff.","index":296,"end_time":1295.96,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1292.52,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"We can change the dates.","index":297,"end_time":1296.96,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1295.96,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"So if they want to see just like, how do we do last week?","index":298,"end_time":1299.32,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1296.96,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"Or how do we do whatever that is.","index":299,"end_time":1303.12,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1299.32,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"Awesome.","index":300,"end_time":1303.64,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1303.12,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"Excuse me.","index":301,"end_time":1307.72,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1307.08,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"Thank you.","index":302,"end_time":1309.57,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1309.09,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Great.","index":303,"end_time":1311.97,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1311.57,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"And then lastly, so one note that Colin wanted to send along is we''d like to change our account that''s partnered with you on HubSpot.","index":304,"end_time":1322.85,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1312.37,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Right now we''re just using our productionewnorth.com account and we just like to change it to production at Marketers in Demand.","index":305,"end_time":1329.73,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1323.33,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"I don''t think there''s anything for you to do.","index":306,"end_time":1333.05,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1331.09,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"I think Colin would handle it.","index":307,"end_time":1334.25,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1333.05,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"But just for your own information, so if you see something come through, you''re not alarmed.","index":308,"end_time":1339.61,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1334.25,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Yep.","index":309,"end_time":1340.65,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1340.09,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"All right, that''s fine.","index":310,"end_time":1343.65,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1342.41,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"So you don''t need us to go in and update the user?","index":311,"end_time":1346.17,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1343.65,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"I don''t think so, but I''ll let you know.","index":312,"end_time":1349.09,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1346.81,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"I''ll check in with Colin.","index":313,"end_time":1350.17,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1349.09,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"All right.","index":314,"end_time":1351.05,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1350.57,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Yeah, I''m not sure if I''m able to do it, but we''ll.","index":315,"end_time":1354.45,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1351.689,"speaker_name":"Samuel Bagnall"},{"text":"Yeah, just let us know.","index":316,"end_time":1355.45,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1354.45,"speaker_name":"Samuel Bagnall"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":317,"end_time":1356.01,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1355.53,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"Okay.","index":318,"end_time":1356.57,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1356.01,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"So are you guys officially like, all the way?","index":319,"end_time":1362.82,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1358.81,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"Like, we always refer to you guys as New North.","index":320,"end_time":1366.26,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1363.06,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"I know you guys sometimes refer to yourselves that way, but I know a lot of all this, like, branded stuff is all like marketers in demand.","index":321,"end_time":1375.38,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1366.34,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"So is that still in transition?","index":322,"end_time":1379.1,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1375.54,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"Are you guys officially all the way marketers in demand or what is happening that with that?","index":323,"end_time":1382.98,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1379.1,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"So both exist, but we refer to ourselves, like in total as marketers in demand.","index":324,"end_time":1389.53,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1384.5,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":325,"end_time":1391.89,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1391.45,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"And I think the difference just comes from how people find us.","index":326,"end_time":1396.73,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1391.89,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Like, if they come in through New north, it''s usually like they''re looking for a full growth marketing agency.","index":327,"end_time":1402.09,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1396.73,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"If they come in through motion or other agencies, like, they''re looking for video work.","index":328,"end_time":1406.73,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1402.33,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"But once they''re actually working with us, they''re with Marketers in demand as a whole.","index":329,"end_time":1411.37,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1407.29,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"I see.","index":330,"end_time":1412.09,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1411.53,"speaker_name":"Samuel Bagnall"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":331,"end_time":1413.3,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1412.98,"speaker_name":"Samuel Bagnall"},{"text":"Cool.","index":332,"end_time":1417.54,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1417.06,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"I was just curious.","index":333,"end_time":1419.86,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1418.98,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"All right.","index":334,"end_time":1424.82,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1424.18,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Okay.","index":335,"end_time":1425.7,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1425.3,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"So I''ll follow up with all of those links to everything and then I''ll.","index":336,"end_time":1430.98,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1425.7,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"I''ll work on those.","index":337,"end_time":1431.98,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1430.98,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"The keyword research as well today and send you everything I have.","index":338,"end_time":1435.06,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1431.98,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"You''re the best.","index":339,"end_time":1436.5,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1435.7,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Thank you so much.","index":340,"end_time":1437.46,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1436.5,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"Of course.","index":341,"end_time":1438.83,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1438.35,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Trying to think if there was anything else.","index":342,"end_time":1442.19,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1440.67,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"Can''t think of anything.","index":343,"end_time":1444.99,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1443.79,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"So, yeah, I think we''re good.","index":344,"end_time":1446.99,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1445.71,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"Thank you.","index":345,"end_time":1450.35,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1449.71,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Thank you.","index":346,"end_time":1451.23,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1450.59,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"Thank you.","index":347,"end_time":1451.95,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1451.31,"speaker_name":"Samuel Bagnall"},{"text":"Bye.","index":348,"end_time":1452.47,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1452.03,"speaker_name":"Samuel Bagnall"},{"text":"Bye.","index":349,"end_time":1452.91,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1452.47,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"}],"dateString":"2026-01-21T15:30:00.000Z","host_email":"rpontbriand@icorps.com","meeting_link":"https://teams.microsoft.com/l/meetup-join/19:meeting_NWVjNDBkODktN2I3OS00ZWQ0LTgzMDEtMWNkNDk5OGVlYjQ2@thread.v2/0?context={\"Tid\":\"0188564a-93de-489c-bf54-1927d4a9ed28\",\"Oid\":\"bdae9fd3-d481-4c5e-aeea-7272e37b7d07\"}","participants":["colin.costigan@marketersindemand.com,nathalie.mintjens@marketersindemand.com,rpontbriand@icorps.com,sbagnall@icorps.com","colin.costigan@marketersindemand.com","nathalie.mintjens@marketersindemand.com","sbagnall@icorps.com"],"transcript_url":"https://app.fireflies.ai/view/01KFBHZKF154TW56YATE5D2SXF","organizer_email":"nathalie.mintjens@marketersindemand.com"}'::jsonb,
    '{"label":"positive","confidence":0.92,"bullets":["Tracked 263 engaged leads including new Legal Services conversions driven by downloadable LinkedIn content.","Confirmed SEO wins: New York page ranks #4 and real estate page improved from #6 to #3.","Completed draft executive dashboard; included MQL totals, SQL conversion, and top marketing lead sources.","Discussed blog content strategy; Nathalie will deliver keyword CSV from Ahrefs for planning updates.","Outlined process to re-engage Brandon Lepke in Q1 based on earlier outreach timing."],"highlights":[{"quote":"Our highly engaged lead list has jumped up to 263.","speaker":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"quote":"That''s really good. I want to share that with Jeff and Mike to bring that full circle.","speaker":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"quote":"We''re already ranking, which is cool.","speaker":"Nathalie Mintjens"}],"topics":["SEO","lead gen","dashboard","content","ABM"],"model":"openai/gpt-4-turbo","version":1,"generated_at":"2026-01-23T00:00:00Z"}'::jsonb,
    '{"fireflies_summary":{"notes":"## **Account-Based Marketing (ABM) Performance and Lead Nurturing**\n\nThe ABM campaign is generating increasing engagement, primarily driven by strong content offers that attract qualified leads.\n\n- **The highly engaged lead list grew to 263**, with new leads coming from the Legal Services campaign and LinkedIn PDF downloads, including two leads who downloaded the \"AI Safety for Law Firms\" guide last week (03:50)  \n    - Ruby confirmed she has begun follow-ups via engaging emails to these leads, maintaining active nurturing despite no immediate conversions  \n    - Nathalie emphasized that content offers, especially PDFs, are the main driver for lead capture, reinforcing the need for strong offers in future campaigns  \n    - Ruby is testing reconversion tactics by sending a quick quiz scorecard as a next step to deepen engagement and encourage meeting bookings  \n    - This nurture strategy aims to convert warm leads over time, building pipeline momentum from initial content interest\n\n- **A key financial services lead, Brandon Lepke, requested outreach in Q1 for IT scaling**, flagged for follow-up now as the quarter begins (05:30)  \n    - This timing aligns with the prospect’s buying cycle, presenting a timely opportunity for targeted outreach  \n    - Ruby will schedule outreach to capitalize on this window, increasing chances of conversion from a warm lead  \n    - This practice exemplifies strategic lead timing to improve sales efficiency and pipeline quality\n\n- **ABM reporting now consolidates LinkedIn messaging, Smart Lead email stats, and paid media campaign metrics**, providing a comprehensive view of lead generation and engagement (06:20)  \n    - Metrics include connection acceptance rates, message reply rates, email sends, opens, replies, and paid campaign performance  \n    - Ruby plans to present these integrated metrics to her team, supporting data-driven decision-making and campaign adjustments  \n    - The unified dashboard aids in pinpointing strong channels and optimizing resource allocation\n\n## **SEO and Organic Growth Progress**\n\nSEO efforts are delivering rapid improvements in keyword rankings, boosting organic visibility and traffic.\n\n- **The New York location page reached 4th place and the real estate page jumped from 6th to 3rd in search rankings within about two weeks** (07:55)  \n    - This fast ranking increase shows effective targeting of localized keywords and content relevance  \n    - Ruby will share these quick wins with Jeff and Mike to demonstrate SEO’s tangible impact on site authority  \n    - Nathalie highlighted monthly search volume data to prioritize keyword focus and content development  \n    - These gains support broader organic growth goals and improve lead inflows from search\n\n- **SEO content updates are underway including new AI assessment pages and Microsoft Copilot consulting edits**, expanding topical coverage to support emerging service lines (08:45)  \n    - Nathalie sent preview pages with visual highlights for feedback, speeding review and iteration  \n    - This content expansion aligns with product evolution and market demand around AI readiness and technology consulting\n\n- **Monthly keyword tracking faces API limitations, so manual CSV exports will provide rising/falling keyword data for ongoing optimization** (17:45)  \n    - Monthly CSV reports will help identify topic trends and guide blog and campaign planning  \n    - Ruby emphasized the need for updated keyword lists to refresh existing blogs and plan new content for the year  \n    - This approach balances new content creation with targeted updates to maintain SEO relevance\n\n## **Marketing Dashboard Development and Data Insights**\n\nA draft executive dashboard consolidates key marketing metrics, with planned enhancements to improve lead qualification visibility.\n\n- **The dashboard currently shows total MQLs for last year, current SQL counts, conversion rates, and top marketing lead sources from HubSpot** (09:45)  \n    - Ruby requested filtering by custom lead source to isolate marketing-attributed leads like content, SEO, paid, and email channels  \n    - Nathalie confirmed this customization is feasible and will implement it to sharpen performance insights  \n    - This granularity helps track the true impact of marketing efforts on pipeline generation\n\n- **Ruby proposed adding a block showing detailed reasons why leads are unqualified, such as out of country, spam, or timing issues, to clarify lead quality** (13:00)  \n    - Nathalie agreed to present unqualified lead reasons alongside counts of qualified leads to improve conversion rate accuracy  \n    - This will help the team better understand lead funnel health and refine qualification criteria  \n    - Including lead status and detail fields provides actionable insights into lead disposition\n\n- **Access to the dashboard will be via a simple link without requiring login to Pulse, ensuring ease of use for stakeholders** (20:30)  \n    - Ruby noted that leadership is unlikely to access dashboards independently, so centralized, meeting-based reviews remain key  \n    - Flexibility in date filtering allows for tailored reporting over different timeframes, supporting regular performance check-ins\n\n## **Branding and Account Management Updates**\n\nThe company is transitioning branding and HubSpot account usage to align with the Marketers in Demand identity.\n\n- **The HubSpot account used for partnership will shift from productionewnorth.com to production at Marketers in Demand, managed by Colin** (22:00)  \n    - Nathalie clarified that Marketers in Demand is the overarching brand for client engagements, while New North remains a recognized agency name for growth marketing searches (23:00)  \n    - This dual-brand strategy balances market recognition and internal consistency  \n    - Ruby and Samuel will coordinate with Colin if any system changes are required during the transition\n\n- **The rebranding effort reflects a strategic positioning to differentiate service offerings by channel and audience while unifying client experience under one umbrella** (23:15)  \n    - This clarity helps streamline marketing messages and internal team alignment  \n    - It supports long-term brand equity building and client trust\n\n## **Content Planning and Campaign Alignment**\n\nContent strategy will emphasize AI readiness and targeted topics, leveraging keyword research and campaign integration.\n\n- **Keyword research for AI and other content buckets will be completed and shared by end of day to support Ruby’s presentation and campaign planning** (19:30)  \n    - Nathalie will deliver updated keyword lists to guide blog topics and content refresh priorities  \n    - This supports coordinated marketing efforts to capitalize on trending themes and improve SEO relevance  \n    - Ruby’s plan includes aligning blogs with ABM campaigns for consistent messaging and lead nurturing\n\n- **The team recognizes that updating existing blogs is as important as creating new ones to maintain topical authority and SEO performance** (19:50)  \n    - This approach maximizes resource efficiency and leverages past content investments  \n    - It helps keep the content library fresh and aligned with evolving market interests\n\n- **Preview pages for AI assessment and development content have been circulated for feedback, accelerating content deployment timelines** (08:50)  \n    - Visual cues in previews help streamline review cycles  \n    - Rapid iteration ensures timely support for emerging business priorities in AI consulting and assessments","outline":null,"keywords":["ABM Campaign","SEO Performance","Executive Dashboard","Lead Nurturing","Keyword Research","HubSpot Integration"],"overview":"- **ABM Performance**: Lead list grew to 263; strong content offers drive engagement, with follow-ups ongoing.\n\n- **Targeted Outreach**: Financial lead Brandon Lepke flagged for Q1 follow-up, aligning with buying cycle for better conversion chances.\n\n- **SEO Success**: New York page up to 4th and real estate page to 3rd; rapid keyword ranking improvements enhance organic traffic.\n\n- **Marketing Dashboard**: Draft dashboard includes MQLs and SQL counts; custom filtering planned for better lead source tracking.\n\n- **Rebranding Transition**: HubSpot account shifting to Marketers in Demand brand, aiming for unified client experience and clear service differentiation.\n\n- **Content Strategy**: Focus on AI readiness and updating existing blogs; keyword research to support aligned messaging in campaigns.","action_items":"\n**Nathalie Mintjens**\nSend note and contact details for Brandon Lepke for Q1 Financial Services follow-up (06:20)\nShare ABM reports including LinkedIn, email, and paid media campaign stats with Ruby for team presentations (06:20)\nImplement Microsoft Copilot consulting page edits as received from Jeff (07:25)\nProvide keyword research data and CSV keyword status reports for blog planning and AI content campaigns by the end of the day (19:00)\nFinalize and send the draft executive dashboard to Ruby, incorporating custom lead source filters and including lead detail blocks for unqualified reasons (09:20)\nConfirm dashboard access method and send relevant links to Ruby and team (20:30)\nFollow up with Colin Costigan on HubSpot account change process for Marketers in Demand branding (22:00)\nSend all related links and keyword research files after meeting (23:40)\n\n**Ruby Pontbriand**\nPresent ABM campaign metrics and updates to internal team and meetings with Mike, Jeff, and Cook (07:26)\nProvide feedback on draft executive dashboard and requested data fields for lead details and conversion insights (12:30)\nIncorporate keyword data into blog and campaign planning for the year, focusing on AI readiness and updating older blog content (18:50)\n"},"migrated_from":"contract_meetings","original_id":"8de25571-1437-43b5-9720-7b2b12a1aa47","master_marketer":{"status":"migrated"}}'::jsonb,
