  VALUES (
    'ade9bb8a-fde3-4756-a63e-11ce7f227292',
    '2026-01-22 17:30:00+00',
    'fireflies',
    '01KF1JGAJAPVCYS4RC5ZE02K4K',
    'Ricoh // New North: Weekly Meeting',
    '{"Roz","Roz","Nathalie Mintjens"}'::text[],
    554,
    'https://us02web.zoom.us/j/85828735088?pwd=b9W3cDKwBeJQyK00Qs0iP3vvCmTxIZ.1',
    '{"id":"01KF1JGAJAPVCYS4RC5ZE02K4K","title":"Ricoh // New North: Weekly Meeting","summary":{"notes":"## **Video Content Updates and Delivery**\n\nThe team finalized the overview video project with key voiceover adjustments, marking it as complete and setting a clear path for upcoming video updates.\n\n- **Roz confirmed the overview video is done after voiceover tweaks**, emphasizing the need for finalized scripts before recording future videos (08:19)\n    - She noted the video design and transitions were solid, requiring only voiceover fixes.\n    - Roz plans to start new overview videos for **IPM** and **RPD**, with RPD needing a fresh look and feel.\n    - The team will have all scripts reviewed internally before moving to production to avoid last-minute changes.\n    - This approach will improve efficiency and reduce rework in video production cycles.\n\n- **Roz requested two versions of the intro slide for future videos**—one splitting product name and title, another combining them—to allow flexible editing for translation and other needs (02:39)\n    - This minor design change responds to practical use cases like localization.\n    - The team agreed this will help maintain consistency while offering adaptability.\n    - It reflects a broader focus on making video assets more reusable and easier to customize.\n    - This adjustment will be implemented in upcoming video projects.\n\n## **Content and Asset Management**\n\nClear communication and file management remain priorities to ensure all source files and assets are accessible and properly organized.\n\n- **Roz verified the status of source files for the Edmund workshop mountain image**, confirming all relevant files are within the version one folder and no files are missing (06:24)\n    - She clarified that while some files were adjusted by Leo Lou, the master source for that image is accounted for.\n    - This ensures no delays or confusion in accessing key assets for future use.\n    - The check prevents material loss due to file format transitions between Illustrator and InDesign.\n    - Maintaining this clarity supports smooth workflow continuity across design and marketing teams.\n\n- **Nathalie agreed to consolidate and upload all product shots and brochures related to the Process Director image suite into the transfer folder** to improve file access reliability (07:11)\n    - Roz highlighted prior issues with Google Transfer folders, so centralizing files will reduce friction.\n    - This step will speed up review and deployment by making assets readily available.\n    - The action supports tighter control over asset distribution and versioning.\n    - It reflects a focus on improving operational efficiency around asset sharing.\n\n## **Project Status and Workflow Coordination**\n\nCurrent projects are in good shape, with clear ownership and timelines to avoid bottlenecks.\n\n- **Roz is awaiting the PM’s review of the battle card content before finalizing it**, placing that deliverable in a temporary hold until feedback arrives (00:34)\n    - This shows a structured handoff and review process to maintain quality.\n    - It prevents premature finalization and ensures alignment with product management.\n    - Roz maintains oversight to track progress and push for updates as needed.\n    - This waiting period is expected to be short, minimizing delays.\n\n- **Roz communicated her high workload due to recent absence but remains committed to advancing tasks**, prioritizing video updates and asset coordination (00:34)\n    - She acknowledged the catch-up needed after being out on Monday.\n    - The team is aware of this timing constraint, allowing for realistic planning.\n    - Roz’s transparency helps manage expectations on deliverable timing.\n    - This clarity supports smoother team collaboration and resource planning.\n\n## **Process Improvements and Learnings**\n\nLessons from current projects are informing better preparation and workflow for future initiatives.\n\n- **Roz emphasized the importance of locking down voiceover scripts early to avoid mid-project changes**, based on recent experience with script updates causing delays (01:12)\n    - This learning aims to reduce last-minute adjustments that hinder smooth video production.\n    - It reflects a shift toward more thorough pre-production planning.\n    - The team will integrate script finalization as a formal early step in video projects.\n    - This process refinement will improve on-time delivery and quality consistency.\n\n- **The team agreed to provide flexible video intro formats to streamline editing and translation**, showing responsiveness to evolving project needs (03:11)\n    - This adjustment anticipates practical challenges and supports faster turnaround.\n    - It demonstrates openness to iterative improvements based on project experience.\n    - The approach will save time on edits and improve asset usability across markets.\n    - This mindset supports a culture of continuous process refinement.\n\n## **Collaboration and Communication**\n\nThe meeting reinforced strong team coordination and clear communication channels to maintain momentum.\n\n- **Roz encouraged open communication and quick updates when new info or files become available**, fostering proactive collaboration (08:25)\n    - She offered to be contacted directly for any outstanding questions or issues.\n    - This openness helps catch potential blockers early and resolve them promptly.\n    - It builds trust and keeps all team members aligned on priorities.\n    - Maintaining this communication rhythm is critical for meeting tight deadlines.\n\n- **Nathalie confirmed ongoing uploads of RPD images, ensuring timely asset availability for upcoming work** (08:19)\n    - This real-time status update supports smooth handoffs.\n    - It keeps Roz informed and ready to move forward as soon as files arrive.\n    - This responsiveness helps avoid unnecessary waiting periods.\n    - The practice underscores effective teamwork and accountability.","outline":null,"keywords":["Inkjet event","battle card","overview video","IPM","RPD redesign","source files"],"overview":"- **Overview Video Completion:** The overview video is finalized with all voiceover tweaks; finalized scripts are needed for future recordings.  \n- **Intro Slide Versions:** Two intro slide versions requested for flexibility in video editing and easier localization adaptation.  \n- **File Management Checks:** Source files for workshop image confirmed complete, addressing past access issues for smoother workflows.  \n- **Project Review Status:** PM’s review of battle card content is pending, ensuring quality before finalizing and preventing delays.  \n- **Emphasis on Early Script Locking:** Early finalization of voiceover scripts will reduce delays and improve video production efficiency.  \n- **Proactive Communication Encouraged:** Open communication and quick updates are vital to avoid blockers and ensure team alignment on priorities.","action_items":"\n**Roz Regan**\nSend final version of the overview video with updated voiceover to the team (01:45)\nProvide video files for IPM and RPD overview projects once scripts are finalized and reviewed (02:15)\nFollow up on source files for Edmund workshop mountain image ensuring all assets are accounted for and upload or share as needed (04:10)\n\n**Nathalie Mintjens**\nWait for PM feedback on battle card content and then update template accordingly (00:50)\nDownload all Process Director product shots and brochures and upload them into the central transfer folder for Roz’s access (07:10)\nContinue uploading RPD images and confirm when transfer is complete (08:20)\n\n**Unassigned**\nProvide two versions of video intro slides for future videos to allow flexibility for editing and translation: one split (name and title separate) and one combined (product name and title on one slide) (02:55)\n"},"duration":9.239999771118164,"speakers":[{"id":0,"name":"Roz"},{"id":1,"name":"Roz"},{"id":2,"name":"Nathalie Mintjens"}],"sentences":[{"text":"And she has that.","index":0,"end_time":1.16,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":0.24,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"It just might take her a bit to, to get to it.","index":1,"end_time":4,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1.16,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"So if you don''t hear anything, that''s fine, you know, and, and I mean if I have an update to anything, of course I''ll let you know.","index":2,"end_time":11.24,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":4.32,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"But the inkjet one sits with her because that''s an event that she''s running lead on.","index":3,"end_time":19.44,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":11.24,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"So.","index":4,"end_time":20.08,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":19.68,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"Okay.","index":5,"end_time":21.28,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":20.72,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":6,"end_time":21.84,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":21.44,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"So good.","index":7,"end_time":22.48,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":21.84,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":8,"end_time":23.52,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":23.04,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"And then the other one that we have is the battle card.","index":9,"end_time":28.01,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":24.56,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"So that one we sent over both on email and the transfer folder just so that you have both versions.","index":10,"end_time":34.25,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":28.17,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"I have been slammed.","index":11,"end_time":36.37,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":34.57,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"I was out Monday, so I''m doing sort of catch up all week, it feels like.","index":12,"end_time":40.09,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":36.37,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"So leave that one with me.","index":13,"end_time":41.77,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":40.09,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"I''m also waiting for the PM to go over the current content of it.","index":14,"end_time":47.77,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":41.77,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"So I''m sure he''ll have some updates, but I''m just waiting on him.","index":15,"end_time":52.33,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":48.01,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"So it''s kind of in a holding pattern for now, but I wanted to get it into the template.","index":16,"end_time":56.09,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":52.41,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"So we had that ready to go and then, you know, any adjustments we need to make, we can go from there.","index":17,"end_time":60.47,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":56.09,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"So I think that''s in a good space.","index":18,"end_time":62.47,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":60.71,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"The video as well, the overview video.","index":19,"end_time":66.31,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":63.59,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"I had to make some adjustments to the voiceover, so I''ll send you the final.","index":20,"end_time":70.07,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":66.55,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"But that is another project you can cross off the list.","index":21,"end_time":73.03,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":70.07,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"I think that one, that one is now done in my world and I''ll send you guys the final.","index":22,"end_time":77.43,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":73.03,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"Yeah, I just had to do a little mucking about with the, with the voiceover a little bit.","index":23,"end_time":83.59,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":78.71,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"So mental note to myself is to have that voiceover script done and dusted with everyone before we get into the planning and, and the execution of the video.","index":24,"end_time":95.16,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":83.67,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"I thought we were fine with that particular script, but we just had some, some updates to it.","index":25,"end_time":101.84,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":95.16,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"So it''s fine.","index":26,"end_time":102.56,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":101.84,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"Not the end of the world.","index":27,"end_time":103.52,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":102.56,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"But mental note for me, I think next what I will do is I will pop in the information for when I have, well, when I have it, the information to do new overviews for both IPM and rpd.","index":28,"end_time":121.54,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":104,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"RPD desperately needs some new like it desperately needs, like new look and feel.","index":29,"end_time":127.58,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":121.54,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"So I think that the scripts are okay with them, but I''m going to have everyone go through them for me first before, you know, I send everything over.","index":30,"end_time":136.22,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":127.58,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"But that will be next as far as videos go.","index":31,"end_time":138.38,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":136.22,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"Because we did like where the overview one went.","index":32,"end_time":140.7,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":138.38,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"It was strictly that voiceover thing that needed updating.","index":33,"end_time":143.34,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":140.7,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"So.","index":34,"end_time":143.63,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":143.42,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"So the design was good.","index":35,"end_time":144.98,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":143.78,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"Everything.","index":36,"end_time":145.3,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":144.98,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"The transitions look great, like all of that good stuff.","index":37,"end_time":147.86,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":145.3,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"So that was fine.","index":38,"end_time":149.94,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":147.86,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":39,"end_time":150.82,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":150.26,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"Okay, great.","index":40,"end_time":152.38,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":151.54,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"And they''re all pretty similar like you''ll have like some of those source videos and then we just help to make it look.","index":41,"end_time":159.22,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":152.38,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Yeah, yeah.","index":42,"end_time":160.34,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":159.22,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"And I think the only like design suggestion I would make and we didn''t change it because I needed the video faster than.","index":43,"end_time":166.9,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":160.34,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"We just didn''t have time.","index":44,"end_time":169.02,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":168.1,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"Like I just didn''t have time.","index":45,"end_time":169.9,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":169.02,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"I just needed the video quickly was at the beginning where it said says the name and then the title.","index":46,"end_time":175.95,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":169.9,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"I might ask you guys to do it in two versions so that I can, I can edit one or the other if I need to.","index":47,"end_time":183.67,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":176.43,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"So one split like we currently have it and then one where it shows the product name and the title all on one slide.","index":48,"end_time":190.91,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":183.67,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"The solution overview.","index":49,"end_time":193.15,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":191.87,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Yeah, so it would say like Ricoh, you know, insert product name here.","index":50,"end_time":197.79,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":193.47,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"Solution overview.","index":51,"end_time":198.99,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":197.87,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"Okay, I, yeah, I, I kind of get where they''re going with it, but I did tell Ania, I said, look, I split it for a purpose was so that, you know, we could have a little bit more flexibility in what we do and I can take that solution overview thing out if needs be for, you know, translation purposes and whatnot.","index":52,"end_time":219.29,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":199.53,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"And she was like, okay, yeah, no, that totally works.","index":53,"end_time":221.21,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":219.29,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"So maybe just going forward, just give me the two options within the video and I can, you know, edit one way or the other if I need to, depending on the, the requirement.","index":54,"end_time":230.17,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":221.29,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"So just minor, like minor thing as we, you know, as we work through all these videos.","index":55,"end_time":237.05,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":230.41,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"So yeah, for sure.","index":56,"end_time":238.49,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":237.13,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":57,"end_time":239.21,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":238.81,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"So that will be, I think next on the list of things.","index":58,"end_time":242.17,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":239.21,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"Is there anything else on our list that we have that I''m missing?","index":59,"end_time":247.37,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":243.93,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"No, that''s everything that we have open right now.","index":60,"end_time":250.33,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":248.09,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Okay.","index":61,"end_time":251.45,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":250.81,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"I''m going to ask you a quick question only because I don''t have the file open quickly.","index":62,"end_time":257.19,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":253.55,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"What did we have a high res version of those mountains from the Edmund workshop.","index":63,"end_time":263.43,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":257.19,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"You know that mountain with the two hero images imposed on it.","index":64,"end_time":267.55,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":263.43,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"I think you guys sent me like a high res version of that if not the actual source files, but I can''t remember.","index":65,"end_time":274.11,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":268.35,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"Just a sec.","index":66,"end_time":275.15,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":274.43,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"The actual mountain itself.","index":67,"end_time":279.07,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":277.23,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Yeah, no, I don''t think you did.","index":68,"end_time":284.06,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":280.22,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"So I''m wondering how did you guys like.","index":69,"end_time":287.3,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":284.14,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"Okay, so here''s, here''s what I''m looking for is I just need to have the source files for that particular, that particular like image.","index":70,"end_time":299.58,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":287.3,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"Like I, I have like, I have the source file for like the email banner and then the name tag.","index":71,"end_time":306.42,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":299.82,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"But I''m wondering if you guys built out the image itself in something else.","index":72,"end_time":311.9,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":306.42,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"So the, I''m just looking at the project submission.","index":73,"end_time":319.5,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":315.58,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"I think you, you.","index":74,"end_time":322.54,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":319.9,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"Because I built, I think I built It.","index":75,"end_time":327.54,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":326.14,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"We built it in.","index":76,"end_time":328.38,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":327.54,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"I built it in something else.","index":77,"end_time":329.94,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":328.62,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"I can''t remember what, but I never got back the full source files for that particular image, like, on its own.","index":78,"end_time":336.18,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":329.94,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"You know what I mean?","index":79,"end_time":336.78,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":336.18,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"Like.","index":80,"end_time":337.1,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":336.78,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"But if it''s living in, like, the email banner source file or one of the other ones, that''s fine.","index":81,"end_time":343.02,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":337.74,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"I just wasn''t sure if you guys had it in another place or not.","index":82,"end_time":346.22,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":343.02,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":83,"end_time":347.7,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":347.34,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"When you submitted the.","index":84,"end_time":350.18,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":347.7,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"The project you sent, you gave us some sort of source file, right?","index":85,"end_time":354.38,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":350.18,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Is that what you''re looking for?","index":86,"end_time":355.58,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":354.38,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Well, I know that.","index":87,"end_time":357.26,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":356.14,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"I remember Leo.","index":88,"end_time":359.74,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":357.98,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"Leo.","index":89,"end_time":360.62,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":360.14,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"Lou said that he had adjusted it slightly, and I never got back, like, the source file of just the image.","index":90,"end_time":367.18,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":360.62,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"But if.","index":91,"end_time":367.66,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":367.18,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"If he just built in, like, the email banner file, that''s fine, too.","index":92,"end_time":373.16,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":367.66,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"Yeah, I just wanted to be sure it wasn''t missing anything, was all.","index":93,"end_time":377.88,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":374.68,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"Yeah, no, I think everything that he created is going to be in that version one folder.","index":94,"end_time":383,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":378.84,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"All right, that''s fine.","index":95,"end_time":385.079,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":384.2,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"I just wanted to be sure that I had everything and that it wasn''t like sometimes I know he creates in, you know, we go from, you know, From Illustrator into InDesign, and.","index":96,"end_time":395.44,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":385.079,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"And I just wanted to be sure that I had everything.","index":97,"end_time":397.79,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":395.44,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"So no worries.","index":98,"end_time":398.79,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":398.03,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"That''s fine.","index":99,"end_time":399.55,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":398.79,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"Okay.","index":100,"end_time":400.59,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":400.03,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"Yes.","index":101,"end_time":402.03,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":401.55,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"Doable.","index":102,"end_time":402.99,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":402.35,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"Okay.","index":103,"end_time":403.87,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":403.23,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"Is there anything else as far as projects that we have on the go?","index":104,"end_time":411.95,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":405.39,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"Your.","index":105,"end_time":414.51,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":414.11,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"It.","index":106,"end_time":415.71,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":415.31,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"I think the.","index":107,"end_time":416.71,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":415.95,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"The image suite that we just did is closed off, right?","index":108,"end_time":419.47,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":416.71,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Oh, yeah.","index":109,"end_time":421.19,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":420.51,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"You did send that to me.","index":110,"end_time":422.35,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":421.19,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"I believe so.","index":111,"end_time":424.67,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":423.47,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"It was Process director.","index":112,"end_time":430.03,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":428.11,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Yeah, I''ve.","index":113,"end_time":433.79,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":431.15,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"I see product shots, I see brochure.","index":114,"end_time":436.59,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":433.95,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"Could you do me a humongous favor and just download them all and drop them into our transfer folder?","index":115,"end_time":449.27,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":444.19,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"That would really help me out.","index":116,"end_time":450.59,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":449.27,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"Yeah, sure.","index":117,"end_time":451.27,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":450.87,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"If you wouldn''t mind, that would be super helpful.","index":118,"end_time":453.35,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":451.27,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":119,"end_time":455.43,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":454.87,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"Yeah, because that.","index":120,"end_time":459.75,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":458.79,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"That Google transfer folder we''ve had issues with in the past, so if you.","index":121,"end_time":465.79,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":460.23,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"Could, that would be great.","index":122,"end_time":466.79,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":465.79,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"Okay.","index":123,"end_time":472.07,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":471.51,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"All right.","index":124,"end_time":473.27,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":472.71,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"Well, I am good.","index":125,"end_time":475.71,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":473.27,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"If you guys are.","index":126,"end_time":476.43,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":475.71,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"I''m happy to end a little bit early.","index":127,"end_time":478.15,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":476.43,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"I could only give 30 minutes to our call today anyway.","index":128,"end_time":482.39,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":479.23,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"I have another call coming up at the bottom of the hour, so unless there''s anything else we needed to discuss, I think we''re in good form.","index":129,"end_time":489.87,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":482.39,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"I just.","index":130,"end_time":491.51,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":491.07,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"Like I said, I just need to get those.","index":131,"end_time":492.79,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":491.51,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"Those video files to you so that you guys can start, you know, working on that and taking a look at.","index":132,"end_time":497.71,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":492.79,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"What those look like, so.","index":133,"end_time":499.23,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":497.71,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"Okay, that sounds good.","index":134,"end_time":501.07,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":499.71,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"So we''ll wait for those.","index":135,"end_time":502.83,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":501.63,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"And the RPD images are uploading right now.","index":136,"end_time":505.63,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":502.83,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"They should be okay.","index":137,"end_time":506.59,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":505.63,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"Okay, great.","index":138,"end_time":507.72,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":507.2,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"I''ll keep my eyes peeled for it.","index":139,"end_time":509.24,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":507.72,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"And just transfer them over when I need them, so.","index":140,"end_time":511.84,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":509.24,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"Okay.","index":141,"end_time":512.64,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":512,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"Very good.","index":142,"end_time":513.24,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":512.64,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"Well, thank you so much to you both.","index":143,"end_time":514.76,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":513.24,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"I''m very much appreciate it.","index":144,"end_time":516.48,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":514.76,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"If there''s anything else, Natalie, you know where I am, so please send a note.","index":145,"end_time":521.44,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":516.64,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"Otherwise, yeah, I think we can end.","index":146,"end_time":523.16,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":521.92,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"A bit early today.","index":147,"end_time":523.92,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":523.16,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"All right, great.","index":148,"end_time":525.52,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":524.88,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Thank you, Roz.","index":149,"end_time":526.16,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":525.52,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Have a good day.","index":150,"end_time":526.96,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":526.16,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"Bye.","index":151,"end_time":527.52,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":527.04,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"Take care.","index":152,"end_time":528.24,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":527.68,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"Bye.","index":153,"end_time":528.48,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":528.24,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"Bye.","index":154,"end_time":528.8,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":528.48,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"Bye.","index":155,"end_time":529.52,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":529.04,"speaker_name":"Roz"}],"dateString":"2026-01-22T17:30:00.000Z","host_email":"nathalie.mintjens@marketersindemand.com","meeting_link":"https://us02web.zoom.us/j/85828735088?pwd=b9W3cDKwBeJQyK00Qs0iP3vvCmTxIZ.1","participants":["nathalie.mintjens@marketersindemand.com,colin.costigan@marketersindemand.com,lou.bogani@marketersindemand.com,kiyan.klocker@marketersindemand.com,nina.belina@marketersindemand.com,rosalynne.regan@ricoh.ca,linnea.wolken@ricoh-usa.com","colin.costigan@marketersindemand.com","lou.bogani@marketersindemand.com","kiyan.klocker@marketersindemand.com","nina.belina@marketersindemand.com","rosalynne.regan@ricoh.ca","linnea.wolken@ricoh-usa.com"],"transcript_url":"https://app.fireflies.ai/view/01KF1JGAJAPVCYS4RC5ZE02K4K","organizer_email":"nathalie.mintjens@marketersindemand.com"}'::jsonb,
    '{"label":"positive","confidence":0.87,"bullets":["Closed out the overview video project after finalizing voiceover tweaks and confirming design success.","Committed to improving video workflow by aligning voiceover scripts earlier in the process.","Prepared next steps for video overhauls of IPM and RPD, with script review planned in advance.","Requested dual-design versions for video titles to optimize flexibility across use cases and translations.","Confirmed all image assets are complete and requested centralized transfer to mitigate folder issues."],"highlights":[{"quote":"That is another project you can cross off the list.","speaker":"Roz"},{"quote":"Next what I will do is I will pop in the information to do new overviews.","speaker":"Roz"},{"quote":"I think that one is now done in my world and I''ll send you guys the final.","speaker":"Roz"}],"topics":["delivery","scope","workflow"],"model":"openai/gpt-4-turbo","version":1,"generated_at":"2026-01-23T00:00:00Z"}'::jsonb,
