SELECT
  new_meeting.contract_id,
  new_meeting.meeting_id,
  'meeting',
  'Meeting Notes: Ricoh // New North: Weekly Meeting',
  '## **Video Content Updates and Delivery**

The team finalized the overview video project with key voiceover adjustments, marking it as complete and setting a clear path for upcoming video updates.

- **Roz confirmed the overview video is done after voiceover tweaks**, emphasizing the need for finalized scripts before recording future videos (08:19)
    - She noted the video design and transitions were solid, requiring only voiceover fixes.
    - Roz plans to start new overview videos for **IPM** and **RPD**, with RPD needing a fresh look and feel.
    - The team will have all scripts reviewed internally before moving to production to avoid last-minute changes.
    - This approach will improve efficiency and reduce rework in video production cycles.

- **Roz requested two versions of the intro slide for future videos**—one splitting product name and title, another combining them—to allow flexible editing for translation and other needs (02:39)
    - This minor design change responds to practical use cases like localization.
    - The team agreed this will help maintain consistency while offering adaptability.
    - It reflects a broader focus on making video assets more reusable and easier to customize.
    - This adjustment will be implemented in upcoming video projects.

## **Content and Asset Management**

Clear communication and file management remain priorities to ensure all source files and assets are accessible and properly organized.

- **Roz verified the status of source files for the Edmund workshop mountain image**, confirming all relevant files are within the version one folder and no files are missing (06:24)
    - She clarified that while some files were adjusted by Leo Lou, the master source for that image is accounted for.
    - This ensures no delays or confusion in accessing key assets for future use.
    - The check prevents material loss due to file format transitions between Illustrator and InDesign.
    - Maintaining this clarity supports smooth workflow continuity across design and marketing teams.

- **Nathalie agreed to consolidate and upload all product shots and brochures related to the Process Director image suite into the transfer folder** to improve file access reliability (07:11)
    - Roz highlighted prior issues with Google Transfer folders, so centralizing files will reduce friction.
    - This step will speed up review and deployment by making assets readily available.
    - The action supports tighter control over asset distribution and versioning.
    - It reflects a focus on improving operational efficiency around asset sharing.

## **Project Status and Workflow Coordination**

Current projects are in good shape, with clear ownership and timelines to avoid bottlenecks.

- **Roz is awaiting the PM’s review of the battle card content before finalizing it**, placing that deliverable in a temporary hold until feedback arrives (00:34)
    - This shows a structured handoff and review process to maintain quality.
    - It prevents premature finalization and ensures alignment with product management.
    - Roz maintains oversight to track progress and push for updates as needed.
    - This waiting period is expected to be short, minimizing delays.

- **Roz communicated her high workload due to recent absence but remains committed to advancing tasks**, prioritizing video updates and asset coordination (00:34)
    - She acknowledged the catch-up needed after being out on Monday.
    - The team is aware of this timing constraint, allowing for realistic planning.
    - Roz’s transparency helps manage expectations on deliverable timing.
    - This clarity supports smoother team collaboration and resource planning.

## **Process Improvements and Learnings**

Lessons from current projects are informing better preparation and workflow for future initiatives.

- **Roz emphasized the importance of locking down voiceover scripts early to avoid mid-project changes**, based on recent experience with script updates causing delays (01:12)
    - This learning aims to reduce last-minute adjustments that hinder smooth video production.
    - It reflects a shift toward more thorough pre-production planning.
    - The team will integrate script finalization as a formal early step in video projects.
    - This process refinement will improve on-time delivery and quality consistency.

- **The team agreed to provide flexible video intro formats to streamline editing and translation**, showing responsiveness to evolving project needs (03:11)
    - This adjustment anticipates practical challenges and supports faster turnaround.
    - It demonstrates openness to iterative improvements based on project experience.
    - The approach will save time on edits and improve asset usability across markets.
    - This mindset supports a culture of continuous process refinement.

## **Collaboration and Communication**

The meeting reinforced strong team coordination and clear communication channels to maintain momentum.

- **Roz encouraged open communication and quick updates when new info or files become available**, fostering proactive collaboration (08:25)
    - She offered to be contacted directly for any outstanding questions or issues.
    - This openness helps catch potential blockers early and resolve them promptly.
    - It builds trust and keeps all team members aligned on priorities.
    - Maintaining this communication rhythm is critical for meeting tight deadlines.

- **Nathalie confirmed ongoing uploads of RPD images, ensuring timely asset availability for upcoming work** (08:19)
    - This real-time status update supports smooth handoffs.
    - It keeps Roz informed and ready to move forward as soon as files arrive.
    - This responsiveness helps avoid unnecessary waiting periods.
    - The practice underscores effective teamwork and accountability.',
  '2026-01-22 17:30:00+00',
  'published',
  '[{"text":"Send final version of the overview video with updated voiceover to the team (01:45)","completed":false},{"text":"Provide video files for IPM and RPD overview projects once scripts are finalized and reviewed (02:15)","completed":false},{"text":"Follow up on source files for Edmund workshop mountain image ensuring all assets are accounted for and upload or share as needed (04:10)","completed":false},{"text":"Wait for PM feedback on battle card content and then update template accordingly (00:50)","completed":false},{"text":"Download all Process Director product shots and brochures and upload them into the central transfer folder for Roz’s access (07:10)","completed":false},{"text":"Continue uploading RPD images and confirm when transfer is complete (08:20)","completed":false},{"text":"Provide two versions of video intro slides for future videos to allow flexibility for editing and translation: one split (name and title separate) and one combined (product name and title on one slide) (02:55)","completed":false}]'::jsonb,
