    'https://us02web.zoom.us/j/83663022990?pwd=R1aTMdTGv2yblYfzlB6Wv1Sup4Z47U.1',
    '{"id":"01KF0ZBV2SQMYHZZJS1ES4J02X","title":"Agrippon // New North Weekly Connect","summary":{"notes":"## **LinkedIn Outreach Strategy**\n\nThe team decided to shift LinkedIn messaging to be more direct about introducing **a grip on** to improve lead quality and reduce irrelevant responses (11:09).\n\n- **Keenan Toward proposed** focusing messages on what a grip on offers rather than general networking to avoid attracting job seekers and unrelated sales pitches (06:22).\n    - This approach aims to reduce wasted time by being upfront about sales intentions.\n    - Shane Billings agreed and requested Nathalie Mintjens update the LinkedIn message sequence accordingly (10:42).\n    - The updated messaging will target prospects more likely to convert, saving Keenan and Shane time spent on unproductive conversations.\n    - This change reflects a strategic priority to generate meaningful sales conversations rather than casual networking.\n\n- **Current LinkedIn campaigns show lower engagement**, with Nathalie noting better response rates from networking-style outreach but acknowledging inefficiency in generating qualified leads (06:52).\n    - The team agreed to run the existing campaign for four more weeks before switching fully to the direct approach if results don’t improve (08:00).\n    - Shane emphasized the need to convert conversations toward a grip on quickly to maintain productive sales discussions (08:28).\n    - Messaging will aim to be transparent and respectful of prospects’ time to build trust and reduce drop-offs (11:20).\n\n- **Operational complexity arises from using Brad’s LinkedIn account**, as it causes confusion when Keenan contacts leads separately (02:17).\n    - Shane suggested creative messaging to clarify roles between Brad and Keenan during outreach.\n    - The team acknowledged the need for phone numbers in campaigns to enable calls, which are more effective than LinkedIn messaging alone (03:38).\n    - Nathalie committed to adding and making phone number fields mandatory in lead capture forms to improve contact quality (03:44, 15:01).\n\n## **Lead Capture and Follow-Up Processes**\n\nThe focus is on improving lead quality through better form data and automated follow-ups to increase conversion rates (22:21).\n\n- **Two promising leads emerged recently**, including one existing **E Assist customer switching to a grip on** and one **RCM company** with potential, highlighting lead quality importance (13:51).\n    - The E Assist lead included a phone number, enabling faster and more effective follow-up (15:12).\n    - Shane and Nathalie agreed to make phone numbers mandatory on all forms to streamline outreach (15:19).\n    - Keenan values leads over website traffic, emphasizing quality over quantity in inbound contacts (15:50).\n\n- **Automation of follow-up emails based on engagement data** from email campaigns will save manual work and improve targeting (22:21).\n    - Nathalie confirmed the system tracks email link clicks and flags contacts with three or more clicks in 30 days for targeted follow-up.\n    - Shane requested Keenan draft the content for automated outreach emails, with the team providing feedback and creative input afterward (23:18).\n    - The offer will likely include a free trial page link to encourage engagement (24:15).\n    - This automation will free Keenan’s time and ensure persistent outreach to warmer leads, increasing conversion chances.\n\n- **Calendly links for demos are currently non-functional and not being used**, due to scheduling conflicts, and will be replaced by forms until mid-February when availability improves (12:39).\n    - This prevents overbooking and ensures leads are managed realistically given Keenan’s current workload (13:08).\n\n## **Marketing Campaign Performance and Website Updates**\n\nThe team is refreshing campaigns and website content to address declining traffic and improve lead generation quality (15:50).\n\n- **Website traffic dropped 27% in the last 30 days, especially from ABM sources**, signaling a need for new account-based marketing campaigns targeting the right audience (15:59).\n    - Nathalie is launching new ABM campaigns to reverse this trend and maintain visibility with key prospects.\n    - LinkedIn cost per click has improved significantly, dropping to **$9 from over $30**, due to wider targeting adjustments (15:59).\n    - These adjustments aim to increase traffic quality while reducing ad spend.\n\n- **Website changes include inserting onboarding package information on key pages**, with Keenan reviewing updates for approval (12:07).\n    - This aims to clarify product offerings and guide visitors toward conversion.\n    - Keenan committed to reviewing and approving these changes promptly to keep the website aligned with current messaging (12:25).\n\n- **Organic traffic decline is partly linked to reduced podcast activity**, which had been driving noticeable traffic through YouTube’s search engine (17:53).\n    - Nathalie emphasized the importance of continuing podcast episodes to maintain organic reach.\n    - Shane proposed involving Keenan and Brad in podcast efforts to boost engagement and create entertaining content (18:49).\n\n## **Sales Cycle Timing and Messaging Tailoring**\n\nThe team recognizes seasonal challenges in dental industry sales and plans to tailor messaging to address these realities (25:14).\n\n- **January is a difficult month due to dental industry turnover and budget resets**, causing many leads to go silent post-demo (25:28).\n    - Keenan is drafting messages acknowledging these pain points to connect personally with prospects.\n    - Messaging will highlight understanding of industry challenges and position a grip on as a solution provider during tough periods (26:00).\n    - This tailored approach aims to increase empathy and relevance, improving response rates.\n\n- **Keenan will deliver the updated LinkedIn and email messaging drafts by Friday for review**, targeting the end of January for campaign refreshes (26:55).\n    - Nathalie will compile click engagement data at the end of January to refine the automated outreach list (27:12).\n    - Shane will coordinate with Brad and Keenan for podcast and outreach integration moving forward (27:30).\n\n## **Team Collaboration and Resource Allocation**\n\nThe meeting concluded with commitments to optimize workflows and leverage team strengths to increase efficiency and focus (07:26).\n\n- **Shane acknowledged the team’s limited expertise in LinkedIn outreach and committed to following Nathalie’s guidance** as marketing experts (07:26).\n    - This reflects a strategic choice to trust specialized vendors to improve campaign effectiveness.\n    - Keenan’s role focuses on business development and crafting outreach content within his capacity.\n\n- **Keenan is actively managing lead outreach with available data, supported by Nathalie and Shane’s automation and campaign efforts** (19:49).\n    - Automation and improved data capture will help Keenan focus on closing rather than prospecting.\n    - The team agreed to maintain flexibility around scheduling and communication channels due to workload constraints (13:08).\n\n- **Shane expressed appreciation for the ongoing support and recent advertising refunds from Facebook**, indicating positive vendor relations and cost management (16:52).\n    - This financial relief contributes to sustaining marketing efforts despite current performance challenges.","outline":null,"keywords":["LinkedIn campaign","direct messaging","lead generation","website updates","podcast marketing","dental industry seasonality"],"overview":"- **Direct LinkedIn Messaging Change:** Shift to direct messaging about a grip on to improve lead quality and reduce irrelevant responses.\n\n- **Mandatory Phone Numbers:** Team agreed to make phone numbers required on forms to enhance follow-up efficiency and lead quality.\n\n- **Automated Follow-Up Emails:** Automation based on engagement data will save manual effort and double follow-up chances on warmer leads.\n\n- **Website Traffic Decline:** 27% drop in traffic noted; new ABM campaigns to be launched to attract better-targeted audience.\n\n- **Podcast Activity Importance:** Continued podcast episodes are essential for maintaining organic traffic and boosting engagement.\n\n- **Customized Messaging for Sales Cycle:** Tailored messages acknowledging dental industry challenges aim to improve connections and response rates.","action_items":"\n**Keenan Toward**\nReview website updates with onboarding packages and provide feedback today (12:25)\nDraft new LinkedIn message sequence focused on introducing Agrippon directly and submit for team approval by Friday (10:42)\nContinue outreach using updated contact lists and send tailored email messages to potential leads (19:49)\nPrepare automated email sequence for re-engagement of clicking leads for review by Natalie and Shane (23:04)\n\n**Nathalie Mintjens**\nUpdate outgoing LinkedIn message sequence as per new direction and send for approval (11:09)\nMake phone number field required on all website lead capture forms to improve lead quality (15:40)\nFix issues with non-functioning Calendly links for demo and consultation forms (12:39)\nMonitor weekly email engagement data and compile list of contacts with three or more clicks per month at month-end for follow-up campaign (27:12)\n\n**Shane Billings**\nCoordinate with Brad to confirm scheduling availability for demo and consultation meetings (19:22)\nReview and provide feedback on Keenan’s drafted email outreach sequence (23:57)\nCommunicate with Natalie and Keenan on progress and next steps including podcast promotion and lead nurturing strategy (27:30)\n"},"duration":28.06999969482422,"speakers":[{"id":0,"name":"Keenan Toward"},{"id":1,"name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"id":2,"name":"Shane Billings"}],"sentences":[{"text":"Right now.","index":0,"end_time":0.48,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":0.08,"speaker_name":"Keenan Toward"},{"text":"So it was an adventure.","index":1,"end_time":2.72,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1.36,"speaker_name":"Keenan Toward"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":2,"end_time":3.68,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":3.2,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"I''m glad you made it out.","index":3,"end_time":4.96,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":3.68,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":4,"end_time":5.84,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":5.36,"speaker_name":"Keenan Toward"},{"text":"So it looks like we got Brad connected, right?","index":5,"end_time":10.8,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":8.08,"speaker_name":"Keenan Toward"},{"text":"Yes.","index":6,"end_time":12.24,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":11.76,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"So that''s, that''s good.","index":7,"end_time":14.48,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":13.12,"speaker_name":"Keenan Toward"},{"text":"He''s all connected and we started sending out connection requests too.","index":8,"end_time":19.12,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":15.68,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"So I don''t know if you''ve gone in, but you, you''re probably going to see a few people have accepted already.","index":9,"end_time":24.08,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":19.52,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"And so, yeah, the messages will just keep going out until we get a response.","index":10,"end_time":29.03,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":25.67,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Okay.","index":11,"end_time":30.47,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":29.91,"speaker_name":"Keenan Toward"},{"text":"So with the connection requests, since I''m using somebody else''s LinkedIn, I''m not aware of, like new people to his account or what people he''s actually reaching out to and what people we are.","index":12,"end_time":44.31,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":30.71,"speaker_name":"Keenan Toward"},{"text":"There''s no way to decipher that.","index":13,"end_time":47.27,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":45.75,"speaker_name":"Keenan Toward"},{"text":"Right.","index":14,"end_time":47.67,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":47.27,"speaker_name":"Keenan Toward"},{"text":"In a connection request, once they accept.","index":15,"end_time":51.27,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":47.83,"speaker_name":"Keenan Toward"},{"text":"You will be able to see when we send the connection request, we send a little note along with it.","index":16,"end_time":57.28,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":51.35,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"So when they accept it, that''s going to show up in your message history with them.","index":17,"end_time":61.2,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":57.6,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"And so you''ll see that it was something that we set up.","index":18,"end_time":65.2,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":61.84,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Okay.","index":19,"end_time":66.64,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":66.08,"speaker_name":"Keenan Toward"},{"text":"Yeah, but we, yeah, we have those messages sending out.","index":20,"end_time":71.36,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":66.96,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"We may want to think about changing them up too because we''re using the messages that we used with Monique and Monique''s really wanted to like, frame the messages like we wanted to network with people.","index":21,"end_time":84.75,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":71.36,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"So not necessarily introducing a grip on right away, but just like getting to know people what they do in the dental industry, setting up a networking call and then maybe seeing if they''d be a good fit for a grip on.","index":22,"end_time":96.91,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":85.39,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"But since we''re using Brad''s account.","index":23,"end_time":99.79,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":97.95,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Yeah, even if they set up a networking call, then it would come to you, which is a bit confusing.","index":24,"end_time":106.03,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":101.95,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":25,"end_time":107.55,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":107.23,"speaker_name":"Keenan Toward"},{"text":"So we had one person that came in over LinkedIn and I reached out to her by email first because initially when I connect, I can''t message until they accept the request.","index":26,"end_time":120.35,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":107.71,"speaker_name":"Keenan Toward"},{"text":"And so I had messaged her, I sent her an email which she didn''t respond to and then she did accept the connection request on LinkedIn.","index":27,"end_time":133.55,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":122.67,"speaker_name":"Keenan Toward"},{"text":"So then I messaged her on LinkedIn, but then she hasn''t responded to that either.","index":28,"end_time":136.55,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":133.55,"speaker_name":"Keenan Toward"},{"text":"So.","index":29,"end_time":136.91,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":136.55,"speaker_name":"Keenan Toward"},{"text":"Okay, so there''s.","index":30,"end_time":138.33,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":137.73,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"Those are actually two separate kind of issues.","index":31,"end_time":140.53,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":138.33,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"So there''s the campaign, which is what you''re talking about, Keenan, and then you reach out to her, which I think if we can, we''ve got to get phone numbers from these people so we can call them because we didn''t have a phone number.","index":32,"end_time":154.33,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":140.77,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"The second thing is, is that when Brad''s account sends something and you reach out to them as Keenan, they''re going to be confused unless you reach out him as Brad, which would be different and creative, but that''s a possibility too, I suppose.","index":33,"end_time":171.2,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":154.33,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"I reached out as Brad and just said, we have a sales leader that will be reaching out to you.","index":34,"end_time":176.44,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":171.2,"speaker_name":"Keenan Toward"},{"text":"Oh, I got you.","index":35,"end_time":177.12,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":176.44,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"Perfect.","index":36,"end_time":177.48,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":177.12,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"Gotcha.","index":37,"end_time":177.96,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":177.48,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":38,"end_time":178.32,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":177.96,"speaker_name":"Keenan Toward"},{"text":"Okay.","index":39,"end_time":180.32,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":179.76,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"But she didn''t respond to either one, so.","index":40,"end_time":184,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":182,"speaker_name":"Keenan Toward"},{"text":"And that works too.","index":41,"end_time":186.08,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":184.96,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"I used to kind of.","index":42,"end_time":188.24,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":186.64,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"To use a brain, kind of a Brad account.","index":43,"end_time":191.2,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":188.4,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"And I would.","index":44,"end_time":193.28,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":192.16,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"What I did was I said, oh, let''s meet my bro.","index":45,"end_time":196.96,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":193.6,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"My co partner is going to meet with you.","index":46,"end_time":198.84,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":196.96,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"And then I would back out.","index":47,"end_time":200.16,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":198.84,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":48,"end_time":201.16,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":200.8,"speaker_name":"Keenan Toward"},{"text":"Meaning.","index":49,"end_time":201.56,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":201.16,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"Meaning we both.","index":50,"end_time":202.36,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":201.56,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"I said, hey, we''re both going to meet with you.","index":51,"end_time":204.28,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":202.36,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"I''d set something up and then I''d.","index":52,"end_time":206.76,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":204.28,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"And then, oh, I''m sorry, I''m too busy.","index":53,"end_time":209,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":206.76,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"And then the other person would meet.","index":54,"end_time":210.88,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":209,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"That''s how I did it.","index":55,"end_time":212,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":210.96,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"Okay.","index":56,"end_time":213.52,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":212.88,"speaker_name":"Keenan Toward"},{"text":"Natalie, is there any way we can get phone numbers on the ad campaigns?","index":57,"end_time":224.41,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":218.33,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"Yeah, we can go into the form that we''re using and then just make that field required.","index":58,"end_time":230.49,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":224.89,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"It''s not even a field, I think, but yes, we need to add it and make it required.","index":59,"end_time":235.61,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":231.13,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"Okay.","index":60,"end_time":237.45,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":236.89,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Cool.","index":61,"end_time":240.57,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":240.09,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"Yeah, that''s important because if people fill that out.","index":62,"end_time":242.97,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":240.65,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"All right.","index":63,"end_time":243.77,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":243.49,"speaker_name":"Keenan Toward"},{"text":"Sorry to interrupt, guys.","index":64,"end_time":244.65,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":243.77,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"Keep talking.","index":65,"end_time":245.25,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":244.65,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":66,"end_time":247.45,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":247.09,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"And then.","index":67,"end_time":247.89,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":247.45,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"So that''s the LinkedIn campaign.","index":68,"end_time":249.81,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":247.89,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"So I''ll send you the sequence that we''re sending out right now just in the Word document so you can see if you want to make any updates.","index":69,"end_time":257.13,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":250.45,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"We can change that.","index":70,"end_time":258.21,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":257.13,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"And then we''re also working on the.","index":71,"end_time":260.61,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":258.85,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"A new email campaign to go out to DSOs and billing orgs like we talked about.","index":72,"end_time":267.05,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":261.25,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"I think the campaigns we have running right now are slowing down, so we''re seeing less traffic to the site.","index":73,"end_time":272.03,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":267.05,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"So now''s a good time to just refresh the messaging and create a new list of people to start sending to.","index":74,"end_time":277.23,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":272.19,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Okay.","index":75,"end_time":278.91,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":278.35,"speaker_name":"Keenan Toward"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":76,"end_time":279.95,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":279.55,"speaker_name":"Keenan Toward"},{"text":"And just to go back to your talk track earlier about us just wanting to connect and get to know people.","index":77,"end_time":289.63,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":279.95,"speaker_name":"Keenan Toward"},{"text":"The reason I personally can''t stand LinkedIn is I get more people trying to sell crap to me and I get more people that are looking for jobs reaching out to me, and I don''t want that to be what we''re dealing with.","index":78,"end_time":305.4,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":291.07,"speaker_name":"Keenan Toward"},{"text":"I would rather it be something more around a grip on and what we do.","index":79,"end_time":311.88,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":306.84,"speaker_name":"Keenan Toward"},{"text":"Because I Also using Brad''s LinkedIn, I also don''t want to inundate his LinkedIn with people that are looking for jobs.","index":80,"end_time":321.32,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":313.72,"speaker_name":"Keenan Toward"},{"text":"And that''s what I see on his LinkedIn already is everybody''s open to work and so they''re reaching out to him to connect to essentially, you know, then Then they''re looking for jobs.","index":81,"end_time":331.35,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":321.48,"speaker_name":"Keenan Toward"},{"text":"So, and that''s what I dealt with.","index":82,"end_time":333.67,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":331.43,"speaker_name":"Keenan Toward"},{"text":"I, I didn''t even find my job on LinkedIn.","index":83,"end_time":338.23,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":333.67,"speaker_name":"Keenan Toward"},{"text":"So LinkedIn is one of my, one of the tools I don''t use a whole lot.","index":84,"end_time":344.63,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":338.47,"speaker_name":"Keenan Toward"},{"text":"So I''d rather the messaging be more around a grip on what we have to offer.","index":85,"end_time":349.67,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":344.79,"speaker_name":"Keenan Toward"},{"text":"Shane, how do you feel about that?","index":86,"end_time":351.83,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":350.07,"speaker_name":"Keenan Toward"},{"text":"And Natalie, you as well.","index":87,"end_time":353.59,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":352.31,"speaker_name":"Keenan Toward"},{"text":"If you guys are, you know, big fans of LinkedIn and the way that it works, then maybe you guys can, can share some of that with me.","index":88,"end_time":360.59,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":353.59,"speaker_name":"Keenan Toward"},{"text":"But to this point, what I''ve seen on LinkedIn is all the people that we had leads from before, even going back through the ones from last year that you guys had, a lot of them were, hey, we want to develop your website for you.","index":89,"end_time":371.27,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":360.59,"speaker_name":"Keenan Toward"},{"text":"Hey, I want a job.","index":90,"end_time":372.75,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":371.27,"speaker_name":"Keenan Toward"},{"text":"Or you know, I was like, yeah, this, this isn''t going to get us sales.","index":91,"end_time":376.19,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":372.75,"speaker_name":"Keenan Toward"},{"text":"We are just talking to people to talk to people right now.","index":92,"end_time":379.15,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":376.59,"speaker_name":"Keenan Toward"},{"text":"Yeah, I, I will say we.","index":93,"end_time":385.08,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":382.2,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"So when, at first, when we did this campaign, we started it being more a grip on, focused, like just straight up talking about what a grip on does and how we could help.","index":94,"end_time":394.44,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":385.4,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"We had much lower response rates, we had a lot higher engagement when it was just about getting to know the person.","index":95,"end_time":401.72,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":394.84,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"But to your point, that''s still just getting to know them and they don''t really know why we''re reaching out.","index":96,"end_time":406.89,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":402.04,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Maybe it is just wasting time if we don''t know if they''re a good fit or not.","index":97,"end_time":410.85,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":406.89,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Shane, what''s your thoughts?","index":98,"end_time":413.57,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":412.29,"speaker_name":"Keenan Toward"},{"text":"Yeah, I mean, I don''t know the secret, I think not just my thoughts.","index":99,"end_time":423.29,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":418.61,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"You''re asking what do I think about LinkedIn and how do we approach it?","index":100,"end_time":426.49,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":423.29,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"Is that fundamentally what you''re asking?","index":101,"end_time":428.05,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":426.49,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":102,"end_time":429.53,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":429.17,"speaker_name":"Keenan Toward"},{"text":"And what message you think could be effective if it''s the get to know you and connect thing or if we should be going directly into a grip.","index":103,"end_time":438.54,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":429.53,"speaker_name":"Keenan Toward"},{"text":"On here is my opinion.","index":104,"end_time":440.5,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":438.54,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"At this point, we don''t know what works because nothing has worked.","index":105,"end_time":445.54,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":441.14,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":106,"end_time":446.46,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":445.94,"speaker_name":"Keenan Toward"},{"text":"And so there is no wrong answer.","index":107,"end_time":448.66,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":446.46,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"That''s my opinion.","index":108,"end_time":450.26,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":449.22,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"Does that make sense?","index":109,"end_time":452.02,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":451.06,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"Like what works?","index":110,"end_time":453.06,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":452.18,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"I, I haven''t, I haven''t a clue because we haven''t figured it out.","index":111,"end_time":455.62,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":453.06,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"I don''t have the expertise in it.","index":112,"end_time":457.78,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":455.94,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"Natalie, that''s fundamentally why we''ve hired your group is, is you guys are smarter than us in this area.","index":113,"end_time":463.3,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":457.86,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"I mean, I''m going to follow your lead.","index":114,"end_time":465.55,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":463.95,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"But I will say that at this point we haven''t been successful in any of our outreach and to be fair, we''ve rotated people frequently and that might be an issue.","index":115,"end_time":474.27,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":465.55,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"But what is your expertise on this?","index":116,"end_time":478.03,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":474.27,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"What should we do?","index":117,"end_time":478.83,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":478.03,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"Yeah, we saw higher responses overall when we were more about just networking with the person to start.","index":118,"end_time":488.35,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":480.19,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Maybe what we can do is just have what''s running right now run for.","index":119,"end_time":494.21,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":490.93,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Give it four weeks, look at it at the end.","index":120,"end_time":497.45,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":494.45,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"If it''s still not producing results, then swap over to Keenan''s idea of just being more transparent about the fact that we''re trying to sell over Bond.","index":121,"end_time":506.77,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":497.45,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"I will say that I''ve done this a little bit, and when people started interacting with me, I felt like it was a waste of time if I couldn''t get them talking about a grip on eventually in chat.","index":122,"end_time":520.669,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":508.61,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"That''s a sales question.","index":123,"end_time":523.389,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":522.109,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"Keenan, you might have a different approach.","index":124,"end_time":525.629,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":523.469,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"But I was like, eventually I''d be like, no, this is what we do.","index":125,"end_time":531.469,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":525.869,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"Are you interested?","index":126,"end_time":532.469,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":531.469,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"Because if we''re going to meet, I want this to be a productive conversation.","index":127,"end_time":535.709,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":532.469,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"So that''s how I pushed him before I''d have a conversation with him.","index":128,"end_time":538.749,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":535.709,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":129,"end_time":539.909,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":539.469,"speaker_name":"Keenan Toward"},{"text":"So there''s two ways to handle that.","index":130,"end_time":541.469,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":539.909,"speaker_name":"Keenan Toward"},{"text":"And.","index":131,"end_time":541.659,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":541.469,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"And I''ll tell you the way that I do it now.","index":132,"end_time":543.81,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":542.05,"speaker_name":"Keenan Toward"},{"text":"When they come to me with a message where I''ve seen the messages where they''re essentially, they''re open to work and they''re just talking about, you know, web developing or whatever else, I''m very pointed as far as, like, hey, I typically word in the message that I would love to meet, connect, get to know them and their business and show them what a grip on can do for them.","index":133,"end_time":569.81,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":544.21,"speaker_name":"Keenan Toward"},{"text":"And.","index":134,"end_time":570.1,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":569.94,"speaker_name":"Keenan Toward"},{"text":"And that pretty much weeds out anybody who doesn''t want to have a conversation.","index":135,"end_time":573.53,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":570.17,"speaker_name":"Keenan Toward"},{"text":"I think that''s why we don''t get responses back in some of those conversations.","index":136,"end_time":577.93,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":573.53,"speaker_name":"Keenan Toward"},{"text":"Because I think the one from the other day, Lord''s Fuentes.","index":137,"end_time":585.53,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":579.69,"speaker_name":"Keenan Toward"},{"text":"There''s two problems that I see with dental.","index":138,"end_time":589.77,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":587.85,"speaker_name":"Keenan Toward"},{"text":"One is you either get your messages early in the morning or in the middle of the day when they''re busy, but then they don''t respond back because they''re busy all day.","index":139,"end_time":599.61,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":589.77,"speaker_name":"Keenan Toward"},{"text":"And so I try to get to that message about a grip on right off the bat.","index":140,"end_time":606.03,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":601.23,"speaker_name":"Keenan Toward"},{"text":"It''s involved first message.","index":141,"end_time":608.11,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":606.03,"speaker_name":"Keenan Toward"},{"text":"And that may be why we don''t get responses back sometimes at all.","index":142,"end_time":612.03,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":608.91,"speaker_name":"Keenan Toward"},{"text":"Because they realize, okay, they''re really about their business.","index":143,"end_time":614.99,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":612.03,"speaker_name":"Keenan Toward"},{"text":"This isn''t just maybe a job opportunity later or that kind of connection.","index":144,"end_time":621.31,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":615.47,"speaker_name":"Keenan Toward"},{"text":"It sounds like we should be more focused on directly introducing a grip on is what you''re proposing.","index":145,"end_time":629.85,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":623.23,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"I think that''s where I''m at.","index":146,"end_time":632.01,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":630.73,"speaker_name":"Keenan Toward"},{"text":"I. I think we have.","index":147,"end_time":633.45,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":632.01,"speaker_name":"Keenan Toward"},{"text":"I think we have 30 people that talk to us, and it doesn''t go anywhere.","index":148,"end_time":637.05,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":633.45,"speaker_name":"Keenan Toward"},{"text":"And we have five people that talk about a grip on and we get an opportunity to swing five times.","index":149,"end_time":640.97,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":637.13,"speaker_name":"Keenan Toward"},{"text":"That''s probably the way to go.","index":150,"end_time":642.49,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":641.21,"speaker_name":"Keenan Toward"},{"text":"Let''s do it.","index":151,"end_time":643.53,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":642.809,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"Natalie, can you update the outgoing message for us to approve?","index":152,"end_time":649.05,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":643.53,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"That would be more focused on introducing a grip on so we have a more targeted and focused.","index":153,"end_time":655.72,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":649.05,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"And also I''ll add this.","index":154,"end_time":657.44,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":655.72,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"Keenan and I have day jobs and this reduces the time that we would use.","index":155,"end_time":665.68,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":658.16,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"Just kind of building instead of just closing.","index":156,"end_time":669.28,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":665.68,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":157,"end_time":670.4,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":669.92,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Okay, I will send over an updated sequence then.","index":158,"end_time":675.76,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":672.08,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Very good.","index":159,"end_time":676.8,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":676.24,"speaker_name":"Keenan Toward"},{"text":"Thank you.","index":160,"end_time":677.36,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":676.8,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":161,"end_time":680.17,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":680.01,"speaker_name":"Keenan Toward"},{"text":"And I''ll just leave with one final thought on that.","index":162,"end_time":682.17,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":680.17,"speaker_name":"Keenan Toward"},{"text":"I definitely, as a busy person when I''m working and I think of this as leaders, I would rather a transparent and direct message that says what your intentions are than to find out.","index":163,"end_time":694.09,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":682.57,"speaker_name":"Keenan Toward"},{"text":"Four messages and you''re trying to sell me something because then I''m irritated you wasted my time.","index":164,"end_time":698.73,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":694.09,"speaker_name":"Keenan Toward"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":165,"end_time":699.61,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":699.13,"speaker_name":"Keenan Toward"},{"text":"If it''s not something I''m interested in, I don''t want to do that either.","index":166,"end_time":702.57,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":699.85,"speaker_name":"Keenan Toward"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":167,"end_time":703.45,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":702.97,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"And so maybe the message is, hey, if you experience the following, we have a solution.","index":168,"end_time":708.92,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":703.85,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"Learn about a grip on kind of thing.","index":169,"end_time":711,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":709,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":170,"end_time":712.52,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":712.04,"speaker_name":"Keenan Toward"},{"text":"Hey, we know, we know your business.","index":171,"end_time":715.32,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":713.56,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"We know you''re struggling with this.","index":172,"end_time":716.84,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":715.4,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"If you''re experiencing that, let us help you solve it kind of thing.","index":173,"end_time":719.64,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":716.84,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"I appreciate the input from both of you.","index":174,"end_time":724.92,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":722.68,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"Thank you.","index":175,"end_time":725.4,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":724.92,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"Okay, what else?","index":176,"end_time":726.76,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":725.8,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"All right, and then so I sent over some of the updates to the website.","index":177,"end_time":732.28,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":727.96,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"So just let me know if you guys have feedback on that and then we''ll get the changes made on the actual live site.","index":178,"end_time":738.79,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":733.83,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"So that''s just inserting the onboarding packages throughout some of our key pages.","index":179,"end_time":744.15,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":738.79,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"And I''ll.","index":180,"end_time":745.67,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":745.11,"speaker_name":"Keenan Toward"},{"text":"I''ll look through that today.","index":181,"end_time":746.71,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":745.67,"speaker_name":"Keenan Toward"},{"text":"Natalie.","index":182,"end_time":747.19,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":746.71,"speaker_name":"Keenan Toward"},{"text":"I''m working from home and I''ll have some time.","index":183,"end_time":748.87,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":747.19,"speaker_name":"Keenan Toward"},{"text":"So I''ll look through those today and get that back to you.","index":184,"end_time":750.95,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":748.87,"speaker_name":"Keenan Toward"},{"text":"Okay.","index":185,"end_time":751.95,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":751.43,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"I probably won''t be able to review, so accept Keenan''s responses.","index":186,"end_time":757.27,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":751.95,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"Okay.","index":187,"end_time":759.6,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":759.2,"speaker_name":"Keenan Toward"},{"text":"And then one other thing, Keenan, for the.","index":188,"end_time":762.24,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":759.6,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"So at the start, you sent over three calendly links that you created.","index":189,"end_time":767.32,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":762.48,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"One was the general virtual meeting.","index":190,"end_time":769.04,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":767.32,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"I think that was just for internally for us.","index":191,"end_time":771.84,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":769.04,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"And then you also have the live demo and the needs consultation.","index":192,"end_time":775.6,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":771.92,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"The live demo and needs consultation links aren''t working for some reason, but I think those would be good to include in the new email campaign we''re writing.","index":193,"end_time":784.8,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":776.24,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"So I''m just wondering if.","index":194,"end_time":786.38,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":785.42,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"I don''t know.","index":195,"end_time":787.34,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":786.78,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"The hard part with that is in my, my day to day job, I don''t have control of my schedule until probably the middle of February.","index":196,"end_time":796.62,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":788.14,"speaker_name":"Keenan Toward"},{"text":"Right now, I''M in that meeting clients phase.","index":197,"end_time":800.14,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":797.02,"speaker_name":"Keenan Toward"},{"text":"And so they''re having people go with me.","index":198,"end_time":802.66,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":800.22,"speaker_name":"Keenan Toward"},{"text":"They''re the ones that are actually reaching out and scheduling things.","index":199,"end_time":805.34,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":802.66,"speaker_name":"Keenan Toward"},{"text":"And so to leave my schedule open, there''s no way I can commit, and I''m not.","index":200,"end_time":811.02,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":805.82,"speaker_name":"Keenan Toward"},{"text":"I think we decided previously that we were going to not have any calendar links at the moment and just do forms.","index":201,"end_time":818.86,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":812.38,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":202,"end_time":819.66,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":819.18,"speaker_name":"Keenan Toward"},{"text":"Okay.","index":203,"end_time":822.62,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":822.06,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"And that could change, but I think that''s where we have to be now.","index":204,"end_time":825.9,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":823.02,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"And.","index":205,"end_time":826.86,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":826.46,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"And by the way, we did get two forms filled out in the past week.","index":206,"end_time":831.42,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":826.86,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"Yep.","index":207,"end_time":832.26,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":831.82,"speaker_name":"Keenan Toward"},{"text":"Which was amazing.","index":208,"end_time":833.82,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":832.26,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"And so we''ll have to be in that space now and excited about those two.","index":209,"end_time":840.3,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":834.7,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":210,"end_time":841.6,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":841.36,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Do they seem like good fits?","index":211,"end_time":842.88,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":841.6,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"So one''s an E Assist customer that''s leaving E Assist but wants to stay with the grip on.","index":212,"end_time":850.16,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":844.16,"speaker_name":"Keenan Toward"},{"text":"So that is a good sign as well.","index":213,"end_time":851.76,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":850.16,"speaker_name":"Keenan Toward"},{"text":"They feel the product''s worth it, even losing that partnership.","index":214,"end_time":855.36,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":851.84,"speaker_name":"Keenan Toward"},{"text":"The other one has not responded back yet, which.","index":215,"end_time":859.2,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":856.399,"speaker_name":"Keenan Toward"},{"text":"That''s kind of the dental world that I''ve.","index":216,"end_time":861.88,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":859.92,"speaker_name":"Keenan Toward"},{"text":"That I''m.","index":217,"end_time":862.44,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":861.88,"speaker_name":"Keenan Toward"},{"text":"I''m getting to see is they either respond first thing in the morning when they get in the office or.","index":218,"end_time":867.76,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":862.44,"speaker_name":"Keenan Toward"},{"text":"Or at some point during the day when their day is hectic, they send a message, but then they don''t respond back.","index":219,"end_time":872.15,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":867.83,"speaker_name":"Keenan Toward"},{"text":"Same day.","index":220,"end_time":873.03,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":872.47,"speaker_name":"Keenan Toward"},{"text":"So hopefully I''ll get something back today.","index":221,"end_time":874.63,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":873.03,"speaker_name":"Keenan Toward"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":222,"end_time":876.31,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":875.83,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"The other one''s an RCM company, which is.","index":223,"end_time":878.87,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":876.63,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"Which is exciting, but they are RCM and kind of everything dso, but not dso.","index":224,"end_time":884.55,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":878.87,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"Like they''ll provide all the services for a fee rather than a partnership.","index":225,"end_time":888.31,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":884.55,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"So I looked them up.","index":226,"end_time":889.99,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":888.95,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"That''s how I would interpret them.","index":227,"end_time":891.51,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":889.99,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"That''s an exciting connection.","index":228,"end_time":893.71,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":891.75,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"If we can capitalize on it.","index":229,"end_time":895.59,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":893.71,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":230,"end_time":897.28,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":896.96,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Yeah, for sure.","index":231,"end_time":898.8,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":897.92,"speaker_name":"Keenan Toward"},{"text":"Awesome.","index":232,"end_time":901.6,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":900.96,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Just out of curiosity, did either of those put their phone number on the form when they filled it?","index":233,"end_time":906.96,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":902,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"I just noticed that that field isn''t required, like on the website.","index":234,"end_time":910.32,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":907.04,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":235,"end_time":911.2,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":910.8,"speaker_name":"Keenan Toward"},{"text":"So one did.","index":236,"end_time":912.079,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":911.2,"speaker_name":"Keenan Toward"},{"text":"Okay.","index":237,"end_time":913.12,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":912.56,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":238,"end_time":914.08,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":913.6,"speaker_name":"Keenan Toward"},{"text":"The one from easist put our phone number in there.","index":239,"end_time":917.68,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":914.08,"speaker_name":"Keenan Toward"},{"text":"We should probably make that required.","index":240,"end_time":920.88,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":919.28,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":241,"end_time":921.85,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":921.45,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"And it.","index":242,"end_time":923.25,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":922.65,"speaker_name":"Keenan Toward"},{"text":"It did make the situation, obviously, a lot easier because I was able to just reach out and get some of the details versus back and forth and trying to figure out, you know, where they''re at, what they''re.","index":243,"end_time":935.69,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":923.25,"speaker_name":"Keenan Toward"},{"text":"What they need and what they''re willing to pay and all those things.","index":244,"end_time":940.01,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":936.25,"speaker_name":"Keenan Toward"},{"text":"Right.","index":245,"end_time":941.05,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":940.65,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Okay.","index":246,"end_time":943.29,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":942.89,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"We''ll get that updated.","index":247,"end_time":944.25,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":943.29,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"But that''s exciting.","index":248,"end_time":945.37,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":944.41,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":249,"end_time":946.73,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":946.25,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"It''s not zero.","index":250,"end_time":947.66,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":946.94,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":251,"end_time":948.78,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":948.3,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Okay.","index":252,"end_time":950.34,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":949.9,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":253,"end_time":950.58,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":950.34,"speaker_name":"Keenan Toward"},{"text":"So I. I honestly am in the position where I don''t mind if the.","index":254,"end_time":954.22,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":950.58,"speaker_name":"Keenan Toward"},{"text":"The website sees less traffic, if we have more leads.","index":255,"end_time":957.5,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":954.3,"speaker_name":"Keenan Toward"},{"text":"The leads are what''s going to make us money.","index":256,"end_time":959.18,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":957.5,"speaker_name":"Keenan Toward"},{"text":"So, yeah, definitely.","index":257,"end_time":961.86,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":959.26,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":258,"end_time":962.3,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":961.86,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Website stats are.","index":259,"end_time":964.46,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":963.42,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"They''re just a good indication, of course, that we''re getting in front of the right people.","index":260,"end_time":968.62,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":964.46,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"That being said, the website stats, like past 30 days have gone down.","index":261,"end_time":973.26,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":969.5,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"I noticed a big dip, especially from ABM traffic that decreased 27%.","index":262,"end_time":979.62,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":974.82,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"So like I said, that''s our focus right now, is standing up new ABM campaigns, just making sure that we''re constantly in front of the right people.","index":263,"end_time":986.42,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":980.34,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"And then for our LinkedIn cost per click.","index":264,"end_time":989.86,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":987.78,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"So we updated the campaigns to have a wider target audience and the cost per click is now down to $9 versus the 30 some.","index":265,"end_time":998.42,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":989.86,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"So, okay, good sign there.","index":266,"end_time":1000.75,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":999.31,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Yeah, good.","index":267,"end_time":1002.99,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1000.75,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"All right, so those were all of my notes.","index":268,"end_time":1008.27,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1004.75,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Anything else that you guys wanted to discuss?","index":269,"end_time":1010.11,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1008.59,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"I appreciate the email I got from Collins and that Facebook''s had some sort of breach.","index":270,"end_time":1017.39,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1012.99,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"Looks like we''re going to get some refunds, but it may take a while and that''s understood.","index":271,"end_time":1025.51,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1019.07,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"Also wanted to express gratitude.","index":272,"end_time":1028.47,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1025.99,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"I know last week I had to jump.","index":273,"end_time":1030.55,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1028.47,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"It was.","index":274,"end_time":1031.03,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1030.55,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"I was putting out a fire at work and appreciate you guys being patient with me and got his Note about the 25 points that you guys are gifting us and wanted to say thank you again.","index":275,"end_time":1045.51,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1032.63,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"And it''s not lost on me and what you''re doing and that you''re invested in our success.","index":276,"end_time":1049.91,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1046.23,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"Now.","index":277,"end_time":1052.41,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1052.17,"speaker_name":"Keenan Toward"},{"text":"That being said, what are our next steps?","index":278,"end_time":1057.05,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1053.61,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"It sounds like, I guess let''s just take a few minutes to brainstorm what are other things that we could try that might bring in more traffic or we might actually.","index":279,"end_time":1071.93,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1057.13,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"Yeah, go ahead.","index":280,"end_time":1073.53,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1072.73,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"One tiny note.","index":281,"end_time":1074.89,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1073.77,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"One thing I also noticed for the website, we.","index":282,"end_time":1078.01,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1075.61,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"One reason why traffic is down as well is our organic channels are down, meaning like Google and stuff like that.","index":283,"end_time":1085.07,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1079.07,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"And I think what was bringing in a lot of organic traffic before was the podcast episodes.","index":284,"end_time":1090.11,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1085.23,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Do we need to continue that?","index":285,"end_time":1092.27,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1090.91,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"Yeah, if.","index":286,"end_time":1093.63,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1092.75,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"How do you.","index":287,"end_time":1094.19,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1093.63,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"How do you know?","index":288,"end_time":1094.99,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1094.19,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"How are you able to connect those?","index":289,"end_time":1097.07,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1095.47,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"Because of YouTube.","index":290,"end_time":1099.55,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1098.43,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"So we put all of the episodes on YouTube and then in the description, we put like very long description of what the episode is about, things that people would be searching.","index":291,"end_time":1110.65,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1099.87,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"And then YouTube is the second largest search engine after Google.","index":292,"end_time":1114.73,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1111.37,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"So it is a really great way to bring in traffic.","index":293,"end_time":1117.85,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1115.45,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"One of our leads, Shane, did have the podcast link.","index":294,"end_time":1125.69,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1119.29,"speaker_name":"Keenan Toward"},{"text":"It said something about the podcast in the.","index":295,"end_time":1128.09,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1125.69,"speaker_name":"Keenan Toward"},{"text":"The lead.","index":296,"end_time":1129.21,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1128.57,"speaker_name":"Keenan Toward"},{"text":"Okay, then we''ve got to kick that.","index":297,"end_time":1131.61,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1129.69,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"Kick that into a little bit of higher gear.","index":298,"end_time":1133.77,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1131.69,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"But I think maybe next week.","index":299,"end_time":1138.21,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1136.13,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"Keenan, this week is slam for me, but next Wednesday it may be for you and Brad are free.","index":300,"end_time":1144.05,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1138.21,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"I will be in Albuquerque with another leader Tuesday Wednesday and Thursday, so my days.","index":301,"end_time":1151.65,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1145.97,"speaker_name":"Keenan Toward"},{"text":"Monday, I work from home.","index":302,"end_time":1153.49,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1151.65,"speaker_name":"Keenan Toward"},{"text":"Typically it''s our meeting day where we have calls and stuff throughout the day.","index":303,"end_time":1156.77,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1153.49,"speaker_name":"Keenan Toward"},{"text":"Friday, don''t worry about it.","index":304,"end_time":1158.69,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1157.01,"speaker_name":"Keenan Toward"},{"text":"So Friday afternoons are great for me, if that''s something you guys can do.","index":305,"end_time":1162.05,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1158.93,"speaker_name":"Keenan Toward"},{"text":"Yeah, maybe.","index":306,"end_time":1163.29,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1162.65,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"Yeah, I need to.","index":307,"end_time":1166.37,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1165.21,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"Let''s start a chat with Brad and we''ll see if we can''t introduce you to the podcast and maybe the three of us.","index":308,"end_time":1173.17,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1166.37,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"And between the three of us, we''ll do some entertainment, I think.","index":309,"end_time":1176.17,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1173.17,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"Okay, good.","index":310,"end_time":1177.13,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1176.33,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"Natalie.","index":311,"end_time":1177.65,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1177.13,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"Thank you.","index":312,"end_time":1178.09,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1177.65,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"Keenan, are you able to interpret that spreadsheet and make contacts with it?","index":313,"end_time":1186.45,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1182.01,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"Is it enough for you?","index":314,"end_time":1187.45,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1186.45,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"Yeah, I mean, I''m going through anything that has an email I''m trying to go through, clean it up.","index":315,"end_time":1196.54,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1189.7,"speaker_name":"Keenan Toward"},{"text":"And I have kind of a. I put together an email that I send that takes them to the agrippon page.","index":316,"end_time":1204.14,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1196.54,"speaker_name":"Keenan Toward"},{"text":"I have links on the.","index":317,"end_time":1205.3,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1204.14,"speaker_name":"Keenan Toward"},{"text":"In the email that I send them that has the.","index":318,"end_time":1209.54,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1205.62,"speaker_name":"Keenan Toward"},{"text":"What is it called?","index":319,"end_time":1213.1,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1212.34,"speaker_name":"Keenan Toward"},{"text":"The walkthrough or, or the.","index":320,"end_time":1214.7,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1213.1,"speaker_name":"Keenan Toward"},{"text":"So I, I put a link in the email body for that and then I''m sending that out.","index":321,"end_time":1223.02,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1216.22,"speaker_name":"Keenan Toward"},{"text":"But none of the ones that I''ve sent so far have had a response.","index":322,"end_time":1227.26,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1223.66,"speaker_name":"Keenan Toward"},{"text":"So I''m going to keep going back through the old data and sending some of that over and seeing just what I can drum up on my own on kind of the business development kind of idea.","index":323,"end_time":1239.82,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1228.62,"speaker_name":"Keenan Toward"},{"text":"And, and, but the, but the data in there is sufficient for you to attempt some sort of contact?","index":324,"end_time":1245.94,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1240.5,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"Yeah, yeah.","index":325,"end_time":1247.58,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1246.74,"speaker_name":"Keenan Toward"},{"text":"So very good.","index":326,"end_time":1248.34,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1247.58,"speaker_name":"Keenan Toward"},{"text":"There''s two pages that can have emails, the other ones that have websites.","index":327,"end_time":1253.3,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1248.34,"speaker_name":"Keenan Toward"},{"text":"I can go to the websites and they typically have some sort of contact info on there utilizing that information.","index":328,"end_time":1260.02,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1253.3,"speaker_name":"Keenan Toward"},{"text":"It''s just more time consuming to do those ones.","index":329,"end_time":1263.62,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1260.58,"speaker_name":"Keenan Toward"},{"text":"Very good.","index":330,"end_time":1264.54,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1264.02,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"I mean, obviously that''s.","index":331,"end_time":1266.02,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1264.54,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"Is that something that we can automate or in studies in Keenan''s time.","index":332,"end_time":1271.62,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1266.82,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"To.","index":333,"end_time":1273.82,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1273.54,"speaker_name":"Keenan Toward"},{"text":"Take that spreadsheet and use it as an outreach, automated effort.","index":334,"end_time":1278.18,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1273.82,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":335,"end_time":1279.46,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1279.06,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"I think the only thing we''re limited by is that we don''t actually know exactly who was on the site.","index":336,"end_time":1286.58,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1279.46,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Just because of the.","index":337,"end_time":1287.54,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1286.66,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"We do with the ABM stuff.","index":338,"end_time":1289.86,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1287.62,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"Right.","index":339,"end_time":1290.18,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1289.86,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"Because that''s the email and they respond to that.","index":340,"end_time":1292.42,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1290.26,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"We do have that one.","index":341,"end_time":1293.62,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1292.42,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":342,"end_time":1295.07,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1294.83,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"So we can see who clicked on links in emails.","index":343,"end_time":1297.71,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1295.07,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Is that what you''re referring to?","index":344,"end_time":1299.11,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1297.87,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Or people that visit the website?","index":345,"end_time":1301.23,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1299.11,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Yeah, the, the, the ones that show email.","index":346,"end_time":1305.39,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1303.07,"speaker_name":"Keenan Toward"},{"text":"So page three of your spreadsheet has the emails.","index":347,"end_time":1309.51,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1305.39,"speaker_name":"Keenan Toward"},{"text":"Are we able to use that data?","index":348,"end_time":1311.07,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1309.51,"speaker_name":"Keenan Toward"},{"text":"If I formulate an email with information, are you able to automate something for that?","index":349,"end_time":1317.79,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1311.23,"speaker_name":"Keenan Toward"},{"text":"I mean, fundamentally what we''re saying is Like a.","index":350,"end_time":1320.27,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1318.03,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"Like a next round of contact that says, hey, we saw you clicked.","index":351,"end_time":1324.42,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1320.82,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"Yeah, yeah, we can definitely do that.","index":352,"end_time":1327.86,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1325.54,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"We also have it set up so that where every week we''re looking at who clicks on an email.","index":353,"end_time":1332.74,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1327.86,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"But just one click maybe isn''t a good indication of interest, but correct the month we look at.","index":354,"end_time":1338.5,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1333.06,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Okay.","index":355,"end_time":1338.86,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1338.5,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Did someone have three plus clicks throughout the month?","index":356,"end_time":1341.06,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1338.86,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Yes.","index":357,"end_time":1341.62,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1341.06,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"Someone we want to keep reaching out to.","index":358,"end_time":1344.1,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1341.86,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"That would be fantastic.","index":359,"end_time":1345.9,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1344.58,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"The log the out.","index":360,"end_time":1347.06,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1345.9,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"The logic would be, have you clicked with three times within the last 30 days.","index":361,"end_time":1350.98,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1347.06,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"And if you have, then here''s an extra email for just for you and maybe it has an offer.","index":362,"end_time":1356.75,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1351.79,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"Keenan, I mean, in Natalie, I''m curious what you guys might have that content be.","index":363,"end_time":1361.39,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1357.31,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"But try now for 30 days or something.","index":364,"end_time":1364.99,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1362.03,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"Or we saw you clicked or I mean, not too creepy, right?","index":365,"end_time":1369.79,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1364.99,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":366,"end_time":1370.67,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1370.19,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"In other words, Keenan is spending time going through that spreadsheet.","index":367,"end_time":1376.59,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1372.83,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"Let''s give him back some time and see if we can''t automate that message that he would send out.","index":368,"end_time":1382.44,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1376.59,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"Okay, I''ll make a note of that.","index":369,"end_time":1388.04,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1384.28,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Keenan, do you want to.","index":370,"end_time":1389.64,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1388.52,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Do you want to write that automated sequence or would you like us to.","index":371,"end_time":1393.64,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1389.72,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Let me put something together on that?","index":372,"end_time":1400.52,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1398.68,"speaker_name":"Keenan Toward"},{"text":"Because I. I think that''s something that kind of fits into my wheelhouse anyway.","index":373,"end_time":1404.6,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1400.76,"speaker_name":"Keenan Toward"},{"text":"And then you guys can kind of do the overlook and say, yeah, it looks.","index":374,"end_time":1408.71,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1405.47,"speaker_name":"Keenan Toward"},{"text":"Looks good.","index":375,"end_time":1409.23,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1408.71,"speaker_name":"Keenan Toward"},{"text":"Or we would add this.","index":376,"end_time":1410.51,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1409.23,"speaker_name":"Keenan Toward"},{"text":"I appreciate that feedback anytime you guys do that.","index":377,"end_time":1413.59,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1411.07,"speaker_name":"Keenan Toward"},{"text":"Because obviously we''re all different in how we communicate and what kind of, you know, what kind of communication we use.","index":378,"end_time":1420.91,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1413.59,"speaker_name":"Keenan Toward"},{"text":"And so I''ll put together something, have you guys look it over, see what you guys want to add to it.","index":379,"end_time":1426.03,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1421.39,"speaker_name":"Keenan Toward"},{"text":"And you guys probably add some photos or pictures, things like that that can, you know, add some spark to it.","index":380,"end_time":1434.23,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1426.67,"speaker_name":"Keenan Toward"},{"text":"And that would definitely help as well.","index":381,"end_time":1436.07,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1434.23,"speaker_name":"Keenan Toward"},{"text":"Yeah, I imagine so, from what I''ve seen of the data, that there are many people that we could contact this way.","index":382,"end_time":1443.03,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1437.11,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"Yeah, yeah.","index":383,"end_time":1445.07,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1443.59,"speaker_name":"Keenan Toward"},{"text":"There was several hundred lines, I think, when I looked at it.","index":384,"end_time":1447.99,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1445.07,"speaker_name":"Keenan Toward"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":385,"end_time":1449.43,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1448.95,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Okay.","index":386,"end_time":1450.95,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1450.39,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"And then just in terms of the offer, we do have this free trial page.","index":387,"end_time":1455.51,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1451.11,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Yep.","index":388,"end_time":1456.43,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1455.91,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"They could do that one.","index":389,"end_time":1457.35,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1456.43,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"That could be an offer.","index":390,"end_time":1458.23,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1457.35,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":391,"end_time":1459.13,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1458.93,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"So that''s one idea.","index":392,"end_time":1460.37,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1459.13,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"And the other thing that we look that they need to understand, like, we''re just going to talk.","index":393,"end_time":1466.09,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1461.09,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"There''s no real pressure, you know, let''s learn about each other.","index":394,"end_time":1470.21,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1466.09,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"Let''s, you know, if you''re curious, we''re curious, let''s talk.","index":395,"end_time":1472.93,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1470.21,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"I don''t know.","index":396,"end_time":1473.61,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1473.01,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"Yeah, yeah.","index":397,"end_time":1475.93,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1473.61,"speaker_name":"Keenan Toward"},{"text":"One of our leads was specifically, she said she wanted a free trial.","index":398,"end_time":1480.25,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1475.93,"speaker_name":"Keenan Toward"},{"text":"And that''s when I Can''t get to respond back.","index":399,"end_time":1482.01,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1480.25,"speaker_name":"Keenan Toward"},{"text":"That''s when I''ve messaged on LinkedIn and an email.","index":400,"end_time":1484.45,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1482.01,"speaker_name":"Keenan Toward"},{"text":"She hasn''t responded back.","index":401,"end_time":1486.76,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1485.64,"speaker_name":"Keenan Toward"},{"text":"So hopefully that''s just a.","index":402,"end_time":1489.52,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1487.56,"speaker_name":"Keenan Toward"},{"text":"She''s a busy.","index":403,"end_time":1490.16,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1489.52,"speaker_name":"Keenan Toward"},{"text":"She''s busy thing, and that''s why she''s not responding.","index":404,"end_time":1492.44,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1490.16,"speaker_name":"Keenan Toward"},{"text":"But I would say the most important thing out of all this conversation is we''ve got to make phone numbers mandatory in all the forms.","index":405,"end_time":1500.92,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1492.68,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":406,"end_time":1501.68,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1501.32,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":407,"end_time":1502.04,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1501.68,"speaker_name":"Keenan Toward"},{"text":"Cool.","index":408,"end_time":1514.93,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1514.61,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"Well, I do feel like we''re making progress.","index":409,"end_time":1517.49,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1515.25,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"We haven''t heard back from people, and I know, Keenan, other people went silent after we did talk to them.","index":410,"end_time":1522.81,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1517.49,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"I know you did a couple demos and then it just kind of died off.","index":411,"end_time":1525.73,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1522.81,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"Unfortunately, this is a time of year in Dental, too.","index":412,"end_time":1530.61,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1528.05,"speaker_name":"Keenan Toward"},{"text":"That''s rough because in January, that.","index":413,"end_time":1534.29,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1530.61,"speaker_name":"Keenan Toward"},{"text":"This is when your company starts making changes based on revenue from the previous year, things of that nature.","index":414,"end_time":1541.15,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1534.29,"speaker_name":"Keenan Toward"},{"text":"Dental typically has turnover in the winter.","index":415,"end_time":1545.39,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1541.39,"speaker_name":"Keenan Toward"},{"text":"That''s just a common thing.","index":416,"end_time":1548.23,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1546.75,"speaker_name":"Keenan Toward"},{"text":"Brad''s dealing with it on his own.","index":417,"end_time":1549.95,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1548.23,"speaker_name":"Keenan Toward"},{"text":"Both clients that I dealt with said the same thing that they were.","index":418,"end_time":1555.11,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1550.67,"speaker_name":"Keenan Toward"},{"text":"They had some issues that they were starting to deal with.","index":419,"end_time":1557.15,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1555.11,"speaker_name":"Keenan Toward"},{"text":"And so that''s just.","index":420,"end_time":1559.27,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1557.55,"speaker_name":"Keenan Toward"},{"text":"I think, can we.","index":421,"end_time":1560.75,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1559.27,"speaker_name":"Keenan Toward"},{"text":"Can we tailor a message that says, we know that January is a big turn, like a challenge for you.","index":422,"end_time":1566.15,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1560.75,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"Let''s.","index":423,"end_time":1566.43,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1566.15,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"Let''s maybe something a little personal.","index":424,"end_time":1568.1,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1566.43,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"Hey, January is tough.","index":425,"end_time":1569.86,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1568.58,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"We know that you''re probably dealing with turnover with blah, blah, blah, blah, blah.","index":426,"end_time":1573.46,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1569.86,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"We want to help.","index":427,"end_time":1574.42,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1573.54,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"Yeah, yeah.","index":428,"end_time":1576.54,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1575.06,"speaker_name":"Keenan Toward"},{"text":"That''s kind of that.","index":429,"end_time":1577.5,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1576.54,"speaker_name":"Keenan Toward"},{"text":"That''s why I wanted to.","index":430,"end_time":1578.66,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1577.5,"speaker_name":"Keenan Toward"},{"text":"To put that message together.","index":431,"end_time":1580.34,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1578.66,"speaker_name":"Keenan Toward"},{"text":"The emails that I''ve been sending is essentially, it has some links in it to get them to the website, and then it says, here''s what a gripon is doing for people already.","index":432,"end_time":1590.9,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1580.34,"speaker_name":"Keenan Toward"},{"text":"And then I have some bullet points in that email that kind of.","index":433,"end_time":1593.86,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1591.14,"speaker_name":"Keenan Toward"},{"text":"To kind of catch the eye of those people that are running an office right now because they lost somebody or dealing with poor communication.","index":434,"end_time":1601.94,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1594.9,"speaker_name":"Keenan Toward"},{"text":"That''s kind of the things that I''m focusing on in that message.","index":435,"end_time":1604.66,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1601.94,"speaker_name":"Keenan Toward"},{"text":"And so that''s kind of how I''ll draft that up as well.","index":436,"end_time":1608.58,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1605.38,"speaker_name":"Keenan Toward"},{"text":"Cool.","index":437,"end_time":1610.98,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1610.5,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"All right, let''s keep plugging.","index":438,"end_time":1615.06,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1613.54,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"Thanks for all you do, Natalie.","index":439,"end_time":1618.02,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1615.3,"speaker_name":"Keenan Toward"},{"text":"For the website revisions, I''ll get that approved to you today.","index":440,"end_time":1621.06,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1618.02,"speaker_name":"Keenan Toward"},{"text":"And then for the message that we want to start sending out out, I''ll probably get that maybe today, but I would say by Friday, I''ll commit to getting that message to you for you guys to take a look at.","index":441,"end_time":1632.12,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1621.3,"speaker_name":"Keenan Toward"},{"text":"Okay, cool.","index":442,"end_time":1633.52,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1632.68,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"And then we''ll.","index":443,"end_time":1634.16,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1633.52,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"At the end of the month, we''ll take a look at all the clicks from January and then compile that list of who we want to send that out to.","index":444,"end_time":1640.68,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1634.16,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Okay?","index":445,"end_time":1641.88,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1641.24,"speaker_name":"Keenan Toward"},{"text":"Awesome.","index":446,"end_time":1646.28,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1645.72,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"Sounds good.","index":447,"end_time":1647.88,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1647.24,"speaker_name":"Keenan Toward"},{"text":"Appreciate it.","index":448,"end_time":1648.44,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1647.88,"speaker_name":"Keenan Toward"},{"text":"Good talking to you guys.","index":449,"end_time":1649.48,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1648.44,"speaker_name":"Keenan Toward"},{"text":"Thanks, everybody.","index":450,"end_time":1651.16,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1650.28,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"I''ll send that meeting or the note.","index":451,"end_time":1653.68,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1651.24,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"I''ll start texting with you and Brad Keenan.","index":452,"end_time":1656.04,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1653.68,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"Okay, sounds good.","index":453,"end_time":1657.2,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1656.36,"speaker_name":"Keenan Toward"},{"text":"Thanks, Shane.","index":454,"end_time":1657.8,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1657.2,"speaker_name":"Keenan Toward"},{"text":"All right, man.","index":455,"end_time":1658.6,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1657.96,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"Bye.","index":456,"end_time":1659.96,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1659.48,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"}],"dateString":"2026-01-22T13:30:00.000Z","host_email":"nathalie.mintjens@marketersindemand.com","meeting_link":"https://us02web.zoom.us/j/83663022990?pwd=R1aTMdTGv2yblYfzlB6Wv1Sup4Z47U.1","participants":["colin.costigan@marketersindemand.com,nathalie.mintjens@marketersindemand.com,david.edmund.reynolds@gmail.com,shane@agrippon.com,f.dominguez@agrippon.com,j.samstag@agrippon.com,monique.king@agrippon.com,david.reynolds@agrippon.com,keenan.toward@agrippon.com","colin.costigan@marketersindemand.com","david.edmund.reynolds@gmail.com","shane@agrippon.com","f.dominguez@agrippon.com","j.samstag@agrippon.com","monique.king@agrippon.com","david.reynolds@agrippon.com","keenan.toward@agrippon.com"],"transcript_url":"https://app.fireflies.ai/view/01KF0ZBV2SQMYHZZJS1ES4J02X","organizer_email":"nathalie.mintjens@marketersindemand.com"}'::jsonb,
    '{"label":"positive","confidence":0.87,"bullets":["Agreed to refocus LinkedIn outreach on directly introducing aGripon to target qualified leads.","Natalie to update LinkedIn connection sequence and send for approval by end of day.","Team identified new leads including one departing eAssist but staying with aGripon.","Mandatory phone number fields to be added to forms to improve lead follow-up efficiency.","Keenan committed to draft automated outreach message for high-engagement email contacts by Friday."],"highlights":[{"quote":"I do feel like we''re making progress.","speaker":"Shane Billings"},{"quote":"I''d rather the messaging be more around a grip on and what we have to offer.","speaker":"Keenan Toward"},{"quote":"Website stats have gone down...our focus right now is standing up new ABM campaigns.","speaker":"Nathalie Mintjens"}],"topics":["outreach","leadgen","linkedin","campaign","messaging"],"model":"openai/gpt-4-1106-preview","version":1,"generated_at":"2026-01-23T20:11:00Z"}'::jsonb,
    '{"fireflies_summary":{"notes":"## **LinkedIn Outreach Strategy**\n\nThe team decided to shift LinkedIn messaging to be more direct about introducing **a grip on** to improve lead quality and reduce irrelevant responses (11:09).\n\n- **Keenan Toward proposed** focusing messages on what a grip on offers rather than general networking to avoid attracting job seekers and unrelated sales pitches (06:22).\n    - This approach aims to reduce wasted time by being upfront about sales intentions.\n    - Shane Billings agreed and requested Nathalie Mintjens update the LinkedIn message sequence accordingly (10:42).\n    - The updated messaging will target prospects more likely to convert, saving Keenan and Shane time spent on unproductive conversations.\n    - This change reflects a strategic priority to generate meaningful sales conversations rather than casual networking.\n\n- **Current LinkedIn campaigns show lower engagement**, with Nathalie noting better response rates from networking-style outreach but acknowledging inefficiency in generating qualified leads (06:52).\n    - The team agreed to run the existing campaign for four more weeks before switching fully to the direct approach if results don’t improve (08:00).\n    - Shane emphasized the need to convert conversations toward a grip on quickly to maintain productive sales discussions (08:28).\n    - Messaging will aim to be transparent and respectful of prospects’ time to build trust and reduce drop-offs (11:20).\n\n- **Operational complexity arises from using Brad’s LinkedIn account**, as it causes confusion when Keenan contacts leads separately (02:17).\n    - Shane suggested creative messaging to clarify roles between Brad and Keenan during outreach.\n    - The team acknowledged the need for phone numbers in campaigns to enable calls, which are more effective than LinkedIn messaging alone (03:38).\n    - Nathalie committed to adding and making phone number fields mandatory in lead capture forms to improve contact quality (03:44, 15:01).\n\n## **Lead Capture and Follow-Up Processes**\n\nThe focus is on improving lead quality through better form data and automated follow-ups to increase conversion rates (22:21).\n\n- **Two promising leads emerged recently**, including one existing **E Assist customer switching to a grip on** and one **RCM company** with potential, highlighting lead quality importance (13:51).\n    - The E Assist lead included a phone number, enabling faster and more effective follow-up (15:12).\n    - Shane and Nathalie agreed to make phone numbers mandatory on all forms to streamline outreach (15:19).\n    - Keenan values leads over website traffic, emphasizing quality over quantity in inbound contacts (15:50).\n\n- **Automation of follow-up emails based on engagement data** from email campaigns will save manual work and improve targeting (22:21).\n    - Nathalie confirmed the system tracks email link clicks and flags contacts with three or more clicks in 30 days for targeted follow-up.\n    - Shane requested Keenan draft the content for automated outreach emails, with the team providing feedback and creative input afterward (23:18).\n    - The offer will likely include a free trial page link to encourage engagement (24:15).\n    - This automation will free Keenan’s time and ensure persistent outreach to warmer leads, increasing conversion chances.\n\n- **Calendly links for demos are currently non-functional and not being used**, due to scheduling conflicts, and will be replaced by forms until mid-February when availability improves (12:39).\n    - This prevents overbooking and ensures leads are managed realistically given Keenan’s current workload (13:08).\n\n## **Marketing Campaign Performance and Website Updates**\n\nThe team is refreshing campaigns and website content to address declining traffic and improve lead generation quality (15:50).\n\n- **Website traffic dropped 27% in the last 30 days, especially from ABM sources**, signaling a need for new account-based marketing campaigns targeting the right audience (15:59).\n    - Nathalie is launching new ABM campaigns to reverse this trend and maintain visibility with key prospects.\n    - LinkedIn cost per click has improved significantly, dropping to **$9 from over $30**, due to wider targeting adjustments (15:59).\n    - These adjustments aim to increase traffic quality while reducing ad spend.\n\n- **Website changes include inserting onboarding package information on key pages**, with Keenan reviewing updates for approval (12:07).\n    - This aims to clarify product offerings and guide visitors toward conversion.\n    - Keenan committed to reviewing and approving these changes promptly to keep the website aligned with current messaging (12:25).\n\n- **Organic traffic decline is partly linked to reduced podcast activity**, which had been driving noticeable traffic through YouTube’s search engine (17:53).\n    - Nathalie emphasized the importance of continuing podcast episodes to maintain organic reach.\n    - Shane proposed involving Keenan and Brad in podcast efforts to boost engagement and create entertaining content (18:49).\n\n## **Sales Cycle Timing and Messaging Tailoring**\n\nThe team recognizes seasonal challenges in dental industry sales and plans to tailor messaging to address these realities (25:14).\n\n- **January is a difficult month due to dental industry turnover and budget resets**, causing many leads to go silent post-demo (25:28).\n    - Keenan is drafting messages acknowledging these pain points to connect personally with prospects.\n    - Messaging will highlight understanding of industry challenges and position a grip on as a solution provider during tough periods (26:00).\n    - This tailored approach aims to increase empathy and relevance, improving response rates.\n\n- **Keenan will deliver the updated LinkedIn and email messaging drafts by Friday for review**, targeting the end of January for campaign refreshes (26:55).\n    - Nathalie will compile click engagement data at the end of January to refine the automated outreach list (27:12).\n    - Shane will coordinate with Brad and Keenan for podcast and outreach integration moving forward (27:30).\n\n## **Team Collaboration and Resource Allocation**\n\nThe meeting concluded with commitments to optimize workflows and leverage team strengths to increase efficiency and focus (07:26).\n\n- **Shane acknowledged the team’s limited expertise in LinkedIn outreach and committed to following Nathalie’s guidance** as marketing experts (07:26).\n    - This reflects a strategic choice to trust specialized vendors to improve campaign effectiveness.\n    - Keenan’s role focuses on business development and crafting outreach content within his capacity.\n\n- **Keenan is actively managing lead outreach with available data, supported by Nathalie and Shane’s automation and campaign efforts** (19:49).\n    - Automation and improved data capture will help Keenan focus on closing rather than prospecting.\n    - The team agreed to maintain flexibility around scheduling and communication channels due to workload constraints (13:08).\n\n- **Shane expressed appreciation for the ongoing support and recent advertising refunds from Facebook**, indicating positive vendor relations and cost management (16:52).\n    - This financial relief contributes to sustaining marketing efforts despite current performance challenges.","outline":null,"keywords":["LinkedIn campaign","direct messaging","lead generation","website updates","podcast marketing","dental industry seasonality"],"overview":"- **Direct LinkedIn Messaging Change:** Shift to direct messaging about a grip on to improve lead quality and reduce irrelevant responses.\n\n- **Mandatory Phone Numbers:** Team agreed to make phone numbers required on forms to enhance follow-up efficiency and lead quality.\n\n- **Automated Follow-Up Emails:** Automation based on engagement data will save manual effort and double follow-up chances on warmer leads.\n\n- **Website Traffic Decline:** 27% drop in traffic noted; new ABM campaigns to be launched to attract better-targeted audience.\n\n- **Podcast Activity Importance:** Continued podcast episodes are essential for maintaining organic traffic and boosting engagement.\n\n- **Customized Messaging for Sales Cycle:** Tailored messages acknowledging dental industry challenges aim to improve connections and response rates.","action_items":"\n**Keenan Toward**\nReview website updates with onboarding packages and provide feedback today (12:25)\nDraft new LinkedIn message sequence focused on introducing Agrippon directly and submit for team approval by Friday (10:42)\nContinue outreach using updated contact lists and send tailored email messages to potential leads (19:49)\nPrepare automated email sequence for re-engagement of clicking leads for review by Natalie and Shane (23:04)\n\n**Nathalie Mintjens**\nUpdate outgoing LinkedIn message sequence as per new direction and send for approval (11:09)\nMake phone number field required on all website lead capture forms to improve lead quality (15:40)\nFix issues with non-functioning Calendly links for demo and consultation forms (12:39)\nMonitor weekly email engagement data and compile list of contacts with three or more clicks per month at month-end for follow-up campaign (27:12)\n\n**Shane Billings**\nCoordinate with Brad to confirm scheduling availability for demo and consultation meetings (19:22)\nReview and provide feedback on Keenan’s drafted email outreach sequence (23:57)\nCommunicate with Natalie and Keenan on progress and next steps including podcast promotion and lead nurturing strategy (27:30)\n"},"migrated_from":"contract_meetings","original_id":"102234f8-a310-477e-bb91-042395b8e6a9","master_marketer":{"status":"migrated"}}'::jsonb,
