INSERT INTO compass_notes (contract_id, meeting_id, note_type, title, content_raw, note_date, status, action_items, is_auto_generated)
SELECT
  new_meeting.contract_id,
  new_meeting.meeting_id,
  'meeting',
  'Meeting Notes: Agrippon // New North Weekly Connect',
  '## **LinkedIn Outreach Strategy**

The team decided to shift LinkedIn messaging to be more direct about introducing **a grip on** to improve lead quality and reduce irrelevant responses (11:09).

- **Keenan Toward proposed** focusing messages on what a grip on offers rather than general networking to avoid attracting job seekers and unrelated sales pitches (06:22).
    - This approach aims to reduce wasted time by being upfront about sales intentions.
    - Shane Billings agreed and requested Nathalie Mintjens update the LinkedIn message sequence accordingly (10:42).
    - The updated messaging will target prospects more likely to convert, saving Keenan and Shane time spent on unproductive conversations.
    - This change reflects a strategic priority to generate meaningful sales conversations rather than casual networking.

- **Current LinkedIn campaigns show lower engagement**, with Nathalie noting better response rates from networking-style outreach but acknowledging inefficiency in generating qualified leads (06:52).
    - The team agreed to run the existing campaign for four more weeks before switching fully to the direct approach if results don’t improve (08:00).
    - Shane emphasized the need to convert conversations toward a grip on quickly to maintain productive sales discussions (08:28).
    - Messaging will aim to be transparent and respectful of prospects’ time to build trust and reduce drop-offs (11:20).

- **Operational complexity arises from using Brad’s LinkedIn account**, as it causes confusion when Keenan contacts leads separately (02:17).
    - Shane suggested creative messaging to clarify roles between Brad and Keenan during outreach.
    - The team acknowledged the need for phone numbers in campaigns to enable calls, which are more effective than LinkedIn messaging alone (03:38).
    - Nathalie committed to adding and making phone number fields mandatory in lead capture forms to improve contact quality (03:44, 15:01).

## **Lead Capture and Follow-Up Processes**

The focus is on improving lead quality through better form data and automated follow-ups to increase conversion rates (22:21).

- **Two promising leads emerged recently**, including one existing **E Assist customer switching to a grip on** and one **RCM company** with potential, highlighting lead quality importance (13:51).
    - The E Assist lead included a phone number, enabling faster and more effective follow-up (15:12).
    - Shane and Nathalie agreed to make phone numbers mandatory on all forms to streamline outreach (15:19).
    - Keenan values leads over website traffic, emphasizing quality over quantity in inbound contacts (15:50).

- **Automation of follow-up emails based on engagement data** from email campaigns will save manual work and improve targeting (22:21).
    - Nathalie confirmed the system tracks email link clicks and flags contacts with three or more clicks in 30 days for targeted follow-up.
    - Shane requested Keenan draft the content for automated outreach emails, with the team providing feedback and creative input afterward (23:18).
    - The offer will likely include a free trial page link to encourage engagement (24:15).
    - This automation will free Keenan’s time and ensure persistent outreach to warmer leads, increasing conversion chances.

- **Calendly links for demos are currently non-functional and not being used**, due to scheduling conflicts, and will be replaced by forms until mid-February when availability improves (12:39).
    - This prevents overbooking and ensures leads are managed realistically given Keenan’s current workload (13:08).

## **Marketing Campaign Performance and Website Updates**

The team is refreshing campaigns and website content to address declining traffic and improve lead generation quality (15:50).

- **Website traffic dropped 27% in the last 30 days, especially from ABM sources**, signaling a need for new account-based marketing campaigns targeting the right audience (15:59).
    - Nathalie is launching new ABM campaigns to reverse this trend and maintain visibility with key prospects.
    - LinkedIn cost per click has improved significantly, dropping to **$9 from over $30**, due to wider targeting adjustments (15:59).
    - These adjustments aim to increase traffic quality while reducing ad spend.

- **Website changes include inserting onboarding package information on key pages**, with Keenan reviewing updates for approval (12:07).
    - This aims to clarify product offerings and guide visitors toward conversion.
    - Keenan committed to reviewing and approving these changes promptly to keep the website aligned with current messaging (12:25).

- **Organic traffic decline is partly linked to reduced podcast activity**, which had been driving noticeable traffic through YouTube’s search engine (17:53).
    - Nathalie emphasized the importance of continuing podcast episodes to maintain organic reach.
    - Shane proposed involving Keenan and Brad in podcast efforts to boost engagement and create entertaining content (18:49).

## **Sales Cycle Timing and Messaging Tailoring**

The team recognizes seasonal challenges in dental industry sales and plans to tailor messaging to address these realities (25:14).

- **January is a difficult month due to dental industry turnover and budget resets**, causing many leads to go silent post-demo (25:28).
    - Keenan is drafting messages acknowledging these pain points to connect personally with prospects.
    - Messaging will highlight understanding of industry challenges and position a grip on as a solution provider during tough periods (26:00).
    - This tailored approach aims to increase empathy and relevance, improving response rates.

- **Keenan will deliver the updated LinkedIn and email messaging drafts by Friday for review**, targeting the end of January for campaign refreshes (26:55).
    - Nathalie will compile click engagement data at the end of January to refine the automated outreach list (27:12).
    - Shane will coordinate with Brad and Keenan for podcast and outreach integration moving forward (27:30).

## **Team Collaboration and Resource Allocation**

The meeting concluded with commitments to optimize workflows and leverage team strengths to increase efficiency and focus (07:26).

- **Shane acknowledged the team’s limited expertise in LinkedIn outreach and committed to following Nathalie’s guidance** as marketing experts (07:26).
    - This reflects a strategic choice to trust specialized vendors to improve campaign effectiveness.
    - Keenan’s role focuses on business development and crafting outreach content within his capacity.

- **Keenan is actively managing lead outreach with available data, supported by Nathalie and Shane’s automation and campaign efforts** (19:49).
    - Automation and improved data capture will help Keenan focus on closing rather than prospecting.
    - The team agreed to maintain flexibility around scheduling and communication channels due to workload constraints (13:08).

- **Shane expressed appreciation for the ongoing support and recent advertising refunds from Facebook**, indicating positive vendor relations and cost management (16:52).
    - This financial relief contributes to sustaining marketing efforts despite current performance challenges.',
  '2026-01-22 13:30:00+00',
  'published',
  '[{"text":"Review website updates with onboarding packages and provide feedback today (12:25)","completed":false},{"text":"Draft new LinkedIn message sequence focused on introducing Agrippon directly and submit for team approval by Friday (10:42)","completed":false},{"text":"Continue outreach using updated contact lists and send tailored email messages to potential leads (19:49)","completed":false},{"text":"Prepare automated email sequence for re-engagement of clicking leads for review by Natalie and Shane (23:04)","completed":false},{"text":"Update outgoing LinkedIn message sequence as per new direction and send for approval (11:09)","completed":false},{"text":"Make phone number field required on all website lead capture forms to improve lead quality (15:40)","completed":false},{"text":"Fix issues with non-functioning Calendly links for demo and consultation forms (12:39)","completed":false},{"text":"Monitor weekly email engagement data and compile list of contacts with three or more clicks per month at month-end for follow-up campaign (27:12)","completed":false},{"text":"Coordinate with Brad to confirm scheduling availability for demo and consultation meetings (19:22)","completed":false},{"text":"Review and provide feedback on Keenan’s drafted email outreach sequence (23:57)","completed":false},{"text":"Communicate with Natalie and Keenan on progress and next steps including podcast promotion and lead nurturing strategy (27:30)","completed":false}]'::jsonb,
  true
FROM new_meeting;

-- Meeting: Ponce Bank // MiD: HubSpot Sync (2026-01-23 15:00:00+00)
WITH new_meeting AS (
  INSERT INTO compass_meetings (contract_id, meeting_date, source, external_id, title, participants, duration_seconds, recording_url, transcript, sentiment, raw_metadata, created_at, updated_at)
  VALUES (
    'b827cc0e-5a1f-420d-8f3d-951078161099',
    '2026-01-23 15:00:00+00',
    'fireflies',
    '01KF48T6K96KV9XZ9W3JNYKF9Q',
    'Ponce Bank // MiD: HubSpot Sync',
    '{"Colin Costigan","Guille Santana","Colin Costigan","victor garcia","Ashlie Taska","christinazanca","gabrielbencosme"}'::text[],
    1821,
    'https://us02web.zoom.us/j/82807622497?pwd=1oWxQKkVvrj4tRTln1UgER5pencHWv.1',
    '{"id":"01KF48T6K96KV9XZ9W3JNYKF9Q","title":"Ponce Bank // MiD: HubSpot Sync","summary":{"notes":"## **Data Migration and Masking Readiness**\n\nThe team confirmed they are ready to begin importing **test contacts** after finalizing the data masking review, aiming to move into testing immediately (08:15).\n\n- **All feedback on data masking was reviewed and deemed sufficient**, allowing the upload of the sample CSV test contacts ahead of the originally planned Wednesday date (09:38).\n    - Ashley and Gabe will monitor the integration once the test contacts are uploaded and notify the team when systems are ready to validate data flow.\n    - Masking of income data will use **ranges formatted as string fields** (e.g., \"0 to 100,000\"), which HubSpot will accept and update dynamically (11:46).\n    - Christina and Colin will align on the specific income range values to be used as options for this field (11:57).\n    - The masking build-out for grouped income ranges will proceed after establishing a stable sync connection (10:43).\n\n- **Colin will upload test contacts into the sandbox by Monday**, initiating Gabe and Ashley’s review and testing phase expected to last **two to three weeks** (22:50).\n    - Gabe confirmed he has cleared pending tasks to fully focus on HubSpot integration during this period (23:51).\n    - Colin does not foresee major issues based on the smooth progress since the recent breakthrough (23:24).\n    - The team will establish both **hard due dates and flexible deadlines** on upcoming tasks to better manage timing and resource allocation (24:43).\n    - Christina emphasized the need for clear deadlines to support content review and resource planning in later phases (24:40).\n\n## **HubSpot and Salesforce Campaign Tracking Strategy**\n\nThe team discussed aligning campaign tracking fields between **HubSpot and Salesforce** to ensure consistent reporting and sales insights (12:43).\n\n- **Victor highlighted the need for a customizable campaign field similar to Salesforce’s \"web source\"**, which tracks specific campaigns like “24 month CD campaign” or branch events for marketing attribution (14:47).\n    - Colin explained HubSpot already captures detailed campaign data, including channel buckets and ad copy, but they need clarity on what Salesforce sales reps require to see (13:25).\n    - Victor will share existing Salesforce campaign documentation and report filters with Colin to clarify mapping needs (13:31).\n    - The team agreed to start with manual campaign setups in Salesforce as a phase one approach, with automation and enhanced tracking planned for phase two (16:11).\n    - There is recognition that contacts may belong to multiple campaigns, and the team needs to define how to prioritize or represent those in reporting (16:57).\n\n- **Ashley and Christina noted sales reps benefit from visibility into ongoing marketing campaigns and attribution options**, including a dropdown for “how did you hear about us?” to capture indirect touchpoints (17:56).\n    - This attribution dropdown does not currently exist but is targeted for phase two development (18:07).\n    - Victor will investigate if Salesforce currently supports this dropdown and report back (18:25).\n    - Colin suggested using a contact notes field temporarily to capture campaign participation as free text if needed (18:33).\n\n## **Process Improvements and Collaboration Tools**\n\nThe team addressed document sharing and collaboration to improve workflow efficiency and access (06:54).\n\n- **Victor will set up a dedicated folder in SharePoint for storing and sharing project files**, enabling Ashley and others to easily drop and access documents (07:17).\n    - The team acknowledged SharePoint’s temperamental behavior with external sharing and agreed to troubleshoot access issues offline (21:14).\n    - Christina recommended sharing with a group email or verified user list to reduce access friction (21:15).\n    - Colin and the team will monitor and ensure smooth file sharing to maintain momentum (21:22).\n\n- The team agreed to ensure **all relevant members, including Betty and Lewis, have access to the project plan** for reference and continuity (28:42).\n    - This will help when team members are unavailable or questions arise during implementation (28:54).\n\n## **Technical Infrastructure and IT Security Coordination**\n\nPreparations for upcoming technical work and IT involvement were discussed to support the integration and data migration (26:02).\n\n- **Colin explained HubSpot’s simplified DNS setup for email migration**, including automated CNAME, TXT, and SPF record updates that complete within 24 hours (26:38).\n    - This reduces complexity and accelerates email migration compared to previous platforms.\n  \n- Christina requested adding a task to discuss **IT security team access to third-party marketing systems**, prompted by recent conversations about Facebook system access (26:56).\n    - Granting IT security visibility would allow them to audit and scrub data for risks such as dark web exposure (27:10).\n    - The team will explore licensing implications and coordinate with Liz to enable this access if needed (27:46).\n\n## **Project Planning and Timeline Management**\n\nThe team emphasized the importance of structured planning to balance deadlines and flexibility across phases (24:25).\n\n- **They will implement dual due date tracking with hard deadlines and flexible target dates** to manage workload and identify impacts on subsequent phases (24:29).\n    - Christina stressed that the project plan needs visibility for leadership to support teams requiring extra time, especially during content review (25:03).\n    - Colin agreed to add a deadline column and keep some deadlines hidden internally to avoid undue pressure on teams (25:27).\n    - The team agreed to start scheduling the next round of working sessions aligned with project milestones and phase transitions (25:47).\n\n- The group acknowledged the project’s scale and complexity, expressing confidence in current progress and collaboration despite learning curves (27:58).\n    - Colin encouraged continuous review and open communication about any blockers or questions (28:17).\n\n## **Team Readiness and Upcoming Workload**\n\nThe team recognized bandwidth needs and prepared for the next phase of activity with clear expectations on time commitment (23:39).\n\n- Ashley and Gabe confirmed readiness to focus on building out the HubSpot integration over the next few weeks (23:45).\n- Colin will provide updates on progress and notify when integration testing can begin, maintaining transparency on timelines (23:11).\n- The team agreed to begin content review and bring back working groups after successful data integration tests, aligning workload with available resources (22:50).","outline":null,"keywords":["HubSpot Integration","Campaign Tracking","Data Masking","SharePoint Access","Salesforce Reporting","Test Contacts Upload"],"overview":"- **Data Migration Ready:** Team can start importing test contacts now; masking review complete ahead of schedule.  \n- **Test Contact Upload:** Colin to upload test contacts by Monday; testing phase lasts two to three weeks.  \n- **Campaign Tracking Alignment:** Need for customizable campaign fields discussed for better sales insights between HubSpot and Salesforce.  \n- **Document Sharing Improvements:** Victor to set up a SharePoint folder for easier document access; troubleshooting external sharing issues agreed.  \n- **IT Security Coordination:** Discuss adding IT security access to third-party marketing systems to audit data risks if necessary.  \n- **Dual Due Date Tracking:** Implementing hard and flexible deadlines to balance workload and project visibility for leadership support.","action_items":"\n**Colin Costigan**\nFollow up again with Google regarding Ads account status after five business days (05:40)\nUpload test contacts (sample CSV) into sandbox environment before Monday meeting (20:37)\nPopulate project plan columns with hard due dates and flexible deadlines (24:40)\nCoordinate with Gabe and Ashley for readiness notification to set up test integration (23:11)\nAdd task to project plan regarding IT security team access discussion for third-party marketing platforms (27:09)\n\n**Victor Garcia**\nCreate folder in SharePoint for document sharing and grant team access; notify once done (07:17)\nProvide documentation and Salesforce report screenshots to Colin for mapping campaign tracking fields (13:31)\nConfirm SharePoint email sharing and troubleshoot access issues with team; consider using group email (21:09)\nVerify access for Betty and Lewis to the project plan and ensure they are included (28:42)\nReport back on Salesforce report filters relevant to marketing attribution field (18:25)\n\n**Ashlie Taska**\nCollaborate with Victor and Gabe on finalizing test contact upload and integration testing (20:37)\nReflect and clarify campaign attribution needs from sales team perspective for future phases (15:52)\n\n**Gabriel Bencosme**\nContinue reviewing HubSpot platform and test contacts integration over next two weeks, escalating issues if any arise (14:17)\nConfirm access and familiarity with the project plan document (28:37)\n\n**Christina Zanca**\nProvide alignment on income range definitions and relevant field naming for masking in HubSpot (11:57)\nConsider naming conventions and campaign source field for Salesforce and marketing mapping (20:20)\nSupport discussion with Ashlie and Victor on sales team usage of campaign fields and attribution tracking (17:14)\n\n**Guille Santana**\nMonitor SharePoint folder creation and access by Victor; ensure team coordination (07:21)\nEnsure project plan access to Betty and Lewis and coordinate team reference (28:42)\nFollow up on access and email sharing issues with SharePoint (21:09)\n"},"duration":30.350000381469727,"speakers":[{"id":0,"name":"Colin Costigan"},{"id":1,"name":"Guille Santana"},{"id":2,"name":"Colin Costigan"},{"id":3,"name":"victor garcia"},{"id":4,"name":"Ashlie Taska"},{"id":5,"name":"christinazanca"},{"id":6,"name":"gabrielbencosme"}],"sentences":[{"text":"Morning.","index":0,"end_time":223.52,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":223.28,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Morning, Colleen.","index":1,"end_time":225.52,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":224.48,"speaker_name":"Guille Santana"},{"text":"Feeling okay?","index":2,"end_time":227.52,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":226.64,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, yeah.","index":3,"end_time":230,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":228.56,"speaker_name":"Guille Santana"},{"text":"I just have.","index":4,"end_time":231.55,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":230.83,"speaker_name":"Guille Santana"},{"text":"I don''t know if you know the band bts.","index":5,"end_time":234.83,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":232.75,"speaker_name":"Guille Santana"},{"text":"It''s a K pop band.","index":6,"end_time":236.19,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":234.91,"speaker_name":"Guille Santana"},{"text":"I do not.","index":7,"end_time":238.19,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":237.39,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"No.","index":8,"end_time":239.15,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":238.75,"speaker_name":"Guille Santana"},{"text":"Well, I have a.","index":9,"end_time":240.19,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":239.23,"speaker_name":"Guille Santana"},{"text":"An army of girls in my.","index":10,"end_time":243.07,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":241.07,"speaker_name":"Guille Santana"},{"text":"In my living room because they.","index":11,"end_time":246.27,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":244.43,"speaker_name":"Guille Santana"},{"text":"They need tickets and I was the only one with wi fi, so it''s chaos over there.","index":12,"end_time":254.95,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":246.91,"speaker_name":"Guille Santana"},{"text":"I''m like, yeah, sounds crazy.","index":13,"end_time":258.12,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":254.95,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":14,"end_time":259,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":258.44,"speaker_name":"Guille Santana"},{"text":"How are you doing?","index":15,"end_time":266.04,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":265.24,"speaker_name":"Guille Santana"},{"text":"Doing well.","index":16,"end_time":267.64,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":267,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"It''s Friday.","index":17,"end_time":268.2,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":267.64,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Finally.","index":18,"end_time":270.68,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":269.96,"speaker_name":"Guille Santana"},{"text":"Yes.","index":19,"end_time":271.56,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":271.08,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Good morning, guys.","index":20,"end_time":275.08,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":274.04,"speaker_name":"victor garcia"},{"text":"Morning, Victor.","index":21,"end_time":276.36,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":275.48,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"How are you doing?","index":22,"end_time":279.32,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":277.48,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"All right.","index":23,"end_time":279.88,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":279.32,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Are you all.","index":24,"end_time":280.84,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":280.04,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"All prepped for whatever may happen this weekend?","index":25,"end_time":285.17,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":281.97,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"The mass.","index":26,"end_time":286.77,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":286.13,"speaker_name":"victor garcia"},{"text":"The massive mayhem that they''re.","index":27,"end_time":289.01,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":286.85,"speaker_name":"victor garcia"},{"text":"They''re making it out to be the 96.","index":28,"end_time":291.81,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":289.01,"speaker_name":"victor garcia"},{"text":"Could be like 4 inches.","index":29,"end_time":293.25,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":292.05,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Could be 2ft.","index":30,"end_time":294.45,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":293.25,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"They don''t know.","index":31,"end_time":295.17,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":294.45,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":32,"end_time":296.29,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":295.81,"speaker_name":"victor garcia"},{"text":"Hello.","index":33,"end_time":297.01,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":296.53,"speaker_name":"Ashlie Taska"},{"text":"Hey, Christina.","index":34,"end_time":298.61,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":297.65,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"If I''m able to do a backflip off the top of my building and.","index":35,"end_time":302.61,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":299.25,"speaker_name":"victor garcia"},{"text":"And be okay with landing on snow, I would do it.","index":36,"end_time":305.89,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":302.77,"speaker_name":"victor garcia"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":37,"end_time":306.53,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":306.05,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":38,"end_time":309.9,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":309.66,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I was joking with some friends that it''s.","index":39,"end_time":312.14,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":309.9,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"The grocery stores are kind of like Covid.","index":40,"end_time":313.66,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":312.14,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Like everyone''s just clearing out all the supplies.","index":41,"end_time":316.54,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":313.82,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":42,"end_time":317.66,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":317.1,"speaker_name":"victor garcia"},{"text":"They''re making it sound like this is going to be insane.","index":43,"end_time":321.18,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":317.98,"speaker_name":"victor garcia"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":44,"end_time":322.22,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":321.74,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"How are you doing, Christina?","index":45,"end_time":326.7,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":325.5,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I''m good.","index":46,"end_time":329.02,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":328.22,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"How are you doing?","index":47,"end_time":330.38,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":329.02,"speaker_name":"Guille Santana"},{"text":"All right.","index":48,"end_time":330.86,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":330.38,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And we''re all dealing with five days.","index":49,"end_time":334.07,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":331.18,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Of work in a four day week.","index":50,"end_time":335.31,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":334.07,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Oh, you''re on mute.","index":51,"end_time":338.99,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":337.95,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"No, I feel like I have 50 days of work.","index":52,"end_time":342.99,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":340.91,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Yes.","index":53,"end_time":343.59,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":343.15,"speaker_name":"victor garcia"},{"text":"Yeah, five days is generous.","index":54,"end_time":346.03,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":343.59,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Hey, you know, while waiting for everybody to join, did you ever hear back.","index":55,"end_time":350.51,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":346.75,"speaker_name":"Ashlie Taska"},{"text":"From Google on the.","index":56,"end_time":351.63,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":350.51,"speaker_name":"Guille Santana"},{"text":"No, I actually, I''m following up again today because it''s been the.","index":57,"end_time":355.55,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":352.67,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"The five business days.","index":58,"end_time":356.67,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":355.55,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay.","index":59,"end_time":357.55,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":356.99,"speaker_name":"Ashlie Taska"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":60,"end_time":358.98,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":358.66,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So reaching back.","index":61,"end_time":359.86,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":358.98,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Back out to Ebenezer.","index":62,"end_time":361.22,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":359.94,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay.","index":63,"end_time":362.02,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":361.46,"speaker_name":"Guille Santana"},{"text":"And is.","index":64,"end_time":363.54,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":362.42,"speaker_name":"Ashlie Taska"},{"text":"Do you think that maybe we''ll have to create a new one?","index":65,"end_time":366.26,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":363.7,"speaker_name":"Ashlie Taska"},{"text":"No, because it says that because of like the information they have to do.","index":66,"end_time":372.82,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":367.78,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"When you set up Google Ads account, they say that if you have an account that''s banned, that they will just.","index":67,"end_time":377.02,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":372.82,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Automatically ban a new one.","index":68,"end_time":378.34,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":377.02,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Great.","index":69,"end_time":378.9,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":378.5,"speaker_name":"Ashlie Taska"},{"text":"So it''s like.","index":70,"end_time":379.94,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":379.14,"speaker_name":"Ashlie Taska"},{"text":"Well, all right.","index":71,"end_time":381.62,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":380.74,"speaker_name":"Guille Santana"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":72,"end_time":382.1,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":381.62,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And they just like, don''t want to look at it as a human.","index":73,"end_time":384.54,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":382.1,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"They want everything to be automated and their AI sucks.","index":74,"end_time":387.58,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":384.54,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"It does this to accounts all the time.","index":75,"end_time":389.9,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":387.58,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"All right, keep posted.","index":76,"end_time":392.78,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":391.1,"speaker_name":"Guille Santana"},{"text":"Will do.","index":77,"end_time":393.82,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":393.18,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Gabe and Ashley, Do we know if Betty and Lewis are planning on joining or.","index":78,"end_time":402.7,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":394.46,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I mean, they should, but we can get started and.","index":79,"end_time":408.02,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":404.94,"speaker_name":"Guille Santana"},{"text":"And you know, if they pop in, you know, we can fill them in sometimes, you know, their schedules skip.","index":80,"end_time":413.1,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":408.02,"speaker_name":"Ashlie Taska"},{"text":"Okay, perfect.","index":81,"end_time":414.73,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":413.1,"speaker_name":"victor garcia"},{"text":"All right.","index":82,"end_time":415.45,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":414.97,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Well, you know, based on our meeting last week.","index":83,"end_time":417.45,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":415.45,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Christine, I know you went through the spreadsheet.","index":84,"end_time":419.17,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":417.53,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I saw some notes pretty soon after the Meeting of like, let''s keep this or let''s not keep this.","index":85,"end_time":423.21,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":419.17,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And then there was an email exchange with Ashley asking if she was comfortable with SharePoint for.","index":86,"end_time":429.45,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":424.09,"speaker_name":"Colin 