d":5,"start_time":663.34,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"That we need to necessarily.","index":184,"end_time":670.1,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":668.78,"speaker_name":"Ashlie Taska"},{"text":"Yeah, we don''t need the exact number we can go by.","index":185,"end_time":673.42,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":671.54,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, yeah.","index":186,"end_time":674.18,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":673.42,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Like the, the range.","index":187,"end_time":674.86,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":674.18,"speaker_name":"Ashlie Taska"},{"text":"Okay, so is that a new.","index":188,"end_time":676.18,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":674.86,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Just figure out what the ranges would be like.","index":189,"end_time":679.18,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":676.5,"speaker_name":"Ashlie Taska"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":190,"end_time":679.5,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":679.18,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And what''s the property?","index":191,"end_time":680.9,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":679.5,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Are you creating a new property, Ashley and Gabe, for that?","index":192,"end_time":683.3,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":680.9,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Well, essentially what I was trying to do is just.","index":193,"end_time":687.13,"speaker_id":6,"start_time":684.89,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"I think it''ll be like a string, most likely.","index":194,"end_time":690.05,"speaker_id":6,"start_time":688.09,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"Because if that''s going to most likely contain dashes in it.","index":195,"end_time":694.93,"speaker_id":6,"start_time":690.05,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"I''m going to say, for example, if something is between 100,000, I''m going to pass that as 0 to 100,000.","index":196,"end_time":702.25,"speaker_id":6,"start_time":694.93,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"So most likely a text field is what we''re trying to generate there.","index":197,"end_time":706.01,"speaker_id":6,"start_time":702.41,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"Okay.","index":198,"end_time":706.45,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":706.01,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"All right, then that''s very easy.","index":199,"end_time":707.97,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":706.45,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Then HubSpot can catch that and update it as it goes.","index":200,"end_time":710.73,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":707.97,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So.","index":201,"end_time":710.89,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":710.73,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, then all we need there, Christina, is just an alignment on what those.","index":202,"end_time":714.37,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":710.89,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Ranges are and will have those as options.","index":203,"end_time":716.63,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":714.37,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I do have.","index":204,"end_time":718.15,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":717.43,"speaker_name":"victor garcia"},{"text":"I do have one question that me and Ashley and Gabe were talking about on the side for different campaigns that we''re obviously going to be running in HubSpot.","index":205,"end_time":728.79,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":718.63,"speaker_name":"victor garcia"},{"text":"We need to have some type of field, kind of like in salesforce, how web source is customizable for each campaign.","index":206,"end_time":735.51,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":728.79,"speaker_name":"victor garcia"},{"text":"Kind of like if we have a 24 month campaign versus a a business checking account campaign, what are we still going to be using web source as that change field to kind of keep it consistent with salesforce and HubSpot or what was the thought process there?","index":207,"end_time":753.94,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":735.59,"speaker_name":"victor garcia"},{"text":"Because the last thing that we would want to do is continuously ask Gabe and Ashley, hey, we need this field created.","index":208,"end_time":760.26,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":753.94,"speaker_name":"victor garcia"},{"text":"Just a customizable field for each.","index":209,"end_time":762.98,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":760.98,"speaker_name":"victor garcia"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":210,"end_time":763.58,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":763.22,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So HubSpot natively captures a lot more drill down than what has been shared with us as far as how salesforce is built right now.","index":211,"end_time":770.1,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":763.58,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So we can have a field that just matches like.","index":212,"end_time":774.31,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":770.5,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Basically we need to understand what does.","index":213,"end_time":775.91,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":774.39,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Salesforce need to see?","index":214,"end_time":777.59,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":775.91,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"What do the sales reps need to see?","index":215,"end_time":779.43,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":777.99,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Is it the first conversion point that someone made when they filled out a form on the website or went to a bank branch, or is it the latest conversion or is it both?","index":216,"end_time":786.79,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":779.43,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So we just need to establish what that is.","index":217,"end_time":788.99,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":787.27,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"HubSpot natively has drill down.","index":218,"end_time":791.39,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":788.99,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So it''ll go by channel bucket saying like it was an email or a form or an ad or whatever.","index":219,"end_time":797.11,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":791.39,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"It was tied to the exact campaign.","index":220,"end_time":798.71,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":797.11,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And then drill down into like the actual copy on the ad, the campaign.","index":221,"end_time":804.01,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":799.03,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"That it was like, all of that.","index":222,"end_time":805.29,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":804.01,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay, so.","index":223,"end_time":806.53,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":805.85,"speaker_name":"victor garcia"},{"text":"So we just need to understand from your side what you.","index":224,"end_time":808.69,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":806.53,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"What the sales reps need to see inside of Salesforce.","index":225,"end_time":810.89,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":808.69,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So what I''m going to do is I have a previous documentation of the last team that created the marketing side of things for Salesforce and I''ll point out some of the things that I was using on a consistent basis to kind of create those reports.","index":226,"end_time":826.17,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":811.29,"speaker_name":"victor garcia"},{"text":"Yeah, and that should kind of clear the air so that you.","index":227,"end_time":829.63,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":826.91,"speaker_name":"victor garcia"},{"text":"Yeah, you can even send me like a screenshot along with that of the.","index":228,"end_time":832.51,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":829.63,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"The filters that you''re putting into the salesforce report.","index":229,"end_time":834.67,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":832.59,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"That''s perfect.","index":230,"end_time":836.27,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":835.55,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Then I can see the exact property that you''re utilizing and we can make.","index":231,"end_time":840.23,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":836.43,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Sure that that''s mapped.","index":232,"end_time":841.15,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":840.23,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I got you.","index":233,"end_time":841.95,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":841.23,"speaker_name":"victor garcia"},{"text":"Awesome.","index":234,"end_time":847.47,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":846.91,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Gabe and Ashley, I know you''ve also still been reading through everything.","index":235,"end_time":850.83,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":848.19,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I know HubSpot''s new platform, so any questions there?","index":236,"end_time":854.91,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":851.07,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Not, Not.","index":237,"end_time":858.36,"speaker_id":6,"start_time":857.96,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"Not as of right now.","index":238,"end_time":859.4,"speaker_id":6,"start_time":858.36,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"You definitely will shoot you an email if I come up with something.","index":239,"end_time":862.68,"speaker_id":6,"start_time":860.44,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"I mean, I still kind of play around with things a little bit, but I''ll dive that over this week and next week.","index":240,"end_time":869.2,"speaker_id":6,"start_time":862.68,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"So as soon as I start encountering any type of issues, I''ll definitely Shoot you an email if anything.","index":241,"end_time":874.04,"speaker_id":6,"start_time":869.2,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"Awesome.","index":242,"end_time":874.72,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":874.2,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And by the way, it sounds like you''re feeling better, so.","index":243,"end_time":876.48,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":874.72,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Glad to hear that.","index":244,"end_time":877.16,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":876.48,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Thanks.","index":245,"end_time":878.04,"speaker_id":6,"start_time":877.56,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"Yeah, sorry guys, I just had to take a call from Carlos.","index":246,"end_time":881.08,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":878.12,"speaker_name":"Ashlie Taska"},{"text":"Back to the.","index":247,"end_time":882.8,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":882.2,"speaker_name":"Ashlie Taska"},{"text":"The question before, just can you confirm what''s web source?","index":248,"end_time":885.16,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":882.8,"speaker_name":"Ashlie Taska"},{"text":"Just so I know is that.","index":249,"end_time":886.44,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":885.16,"speaker_name":"Ashlie Taska"},{"text":"So web source was what we use as a customizable field in order for us to track specifically, you know, like let Jay, for instance, in the New Jersey branch, he threw an event.","index":250,"end_time":899.12,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":887.76,"speaker_name":"victor garcia"},{"text":"We used web source as 2026 customer appreciation or we did 24 month CD campaign.","index":251,"end_time":906.24,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":899.12,"speaker_name":"victor garcia"},{"text":"We were able to take that web source, throw it into a report in Salesforce so that all of that, all of that information was populated.","index":252,"end_time":913.36,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":906.56,"speaker_name":"victor garcia"},{"text":"Okay.","index":253,"end_time":914.55,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":914.07,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"All right.","index":254,"end_time":914.99,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":914.55,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Yeah, let''s call it something different if possible because web in my mind connects.","index":255,"end_time":918.91,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":914.99,"speaker_name":"Ashlie Taska"},{"text":"To website, not necessarily like campaign source.","index":256,"end_time":923.19,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":918.91,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"So.","index":257,"end_time":925.19,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":924.79,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":258,"end_time":925.83,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":925.51,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And so for that, Christina, that''s where we just need whatever like decision needs to be made.","index":259,"end_time":929.59,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":925.83,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So as you know, HubSpot can track on a very granular level and buy different campaign mediums by the campaign names by.","index":260,"end_time":937.43,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":929.67,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"They clicked on this ad.","index":261,"end_time":938.63,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":937.43,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So we just need.","index":262,"end_time":939.83,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":939.11,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"From your side, like, what do the Salesforce reps want to see?","index":263,"end_time":942.55,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":939.83,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I''m sorry, the Salesforce, like the sales team on Salesforce, what do they need to see?","index":264,"end_time":946.23,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":942.87,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Is it the first conversion point that someone made to get into the system or is it the most recent?","index":265,"end_time":950.35,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":946.23,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Or is it both?","index":266,"end_time":951.27,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":950.35,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"All right, let me think about that a little bit because I think.","index":267,"end_time":955.75,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":952.47,"speaker_name":"Ashlie Taska"},{"text":"And maybe.","index":268,"end_time":957.19,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":956.71,"speaker_name":"Ashlie Taska"},{"text":"Ashley, this is a question for you in.","index":269,"end_time":958.87,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":957.19,"speaker_name":"Ashlie Taska"},{"text":"In what word, Gabe?","index":270,"end_time":961.23,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":958.95,"speaker_name":"Ashlie Taska"},{"text":"In Salesforce, there''s the campaign setup section.","index":271,"end_time":965.95,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":961.23,"speaker_name":"Ashlie Taska"},{"text":"Right.","index":272,"end_time":966.19,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":965.95,"speaker_name":"Ashlie Taska"},{"text":"And right now the campaigns aren''t automatically set up.","index":273,"end_time":969.31,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":966.19,"speaker_name":"Ashlie Taska"},{"text":"They''re.","index":274,"end_time":969.55,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":969.31,"speaker_name":"Ashlie Taska"},{"text":"They''re set up by us if we.","index":275,"end_time":971.87,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":969.55,"speaker_name":"Ashlie Taska"},{"text":"Have prospects or anything of that nature.","index":276,"end_time":975.37,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":971.87,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"There''s leads lists that are automated but not official campaigns.","index":277,"end_time":979.77,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":975.45,"speaker_name":"Ashlie Taska"},{"text":"So maybe we could talk a little bit about that process and how we can have them automatically set up.","index":278,"end_time":986.09,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":980.01,"speaker_name":"Ashlie Taska"},{"text":"I was just honestly planning on setting them up manually because I didn''t think about maybe the connection possibilities.","index":279,"end_time":993.61,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":986.89,"speaker_name":"Ashlie Taska"},{"text":"But maybe that''s where we define how we name them.","index":280,"end_time":997.45,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":993.61,"speaker_name":"Ashlie Taska"},{"text":"And if we define various names and breakouts, maybe then that''s where Salesforce can capture them.","index":281,"end_time":1005.06,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":998.09,"speaker_name":"Ashlie Taska"},{"text":"So I mean, we could most likely put that as a phase two.","index":282,"end_time":1009.22,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1006.42,"speaker_name":"Ashlie Taska"},{"text":"We''ll do that, do it manually for now because that might require some more setup on the Salesforce side.","index":283,"end_time":1014.3,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1009.22,"speaker_name":"Ashlie Taska"},{"text":"But if we could just track that as a takeaway.","index":284,"end_time":1016.42,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1014.3,"speaker_name":"Ashlie Taska"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":285,"end_time":1017.78,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1017.46,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And the other thing, just to keep in our back pocket, there is, you know, someone could be in multiple campaigns, right.","index":286,"end_time":1022.42,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1017.78,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Like for the products that they''re signed up for their income range could signify another campaign.","index":287,"end_time":1026.18,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1022.42,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So, you know, how do we want to capture that?","index":288,"end_time":1029.54,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1026.66,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Is it.","index":289,"end_time":1030.1,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1029.54,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"What campaign do we want to track.","index":290,"end_time":1032.38,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1030.9,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"In the latest campaign they''re in, etc.","index":291,"end_time":1034.42,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1032.38,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, and.","index":292,"end_time":1035.34,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1034.74,"speaker_name":"Ashlie Taska"},{"text":"And I don''t necessarily know because right now we.","index":293,"end_time":1037.34,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1035.34,"speaker_name":"Ashlie Taska"},{"text":"We''re still kind of building out the sales culture, you know, process with Maria internally.","index":294,"end_time":1043.22,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1037.34,"speaker_name":"Ashlie Taska"},{"text":"And I mean, I do think it would be helpful for the reps to see what marketing campaigns are.","index":295,"end_time":1050.18,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1043.38,"speaker_name":"Ashlie Taska"},{"text":"Are ongoing and then maybe even be able to, you know, have the materials that.","index":296,"end_time":1054.18,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1050.18,"speaker_name":"Ashlie Taska"},{"text":"That we''re, you know, submitting out for reference if they speak to them.","index":297,"end_time":1058.96,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1054.18,"speaker_name":"Ashlie Taska"},{"text":"But beyond that, there''s also, I know, typically in systems, a drop down for the reps to say, like, you know, how did you hear about us?","index":298,"end_time":1068.44,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1060.16,"speaker_name":"Ashlie Taska"},{"text":"And it''s not necessarily triggered by, like an action taken on the campaign, but it''s more or less like an attribution factor that we can say, you know.","index":299,"end_time":1076.8,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1068.44,"speaker_name":"Ashlie Taska"},{"text":"There wasn''t a direct link, but they.","index":300,"end_time":1078.56,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":1076.88,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Heard about us from social media.","index":301,"end_time":1079.88,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1078.56,"speaker_name":"Ashlie Taska"},{"text":"So then we can get that attribute there.","index":302,"end_time":1081.6,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1079.88,"speaker_name":"Ashlie Taska"},{"text":"I don''t know if you''re tracking that.","index":303,"end_time":1083.08,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1081.76,"speaker_name":"Ashlie Taska"},{"text":"Right now, so maybe that''s another thing.","index":304,"end_time":1084.6,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":1083.08,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"That we can add as a.","index":305,"end_time":1087.09,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1084.6,"speaker_name":"Guille Santana"},{"text":"As a.","index":306,"end_time":1087.41,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1087.09,"speaker_name":"Ashlie Taska"},{"text":"Maybe a phase two takeaway to determine what that dropdown looks like, if it.","index":307,"end_time":1092.69,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":1087.41,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Exists, and if not, how do we build it?","index":308,"end_time":1094.29,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1092.69,"speaker_name":"Ashlie Taska"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":309,"end_time":1095.09,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1094.61,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And Victor, I don''t know if, you know, off the top of your head, but I''m sure you could run a.","index":310,"end_time":1098.13,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1095.25,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Salesforce report and see if that''s a.","index":311,"end_time":1099.41,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1098.13,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Filter in there and if it.","index":312,"end_time":1101.329,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1099.41,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Where it''s populated.","index":313,"end_time":1102.45,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1101.329,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I''ll get back to you on that.","index":314,"end_time":1106.13,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1105.01,"speaker_name":"victor garcia"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":315,"end_time":1106.65,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1106.13,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":316,"end_time":1107.09,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1106.65,"speaker_name":"Guille Santana"},{"text":"Okay.","index":317,"end_time":1107.73,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1107.17,"speaker_name":"Guille Santana"},{"text":"But definitely something that we can build on the HubSpot side and map it anywhere.","index":318,"end_time":1112.41,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1109.33,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":319,"end_time":1112.77,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1112.41,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay.","index":320,"end_time":1113.49,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1113.25,"speaker_name":"Ashlie Taska"},{"text":"I mean, we could even use the contact notes option as an open text field and be like, this is all.","index":321,"end_time":1117.57,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1113.49,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"The campaigns that they''re loaded into.","index":322,"end_time":1119.49,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1117.57,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":323,"end_time":1122.29,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":1121.81,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Sorry, Victor.","index":324,"end_time":1125.41,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1124.53,"speaker_name":"Ashlie Taska"},{"text":"It''s like aligning like the sophistication that we''re looking to get with kind of how not only just the system is.","index":325,"end_time":1132.45,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":1125.97,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Set up, but our team, but how sales needs this.","index":326,"end_time":1134.21,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1132.45,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, yeah, yeah.","index":327,"end_time":1135.41,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":1134.21,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Like how our teams are trained or, you know, used to using the system.","index":328,"end_time":1139.45,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":1135.41,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"So that''s why I''m thinking it might need a little bit more discussion before we build that out.","index":329,"end_time":1143.96,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":1139.45,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"So Ashley gave it.","index":330,"end_time":1145.4,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":1144.04,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"You know, this is kind of the category that there may be like some ancillary programming or things that need to happen, like after we officially launch, what''s priority.","index":331,"end_time":1154.12,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":1145.4,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"But just that was one of the things that Wanda had pointed out when we were initially going through that process where we uploaded I think six different lists.","index":332,"end_time":1166.89,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1154.44,"speaker_name":"victor garcia"},{"text":"They were categorized by how much money each company makes, ranging from 250k, 577 50, a million, etc.","index":333,"end_time":1175.73,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1167.13,"speaker_name":"victor garcia"},{"text":"Etc.","index":334,"end_time":1176.09,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1175.73,"speaker_name":"victor garcia"},{"text":"That little piece of information was important for her to know so that she knows how to approach it differently.","index":335,"end_time":1182.569,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1176.97,"speaker_name":"victor garcia"},{"text":"But there was no way for us to put that into a description.","index":336,"end_time":1186.09,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1182.65,"speaker_name":"victor garcia"},{"text":"So the only way that I was able to do that is categorizing it by a report, but had that little thing of description.","index":337,"end_time":1193.65,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1186.25,"speaker_name":"victor garcia"},{"text":"Then there it''ll just, you know, it''s, it''s just a pop up at that point.","index":338,"end_time":1197.49,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1193.81,"speaker_name":"victor garcia"},{"text":"So customizable off of that menu system would be nice.","index":339,"end_time":1201.49,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1197.89,"speaker_name":"victor garcia"},{"text":"All right, so throw that.","index":340,"end_time":1202.77,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1201.73,"speaker_name":"Guille Santana"},{"text":"Or throw these tasks Victor in Asana as a subtest for us to talk about.","index":341,"end_time":1209.33,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":1203.81,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"And Ashley gave me.","index":342,"end_time":1210.69,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":1209.33,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"I''ll just set a quick chat so we get sidebar.","index":343,"end_time":1213.49,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":1210.69,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":344,"end_time":1214.73,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1214.37,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Then whatever, whatever outcome of that, like we''ll, we''ll just need to know the field name and the field type and.","index":345,"end_time":1219.05,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1214.73,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Where you want it to spit out.","index":346,"end_time":1220.21,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1219.05,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, I mean at the very least I could probably just give you the field name.","index":347,"end_time":1223.19,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":1220.55,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"You know, it''ll probably just be something generic like campaign or source, you know, marketing referral source or something like that.","index":348,"end_time":1230.31,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":1223.75,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"But.","index":349,"end_time":1231.67,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1231.35,"speaker_name":"victor garcia"},{"text":"But yeah, I''ll confirm.","index":350,"end_time":1232.87,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":1231.67,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Cool.","index":351,"end_time":1233.51,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1233.03,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay, cool.","index":352,"end_time":1234.63,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1233.75,"speaker_name":"Guille Santana"},{"text":"All right, what''s next in the.","index":353,"end_time":1236.95,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1235.03,"speaker_name":"Guille Santana"},{"text":"So now we''re, we''re.","index":354,"end_time":1238.67,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1237.59,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Sounds like we''re clear to upload the test contacts and then we''ll notify Gabe and Ashley as soon as that''s done.","index":355,"end_time":1243.83,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1238.67,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And then, and then get the test integration in place to make sure that.","index":356,"end_time":1248.53,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1244.55,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"They''Re updating across the systems correctly before we leave.","index":357,"end_time":1251.29,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1248.53,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":358,"end_time":1251.69,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1251.29,"speaker_name":"victor garcia"},{"text":"Can you confirm that you actually are able to access that.","index":359,"end_time":1254.25,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1251.69,"speaker_name":"victor garcia"},{"text":"That email that I sent you.","index":360,"end_time":1256.01,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1254.73,"speaker_name":"victor garcia"},{"text":"Is.","index":361,"end_time":1259.17,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1258.89,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"That the one on this call?","index":362,"end_time":1260.09,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1259.17,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, I sent it.","index":363,"end_time":1261.85,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1260.81,"speaker_name":"victor garcia"},{"text":"I sent it to you and it''s in SharePoint.","index":364,"end_time":1266.05,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1261.85,"speaker_name":"victor garcia"},{"text":"That''s the only reason why I want to confirm.","index":365,"end_time":1267.41,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1266.05,"speaker_name":"victor garcia"},{"text":"Because it''s SharePoint.","index":366,"end_time":1269.37,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1267.41,"speaker_name":"victor garcia"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":367,"end_time":1269.97,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1269.61,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And SharePoint likes to get.","index":368,"end_time":1271.53,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1269.97,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"It''s not letting me in.","index":369,"end_time":1273.53,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1271.93,"speaker_name":"Guille Santana"},{"text":"No.","index":370,"end_time":1275.15,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1274.91,"speaker_name":"Ashlie Taska"},{"text":"Victor, when you share SharePoint externally, you have to go in the settings and add the individual user email address.","index":371,"end_time":1281.31,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":1275.87,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"So maybe.","index":372,"end_time":1282.31,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":1281.47,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Yeah, I did.","index":373,"end_time":1283.31,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1282.31,"speaker_name":"victor garcia"},{"text":"That''s why I, I wanted to make.","index":374,"end_time":1284.87,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1283.31,"speaker_name":"victor garcia"},{"text":"Sure it works half the time.","index":375,"end_time":1287.95,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1284.87,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"It''s so strange.","index":376,"end_time":1289.39,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1288.27,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Is it better if we just use.","index":377,"end_time":1291.63,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1290.11,"speaker_name":"Guille Santana"},{"text":"The reduction email and then everybody will get it?","index":378,"end_time":1294.75,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":1291.63,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Colin?","index":379,"end_time":1296.99,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1296.35,"speaker_name":"Guille Santana"},{"text":"Yeah, we could do that.","index":380,"end_time":1298.35,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1297.39,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"All right.","index":381,"end_time":1299.47,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":1298.91,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"If you throw that email in the chat and then Victor pick it up and chat, maybe it''ll work.","index":382,"end_time":1307.05,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":1300.25,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"And then if that doesn''t work, we''ll just, we''ll just ask, you know, if there''s a more secure.","index":383,"end_time":1317.53,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":1312.09,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Another secure Way to.","index":384,"end_time":1319.13,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":1317.77,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"To share.","index":385,"end_time":1320.09,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":1319.45,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Although it should because we''ve already been sharing.","index":386,"end_time":1325.69,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":1322.57,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Yeah, that''s why it''s weird, because it''s.","index":387,"end_time":1328.06,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1325.93,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"It''s temperamental.","index":388,"end_time":1329.41,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1328.53,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"It''s like.","index":389,"end_time":1329.97,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1329.41,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I think, Victor, you even said at the beginning of this call that it was temperamental for you this morning.","index":390,"end_time":1333.89,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1330.21,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I don''t know.","index":391,"end_time":1335.93,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":1335.41,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"All right, well, we''ll figure that offline.","index":392,"end_time":1338.61,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":1335.93,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"So just for kind of Ashley and Gabe''s purposes within the timeline, what are the remaining tasks and then how much more time are we going to require of their team?","index":393,"end_time":1352.93,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":1338.61,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Because I think at this point, we''re almost into, like, the next phase where we start to bring back in the working team, you know, content review and things like that.","index":394,"end_time":1362.45,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":1354.21,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"So I just want to start to plan ahead and also just, you know, give them heads up for bandwidth on their own.","index":395,"end_time":1368.97,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":1362.61,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Their own team.","index":396,"end_time":1369.65,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":1368.97,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":397,"end_time":1370.53,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1370.13,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So before our meeting Monday, I''m going to upload those test contacts into the sandbox system, and then it''s basically on Gabe and Ashley''s timeline.","index":398,"end_time":1378.61,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1370.53,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I know, Gabe, you said, like, between.","index":399,"end_time":1380.21,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1378.61,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Next week and the week after, you''re.","index":400,"end_time":1381.53,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1380.21,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Reviewing and going through everything and going to let me know if you have any questions.","index":401,"end_time":1385.21,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1381.53,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"But then I would just be letting.","index":402,"end_time":1386.57,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1385.21,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"You guys know, like, hey, we''re good.","index":403,"end_time":1387.61,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1386.57,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"To set up this test integration.","index":404,"end_time":1388.97,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1387.61,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay.","index":405,"end_time":1392.17,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1391.53,"speaker_name":"Guille Santana"},{"text":"Okay.","index":406,"end_time":1392.97,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1392.33,"speaker_name":"Guille Santana"},{"text":"So do you expect, like, this component to be all complete?","index":407,"end_time":1396.25,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":1392.97,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Sorry, the project plan is not up again, but what, three weeks?","index":408,"end_time":1400.17,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":1396.33,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Yeah, with, I think, well within.","index":409,"end_time":1402.25,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1400.73,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Inside of three weeks.","index":410,"end_time":1403.53,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1402.57,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay.","index":411,"end_time":1404.57,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1403.93,"speaker_name":"Guille Santana"},{"text":"I don''t forecast Gabe running into.","index":412,"end_time":1406.45,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1404.89,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Gabe and Ashley running into any issues.","index":413,"end_time":1407.93,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1406.45,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"But.","index":414,"end_time":1410.28,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1410.16,"speaker_name":"victor garcia"},{"text":"And if they do, I mean, we''ll.","index":415,"end_time":1411.44,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1410.28,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We''ll address anything really quickly.","index":416,"end_time":1413.04,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1411.44,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I don''t know.","index":417,"end_time":1414.84,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1414.4,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I think it''s been smooth since.","index":418,"end_time":1416,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1414.84,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Since we had like, the breakthrough two weeks ago.","index":419,"end_time":1417.84,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1416,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay.","index":420,"end_time":1419.04,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1418.4,"speaker_name":"Guille Santana"},{"text":"All right.","index":421,"end_time":1419.68,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":1419.2,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Ashley and Gabe, does that work for.","index":422,"end_time":1421.24,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":1419.76,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"For you guys?","index":423,"end_time":1422,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":1421.24,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Are you guys comfortable with that?","index":424,"end_time":1423.84,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":1422,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"I''ll defer to Gabe.","index":425,"end_time":1426.72,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1425.6,"speaker_name":"Ashlie Taska"},{"text":"He''s the one that''s building this out.","index":426,"end_time":1428.32,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1426.72,"speaker_name":"Ashlie Taska"},{"text":"I did some cleanup on other things that we had pending as of yesterday, between yesterday and day before.","index":427,"end_time":1438.48,"speaker_id":6,"start_time":1431.68,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"So I should have a clean slate to just focus on hotspot for the most time.","index":428,"end_time":1443.61,"speaker_id":6,"start_time":1438.56,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"Okay, awesome.","index":429,"end_time":1444.93,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1444.01,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"A couple of weeks, so, yeah, I''m hoping to have enough time to build this out.","index":430,"end_time":1450.65,"speaker_id":6,"start_time":1444.93,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"Okay.","index":431,"end_time":1451.53,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1450.97,"speaker_name":"Guille Santana"},{"text":"And Colin, and just looking at the.","index":432,"end_time":1452.97,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1451.53,"speaker_name":"Guille Santana"},{"text":"Project plan, I mean, you know, we''re saying that we think it should, you know, take that long, but I mean, we have some cushion leeway.","index":433,"end_time":1459.37,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":1452.97,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"We do, you know.","index":434,"end_time":1460.29,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1459.37,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay.","index":435,"end_time":1460.73,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1460.29,"speaker_name":"Ashlie Taska"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":436,"end_time":1461.13,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1460.73,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So what we could start to do.","index":437,"end_time":1465.57,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1462.41,"speaker_name":"Guille Santana"},{"text":"Is set, like, do, like, hard.","index":438,"end_time":1469.71,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":1465.57,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Hard due dates, but then also in.","index":439,"end_time":1471.83,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1469.87,"speaker_name":"Guille Santana"},{"text":"The background, understand where we have the flexibility to push the Due date.","index":440,"end_time":1475.43,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":1471.83,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"This way we''ll be able to see like impact to next phase or next step.","index":441,"end_time":1479.71,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":1475.43,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":442,"end_time":1480.63,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1480.27,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So maybe like a due date and a deadline column.","index":443,"end_time":1482.75,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1480.63,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, yeah.","index":444,"end_time":1484.35,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":1483.31,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Like a hard deadline I think is something that we need to be mindful of.","index":445,"end_time":1488.03,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":1484.35,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"So for example, you know, I don''t want to, I don''t want to not give a team additional time if they, if they have a project that comes up because I''m, I''m looking at something that has flexibility where I don''t have a line as to where the flex is.","index":446,"end_time":1502.15,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":1488.11,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Totally.","index":447,"end_time":1502.95,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1502.39,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So if, if you guys could do that for the next, you know, few tasks, I think that''ll be super helpful because we''re probably going to need to build an extra time, especially when you get to the, the content review stage.","index":448,"end_time":1516.63,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":1503.67,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":449,"end_time":1517.35,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1516.79,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And you know, we don''t necessarily always have to share that hard deadline out.","index":450,"end_time":1523.15,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":1518.63,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"You can hide it, Colin, because I don''t want teams to get.","index":451,"end_time":1526.39,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":1523.15,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Yeah, like, oh, I have until that.","index":452,"end_time":1528.29,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1527.09,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, I got you.","index":453,"end_time":1529.05,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1528.29,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, yeah.","index":454,"end_time":1529.73,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":1529.05,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"But like from my, for my awareness, like that''s where I could, you know, bake in the flexibility and you know, support the teams that need more time.","index":455,"end_time":1538.21,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":1529.73,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Yep, totally.","index":456,"end_time":1539.21,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1538.45,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Area.","index":457,"end_time":1539.49,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1539.21,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, we''ll, we''ll populate that column.","index":458,"end_time":1541.73,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1539.49,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay.","index":459,"end_time":1542.37,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1541.81,"speaker_name":"Guille Santana"},{"text":"And then I guess Colin, we can.","index":460,"end_time":1547.01,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1545.49,"speaker_name":"Guille Santana"},{"text":"Talk on our meeting about the, the next phase and when we need to start having the next round of working session meetings.","index":461,"end_time":1555.18,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":1547.01,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"And also I don''t, I don''t think, I think it would be more the.","index":462,"end_time":1562.7,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":1556.38,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"IT team that would need to.","index":463,"end_time":1564.18,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1562.7,"speaker_name":"Guille Santana"},{"text":"Once we have the emails in the system and we''re ready, we probably would are going to need to move forward with the email migration like the DNS servers and all that.","index":464,"end_time":1575.82,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":1564.18,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"So then I want to start to get that team on board and also just make sure that we have a clear differentiation between that is still like kind of.","index":465,"end_time":1587.33,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":1575.82,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"I, I would consider like a data component but make sure that we break it out between data IT and data, you know, gps.","index":466,"end_time":1596.17,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":1587.33,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"So yeah, the wrong team members.","index":467,"end_time":1598.25,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":1596.17,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Yeah, yeah, totally hear you.","index":468,"end_time":1600.05,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1598.73,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And hubs up makes it much easier than they have previously.","index":469,"end_time":1602.89,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1600.05,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So now we can even hit like.","index":470,"end_time":1604.05,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1602.89,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Copy instructions for developer and it''ll give.","index":471,"end_time":1606.37,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1604.05,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Them like the CNAME record.","index":472,"end_time":1607.85,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1606.37,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"They need to update the TXT record, the SPF record and.","index":473,"end_time":1610.4,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1607.85,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And everything updates within 24 hours in HubSpot.","index":474,"end_time":1613.91,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1610.47,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay.","index":475,"end_time":1615.19,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1614.55,"speaker_name":"Guille Santana"},{"text":"And one development.","index":476,"end_time":1616.47,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1615.67,"speaker_name":"Guille Santana"},{"text":"This is not necessarily related here, but I just don''t want to forget.","index":477,"end_time":1619.15,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":1616.63,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Colin, please add a task to discuss access for our IT security teams.","index":478,"end_time":1627.67,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":1619.15,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Something came up yesterday when I was.","index":479,"end_time":1630.67,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1629.03,"speaker_name":"Guille Santana"},{"text":"Talking to Liz about the Facebook component and apparently I think they''ve had historical.","index":480,"end_time":1638.23,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":1630.67,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Access to any third party marketing system.","index":481,"end_time":1640.83,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1638.23,"speaker_name":"Guille Santana"},{"text":"That wasn''t owned by them as a tech.","index":482,"end_time":1644.39,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":1640.83,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"And so I think that might be helpful for them to have access.","index":483,"end_time":1649.83,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":1644.95,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"So if at any point they need to have their third party, like it security team scrub anything or review anything for any, like, dark web stuff, we can.","index":484,"end_time":1660.47,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":1650.07,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"We can make sure that happens.","index":485,"end_time":1661.83,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":1660.55,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"And I think that that would be helpful for Liz to have that conversation.","index":486,"end_time":1665.75,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":1661.83,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"So.","index":487,"end_time":1666.15,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":1665.75,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Okay.","index":488,"end_time":1666.85,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1666.45,"speaker_name":"Guille Santana"},{"text":"They might not do anything, you know, so we''ll figure out licensing, but.","index":489,"end_time":1671.09,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":1667.09,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Gotcha.","index":490,"end_time":1672.05,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1671.33,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay.","index":491,"end_time":1673.65,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1673.01,"speaker_name":"Guille Santana"},{"text":"Anybody have anything else to add?","index":492,"end_time":1676.13,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1674.45,"speaker_name":"Guille Santana"},{"text":"I think we''re in a, you know, really good space and I.","index":493,"end_time":1678.37,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1676.13,"speaker_name":"Guille Santana"},{"text":"And I really appreciate, you know, you guys working through some of just the learning curves, you know, that.","index":494,"end_time":1683.97,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":1678.37,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"That we had and then just the.","index":495,"end_time":1685.17,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1683.97,"speaker_name":"Guille Santana"},{"text":"Project plan set up and all of that.","index":496,"end_time":1686.65,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":1685.17,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"You know, it''s a big project, so.","index":497,"end_time":1687.97,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":1686.65,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Yeah, Feeling good.","index":498,"end_time":1690.29,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1689.17,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yep.","index":499,"end_time":1691.01,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1690.53,"speaker_name":"Guille Santana"},{"text":"We''ll continue to review on our site and reach out for, you know, if you come across anything.","index":500,"end_time":1697.17,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1691.01,"speaker_name":"Guille Santana"},{"text":"Please do.","index":501,"end_time":1698.29,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1697.65,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":502,"end_time":1699.09,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1698.61,"speaker_name":"Guille Santana"},{"text":"Awesome.","index":503,"end_time":1699.73,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1699.17,"speaker_name":"Guille Santana"},{"text":"Louis, Anything that you have questions on or.","index":504,"end_time":1703.09,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1700.61,"speaker_name":"Guille Santana"},{"text":"Sorry, I know you just listen in.","index":505,"end_time":1705.41,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":1704.29,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"The background, but I don''t know, just listen in.","index":506,"end_time":1708.05,"speaker_id":6,"start_time":1705.41,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"Trying to make sure I''m tracking.","index":507,"end_time":1709.17,"speaker_id":6,"start_time":1708.05,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"Okay, cool.","index":508,"end_time":1711.21,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1710.29,"speaker_name":"Guille Santana"},{"text":"And do you have access to this project plan?","index":509,"end_time":1714.05,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1711.21,"speaker_name":"Guille Santana"},{"text":"I have to look back.","index":510,"end_time":1718.69,"speaker_id":6,"start_time":1717.49,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"I don''t think I have that one favorited on my.","index":511,"end_time":1720.61,"speaker_id":6,"start_time":1718.69,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"All right, yeah.","index":512,"end_time":1722.7,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":1721.54,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Can we make sure that Lewis and Betty.","index":513,"end_time":1725.38,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1722.7,"speaker_name":"Guille Santana"},{"text":"I mean, I''m sure Betty has it, but if not, just make sure that we get access just in case, you know, you''re ever in discussions with anyone on your team and a question comes.","index":514,"end_time":1734.22,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1725.46,"speaker_name":"Guille Santana"},{"text":"Up, you know, you can refer back to it if needed.","index":515,"end_time":1738.02,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":1734.22,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"That''s.","index":516,"end_time":1738.98,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1738.42,"speaker_name":"Guille Santana"},{"text":"That''d be helpful.","index":517,"end_time":1740.1,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1739.14,"speaker_name":"Guille Santana"},{"text":"No problem.","index":518,"end_time":1740.82,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1740.26,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"All right, well, are we giving.","index":519,"end_time":1742.9,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1741.38,"speaker_name":"Guille Santana"},{"text":"Are we giving four minutes back or are we.","index":520,"end_time":1745.06,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1743.14,"speaker_name":"Guille Santana"},{"text":"I think so.","index":521,"end_time":1745.82,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1745.22,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I think we''ve hit a record.","index":522,"end_time":1746.74,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1745.82,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Christina.","index":523,"end_time":1747.38,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1746.74,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":524,"end_time":1748.34,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1747.86,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Guys, please stay safe this weekend.","index":525,"end_time":1750.51,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1748.75,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I have no idea what''s going to happen.","index":526,"end_time":1752.03,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1750.51,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I still am 50, 50 in my mind that nothing''s going to happen.","index":527,"end_time":1754.91,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1752.35,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So.","index":528,"end_time":1755.27,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1754.99,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We will see.","index":529,"end_time":1755.95,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1755.27,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, it''s.","index":530,"end_time":1757.15,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":1756.67,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"All right.","index":531,"end_time":1757.39,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":1757.15,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Well, we''ll have just a dusting.","index":532,"end_time":1758.99,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":1757.39,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Yeah, I''m sure they''re going to cancel.","index":533,"end_time":1761.99,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1759.31,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"School everywhere for like a week.","index":534,"end_time":1763.15,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1761.99,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So listen, I don''t know, Louis.","index":535,"end_time":1765.79,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1763.15,"speaker_name":"Guille Santana"},{"text":"You got.","index":536,"end_time":1766.27,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":1765.79,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"You got to push for, you know, two hour, you know, free time for those of us that have kids that.","index":537,"end_time":1772.87,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":1766.27,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Are going to want to go out.","index":538,"end_time":1773.75,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1772.87,"speaker_name":"Ashlie Taska"},{"text":"In the snow, take the day off.","index":539,"end_time":1775.55,"speaker_id":6,"start_time":1773.75,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"What do you mean two hours?","index":540,"end_time":1776.63,"speaker_id":6,"start_time":1775.55,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"Take the day.","index":541,"end_time":1777.35,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1776.63,"speaker_name":"victor garcia"},{"text":"Listen, we need real snow days back.","index":542,"end_time":1780.07,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1777.43,"speaker_name":"Guille Santana"},{"text":"I know.","index":543,"end_time":1781.03,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":1780.39,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"I''m like.","index":544,"end_time":1781.67,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":1781.19,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"I''m trying to be, like, realistic.","index":545,"end_time":1783.03,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":1781.67,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Two hour delay.","index":546,"end_time":1783.83,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1783.03,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I tell you what, I tell you what.","index":547,"end_time":1785.31,"speaker_id":6,"start_time":1783.83,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"I will grant that if it snows on Sunday, you can all take Sunday off.","index":548,"end_time":1788.63,"speaker_id":6,"start_time":1785.31,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"Gosh.","index":549,"end_time":1791.11,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1790.629,"speaker_name":"Guille Santana"},{"text":"Leave it to Lewis to find the loopholes.","index":550,"end_time":1792.87,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1791.11,"speaker_name":"Guille Santana"},{"text":"All right.","index":551,"end_time":1795.03,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":1794.55,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"All right.","index":552,"end_time":1796.07,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1795.67,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Well, thank you all so much for your time, and have an awesome weekend, all right?","index":553,"end_time":1799.27,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1796.07,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"}],"dateString":"2026-01-23T15:00:00.000Z","host_email":"guille.santana@marketersindemand.com","meeting_link":"https://us02web.zoom.us/j/82807622497?pwd=1oWxQKkVvrj4tRTln1UgER5pencHWv.1","participants":["guille.santana@marketersindemand.com,gabriel.bencosme@poncebank.net,christina.zanca@poncebank.net,colin.costigan@marketersindemand.com,ashlie.taska@poncebank.net,betty.campiz@poncebank.net,victor.garcia@poncebank.net","gabriel.bencosme@poncebank.net","christina.zanca@poncebank.net","colin.costigan@marketersindemand.com","ashlie.taska@poncebank.net","betty.campiz@poncebank.net","victor.garcia@poncebank.net"],"transcript_url":"https://app.fireflies.ai/view/01KF48T6K96KV9XZ9W3JNYKF9Q","organizer_email":"guille.santana@marketersindemand.com"}'::jsonb,
    '{"label":"positive","confidence":0.92,"bullets":["Confirmed masking requirements are complete; test contact upload will proceed before next meeting.","Victor will provide Salesforce report examples to guide integration field mapping consistency.","Team aligned on using income ranges as a text property for future campaign segmentation.","Established rough three-week timeline to complete HubSpot-Salesforce integration buildout.","Agreed to track phase two items like campaign attribution and dropdown development in Asana."],"highlights":[{"quote":"I think we''re in a good spot to move into testing.","speaker":"Colin Costigan"},{"quote":"I think we''re in a, you know, really good space.","speaker":"Guille Santana"},{"quote":"We''re probably going to need to build in extra time, especially when you get to the content review stage.","speaker":"Christinazanca"}],"topics":["delivery","integration","timeline","campaign","testing"],"model":"openai/gpt-4-turbo","version":1,"generated_at":"2026-01-23T00:00:00Z"}'::jsonb,
    '{"fireflies_summary":{"notes":"## **Data Migration and Masking Readiness**\n\nThe team confirmed they are ready to begin importing **test contacts** after finalizing the data masking review, aiming to move into testing immediately (08:15).\n\n- **All feedback on data masking was reviewed and deemed sufficient**, allowing the upload of the sample CSV test contacts ahead of the originally planned Wednesday date (09:38).\n    - Ashley and Gabe will monitor the integration once the test contacts are uploaded and notify the team when systems are ready to validate data flow.\n    - Masking of income data will use **ranges formatted as string fields** (e.g., \"0 to 100,000\"), which HubSpot will accept and update dynamically (11:46).\n    - Christina and Colin will align on the specific income range values to be used as options for this field (11:57).\n    - The masking build-out for grouped income ranges will proceed after establishing a stable sync connection (10:43).\n\n- **Colin will upload test contacts into the sandbox by Monday**, initiating Gabe and Ashley’s review and testing phase expected to last **two to three weeks** (22:50).\n    - Gabe confirmed he has cleared pending tasks to fully focus on HubSpot integration during this period (23:51).\n    - Colin does not foresee major issues based on the smooth progress since the recent breakthrough (23:24).\n    - The team will establish both **hard due dates and flexible deadlines** on upcoming tasks to better manage timing and resource allocation (24:43).\n    - Christina emphasized the need for clear deadlines to support content review and resource planning in later phases (24:40).\n\n## **HubSpot and Salesforce Campaign Tracking Strategy**\n\nThe team discussed aligning campaign tracking fields between **HubSpot and Salesforce** to ensure consistent reporting and sales insights (12:43).\n\n- **Victor highlighted the need for a customizable campaign field similar to Salesforce’s \"web source\"**, which tracks specific campaigns like “24 month CD campaign” or branch events for marketing attribution (14:47).\n    - Colin explained HubSpot already captures detailed campaign data, including channel buckets and ad copy, but they need clarity on what Salesforce sales reps require to see (13:25).\n    - Victor will share existing Salesforce campaign documentation and report filters with Colin to clarify mapping needs (13:31).\n    - The team agreed to start with manual campaign setups in Salesforce as a phase one approach, with automation and enhanced tracking planned for phase two (16:11).\n    - There is recognition that contacts may belong to multiple campaigns, and the team needs to define how to prioritize or represent those in reporting (16:57).\n\n- **Ashley and Christina noted sales reps benefit from visibility into ongoing marketing campaigns and attribution options**, including a dropdown for “how did you hear about us?” to capture indirect touchpoints (17:56).\n    - This attribution dropdown does not currently exist but is targeted for phase two development (18:07).\n    - Victor will investigate if Salesforce currently supports this dropdown and report back (18:25).\n    - Colin suggested using a contact notes field temporarily to capture campaign participation as free text if needed (18:33).\n\n## **Process Improvements and Collaboration Tools**\n\nThe team addressed document sharing and collaboration to improve workflow efficiency and access (06:54).\n\n- **Victor will set up a dedicated folder in SharePoint for storing and sharing project files**, enabling Ashley and others to easily drop and access documents (07:17).\n    - The team acknowledged SharePoint’s temperamental behavior with external sharing and agreed to troubleshoot access issues offline (21:14).\n    - Christina recommended sharing with a group email or verified user list to reduce access friction (21:15).\n    - Colin and the team will monitor and ensure smooth file sharing to maintain momentum (21:22).\n\n- The team agreed to ensure **all relevant members, including Betty and Lewis, have access to the project plan** for reference and continuity (28:42).\n    - This will help when team members are unavailable or questions arise during implementation (28:54).\n\n## **Technical Infrastructure and IT Security Coordination**\n\nPreparations for upcoming technical work and IT involvement were discussed to support the integration and data migration (26:02).\n\n- **Colin explained HubSpot’s simplified DNS setup for email migration**, including automated CNAME, TXT, and SPF record updates that complete within 24 hours (26:38).\n    - This reduces complexity and accelerates email migration compared to previous platforms.\n  \n- Christina requested adding a task to discuss **IT security team access to third-party marketing systems**, prompted by recent conversations about Facebook system access (26:56).\n    - Granting IT security visibility would allow them to audit and scrub data for risks such as dark web exposure (27:10).\n    - The team will explore licensing implications and coordinate with Liz to enable this access if needed (27:46).\n\n## **Project Planning and Timeline Management**\n\nThe team emphasized the importance of structured planning to balance deadlines and flexibility across phases (24:25).\n\n- **They will implement dual due date tracking with hard deadlines and flexible target dates** to manage workload and identify impacts on subsequent phases (24:29).\n    - Christina stressed that the project plan needs visibility for leadership to support teams requiring extra time, especially during content review (25:03).\n    - Colin agreed to add a deadline column and keep some deadlines hidden internally to avoid undue pressure on teams (25:27).\n    - The team agreed to start scheduling the next round of working sessions aligned with project milestones and phase transitions (25:47).\n\n- The group acknowledged the project’s scale and complexity, expressing confidence in current progress and collaboration despite learning curves (27:58).\n    - Colin encouraged continuous review and open communication about any blockers or questions (28:17).\n\n## **Team Readiness and Upcoming Workload**\n\nThe team recognized bandwidth needs and prepared for the next phase of activity with clear expectations on time commitment (23:39).\n\n- Ashley and Gabe confirmed readiness to focus on building out the HubSpot integration over the next few weeks (23:45).\n- Colin will provide updates on progress and notify when integration testing can begin, maintaining transparency on timelines (23:11).\n- The team agreed to begin content review and bring back working groups after successful data integration tests, aligning workload with available resources (22:50).","outline":null,"keywords":["HubSpot Integration","Campaign Tracking","Data Masking","SharePoint Access","Salesforce Reporting","Test Contacts Upload"],"overview":"- **Data Migration Ready:** Team can start importing test contacts now; masking review complete ahead of schedule.  \n- **Test Contact Upload:** Colin to upload test contacts by Monday; testing phase lasts two to three weeks.  \n- **Campaign Tracking Alignment:** Need for customizable campaign fields discussed for better sales insights between HubSpot and Salesforce.  \n- **Document Sharing Improvements:** Victor to set up a SharePoint folder for easier document access; troubleshooting external sharing issues agreed.  \n- **IT Security Coordination:** Discuss adding IT security access to third-party marketing systems to audit data risks if necessary.  \n- **Dual Due Date Tracking:** Implementing hard and flexible deadlines to balance workload and project visibility for leadership support.","action_items":"\n**Colin Costigan**\nFollow up again with Google regarding Ads account status after five business days (05:40)\nUpload test contacts (sample CSV) into sandbox environment before Monday meeting (20:37)\nPopulate project plan columns with hard due dates and flexible deadlines (24:40)\nCoordinate with Gabe and Ashley for readiness notification to set up test integration (23:11)\nAdd task to project plan regarding IT security team access discussion for third-party marketing platforms (27:09)\n\n**Victor Garcia**\nCreate folder in SharePoint for document sharing and grant team access; notify once done (07:17)\nProvide documentation and Salesforce report screenshots to Colin for mapping campaign tracking fields (13:31)\nConfirm SharePoint email sharing and troubleshoot access issues with team; consider using group email (21:09)\nVerify access for Betty and Lewis to the project plan and ensure they are included (28:42)\nReport back on Salesforce report filters relevant to marketing attribution field (18:25)\n\n**Ashlie Taska**\nCollaborate with Victor and Gabe on finalizing test contact upload and integration testing (20:37)\nReflect and clarify campaign attribution needs from sales team perspective for future phases (15:52)\n\n**Gabriel Bencosme**\nContinue reviewing HubSpot platform and test contacts integration over next two weeks, escalating issues if any arise (14:17)\nConfirm access and familiarity with the project plan document (28:37)\n\n**Christina Zanca**\nProvide alignment on income range definitions and relevant field naming for masking in HubSpot (11:57)\nConsider naming conventions and campaign source field for Salesforce and marketing mapping (20:20)\nSupport discussion with Ashlie and Victor on sales team usage of campaign fields and attribution tracking (17:14)\n\n**Guille Santana**\nMonitor SharePoint folder creation and access by Victor; ensure team coordination (07:21)\nEnsure project plan access to Betty and Lewis and coordinate team reference (28:42)\nFollow up on access and email sharing issues with SharePoint (21:09)\n"},"migrated_from":"contract_meetings","original_id":"e6df9523-5ec4-4dab-9f53-842ca24cbfee","master_marketer":{"status":"migrated"}}'::jsonb,
