    'https://us02web.zoom.us/j/89786281993?pwd=li2lwrSFpmITXPKEdOBBgaXPwh8ONO.1',
    '{"id":"01KF48T6KAV8N4ZCYBR99CQ0P3","title":"AQI // MiD: Weekly Marketing Meeting","summary":{"notes":"## **HubSpot Migration and Integration**\n\nThe team is actively progressing on the **HubSpot migration** with a focus on clean data import and controlled sync between HubSpot and Salesforce to avoid unwanted contact creation (02:18).\n\n- **Colin Costigan** completed the initial swaps and is importing contacts while mapping fields precisely to ensure clean data transfer.\n- Integration will allow updates between HubSpot and Salesforce only for relevant contacts, preventing random Salesforce entries from creating HubSpot contacts.\n- The current segment contains **208 contacts**, with **30 from Eventbrite**, all set to sync properly under the new system.\n- This careful approach reduces data noise, supports sales and marketing alignment, and maintains database hygiene, critical for future ABM efforts.\n\n## **Lead Scoring Development and Testing**\n\nLead scoring is fully built and now entering the testing phase, with workflows being created to automate lifecycle stage changes based on scores (04:00).\n\n- The scoring model uses the points defined by **Barb Willans** and was built by **Guille Santana** and **Colin Costigan** to reflect engagement accurately.\n- Testing involves imported contacts from Barb’s spreadsheet to ensure the scoring applies correctly and triggers proper lifecycle updates.\n- Workflows will handle actions like subtracting points or moving contacts to marketing-accepted leads to maintain score integrity.\n- Adjustments for additional padding in scoring are planned based on feedback from Barb and Tristan to improve lead qualification before sales engagement.\n\n## **On-Demand Webinars and Form Management**\n\nAll on-demand webinar forms are being transitioned fully to HubSpot, removing Marketo forms to ensure streamlined data capture and integration (06:30).\n\n- **Guille Santana** explained that only the thank-you page needs updating to host videos and capture form submissions correctly in HubSpot.\n- Barb emphasized the need to avoid Marketo forms because its phase-out requires full HubSpot adoption for future webinars.\n- A video tutorial will be created to empower Barb’s team to update forms independently for the expected **3-4 webinars per month**, reducing support overhead.\n- The team agreed to proceed with updating all older forms for toolkits and webinars to HubSpot immediately, ensuring consistent data flow and reporting.\n\n## **ABM Scoring and Lead Nurturing Strategy**\n\nThe ABM scoring framework looks solid but requires more “padding” to better qualify leads before sales outreach, with sign-off expected next week from **Vinny** (08:14).\n\n- Barb and Colin plan to meet sales leads next week to align on ABM offers and tangible incentives to include in nurture emails.\n- Colin highlighted the need to clarify what free or valuable content can be offered to Aquarius leads to improve engagement and conversion.\n- The scoring includes handling multiple opportunities per contact and adding new properties like pronouns and gender ID to enrich lead profiles.\n- This refined ABM approach aims to increase lead quality, improve sales conversations, and better target key accounts based on enriched data.\n\n## **Lead Routing and User Setup**\n\nThere is a gap in lead routing for the **Hawk lead form**, with no current mapping for notifications or Salesforce integration, which is being addressed (10:26).\n\n- Barb will set up the individual BDR users in HubSpot and coordinate with Colin to ensure leads route correctly by territory and ownership.\n- Colin confirmed that with proper user setup, Hawk leads will flow into Salesforce via the integration, ensuring no loss of leads.\n- Barb will send detailed mapping and ownership info by email to finalize routing and avoid orphan leads.\n- This fix ensures all inbound leads are assigned promptly, supporting fast follow-up and improving conversion chances.\n\n## **Event and Presentation Success**\n\nThe recent **Hawk lead form** was highly effective at the San Diego event, generating real leads and positive exposure (09:40).\n\n- Barb praised the team’s support and highlighted the need to know where new leads go after submission to close the loop with sales.\n- Vivian’s presentation at San Diego showcased the company’s capabilities well, boosting credibility and interest in the product.\n- This success reinforces the importance of clean data flow and form integrations as foundational to effective event marketing and lead capture.\n- Continued collaboration and refinement of these systems will support future event-driven lead generation efforts.","outline":null,"keywords":["HubSpot","Salesforce","Lead Scoring","Webinar Forms","ABM","Hawk Lead"],"overview":"- **HubSpot Migration Progress:** Focus on clean data transfer and controlled sync to prevent unwanted contact creation; 208 contacts ready to sync.\n\n- **Lead Scoring Testing:** Completed scoring model entering testing; workflows will automate lead stages based on scoring for better qualification.\n\n- **Webinar Form Transition:** Transitioning all webinar forms to HubSpot for streamlined data; video tutorial planned for self-management of form updates.\n\n- **ABM Scoring Refinement:** Need for padding in ABM scoring to improve lead qualification before sales; upcoming meeting with sales leads to align on offers.\n\n- **Lead Routing Issues:** Current gaps in lead routing for Hawk forms being addressed; Barb will set up BDR users for proper lead distribution.\n\n- **Event Success Recognition:** The San Diego event generated valuable leads; highlights importance of clean data flow and ongoing collaboration for future events.","action_items":"\n**Colin Costigan**\nComplete the import of contacts and finalize HubSpot-Salesforce integration with conditional syncing rules (01:56)\nContinue lead scoring testing and build workflows for lifecycle stage automation (04:00)\nConduct a full sweep replacing legacy webinar forms with HubSpot forms and create a Loom video tutorial for the team (07:13)\nImplement additional properties (pronouns, gender) to contact profiles during import (09:09)\nVerify and configure Hawk lead integration routing to Salesforce and HubSpot users (10:50)\n\n**Guille Santana**\nSupport form updates and manage thank you page changes for on demand webinars, create tutorial video for form management (05:28)\nBegin updating older forms such as toolkits and on-demand webinars to HubSpot forms (07:40)\n\n**Barb Willans**\nProvide contact details and territory logic for BDR users to Colin and Guille for setup in HubSpot and Salesforce (11:12)\nCollaborate with sales leads on ABM offer strategy and scoring adjustments next week (08:46)\n"},"duration":13.430000305175781,"speakers":[{"id":0,"name":"bwillans"},{"id":1,"name":"Colin Costigan"},{"id":2,"name":"Guille Santana"}],"sentences":[{"text":"Did that storm hit you yet?","index":0,"end_time":1.44,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":0.24,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"So if it''s gonna hit, it''s gonna be tomorrow night into Sunday into Monday and unfortunately we were trying to have my daughter''s first birthday party tomorrow which we have canceled because of travel safety.","index":1,"end_time":18.08,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":3.28,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Oh.","index":2,"end_time":19.6,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":19.04,"speaker_name":"Guille Santana"},{"text":"But it''s all good.","index":3,"end_time":20.84,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":20.08,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"If it''s gonna be any birthday that we have to cancel, I think the first one''s the best one.","index":4,"end_time":24.08,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":20.84,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"She''ll have no idea.","index":5,"end_time":26.56,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":25.2,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"She won''t, but still.","index":6,"end_time":28.43,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":27.39,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":7,"end_time":29.31,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":28.83,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"Well, take care.","index":8,"end_time":32.11,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":30.35,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"It looks scary.","index":9,"end_time":32.99,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":32.11,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"Yeah, we''ll see.","index":10,"end_time":34.47,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":33.79,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I don''t know.","index":11,"end_time":34.91,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":34.47,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I mean to me there''s still 50, 50 shot that nothing happens.","index":12,"end_time":37.47,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":34.91,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, for sure.","index":13,"end_time":38.75,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":37.71,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"Awesome.","index":14,"end_time":41.71,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":41.07,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"All right.","index":15,"end_time":43.31,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":42.67,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So Gay, do you want to pull up our slide deck?","index":16,"end_time":46.35,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":44.03,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Barb, I''ve.","index":17,"end_time":47.23,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":46.35,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I apologize.","index":18,"end_time":48.51,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":47.71,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I''ve been much less responsive than I usually am on email.","index":19,"end_time":51.39,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":48.51,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Five day week crunched into four days.","index":20,"end_time":54.84,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":53.12,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"But we''ve got a lot of great updates for you.","index":21,"end_time":57.36,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":54.84,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, no worries at all.","index":22,"end_time":59.12,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":57.92,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"And our teams, Microsoft, like if you sent me any emails, they weren''t coming through anyway.","index":23,"end_time":64.72,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":59.12,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"So.","index":24,"end_time":65.12,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":64.72,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"Yeah, teams was having major issues this week.","index":25,"end_time":67.68,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":65.68,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, yeah, we were.","index":26,"end_time":69.28,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":67.84,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"We were majorly hit.","index":27,"end_time":70.72,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":69.28,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"So we just.","index":28,"end_time":71.84,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":70.88,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"No email from anybody all week.","index":29,"end_time":76.08,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":73.2,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"It''s all good.","index":30,"end_time":79.04,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":78.16,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"All right, so our agenda for today, we''re going to talk about the HubSpot migration lead scoring our on demand webinars.","index":31,"end_time":90.23,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":80.79,"speaker_name":"Guille Santana"},{"text":"Barb, I know you send an email about that and all forms.","index":32,"end_time":93.75,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":90.23,"speaker_name":"Guille Santana"},{"text":"Perfect, thanks.","index":33,"end_time":95.27,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":94.15,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"So our HubSpot migration, we''re actively working on that like making the connections and just setting everything up.","index":34,"end_time":106.56,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":97.11,"speaker_name":"Guille Santana"},{"text":"So don''t worry about that.","index":35,"end_time":108.32,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":106.88,"speaker_name":"Guille Santana"},{"text":"We got that email from Kyle and we''re actively working on it.","index":36,"end_time":113.6,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":108.32,"speaker_name":"Guille Santana"},{"text":"Colin, I don''t know if you want to add something.","index":37,"end_time":115.6,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":113.6,"speaker_name":"Guille Santana"},{"text":"Yeah, so I made the swaps that Kyle said so that was pretty easy.","index":38,"end_time":120.84,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":116.08,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And I''m literally in the import right now.","index":39,"end_time":123.12,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":120.84,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So I''m importing everyone in and then setting up the integration so that HubSpot updates Salesforce.","index":40,"end_time":129.32,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":123.12,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Salesforce will update contacts that we''ve integrated but not the ones that we don''t want.","index":41,"end_time":133.44,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":129.32,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"That''s just the complicated layer on top of it that requires a little extra care.","index":42,"end_time":137.51,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":134.47,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay, quick question.","index":43,"end_time":140.23,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":138.71,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"So there''s not many people in there.","index":44,"end_time":141.91,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":140.23,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"There''s like 208 in the one segment in HubSpot now.","index":45,"end_time":148.27,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":141.91,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"So like 30 of them came through Eventbrite when the others just came through me.","index":46,"end_time":152.31,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":148.27,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"So those contacts will be updated or.","index":47,"end_time":155.91,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":152.31,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"Yeah, okay.","index":48,"end_time":157.91,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":156.31,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"All right.","index":49,"end_time":158.31,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":157.91,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"Yeah, that''ll be all taken care of.","index":50,"end_time":160.03,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":158.63,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So the first part that we''re focusing on is an import that we''re doing and setting up all the fields and everything''s mapped and then the Next part is setting up the integration so that they''ll update each other, but the way they were doing it and correct me if I''m wrong if things have changed, but we don''t want like if someone randomly enters someone in Salesforce for any reason, we don''t need them being created as a contact in HubSpot.","index":51,"end_time":180.93,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":160.03,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Correct.","index":52,"end_time":182.17,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":181.73,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":53,"end_time":182.41,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":182.17,"speaker_name":"Guille Santana"},{"text":"Okay.","index":54,"end_time":182.73,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":182.41,"speaker_name":"Guille Santana"},{"text":"And if they.","index":55,"end_time":183.45,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":182.73,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"There''s any reason why we do need to in the future and we''d have those discussions then we''ll do it then.","index":56,"end_time":187.89,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":183.45,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"But.","index":57,"end_time":188.21,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":187.89,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"Yep.","index":58,"end_time":188.85,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":188.37,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"Okay, cool.","index":59,"end_time":189.73,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":188.85,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"Just.","index":60,"end_time":190.17,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":189.81,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"Just always double checking.","index":61,"end_time":191.73,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":190.17,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Perfect.","index":62,"end_time":192.62,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":192.22,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"But yeah, so we''ll have updates on this today.","index":63,"end_time":195.98,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":193.5,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay, perfect.","index":64,"end_time":197.34,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":196.46,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"Thank you.","index":65,"end_time":197.82,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":197.34,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"Then for lead scoring, the lead scoring flow is built.","index":66,"end_time":204.26,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":200.06,"speaker_name":"Guille Santana"},{"text":"I''m going to show it to you.","index":67,"end_time":205.58,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":204.26,"speaker_name":"Guille Santana"},{"text":"Can you see my screen?","index":68,"end_time":207.26,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":205.74,"speaker_name":"Guille Santana"},{"text":"I can.","index":69,"end_time":208.099,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":207.659,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"Thank you.","index":70,"end_time":208.62,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":208.099,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"All right, so it''s over here.","index":71,"end_time":210.7,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":209.1,"speaker_name":"Guille Santana"},{"text":"Everything''s built with the points you send out, with the last email that you send out, the last update.","index":72,"end_time":217.02,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":210.86,"speaker_name":"Guille Santana"},{"text":"I know you added some.","index":73,"end_time":218.47,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":217.43,"speaker_name":"Guille Santana"},{"text":"On demand.","index":74,"end_time":220.83,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":220.23,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"Yeah, yeah.","index":75,"end_time":222.39,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":220.83,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"So everything''s here, everything''s built.","index":76,"end_time":224.79,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":222.47,"speaker_name":"Guille Santana"},{"text":"Now we''re working on the workflow.","index":77,"end_time":228.07,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":225.43,"speaker_name":"Guille Santana"},{"text":"So the first part of the build is like building it and then we need to like some actions require workflows to work.","index":78,"end_time":238.07,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":228.07,"speaker_name":"Guille Santana"},{"text":"So we''re working on that as well.","index":79,"end_time":240.63,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":238.31,"speaker_name":"Guille Santana"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":80,"end_time":241.07,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":240.71,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So Barb, the lead scoring is built.","index":81,"end_time":242.79,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":241.07,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We''re putting into testing now because we have the contacts that we''re importing the portion of the spreadsheet that you shared.","index":82,"end_time":248.96,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":242.79,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, perfect.","index":83,"end_time":249.6,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":248.96,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Here if you go to the right, it says like action.","index":84,"end_time":252.76,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":249.6,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yes.","index":85,"end_time":253.4,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":252.92,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"That stuff has to be handled in a workflow because the lead scoring metric, like doesn''t affect these life cycle stages necessarily.","index":86,"end_time":262.8,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":254.2,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Like in a way of like if we just subtract 10 points then move them to mal.","index":87,"end_time":266.92,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":262.8,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Makes sense.","i