ime":704.02,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":312,"end_time":705.18,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":704.74,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"Well, we''ll do both, but thank you.","index":313,"end_time":706.98,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":705.18,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"We were so excited to see it.","index":314,"end_time":708.5,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":707.22,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"And then I said just.","index":315,"end_time":709.66,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":708.5,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"Adam.","index":316,"end_time":710.1,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":709.66,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"It''s just sitting there.","index":317,"end_time":710.86,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":710.1,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"I don''t think I gave you guys any.","index":318,"end_time":712.1,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":710.86,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"I didn''t tell you who.","index":319,"end_time":713.5,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":712.5,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"It goes.","index":320,"end_time":714.02,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":713.5,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"Like, it''s New Hampshire and there''s somebody who covers New Hampshire.","index":321,"end_time":717.66,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":714.02,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"I just have to find it.","index":322,"end_time":718.58,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":717.66,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"So.","index":323,"end_time":718.82,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":718.58,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"Yeah, I didn''t.","index":324,"end_time":719.46,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":718.82,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":325,"end_time":720.6,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":720.36,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"So I''ll figure that out.","index":326,"end_time":721.88,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":720.6,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"Perfect.","index":327,"end_time":722.52,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":721.96,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Thanks, guys.","index":328,"end_time":723.76,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":723,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"And that''s it?","index":329,"end_time":724.44,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":723.76,"speaker_name":"Guille Santana"},{"text":"I think so.","index":330,"end_time":725.48,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":724.6,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay, awesome.","index":331,"end_time":727.08,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":725.96,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"Well, thanks for everything, as usual, and everything looks really, really good.","index":332,"end_time":730.36,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":727.08,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"And Vivian was a superstar in San Diego, thanks to you guys.","index":333,"end_time":734.92,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":730.36,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"Did she talk through Databox or was that.","index":334,"end_time":737.2,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":734.92,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"That was a different meeting that she was having.","index":335,"end_time":738.92,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":737.2,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"No, no, it wasn''t eventbrite and data box, and I''m not sure how far she got in all of it, but all the art forms, and she.","index":336,"end_time":748.13,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":738.92,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"I saw her presentation.","index":337,"end_time":749.73,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":748.61,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"I''m not sure how much she got to talk about, but, man, we looked, like, freaking awesome.","index":338,"end_time":755.41,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":749.73,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"Like, we looked pretty good, so.","index":339,"end_time":758.13,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":755.41,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"And that''s.","index":340,"end_time":758.93,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":758.21,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"That''s thanks to the two of you, so thank you so much.","index":341,"end_time":762.13,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":759.41,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":342,"end_time":762.65,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":762.289,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"Well, thank you, Barb.","index":343,"end_time":763.65,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":762.65,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"As Tristan said, you''re definitely our favorite to work with you.","index":344,"end_time":767.49,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":764.13,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"You totally understand how these relationships are able to get things done, and we appreciate it so much.","index":345,"end_time":773.4,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":767.81,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So thank you.","index":346,"end_time":774.44,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":773.56,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Have an awesome weekend.","index":347,"end_time":776.36,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":775.24,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":348,"end_time":777,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":776.6,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"Stay.","index":349,"end_time":777.32,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":777,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"Stay warm and safe.","index":350,"end_time":779.08,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":777.72,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"We''ll try.","index":351,"end_time":779.88,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":779.32,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"All right, thanks, guys.","index":352,"end_time":781.52,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":780.52,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"Bye.","index":353,"end_time":781.88,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":781.52,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"Thank.","index":354,"end_time":782.68,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":782.28,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"Bye.","index":355,"end_time":783.08,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":782.68,"speaker_name":"bwillans"}],"dateString":"2026-01-23T16:00:00.000Z","host_email":"colin.costigan@marketersindemand.com","meeting_link":"https://us02web.zoom.us/j/89786281993?pwd=li2lwrSFpmITXPKEdOBBgaXPwh8ONO.1","participants":["guille.santana@marketersindemand.com,colin.costigan@marketersindemand.com,barb.willans@aquaticinformatics.com","guille.santana@marketersindemand.com","barb.willans@aquaticinformatics.com"],"transcript_url":"https://app.fireflies.ai/view/01KF48T6KAV8N4ZCYBR99CQ0P3","organizer_email":"colin.costigan@marketersindemand.com"}'::jsonb,
    '{"label":"positive","confidence":0.92,"bullets":["Completed HubSpot contact import and bi-directional integration setup with Salesforce now underway.","Finalized lead scoring logic; testing active with workflows to trigger life cycle updates.","Agreed to update all legacy forms, including toolkits and webinar flows, to HubSpot.","Confirmed ABM scoring model looks good; minor padding updates planned pending Monday sign-off.","Planned full transition from Marketo forms with how-to video and owner mapping to follow."],"highlights":[{"quote":"The lead scoring is built. We''re putting into testing now.","speaker":"Colin Costigan"},{"quote":"We just need it to be a HubSpot form and flow appropriately.","speaker":"bwillans"},{"quote":"Everything looks really, really good. And Vivian was a superstar in San Diego.","speaker":"bwillans"}],"topics":["lead scoring","integration","migration","webinars","abm"],"model":"openai/gpt-4-1106-preview","version":1,"generated_at":"2026-01-23T00:00:00Z"}'::jsonb,
    '{"fireflies_summary":{"notes":"## **HubSpot Migration and Integration**\n\nThe team is actively progressing on the **HubSpot migration** with a focus on clean data import and controlled sync between HubSpot and Salesforce to avoid unwanted contact creation (02:18).\n\n- **Colin Costigan** completed the initial swaps and is importing contacts while mapping fields precisely to ensure clean data transfer.\n- Integration will allow updates between HubSpot and Salesforce only for relevant contacts, preventing random Salesforce entries from creating HubSpot contacts.\n- The current segment contains **208 contacts**, with **30 from Eventbrite**, all set to sync properly under the new system.\n- This careful approach reduces data noise, supports sales and marketing alignment, and maintains database hygiene, critical for future ABM efforts.\n\n## **Lead Scoring Development and Testing**\n\nLead scoring is fully built and now entering the testing phase, with workflows being created to automate lifecycle stage changes based on scores (04:00).\n\n- The scoring model uses the points defined by **Barb Willans** and was built by **Guille Santana** and **Colin Costigan** to reflect engagement accurately.\n- Testing involves imported contacts from Barb’s spreadsheet to ensure the scoring applies correctly and triggers proper lifecycle updates.\n- Workflows will handle actions like subtracting points or moving contacts to marketing-accepted leads to maintain score integrity.\n- Adjustments for additional padding in scoring are planned based on feedback from Barb and Tristan to improve lead qualification before sales engagement.\n\n## **On-Demand Webinars and Form Management**\n\nAll on-demand webinar forms are being transitioned fully to HubSpot, removing Marketo forms to ensure streamlined data capture and integration (06:30).\n\n- **Guille Santana** explained that only the thank-you page needs updating to host videos and capture form submissions correctly in HubSpot.\n- Barb emphasized the need to avoid Marketo forms because its phase-out requires full HubSpot adoption for future webinars.\n- A video tutorial will be created to empower Barb’s team to update forms independently for the expected **3-4 webinars per month**, reducing support overhead.\n- The team agreed to proceed with updating all older forms for toolkits and webinars to HubSpot immediately, ensuring consistent data flow and reporting.\n\n## **ABM Scoring and Lead Nurturing Strategy**\n\nThe ABM scoring framework looks solid but requires more “padding” to better qualify leads before sales outreach, with sign-off expected next week from **Vinny** (08:14).\n\n- Barb and Colin plan to meet sales leads next week to align on ABM offers and tangible incentives to include in nurture emails.\n- Colin highlighted the need to clarify what free or valuable content can be offered to Aquarius leads to improve engagement and conversion.\n- The scoring includes handling multiple opportunities per contact and adding new properties like pronouns and gender ID to enrich lead profiles.\n- This refined ABM approach aims to increase lead quality, improve sales conversations, and better target key accounts based on enriched data.\n\n## **Lead Routing and User Setup**\n\nThere is a gap in lead routing for the **Hawk lead form**, with no current mapping for notifications or Salesforce integration, which is being addressed (10:26).\n\n- Barb will set up the individual BDR users in HubSpot and coordinate with Colin to ensure leads route correctly by territory and ownership.\n- Colin confirmed that with proper user setup, Hawk leads will flow into Salesforce via the integration, ensuring no loss of leads.\n- Barb will send detailed mapping and ownership info by email to finalize routing and avoid orphan leads.\n- This fix ensures all inbound leads are assigned promptly, supporting fast follow-up and improving conversion chances.\n\n## **Event and Presentation Success**\n\nThe recent **Hawk lead form** was highly effective at the San Diego event, generating real leads and positive exposure (09:40).\n\n- Barb praised the team’s support and highlighted the need to know where new leads go after submission to close the loop with sales.\n- Vivian’s presentation at San Diego showcased the company’s capabilities well, boosting credibility and interest in the product.\n- This success reinforces the importance of clean data flow and form integrations as foundational to effective event marketing and lead capture.\n- Continued collaboration and refinement of these systems will support future event-driven lead generation efforts.","outline":null,"keywords":["HubSpot","Salesforce","Lead Scoring","Webinar Forms","ABM","Hawk Lead"],"overview":"- **HubSpot Migration Progress:** Focus on clean data transfer and controlled sync to prevent unwanted contact creation; 208 contacts ready to sync.\n\n- **Lead Scoring Testing:** Completed scoring model entering testing; workflows will automate lead stages based on scoring for better qualification.\n\n- **Webinar Form Transition:** Transitioning all webinar forms to HubSpot for streamlined data; video tutorial planned for self-management of form updates.\n\n- **ABM Scoring Refinement:** Need for padding in ABM scoring to improve lead qualification before sales; upcoming meeting with sales leads to align on offers.\n\n- **Lead Routing Issues:** Current gaps in lead routing for Hawk forms being addressed; Barb will set up BDR users for proper lead distribution.\n\n- **Event Success Recognition:** The San Diego event generated valuable leads; highlights importance of clean data flow and ongoing collaboration for future events.","action_items":"\n**Colin Costigan**\nComplete the import of contacts and finalize HubSpot-Salesforce integration with conditional syncing rules (01:56)\nContinue lead scoring testing and build workflows for lifecycle stage automation (04:00)\nConduct a full sweep replacing legacy webinar forms with HubSpot forms and create a Loom video tutorial for the team (07:13)\nImplement additional properties (pronouns, gender) to contact profiles during import (09:09)\nVerify and configure Hawk lead integration routing to Salesforce and HubSpot users (10:50)\n\n**Guille Santana**\nSupport form updates and manage thank you page changes for on demand webinars, create tutorial video for form management (05:28)\nBegin updating older forms such as toolkits and on-demand webinars to HubSpot forms (07:40)\n\n**Barb Willans**\nProvide contact details and territory logic for BDR users to Colin and Guille for setup in HubSpot and Salesforce (11:12)\nCollaborate with sales leads on ABM offer strategy and scoring adjustments next week (08:46)\n"},"migrated_from":"contract_meetings","original_id":"fed4bc20-f6b5-421a-99fe-8aea402e8156","master_marketer":{"status":"migrated"}}'::jsonb,
