    '{"id":"01KF4NQ2SDJFSMA3Y6QYMGQNJE","title":"Colin Costigan and Kate Burwood","summary":{"notes":"## **Marketing Campaign and Localization Strategy**\n\nThe team decided to launch the **Disruption White Paper on January 28th** with full backend website and HubSpot support confirmed by Colin (01:05).\n\n- **Kate ThreatMark confirmed readiness for website and HubSpot integration** to coincide with the white paper release (01:17).  \n    - This ensures seamless user experience and lead capture aligned with the launch.  \n    - Colin emphasized the backend pieces are all completed.  \n    - This integration supports marketing automation and data tracking for the campaign.  \n    - Timely launch on January 28th is essential to meet strategic marketing goals.\n\n- **German market localization was prioritized for paid ads and lead magnets** after discussion involving Kate, Nina, Colin, and Greg (02:14).  \n    - Colin recommended translated ads in German to boost performance and reinforce global presence.  \n    - Nina highlighted the German audience demands more technical and product-specific content compared to US/UK markets.  \n    - Kate explained they are producing a German version of a regulation lead magnet, prompting a discussion on how best to deliver it.  \n    - They agreed on testing both English and German ads with corresponding landing pages to optimize engagement.\n\n- **The team resolved to run separate German and English ads directing to language-specific landing pages** to keep experiments clean and clear, as advised by Greg and Colin (06:09).  \n    - Colin noted the German landing page needs to be created but the lead magnet is ready.  \n    - This approach simplifies user experience and tracking for marketing effectiveness.  \n    - The decision reflects a balance between localization and operational simplicity.  \n    - Testing this will inform future international campaign strategies.\n\n- **Target geographies for the Central Europe campaign were confirmed to include Germany, Hungary, Slovakia, Austria, Czechia, Poland, Slovenia, and Switzerland** based on Nina’s LinkedIn audience data (07:17).  \n    - Kate confirmed these align with the regional sales rep Cooper’s territory.  \n    - Greg clarified LinkedIn targeting will combine company lists and country filters to reach these markets precisely.  \n    - This targeting strategy aims to maximize relevant leads across multiple Central European countries.  \n    - The team is refining contact data for bank-related campaigns, with Kate agreeing to share contact records for better targeting.\n\n## **Product and Technical Integration**\n\nThe team enhanced podcast metric tracking through a **custom integration with Buzzsprout**, enabling automated data updates on episode plays (09:06).\n\n- **Colin built an integration that pulls total plays and episode-level breakdowns into a dashboard** to provide clearer insights (09:06).  \n    - This fills a previous gap where data was fragmented across platforms like Apple and Spotify.  \n    - Kate can adjust the time filter to analyze various time periods dynamically.  \n    - This tool aids marketing analysis and content planning based on listener engagement patterns.  \n    - It supports better decision-making around podcast promotion and investment.\n\n- **Discussion about integrating podcast metrics into HubSpot surfaced as a future enhancement, though not a current priority** (10:25).  \n    - Greg expressed interest in consolidating reporting but acknowledged it is not urgent.  \n    - Colin suggested a potential interim solution using automated Google Sheets syncing data from Buzzsprout.  \n    - Centralizing podcast metrics in HubSpot would streamline reporting for board meetings and internal reviews.  \n    - This reflects ongoing efforts to unify marketing data for improved visibility and strategic insight.\n\n## **Process Clarity and Collaboration**\n\nThe team clarified data and targeting requirements, improving campaign precision and coordination (06:37).\n\n- **Kate agreed to share contact records for bank-related German campaigns to enhance list targeting** (08:33).  \n    - Nina confirmed this data is needed to link with target lists effectively.  \n    - This step will improve campaign reach and contact accuracy in German markets.  \n    - It supports better personalization and higher campaign relevance.  \n    - This exchange illustrates effective collaboration between marketing and data teams.\n\n- **Greg confirmed LinkedIn audience layering by company and country to refine targeting** (07:58).  \n    - This ensures campaigns only reach relevant accounts within specified countries.  \n    - The approach balances broad regional targeting with account-level precision.  \n    - This strategy reduces wasted spend and improves lead quality.  \n    - It reflects thoughtful use of LinkedIn’s targeting capabilities to maximize ROI.\n\n## **Timelines and Deliverables**\n\nKey deliverables and deadlines were confirmed to keep marketing efforts on track.\n\n- **The Disruption White Paper release is fixed for January 28th, with all related backend integrations completed** (00:47).  \n    - This date anchors marketing campaigns and resource allocation.  \n    - Kate and Colin aligned on readiness to launch website and HubSpot components.  \n    - Clear deadlines support coordinated rollout across channels.  \n    - This milestone drives momentum for the quarter’s demand generation.\n\n- **The German-language landing page for the lead magnet needs to be created promptly to support ad campaigns** (06:32).  \n    - Colin confirmed the English version is ready and the German page is the remaining task.  \n    - This asset is critical for localized campaigns and lead capture.  \n    - Timely completion will enable simultaneous testing of English and German ads.  \n    - The team plans to explore developer support for creating language toggle options if needed.\n\n## **Strategic Insights and Market Positioning**\n\nThe meeting revealed strategic thinking behind localization and campaign design to strengthen ThreatMark’s presence in German-speaking regions.\n\n- **Colin emphasized that translated ads would not only perform better but also build ThreatMark’s global brand presence** (02:44).  \n    - This aligns with a broader vision of presenting ThreatMark as a truly international player.  \n    - Localized content addresses market expectations and competitive differentiation.  \n    - The decision reflects prioritizing user experience and cultural relevance.  \n    - It underscores the importance of tailoring messaging to specific regional needs.\n\n- **Nina’s input on the German market’s preference for technical detail shapes content strategy** (02:57).  \n    - This insight ensures that messaging resonates with the target audience’s buying criteria.  \n    - It informs copywriting and asset development to increase conversion rates.  \n    - Incorporating these nuances strengthens campaign effectiveness.  \n    - This represents a customer-centric approach to marketing in diverse markets.\n\n- **The plan to test both English and German ads with clear segmentation supports data-driven optimization** (04:44).  \n    - Greg and Colin advocate for clean experiments to understand language impact on engagement.  \n    - This testing framework will guide future localization investments.  \n    - It reflects a disciplined approach to campaign measurement.  \n    - The results will inform ThreatMark’s broader international marketing roadmap.","outline":null,"keywords":["Disruption White Paper","German Market Ads","Lead Magnet Translation","LinkedIn Campaign","Podcast Metrics","Language-specific Landing Pages"],"overview":"- **Disruption White Paper Launch:** Scheduled for January 28th, with all backend integrations ready for marketing support.  \n- **German Market Focus:** Prioritized for localized ads; translated content to enhance performance and engagement with specific audience needs.  \n- **Targeted Campaigns:** Separate German and English ads will direct to language-specific landing pages for effective tracking and optimization.  \n- **Podcast Metrics Integration:** Custom integration with Buzzsprout improves tracking; future integration with HubSpot discussed but not urgent.  \n- **Data Collaboration:** Sharing contact records enhances campaign targeting for German markets, improving reach and personalization efforts.  \n- **Strategic Localization:** Tailoring ads and content to the German market increases ThreatMark’s global presence and aligns with customer preferences.","action_items":"\n**Colin Costigan**\nPrepare and confirm backend setup for the disruption white paper release on website and HubSpot by January 28 (01:10)\nResearch and implement landing page language selection or separate German landing page for the lead magnet, coordinating with developers to avoid extra plugins (04:40)\nProvide demo or access to podcast metrics dashboard and explore options for integrating data into HubSpot or external reporting tools (09:55)\n\n**Kate ThreatMark**\nConfirm readiness to launch website and HubSpot backend tasks related to the disruption white paper release (01:17)\nSend contact record details to Nina Belina to enhance bank-related LinkedIn target lists for Germany (08:38)\n\n**Nina Belina**\nConfirm target countries inclusion in LinkedIn campaigns and clarify coordination of layered company and country filters with Greg and Kate (07:15)\n\n**Greg Smith**\nLead strategic testing (A/B) of German vs. English ads to establish optimal language approach for campaigns (04:50)\nCoordinate with team on filters applied to LinkedIn target audiences across Central European countries (07:20)\n"},"duration":12.149999618530273,"speakers":[{"id":0,"name":"Colin Costigan"},{"id":1,"name":"Kate ThreatMark"},{"id":2,"name":"Nina Belina"},{"id":3,"name":"Greg"}],"sentences":[{"text":"And my daughter''s first birthday party''s tomorrow and we are getting of course biggest snow in our state in 10 years.","index":0,"end_time":8.32,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1.04,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So we had to cancel her party.","index":1,"end_time":10.48,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":9.04,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Good time.","index":2,"end_time":11.36,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":10.8,"speaker_name":"Kate ThreatMark"},{"text":"Oh, that''s sad.","index":3,"end_time":12.8,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":11.36,"speaker_name":"Nina Belina"},{"text":"Yeah, we''re just gonna do just at our house, just like very, very, very, very small party and just trying to have as much fun as possible.","index":4,"end_time":22.24,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":13.36,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Luckily it''s her first birthday, so she''s not gonna know the difference.","index":5,"end_time":25.44,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":22.4,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I hope you guys.","index":6,"end_time":27.94,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":27.3,"speaker_name":"Kate ThreatMark"},{"text":"Well, appreciate that.","index":7,"end_time":29.7,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":27.94,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I see Greg is on here, but I''m not sure if he''s traveling.","index":8,"end_time":34.22,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":29.7,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, I''m on a train, but.","index":9,"end_time":35.86,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":34.22,"speaker_name":"Greg"},{"text":"So I''m listening in.","index":10,"end_time":36.9,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":35.86,"speaker_name":"Greg"},{"text":"Okay, gotcha.","index":11,"end_time":37.94,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":36.98,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Awesome.","index":12,"end_time":40.18,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":39.54,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"All right, Kate, I know that you and Nina met on Monday as well.","index":13,"end_time":43.94,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":40.42,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So how can we help?","index":14,"end_time":46.26,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":44.1,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I just wanted to go through two main things.","index":15,"end_time":50.26,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":47.22,"speaker_name":"Kate ThreatMark"},{"text":"The first is easier.","index":16,"end_time":52.02,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":50.82,"speaker_name":"Kate ThreatMark"},{"text":"We''ve got a target date for the disruption while white paper release which is the 28th of Jan.","index":17,"end_time":57.87,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":52.42,"speaker_name":"Kate ThreatMark"},{"text":"So next Wednesday I think.","index":18,"end_time":60.27,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":57.95,"speaker_name":"Kate ThreatMark"},{"text":"Wednesday.","index":19,"end_time":60.83,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":60.43,"speaker_name":"Kate ThreatMark"},{"text":"Almost certain.","index":20,"end_time":61.63,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":60.99,"speaker_name":"Kate ThreatMark"},{"text":"It is now doubting myself.","index":21,"end_time":63.47,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":61.63,"speaker_name":"Kate ThreatMark"},{"text":"Yes.","index":22,"end_time":65.55,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":65.07,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, it is.","index":23,"end_time":68.11,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":67.39,"speaker_name":"Kate ThreatMark"},{"text":"So I just wanted to double check that you guys are good to do like the website and HubSpot pieces in the back end of that.","index":24,"end_time":77.39,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":69.47,"speaker_name":"Kate ThreatMark"},{"text":"Oh yeah, all done.","index":25,"end_time":78.59,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":77.63,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay, Fabus.","index":26,"end_time":79.95,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":78.83,"speaker_name":"Kate ThreatMark"},{"text":"Thank you.","index":27,"end_time":80.83,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":80.27,"speaker_name":"Kate ThreatMark"},{"text":"That''s good.","index":28,"end_time":86.03,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":85.55,"speaker_name":"Kate ThreatMark"},{"text":"The second one was just their paid channels.","index":29,"end_time":88.11,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":86.11,"speaker_name":"Kate ThreatMark"},{"text":"Nina and I did go over the new deals around one with bank fur lag but you needed some additional info and I wasn''t 100 sure what you were asking me for.","index":30,"end_time":99.39,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":88.75,"speaker_name":"Kate ThreatMark"},{"text":"So if we could go through that and I also wanted to clarify and it might be a question for Greg.","index":31,"end_time":106.75,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":99.39,"speaker_name":"Kate ThreatMark"},{"text":"Sorry.","index":32,"end_time":107.15,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":106.75,"speaker_name":"Kate ThreatMark"},{"text":"How much of this one we want to do as fully in German.","index":33,"end_time":113.46,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":107.23,"speaker_name":"Kate ThreatMark"},{"text":"So this is a German opportunity for us.","index":34,"end_time":115.86,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":114.18,"speaker_name":"Kate ThreatMark"},{"text":"We also have an additional one we want to add that is also in German or based in Germany.","index":35,"end_time":121.3,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":115.86,"speaker_name":"Kate ThreatMark"},{"text":"Do we want to run these as our first like attempted translated ads or stick to English for the first one?","index":36,"end_time":130.66,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":121.94,"speaker_name":"Kate ThreatMark"},{"text":"Who''s the rep that handles Germany?","index":37,"end_time":137.55,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":134.67,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Cooper.","index":38,"end_time":139.15,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":138.43,"speaker_name":"Kate ThreatMark"},{"text":"Okay.","index":39,"end_time":140.23,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":139.71,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I imagine he speaks German.","index":40,"end_time":141.55,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":140.23,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"He does not.","index":41,"end_time":142.83,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":142.11,"speaker_name":"Kate ThreatMark"},{"text":"Oh, interesting.","index":42,"end_time":144.59,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":143.31,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Unless he''s hiding that from us.","index":43,"end_time":147.59,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":146.27,"speaker_name":"Kate ThreatMark"},{"text":"Greg?","index":44,"end_time":147.91,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":147.59,"speaker_name":"Kate ThreatMark"},{"text":"I''m not sure, but I don''t think he does that.","index":45,"end_time":150.83,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":147.91,"speaker_name":"Kate ThreatMark"},{"text":"I asked him specifically.","index":46,"end_time":152.19,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":150.83,"speaker_name":"Greg"},{"text":"Okay, I know.","index":47,"end_time":153.51,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":152.51,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I mean, I know English is still a very common language in that region.","index":48,"end_time":157.27,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":153.51,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"In the docked region.","index":49,"end_time":158.27,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":157.27,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay.","index":50,"end_time":160.6,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":160.12,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I mean, I don''t know.","index":51,"end_time":163.12,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":161.08,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I think that German or ads in German would perform better.","index":52,"end_time":166.6,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":163.12,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Also provides more of that global presence that threatmark is able to offer.","index":53,"end_time":171.8,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":167.72,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So I would lean towards having them translated.","index":54,"end_time":177.16,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":174.44,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Oh, sorry.","index":55,"end_time":178.12,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":177.4,"speaker_name":"Nina Belina"},{"text":"Also I wanted to mention that for example, for the German market they usually look for different things than US or UK based stats.","index":56,"end_time":187.24,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":178.12,"speaker_name":"Nina Belina"},{"text":"So for example, they like a lot more technical, specifics they want to know a lot more about the product.","index":57,"end_time":193.03,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":187.24,"speaker_name":"Nina Belina"},{"text":"So that''s also something to take into consideration when writing it in German that they really need different type of information than usual ads.","index":58,"end_time":201.75,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":193.03,"speaker_name":"Nina Belina"},{"text":"So for like additional context, we''re, we''re producing a new regulation lead magnet, download whatever you want to call it and we''re translating that into German.","index":59,"end_time":215.03,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":205.59,"speaker_name":"Kate ThreatMark"},{"text":"But I hadn''t really thought through exactly where they''re going to get the download in German but see the ad in English.","index":60,"end_time":223.74,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":217.58,"speaker_name":"Kate ThreatMark"},{"text":"Do we want to do a direct translation?","index":61,"end_time":227.18,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":225.02,"speaker_name":"Kate ThreatMark"},{"text":"Do we actually want to have a, a more thought out ad for that region and then provide them with that translated asset?","index":62,"end_time":235.02,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":227.18,"speaker_name":"Kate ThreatMark"},{"text":"What exactly that looks like?","index":63,"end_time":236.54,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":235.1,"speaker_name":"Kate ThreatMark"},{"text":"Yeah, I don''t know.","index":64,"end_time":242.67,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":238.7,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I think we might need of both options.","index":65,"end_time":245.83,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":242.67,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Like I think we need an English and a German option and I think that we should be able to build in somewhere that they can select which one they''re interested in to download.","index":66,"end_time":255.99,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":246.23,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We could test it.","index":67,"end_time":258.07,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":257.19,"speaker_name":"Kate ThreatMark"},{"text":"Yeah, yeah, we can, we can explore that with our developers.","index":68,"end_time":265.27,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":259.43,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I''m sure that wouldn''t be too much of a problem to set up.","index":69,"end_time":267.43,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":265.27,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"What is.","index":70,"end_time":269.06,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":268.66,"speaker_name":"Greg"},{"text":"Yeah, I was going to say what does the effort look like on something like that?","index":71,"end_time":273.38,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":269.78,"speaker_name":"Greg"},{"text":"What does it look like translation as well as the.","index":72,"end_time":276.66,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":274.1,"speaker_name":"Greg"},{"text":"What does the effort look like for something like that?","index":73,"end_time":278.86,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":276.98,"speaker_name":"Greg"},{"text":"Both from a translation perspective but also from a like capability perspective?","index":74,"end_time":283.38,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":278.86,"speaker_name":"Greg"},{"text":"Yeah, from the translation point, I mean pretty, pretty straightforward.","index":75,"end_time":287.62,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":284.5,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"But for the, we''ll have to do some research on, you know, the current setup with the WordPress site and the HubSpot relationship with the file management.","index":76,"end_time":296.26,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":288.26,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"But I mean after we do some research and just make sure if we, if we need an extra plugin or something like that, which we''d like to avoid, I''m sure that we can custom, you know, put something together that they can go to that landing page and choose which language they want to download the, the document in.","index":77,"end_time":312.82,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":296.34,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay, why don''t we, why don''t we scope the effort for the landing page part but for the ad itself, I think it would, it would make sense to ab Test.","index":78,"end_time":324.02,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":313.54,"speaker_name":"Greg"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":79,"end_time":324.74,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":324.18,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Both languages and see what we get.","index":80,"end_time":327.13,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":325.45,"speaker_name":"Greg"},{"text":"We''re losing you, Craig.","index":81,"end_time":337.29,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":336.01,"speaker_name":"Kate ThreatMark"},{"text":"Is it as simple as like in each ad goes to its corresponding landing page?","index":82,"end_time":348.81,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":341.13,"speaker_name":"Greg"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":83,"end_time":350.09,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":349.69,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":84,"end_time":350.33,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":350.09,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Probably breaking up.","index":85,"end_time":352.17,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":350.33,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, you were breaking up a bit, but I think I heard.","index":86,"end_time":354.37,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":352.37,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Do we have each ad go to a specific landing page?","index":87,"end_time":357.25,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":354.85,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So that''s, that''s one approach.","index":88,"end_time":358.69,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":357.49,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Or we could even have the option for them to, you know, pick a flag or a language or something for which version they want to download.","index":89,"end_time":365.57,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":358.69,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I''d say like let''s, let''s try to keep the experimentation clean.","index":90,"end_time":372.61,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":369.17,"speaker_name":"Greg"},{"text":"Okay.","index":91,"end_time":373.41,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":372.93,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"To keep it simple.","index":92,"end_time":374.21,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":373.41,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And German ad goes to a German landing page.","index":93,"end_time":376.01,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":374.21,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Keep it simple.","index":94,"end_time":376.85,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":376.01,"speaker_name":"Greg"},{"text":"Yep, yep, yep.","index":95,"end_time":378.63,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":376.93,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Da, da.","index":96,"end_time":380.31,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":378.87,"speaker_name":"Greg"},{"text":"Wunderbar.","index":97,"end_time":383.59,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":382.71,"speaker_name":"Greg"},{"text":"So the download will be ready by next week?","index":98,"end_time":391.27,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":387.75,"speaker_name":"Kate ThreatMark"},{"text":"Yeah, it''s already ready.","index":99,"end_time":393.83,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":392.95,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We can turn that on whenever we just.","index":100,"end_time":395.19,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":393.83,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Now we need to make a German version of that page.","index":101,"end_time":397.27,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":395.19,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":102,"end_time":398.47,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":397.99,"speaker_name":"Kate ThreatMark"},{"text":"Okay, cool.","index":103,"end_time":401.19,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":398.63,"speaker_name":"Kate ThreatMark"},{"text":"What was the extra info that you needed, Nina?","index":104,"end_time":408.56,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":406,"speaker_name":"Kate ThreatMark"},{"text":"I know, I''m sorry, I did already ask this, but I wasn''t super clear on what you did need.","index":105,"end_time":412.88,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":408.56,"speaker_name":"Kate ThreatMark"},{"text":"Just a sec.","index":106,"end_time":414.48,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":413.76,"speaker_name":"Nina Belina"},{"text":"So for the Central Europe campaign.","index":107,"end_time":418.08,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":414.56,"speaker_name":"Nina Belina"},{"text":"The campaign is built.","index":108,"end_time":420,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":418.64,"speaker_name":"Nina Belina"},{"text":"The only thing that we wanted to confirm was for certain countries, do you want them to be included?","index":109,"end_time":426.92,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":420.48,"speaker_name":"Nina Belina"},{"text":"So Hungary, Germany, Slovakia, Austria, Czechia, Poland, Slovenia, and Switzerland.","index":110,"end_time":431.6,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":426.92,"speaker_name":"Nina Belina"},{"text":"Germany.","index":111,"end_time":432.16,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":431.6,"speaker_name":"Nina Belina"},{"text":"I would say that you do.","index":112,"end_time":433.4,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":432.16,"speaker_name":"Nina Belina"},{"text":"But for the others who weren''t sure if you agree.","index":113,"end_time":436.67,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":433.4,"speaker_name":"Nina Belina"},{"text":"Yeah, those are all in Cuba''s region, so yes.","index":114,"end_time":440.59,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":437.23,"speaker_name":"Kate ThreatMark"},{"text":"Okay, so is this.","index":115,"end_time":444.67,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":441.63,"speaker_name":"Greg"},{"text":"Hold on.","index":116,"end_time":445.31,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":444.67,"speaker_name":"Greg"},{"text":"Is this LinkedIn or is this other.","index":117,"end_time":448.11,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":445.47,"speaker_name":"Greg"},{"text":"This is the link that.","index":118,"end_time":450.99,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":449.95,"speaker_name":"Nina Belina"},{"text":"The LinkedIn list.","index":119,"end_time":453.23,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":451.55,"speaker_name":"Nina Belina"},{"text":"Sorry.","index":120,"end_time":456.35,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":455.87,"speaker_name":"Nina Belina"},{"text":"I think what Greg''s saying is that we created.","index":121,"end_time":460.99,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":457.23,"speaker_name":"Kate ThreatMark"},{"text":"Okay, now we.","index":122,"end_time":465.22,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":461.3,"speaker_name":"Kate ThreatMark"},{"text":"We have the company audience for across those regions that are the target companies.","index":123,"end_time":472.18,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":465.54,"speaker_name":"Greg"},{"text":"Like, does it.","index":124,"end_time":473.94,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":472.9,"speaker_name":"Greg"},{"text":"Are you saying we''re going to layer the companies and then the countries?","index":125,"end_time":476.9,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":474.18,"speaker_name":"Greg"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":126,"end_time":478.74,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":478.34,"speaker_name":"Nina Belina"},{"text":"So that''s the list that Kate said that she already uploaded to LinkedIn.","index":127,"end_time":482.74,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":478.74,"speaker_name":"Nina Belina"},{"text":"Yeah, yeah, yeah, yeah.","index":128,"end_time":485.06,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":482.74,"speaker_name":"Greg"},{"text":"So we''re putting just a country control filter on it.","index":129,"end_time":488.47,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":485.46,"speaker_name":"Greg"},{"text":"Yes.","index":130,"end_time":489.11,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":488.63,"speaker_name":"Nina Belina"},{"text":"Okay.","index":131,"end_time":490.23,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":489.75,"speaker_name":"Kate ThreatMark"},{"text":"Okay, cool.","index":132,"end_time":490.87,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":490.23,"speaker_name":"Greg"},{"text":"Yeah, that sounds right then.","index":133,"end_time":492.15,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":490.87,"speaker_name":"Greg"},{"text":"And for the other question was the same one from Monday.","index":134,"end_time":496.79,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":493.19,"speaker_name":"Nina Belina"},{"text":"So for the bank in Germany, just if you have any other additional information when it comes to contact people, like email or something, we can connect it for the target lists.","index":135,"end_time":508.47,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":496.87,"speaker_name":"Nina Belina"},{"text":"So if I share with you what the contact record that we have at the moment, would that be sufficient?","index":136,"end_time":518.6,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":513.28,"speaker_name":"Kate ThreatMark"},{"text":"Yeah, that would be great.","index":137,"end_time":519.84,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":518.6,"speaker_name":"Nina Belina"},{"text":"Cool, cool.","index":138,"end_time":520.88,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":520.08,"speaker_name":"Kate ThreatMark"},{"text":"I will send that over.","index":139,"end_time":531.36,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":530.24,"speaker_name":"Kate ThreatMark"},{"text":"I think that was all I had, question wise.","index":140,"end_time":546.57,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":543.53,"speaker_name":"Kate ThreatMark"},{"text":"Awesome.","index":141,"end_time":547.61,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":546.97,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"One other update, I built a custom integration with buzzfeed or buzzsprout.","index":142,"end_time":554.609,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":547.77,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I keep calling it buzzfeed.","index":143,"end_time":555.85,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":554.609,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So we can measure your podcast metrics.","index":144,"end_time":560.33,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":558.49,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So it is going to automatically pull in an update.","index":145,"end_time":564.01,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":561.13,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So I''ll show you what we have there.","index":146,"end_time":565.69,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":564.01,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"There''s only so much that we can really even see.","index":147,"end_time":570.09,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":567.21,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"That''s not what I''m looking for because it''s not measuring like per.","index":148,"end_time":576.89,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":570.41,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Per.","index":149,"end_time":577.49,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":577.13,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Like Apple per Spotify.","index":150,"end_time":579.25,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":577.49,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"It''s more of the episodes in Total Computer''s fighting me right now.","index":151,"end_time":589.05,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":579.25,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Give me one second.","index":152,"end_time":589.93,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":589.05,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"All right, so now up here, it''ll show total plays with a breakdown by episode.","index":153,"end_time":604.9,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":600.5,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Can you see this?","index":154,"end_time":612.66,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":611.86,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, yeah, sorry.","index":155,"end_time":613.9,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":613.06,"speaker_name":"Kate ThreatMark"},{"text":"And we can amend the time filter as well.","index":156,"end_time":616.26,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":613.9,"speaker_name":"Kate ThreatMark"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":157,"end_time":616.78,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":616.42,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So you can change the time filter.","index":158,"end_time":617.82,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":616.78,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I just have it set to all time for right now.","index":159,"end_time":619.62,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":617.82,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":160,"end_time":620.3,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":619.98,"speaker_name":"Kate ThreatMark"},{"text":"Oh, cool.","index":161,"end_time":621.18,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":620.46,"speaker_name":"Kate ThreatMark"},{"text":"Great.","index":162,"end_time":621.86,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":621.5,"speaker_name":"Kate ThreatMark"},{"text":"But this will flow through by title.","index":163,"end_time":623.74,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":621.86,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And how many plays by episode?","index":164,"end_time":625.5,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":623.82,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Is that something we could get into HubSpot?","index":165,"end_time":628.14,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":625.98,"speaker_name":"Greg"},{"text":"Somehow we can explore that.","index":166,"end_time":631.26,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":628.14,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I mean, if anything, we might just need to create, like, a Google sheet that automatically updates and it pulls from that or something like that.","index":167,"end_time":637.26,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":631.42,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, yeah.","index":168,"end_time":638.46,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":637.34,"speaker_name":"Greg"},{"text":"I mean, it''s not.","index":169,"end_time":639.7,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":638.78,"speaker_name":"Greg"},{"text":"It''s not priority, but it just would be good to get it consolidated.","index":170,"end_time":643.98,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":639.7,"speaker_name":"Greg"},{"text":"Yeah, I know.","index":171,"end_time":644.94,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":644.3,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I know.","index":172,"end_time":645.34,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":644.94,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"You''d like to have HubSpot as, like, the reporting hub, no pun intended.","index":173,"end_time":650.58,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":645.34,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"That''s cool, though, because then we can at least, like, take a snap of it that I can, like, work into the board meeting or something like that.","index":174,"end_time":663.54,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":656.42,"speaker_name":"Greg"},{"text":"Yeah, yeah.","index":175,"end_time":664.98,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":663.7,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"To give it some extra love.","index":176,"end_time":666.58,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":665.14,"speaker_name":"Greg"},{"text":"Love it.","index":177,"end_time":667.62,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":667.06,"speaker_name":"Greg"},{"text":"Absolutely.","index":178,"end_time":668.82,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":668.02,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Awesome.","index":179,"end_time":671.06,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":670.5,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So, Kate, that was all from your side?","index":180,"end_time":673.06,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":671.46,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":181,"end_time":674.3,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":674.1,"speaker_name":"Kate ThreatMark"},{"text":"And that looks great.","index":182,"end_time":675.06,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":674.3,"speaker_name":"Kate ThreatMark"},{"text":"All right.","index":183,"end_time":676.82,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":676.26,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Fantastic.","index":184,"end_time":677.7,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":676.9,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Awesome.","index":185,"end_time":679.38,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":678.74,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Well, Greg, safe travels.","index":186,"end_time":681.06,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":679.54,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And I''m the only one in this call that''s in America, and you guys hopefully are not getting hit with any snowstorms that I haven''t heard about, so enjoy the weekend.","index":187,"end_time":692.66,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":682.82,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"No stone here, and we''re done for the week, so.","index":188,"end_time":698.02,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":695.14,"speaker_name":"Greg"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":189,"end_time":699.02,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":698.66,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"There you go.","index":190,"end_time":699.62,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":699.02,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Good luck.","index":191,"end_time":701.38,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":700.74,"speaker_name":"Greg"},{"text":"Have an awesome weekend.","index":192,"end_time":703.42,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":702.18,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":193,"end_time":703.7,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":703.42,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Thank you, guys.","index":194,"end_time":704.32,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":703.7,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Thank you.","index":195,"end_time":705.03,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":704.71,"speaker_name":"Nina Belina"},{"text":"Bye.","index":196,"end_time":705.43,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":705.03,"speaker_name":"Nina Belina"},{"text":"Thanks, guys.","index":197,"end_time":706.39,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":705.59,"speaker_name":"Kate ThreatMark"},{"text":"Take care.","index":198,"end_time":707.27,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":706.71,"speaker_name":"Greg"}],"dateString":"2026-01-23T14:30:00.000Z","host_email":"colin.costigan@marketersindemand.com","meeting_link":"https://us02web.zoom.us/j/82473500654?pwd=jqVnFaqE5BkdHZDaIQiIfffyQ5zyYV.1","participants":["colin.costigan@marketersindemand.com,kate.burwood@threatmark.com,nina.belina@marketersindemand.com,gregory.smith@threatmark.com,greg.smith@threatmark.com,iulia.lungu@threatmark.com","kate.burwood@threatmark.com","nina.belina@market