  VALUES (
    'e50afe94-037e-49d6-8f2e-8c05ac7e3294',
    '2026-01-23 14:00:00+00',
    'fireflies',
    '01KF3KCYHH05TZQCCXM86V8C5M',
    'Data Assessment // MiD: Weekly Marketing Meeting',
    '{"Colin Costigan","MaximilianRabeler","Axel Völker","Axel Völker"}'::text[],
    2248,
    'https://us02web.zoom.us/j/86344108572?pwd=qdakcUFJbrjywReJlBZ3DxNLrBYqXb.1',
    '{"id":"01KF3KCYHH05TZQCCXM86V8C5M","title":"Data Assessment // MiD: Weekly Marketing Meeting","summary":{"notes":"## **Data Enrichment and Automation Tools**\n\nThe team has developed and compared two advanced tools to enrich contact data and identify gender, streamlining outreach accuracy.\n\n- **Axel Völker shared a new tool developed by a working student that uploads Excel files and enriches them by identifying gender with a confidence threshold set at 70%, batching 500 names in groups of 50 via Azure OpenAI service, delivering updated CSV files within a week** (07:06)  \n    - This local JavaScript/TypeScript tool integrates with an N8N workflow to automate the enrichment process end-to-end.  \n    - Colin Costigan confirmed a similar existing tool using Clay’s enrichment and OpenAI to enrich LinkedIn data and establish salutations.  \n    - The team plans to run a comparison by sharing files on their Teams channel for evaluation.  \n    - This approach aims to improve lead personalization and campaign effectiveness by ensuring higher data quality.  \n\n- **Colin Costigan demonstrated their N8N automation flow that integrates multiple tools such as Smart Lead for cold emails, HubSpot CRM for contact tracking, and OpenAI sentiment analysis to classify replies, all hosted on a self-managed server** (09:39)  \n    - The workflow processes webhooks for actions like email replies, opens, and unsubscribes, updating lead scores and notifying teams via Slack and email.  \n    - This setup reduces manual monitoring and speeds up response time while ensuring compliance by unsubscribing contacts automatically.  \n    - Colin noted the system has been stable for nearly a year with continuous automations running smoothly.  \n    - Axel expressed interest in deeper access and screen sharing is planned to onboard and transfer knowledge.  \n\n## **Lead Data Acquisition and Quality**\n\nThey prioritize Clay over ZoomInfo for lead data due to better accuracy and cost efficiency.\n\n- **Colin confirmed Clay provides superior and more up-to-date company and contact data than ZoomInfo, which they discontinued due to outdated information and high cost** (15:21)  \n    - Clay sources primarily from LinkedIn with enrichment from other signals like Google Maps and CRM data, enabling filtered searches by industry, revenue, and employee count.  \n    - The team uses OpenAI to normalize company names and classify leads into strong, possible, or poor fit categories for targeted outreach.  \n    - They run email address discovery waterfalls across multiple tools within Clay, halting once a valid email is found to optimize costs.  \n    - Cost-wise, Clay is significantly cheaper than ZoomInfo, strengthening their business case for switching fully.  \n\n- **Axel and Maximilian plan to review Clay’s data integration and licensing to replicate similar success in their region, emphasizing the importance of clean, current contact data for campaign ROI** (16:45)  \n    - They discussed the need for API integration and seamless data flow to maintain enriched and normalized records.  \n    - The superior data quality supports faster deal responses and improved lead targeting, directly impacting conversion rates.  \n\n## **Marketing Creative and Messaging Strategy**\n\nThe team is refining LinkedIn ad creatives and landing page messaging to improve engagement and conversion.\n\n- **Colin will share Figma files for LinkedIn ad creatives, pre-sized for platform requirements, enabling direct text edits and translation by Axel’s team** (19:52)  \n    - Ads consist of images linked to lead gen forms on LinkedIn, simplifying campaign setup.  \n    - This approach shortens time to market and ensures brand consistency across regions.  \n    - Axel requested details on LinkedIn’s technical ad specs to optimize future ad formats.  \n\n- **Feedback from Maximilian and Axel recommends adjusting landing page copy to reduce repetitive AI mentions upfront, given mixed market perceptions, while still highlighting AI capabilities in skill management sections to target relevant searches** (29:19)  \n    - They agreed AI should be mentioned but positioned carefully to avoid scaring potential users in Germany.  \n    - Emphasizing benefits like faster RFP responses, bench time reduction, and resource utilization optimization better addresses customer pain points.  \n    - Testimonials should feature well-known client company names instead of lesser-known smaller firms to boost credibility.  \n    - The team plans to experiment with rotating testimonials and company logos to test impact on trust and conversion.  \n\n## **Website Localization and Development Workflow**\n\nThe website supports bilingual content with a WordPress-based translation module, and new designs require redevelopment from Figma.\n\n- **Axel demonstrated the WordPress language switching interface that maintains separate English and German versions for pages, enabling direct translation edits within the CMS** (24:30)  \n    - This setup allows easy content updates but requires manual translation management, which the team will monitor for efficiency.  \n    - The current translation plugin or module details remain unclear but will be investigated further by Axel’s team.  \n\n- **Colin clarified that new website designs are created in Figma and then rebuilt by developers in WordPress, as Figma cannot export directly to WordPress-compatible code** (28:44)  \n    - This redevelopment ensures design fidelity but adds steps and requires developer resources.  \n    - Figma files will be shared to allow Axel’s team to work on translations and text updates before final integration.  \n    - The process aims to maintain quality and consistency while enabling localized content rollout.  \n\n## **Strategic Insights and Next Steps**\n\nThe discussion highlighted the need to balance AI messaging with customer concerns and improve operational collaboration.\n\n- **Maximilian and Axel emphasized the importance of leading with problem-solving messages such as speeding up deal responses and reducing bench time over generic AI buzzwords to better connect with target customers** (29:19)  \n    - They suggested positioning skill management and resource optimization as core AI-powered features in the middle or lower landing page sections to align with buyer intent.  \n    - Colin agreed, noting that LLMs use initial website text for indexing, so AI should be present but not overwhelming upfront.  \n\n- **The team agreed to schedule follow-up screen sharing sessions to review Clay integration, N8N workflows, and landing page translations, with Colin assigning Max and Axel these collaboration tasks for next week** (10:11)  \n    - This will ensure knowledge transfer, system transparency, and coordinated campaign execution.  \n    - Ongoing feedback loops are planned to refine messaging, data enrichment, and automation for measurable improvements in lead quality and response times.","outline":null,"keywords":["N8N Automation","Clay Enrichment","LinkedIn Ads","WordPress Translation","AI Marketing Copy","Gender Identification Tool"],"overview":"- **Data Enrichment Tools:** Team developed a tool that enriches 500 Excel contacts in groups of 50 via Azure OpenAI service.  \n- **N8N Automation:** A workflow integrates multiple tools for automated email responses, improving efficiency and ensuring compliance.  \n- **Lead Data Choice:** Clay outperforms ZoomInfo in data accuracy and cost, sourced mainly from LinkedIn.  \n- **Marketing Messaging:** Focus on problem-solving messages over AI buzzwords in ads and landing pages to engage customers better.  \n- **Website Development:** New designs from Figma are rebuilt in WordPress for better design fidelity, with a bilingual content management workflow.  \n- **Next Steps:** Schedule sessions for Clay integration reviews, N8N workflows, and landing page adjustments to enhance collaboration.","action_items":"\n**Axel Völker**\nSend updated N8N notebook files to Colin Costigan and Maximilian Rabeler for campaign comparison and review (09:30)\nCheck and verify WordPress translation plugin and confirm how multilingual versions are managed to advise on website translation implementation (25:00)\n\n**Colin Costigan**\nShare behind-the-scenes N8N workflow and campaign automation setup with Axel and Max; provide .fig Figma files for LinkedIn ads for translation purposes (09:39)\n\n**Maximilian Rabeler**\nCoordinate translation of LinkedIn ads within Figma directly, and work with Axel on landing page translation management (20:04)\n\n**Colin Costigan & Team**\nIncorporate landing page feedback including replacing testimonial company name with well-known references and optimize marketing copy to balance AI emphasis and client concerns about public perception (22:33)\n\n**All participants**\nSchedule and attend follow-up Teams call to finalize landing page text, translation workflow, and campaign automation refinements (36:58)\n"},"duration":37.470001220703125,"speakers":[{"id":0,"name":"Colin Costigan"},{"id":1,"name":"MaximilianRabeler"},{"id":2,"name":"Axel Völker"},{"id":3,"name":"Axel Völker"}],"sentences":[{"text":"It.","index":0,"end_time":204.64,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":204.4,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Good morning.","index":1,"end_time":246.25,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":245.77,"speaker_name":"MaximilianRabeler"},{"text":"It.","index":2,"end_time":255.7,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":255.46,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Hey.","index":3,"end_time":300.75,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":300.43,"speaker_name":"MaximilianRabeler"},{"text":"Hey.","index":4,"end_time":302.31,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":301.79,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"How''s it going?","index":5,"end_time":302.99,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":302.31,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, well.","index":6,"end_time":305.31,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":304.03,"speaker_name":"MaximilianRabeler"},{"text":"Yes, that was good.","index":7,"end_time":309,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":305.47,"speaker_name":"MaximilianRabeler"},{"text":"How is it on your site?","index":8,"end_time":311.64,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":310.2,"speaker_name":"MaximilianRabeler"},{"text":"Good.","index":9,"end_time":313.36,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":313,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We had a bank holiday on Monday, so our five day week got condensed into four, so just got to move faster on things, you know.","index":10,"end_time":323.32,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":313.36,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, that''s good.","index":11,"end_time":325.16,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":324.28,"speaker_name":"MaximilianRabeler"},{"text":"I mean we could also use some more bank how it is here.","index":12,"end_time":329.56,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":326.68,"speaker_name":"MaximilianRabeler"},{"text":"So that Hendrik declined, you know, if Axel still planning on joining.","index":13,"end_time":341.17,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":336.77,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So check his calendar.","index":14,"end_time":347.09,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":342.93,"speaker_name":"MaximilianRabeler"},{"text":"I don''t know.","index":15,"end_time":351.93,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":351.33,"speaker_name":"MaximilianRabeler"},{"text":"Also, my Zoom app is not accepting the link anymore.","index":16,"end_time":355.53,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":351.93,"speaker_name":"MaximilianRabeler"},{"text":"I always have to get in the ID and the password.","index":17,"end_time":358.25,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":355.53,"speaker_name":"MaximilianRabeler"},{"text":"I mean that''s not a.","index":18,"end_time":359.33,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":358.25,"speaker_name":"MaximilianRabeler"},{"text":"Not a big problem, but always takes one more minute.","index":19,"end_time":363.65,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":359.65,"speaker_name":"MaximilianRabeler"},{"text":"Yeah, I don''t know.","index":20,"end_time":383.33,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":381.65,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So you said you were having Zoom issues.","index":21,"end_time":384.93,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":383.33,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Max.","index":22,"end_time":388.86,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":388.46,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"I mean I can get into the meeting, but just with ID and.","index":23,"end_time":393.34,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":390.06,"speaker_name":"MaximilianRabeler"},{"text":"Oh, gotcha.","index":24,"end_time":394.94,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":394.14,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay.","index":25,"end_time":395.5,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":394.94,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Well maybe let''s.","index":26,"end_time":411.42,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":409.18,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Just dive into this and then when Axel joins we can answer any questions.","index":27,"end_time":417.03,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":413.91,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Oh, here he is.","index":28,"end_time":417.99,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":417.03,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Hi.","index":29,"end_time":426.71,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":426.23,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Sorry, but I just got the files with the gender and dissertation.","index":30,"end_time":435.03,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":426.79,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"We have a working student.","index":31,"end_time":437.35,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":435.03,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Actually not even a student.","index":32,"end_time":440.2,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":439.32,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"He''s still going to school and we gave him the task to develop a tool to upload an Excel file and then add the.","index":33,"end_time":448.76,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":440.2,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Identify the gender and add that.","index":34,"end_time":451.96,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":449.8,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"It''s pretty cool.","index":35,"end_time":452.84,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":451.96,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"He just sent me.","index":36,"end_time":453.56,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":452.84,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"He just showed it to me and that''s why I''m a bit late and like I got the file.","index":37,"end_time":457.64,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":453.56,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"So I''m not sure if you.","index":38,"end_time":458.68,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":457.64,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"I think you said you also have one but one now and we have a tool where you can actually generate that.","index":39,"end_time":464.68,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":458.76,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"So you can just upload any.","index":40,"end_time":466.12,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":464.76,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Any address or people list and will add the.","index":41,"end_time":472.73,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":467.21,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Identify the gender.","index":42,"end_time":474.09,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":472.89,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"So did he write a specific.","index":43,"end_time":476.33,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":475.05,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"You said he''s using Gemini or notebook.","index":44,"end_time":478.33,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":476.49,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, he''s actually.","index":45,"end_time":479.45,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":478.49,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"He''s done a.","index":46,"end_time":480.33,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":479.53,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"He did a lot of stuff.","index":47,"end_time":482.33,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":481.21,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Was kind of impressed.","index":48,"end_time":483.33,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":482.33,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"So he has like a little local.","index":49,"end_time":484.53,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":483.33,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Tool that he wrote and JavaScript TypeScript where he''s doing.","index":50,"end_time":488.45,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":484.53,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"He''s uploading it.","index":51,"end_time":489.33,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":488.45,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Then he has an Nathan is an 8N workflow that is he sending that file to and that is then doing.","index":52,"end_time":497.89,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":489.33,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"There''s batching it because it''s 500 or so.","index":53,"end_time":500.77,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":497.89,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"So he''s batching that into 50 names, sending them to OpenAI Azure, OpenAI service, getting it back, transforming that back into a CSV and adding it.","index":54,"end_time":513.57,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":501.25,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"So this is quite a few steps.","index":55,"end_time":515.81,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":513.57,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Yeah, he''s done that in a week.","index":56,"end_time":518.49,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":515.89,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"It''s pretty cool.","index":57,"end_time":519.05,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":518.49,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"It''s a nice little project.","index":58,"end_time":519.97,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":519.05,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"And so you basically he can now upload an Excel file and then you''ll get back the updated Excel file.","index":59,"end_time":529.47,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":521.63,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Awesome.","index":60,"end_time":530.43,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":529.87,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, we.","index":61,"end_time":531.23,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":530.59,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We had just kind of Built something similar using just Clay''s enrichment.","index":62,"end_time":535.39,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":531.39,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So using OpenAI to do research via the person''s LinkedIn profile and anything else that we''re able to enrich and establish the salutation.","index":63,"end_time":545.79,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":535.39,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"But I would be very interested to run this comparison.","index":64,"end_time":549.12,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":545.79,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"He''s actually getting back like a confidence level.","index":65,"end_time":551.84,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":549.28,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":66,"end_time":552.88,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":552.32,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"How likely.","index":67,"end_time":553.72,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":553.2,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"And then he can define a threshold.","index":68,"end_time":555.44,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":553.72,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Basically, he says not everything above 70% use it.","index":69,"end_time":560.64,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":556.24,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"And below that just leave it empty.","index":70,"end_time":562.56,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":560.64,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"And I can just drag the file and you can compare.","index":71,"end_time":566.64,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":562.72,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Yeah, that''d be great.","index":72,"end_time":567.72,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":566.96,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"If you just drop that in our teams channel.","index":73,"end_time":569.6,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":567.72,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, let me just download that.","index":74,"end_time":571.84,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":570,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":75,"end_time":573.32,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":572.96,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And I don''t know if we''ve ever shown you really, like, behind the scenes of what our N8N flow looks like for the campaign.","index":76,"end_time":577.76,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":573.32,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And now have you.","index":77,"end_time":580.37,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":579.81,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Can you share that?","index":78,"end_time":581.01,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":580.37,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Because I would also be interested in how you do the.","index":79,"end_time":584.29,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":581.01,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Yeah, yeah.","index":80,"end_time":585.53,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":584.61,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So if you can see my screen now, I have it pulled up.","index":81,"end_time":587.81,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":585.53,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So hold on.","index":82,"end_time":590.61,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":589.65,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Oh, it''s really big.","index":83,"end_time":593.81,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":592.69,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":84,"end_time":594.65,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":594.209,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"As you can see, it''s quite a lot of nodes, a lot of activities being tracked.","index":85,"end_time":598.57,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":594.65,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So starting up top.","index":86,"end_time":600.49,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":598.57,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Smart Lead is the tool that we use to send cold emails.","index":87,"end_time":603.25,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":600.49,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So that''s capturing a webhook for any event, such as an email reply.","index":88,"end_time":606.69,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":603.41,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Do we have access to that?","index":89,"end_time":608.42,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":607.58,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Max.","index":90,"end_time":608.7,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":608.42,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Do you have access to that or is it somewhere.","index":91,"end_time":611.1,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":608.7,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Yeah, I already talked to Colin for that.","index":92,"end_time":613.34,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":611.5,"speaker_name":"MaximilianRabeler"},{"text":"It''s a bit tricky because they have confidential data which we may not see.","index":93,"end_time":617.74,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":613.34,"speaker_name":"MaximilianRabeler"},{"text":"Okay.","index":94,"end_time":619.1,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":618.46,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"But we will.","index":95,"end_time":620.7,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":619.9,"speaker_name":"MaximilianRabeler"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":96,"end_time":622.18,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":621.74,"speaker_name":"MaximilianRabeler"},{"text":"Whether we have time today or otherwise.","index":97,"end_time":625.58,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":622.18,"speaker_name":"MaximilianRabeler"},{"text":"Next week we will do some screen sharing and you can show me what I may see.","index":98,"end_time":629.46,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":625.58,"speaker_name":"MaximilianRabeler"},{"text":"Yeah, that would be cool.","index":99,"end_time":630.7,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":629.46,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"What is it?","index":100,"end_time":631.62,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":631.1,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"So there''s different.","index":101,"end_time":632.18,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":631.62,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"So what''s the info?","index":102,"end_time":632.94,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":632.18,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"What''s the.","index":103,"end_time":633.42,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":632.94,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Oh, can you zoom in a bit?","index":104,"end_time":634.9,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":633.58,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Yeah, of course.","index":105,"end_time":635.82,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":634.9,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So this first is.","index":106,"end_time":637.22,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":636.38,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Everything that we do is based on webhooks from different tools, the tools that we always sign up for.","index":107,"end_time":640.94,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":637.22,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We look for open AIs and easy webhook access.","index":108,"end_time":644.38,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":640.94,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Then we define constant variables.","index":109,"end_time":646.9,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":645.26,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Sorry, go ahead.","index":110,"end_time":647.66,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":646.9,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So Smart Lead is.","index":111,"end_time":649.74,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":648.14,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Which one?","index":112,"end_time":650.46,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":649.74,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"What is it?","index":113,"end_time":651.26,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":650.54,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Smart Lead is for email sending.","index":114,"end_time":653.18,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":651.5,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So that''s.","index":115,"end_time":654.62,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":653.9,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"And it''s calling it on a reply or what''s the trigger?","index":116,"end_time":657.34,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":654.62,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"So, yeah, reply opens, unsubscribes, really anything.","index":117,"end_time":663.3,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":657.34,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"That''S basically a link in the mail that people click or what is it?","index":118,"end_time":666.22,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":663.3,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"So it''s.","index":119,"end_time":667.1,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":666.62,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"It''s Smart Lead has this already natively, like in their tracking.","index":120,"end_time":670.42,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":667.1,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We just have a webhook sending from smart lead to N8N to notify us.","index":121,"end_time":675.06,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":670.42,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"When any of those actions link or something in the mail.","index":122,"end_time":677.42,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":675.06,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":123,"end_time":678.02,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":677.58,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay.","index":124,"end_time":678.54,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":678.02,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Then we define Constant variables.","index":125,"end_time":680.38,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":678.62,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So in here it''s like we have our contract id who like your email in here to get notifications.","index":126,"end_time":686.3,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":680.38,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay.","index":127,"end_time":687.1,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":686.46,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Slack channels, things like that.","index":128,"end_time":688.78,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":687.26,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And then it basically goes through a switch so it understands what type of data is coming in right now.","index":129,"end_time":695.06,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":689.54,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Did someone unsubscribe?","index":130,"end_time":696.06,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":695.06,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Did someone reply?","index":131,"end_time":696.98,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":696.06,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"What am I being asked to do right now?","index":132,"end_time":700.18,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":698.1,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So I told you, we created a free instance in HubSpot just so we can track contacts.","index":133,"end_time":705.3,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":701.06,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So we update them with lead scoring and HubSpot track when we send the first email.","index":134,"end_time":711.22,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":705.86,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And all of that gets added in as notes.","index":135,"end_time":713.38,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":711.3,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"If someone replies to an email, it goes through OpenAI sentiment.","index":136,"end_time":717.5,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":714.18,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"What is the last one?","index":137,"end_time":718.22,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":717.5,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Is that the.","index":138,"end_time":718.75,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":718.22,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"That''s your note taking tool or what is that?","index":139,"end_time":721.46,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":718.82,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"This right here, this is just a Supabase.","index":140,"end_time":723.62,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":721.62,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So this is using a Supabase node.","index":141,"end_time":727.06,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":724.18,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Supabase is a postgres tool.","index":142,"end_time":730.22,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":727.62,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, exactly.","index":143,"end_time":730.98,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":730.22,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay, Here it goes through sentiment analysis to understand was it an out of office response that was sent automatically, did they respond negatively, did they respond positively?","index":144,"end_time":741.78,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":731.62,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Then updating the record based on that and notifying us in Slack and then you via email and we can update you via teams.","index":145,"end_time":748.82,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":741.94,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"That''s pretty cool.","index":146,"end_time":752.68,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":751.96,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":147,"end_time":753.56,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":753,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So all of that happening here and then even just, you know, if they do unsubscribe, it''ll unsubscribe them from all of our marketing communication so that we don''t run into any issues.","index":148,"end_time":763.64,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":753.96,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"If they respond out of Office, it''ll update that.","index":149,"end_time":766.28,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":763.96,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"What is it?","index":150,"end_time":769.08,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":768.52,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Because we''re using this free version currently for N8N.","index":151,"end_time":774.76,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":769.08,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"What is their pricing model?","index":152,"end_time":776.84,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":775.6,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Is it like per use or how to do.","index":153,"end_time":779.04,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":776.84,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"So we.","index":154,"end_time":779.6,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":779.04,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"It''s actually like based on.","index":155,"end_time":780.96,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":779.6,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We set up our own server, which means that you can run as many as you want.","index":156,"end_time":786.4,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":781.44,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"It''s open source.","index":157,"end_time":788.24,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":787.28,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Right.","index":158,"end_time":788.48,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":788.24,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"But you have to install it then somewhere.","index":159,"end_time":790.24,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":788.48,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":160,"end_time":790.84,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":790.48,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So if you set up your own server, I mean, you can basically run as much as you want and it''s.","index":161,"end_time":794.24,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":790.84,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Virtual hosted version, but you haven''t set it up yourself.","index":162,"end_time":798.2,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":794.8,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Okay.","index":163,"end_time":798.72,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":798.2,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":164,"end_time":799.36,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":798.88,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay.","index":165,"end_time":800.88,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":800.24,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"So we have the same thing from Factors.","index":166,"end_time":803.85,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":802.61,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"This is website de anonymization.","index":167,"end_time":805.33,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":803.85,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So you know when we''re sending people emails and we''re like, hey, we can see that people at your company are browsing the website, we can say, you know, beyond a reasonable doubt, it''s probably the person we sent this email to, they didn''t just randomly land on this specific page.","index":168,"end_time":818.29,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":806.13,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So updating them Factors also ties into LinkedIn advertising, where it can see not only who''s clicked on ads, but who has viewed ads.","index":169,"end_time":826.45,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":818.93,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So we use that to Update lead scoring as well.","index":170,"end_time":829.18,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":826.7,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Similar activity for Heyreach as Smart Lead.","index":171,"end_time":833.9,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":831.58,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So this is the LinkedIn messaging side of things.","index":172,"end_time":836.3,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":833.98,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So just catching webhooks for connections accepted or reply events.","index":173,"end_time":840.78,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":836.94,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay.","index":174,"end_time":842.14,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":841.5,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"And then HubSpot is just the free level, the CRM that we set up to hold so that we can just send you batch updates for Dynamics.","index":175,"end_time":850.22,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":842.3,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, that''s pretty cool.","index":176,"end_time":854.71,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":853.59,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"It is, yeah.","index":177,"end_time":856.59,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":855.75,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"This is.","index":178,"end_time":857.03,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":856.59,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We''re very, very happy with it.","index":179,"end_time":858.95,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":857.43,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We''re always looking for ways to improve it, though.","index":180,"end_time":860.95,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":858.95,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So you''re hosting that.","index":181,"end_time":863.15,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":862.15,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"So you have just a virtual machine somewhere where you installed it or.","index":182,"end_time":866.71,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":863.15,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":183,"end_time":867.67,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":867.11,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And is it like every once in a while you have to update it into a new version or is it.","index":184,"end_time":873.43,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":868.55,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"No, I mean, it''s been pretty.","index":185,"end_time":874.95,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":873.59,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Pretty smooth sailing since we set it up just probably little under a year ago.","index":186,"end_time":879.41,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":875.03,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay.","index":187,"end_time":880.77,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":880.13,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Yeah, we have a bunch of automations that run through that.","index":188,"end_time":884.93,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":882.85,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, there''s a lot of stuff that you.","index":189,"end_time":886.37,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":885.01,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"So I just played around with it a bit over the weekend and that''s why I gave it to the.","index":190,"end_time":891.65,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":886.93,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"To our intern here to test it.","index":191,"end_time":893.97,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":892.05,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"I think it''s.","index":192,"end_time":894.81,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":893.97,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"It''s has a lot of potential to do.","index":193,"end_time":896.73,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":894.81,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"It does.","index":194,"end_time":897.25,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":896.73,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And then, Max, I know you were asking about Clay, so we can certainly set up a additional time next week.","index":195,"end_time":902.85,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":897.97,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Clay is just a massive spreadsheet with enrichments already built into it.","index":196,"end_time":906.61,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":903.49,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So it starts by utilizing LinkedIn''s contact database.","index":197,"end_time":910.68,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":907.72,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We''re able to say, like, I want companies in this industry, this employee count, this revenue level, all of that.","index":198,"end_time":917.16,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":910.92,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"That is done.","index":199,"end_time":918.36,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":917.56,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And actually, I can show you this over.","index":200,"end_time":921.72,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":920.04,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Does that have like LinkedIn API or how do they get the data?","index":201,"end_time":925.08,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":921.8,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"They just have a partnership with LinkedIn.","index":202,"end_time":927.56,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":925.88,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay.","index":203,"end_time":928.76,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":928.12,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":204,"end_time":929.2,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":928.84,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So, but essentially you have to pay.","index":205,"end_time":930.64,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":929.2,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"For it then somehow, I guess.","index":206,"end_time":932.04,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":930.64,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Yeah, yeah, we pay for.","index":207,"end_time":933,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":932.04,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We pay for all of these contacts that we download.","index":208,"end_time":934.92,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":933,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And do they also have like.","index":209,"end_time":937.28,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":935.84,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Do they also have some partnership with Zoom Info or something?","index":210,"end_time":940.16,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":937.28,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Or do you need a Zoom Info license?","index":211,"end_time":942.4,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":940.16,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Yeah, you would need a separate Zoom Info license, but that is an available integration in here and you use them.","index":212,"end_time":948.68,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":942.4,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"You.","index":213,"end_time":948.96,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":948.68,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"We had Zoom Info until last year.","index":214,"end_time":950.84,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":948.96,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"But we didn''t find it like too.","index":215,"end_time":952.64,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":950.84,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Yeah, we found it for Europe.","index":216,"end_time":955.12,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":953.52,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"We actually found it to be updated less often than.","index":217,"end_time":958.4,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":956.08,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Than what we''re seeing in Clay.","index":218,"end_time":960,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":958.4,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So we would find, like, we would pull contacts and then we''d be emailing them and it''s like, oh, they changed jobs six months ago.","index":219,"end_time":966.13,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":960.73,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And then when we pull from Clay, that''s actually already updated.","index":220,"end_time":968.73,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":966.13,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So Clay is also providing the data or is that.","index":221,"end_time":972.17,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":969.69,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"You have to purchase.","index":222,"end_time":973.69,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":972.17,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"It''s Providing the data.","index":223,"end_time":975.37,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":974.25,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So like for example, we just go in and we say, I want to find companies.","index":224,"end_time":981.77,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":975.61,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And then you put in like parameters here.","index":225,"end_time":985.53,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":983.05,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"If I started a fresh search.","index":226,"end_time":986.89,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":985.53,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So you pick a, like a trigger to start from, I want to find companies.","index":227,"end_time":994.42,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":990.18,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And then you put it in all of your filters and parameters.","index":228,"end_time":997.42,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":994.74,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And you can see right here it''s live updating how many results it''s pulling.","index":229,"end_time":1000.74,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":997.42,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay, so they''re pulling that from different.","index":230,"end_time":1004.26,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1002.66,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Sources basically, or how do they.","index":231,"end_time":1005.86,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1004.26,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Yeah, it''s.","index":232,"end_time":1006.42,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1005.86,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"It''s mainly from LinkedIn initially and then you enrich through other sources or you can add through different sources as well.","index":233,"end_time":1012.5,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1006.42,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So we could upload a spreadsheet, we can have signals from your CRM, we can do Google Maps, we can do signals for new hires, things like that.","index":234,"end_time":1020.86,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1012.5,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And the data, and the data quality is okay.","index":235,"end_time":1022.98,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1020.86,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"So it''s better than zooming for you said.","index":236,"end_time":1024.7,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1022.98,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Yeah, it''s been stronger than zoom info pretty consistently.","index":237,"end_time":1027.26,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1024.78,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So are you using zooming info in addition to it for anything or is.","index":238,"end_time":1033.1,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1029.74,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"It just clear that you need now?","index":239,"end_time":1034.58,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1033.1,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, we''ve switched away from zoom info.","index":240,"end_time":1036.22,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1034.58,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, we also moved away.","index":241,"end_time":1038.06,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1036.46,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"So then we pull all these companies in, we normalize their names using OpenAI because sometimes they''ll have like a trademark symbol or something weird that really doesn''t need to be used in email.","index":242,"end_time":1047.1,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1038.7,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Clean our company description as well.","index":243,"end_time":1049.64,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1047.88,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Then we run a prompt to see if they''re a strong fit, a possible fit or a poor fit based on the plan that we have in place.","index":244,"end_time":1059.16,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1051.96,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And then from there for each user, you do that basically for each company and then also for each user.","index":245,"end_time":1065.16,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1060.68,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay, yeah, so then we pull and then we basically say you can go here and say I want to find people at these companies.","index":246,"end_time":1073.04,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1065.72,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And then you enter in like the job title, seniority locations, everything like that.","index":247,"end_time":1077.49,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1073.04,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"It then pulls automatically their first name, last name, job title, location, LinkedIn profile.","index":248,"end_time":1083.65,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1078.21,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And then from there we''ve enriched for salutation and we can enrich for their email address as well.","index":249,"end_time":1090.13,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1084.37,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So we can just go in here and type in like if you want to zoom info, you could do a direct integration here and enrich anything.","index":250,"end_time":1097.97,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1091.25,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"But you would need a zoom info.","index":251,"end_time":1100.53,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1099.17,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"License to do that, correct?","index":252,"end_time":1101.89,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1100.53,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":253,"end_time":1102.53,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1102.05,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So you can use a bunch of different tools.","index":254,"end_time":1104.77,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1102.53,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I mean there''s waterfalls that you can set up.","index":255,"end_time":1107.09,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1104.77,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So I can say you just need.","index":256,"end_time":1110.78,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1108.42,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"A CLAY license and you will get.","index":257,"end_time":1112.18,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1110.78,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Their address database with it.","index":258,"end_time":1113.9,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1112.18,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Exactly, yeah.","index":259,"end_time":1115.62,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1113.9,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So like I could set up a waterfall that''ll automatically go through like all of these 10 tools to find an email address and it''ll stop if it finds it before it gets to like step three or whatever.","index":260,"end_time":1124.34,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1115.62,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"What is there?","index":261,"end_time":1124.82,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1124.34,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Because zoom info, initially, when we first.","index":262,"end_time":1126.66,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1124.82,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Started with them, they were super expensive, but then they like decreased in price every year.","index":263,"end_time":1131.7,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1126.66,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Yeah, I know, it used to be crazy.","index":264,"end_time":1133.58,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1132.1,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"It used to be like $15,000 for three months and then they started changing their prices and then they went like a credit model and I think that''s what they were migrating to, like when we switched away from them.","index":265,"end_time":1144.88,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1133.58,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, but it''s clay.","index":266,"end_time":1147.4,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1145.28,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Is it.","index":267,"end_time":1147.72,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1147.4,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Is it like the same price range or is it much plays?","index":268,"end_time":1150.44,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1147.72,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Clay is much cheaper.","index":269,"end_time":1151.36,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1150.44,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Cheaper and better data.","index":270,"end_time":1153.44,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1151.76,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Interesting.","index":271,"end_time":1156.08,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1155.28,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Awesome.","index":272,"end_time":1157.68,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1157.04,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"But yeah, Max, we can certainly go through that whenever.","index":273,"end_time":1160.96,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1158.24,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So, yeah, if you could send over the notebook updates, that would be great.","index":274,"end_time":1164.28,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1161.28,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And then I saw your feedback axle on changing the copy here to identify new opportunities.","index":275,"end_time":1170.57,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1164.28,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So we''ve updated that in all of the designs.","index":276,"end_time":1172.65,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1170.57,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, because there was.","index":277,"end_time":1173.85,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1172.81,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Yeah, I mean, if people are on the bench, then you have already identified the people, basically.","index":278,"end_time":1178.25,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1174.01,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Yep.","index":279,"end_time":1179.13,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1178.57,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So that''s updated and I saw that you just left some feedback on the landing.","index":280,"end_time":1185.13,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1179.61,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Oh, yeah.","index":281,"end_time":1185.53,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1185.13,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"So there''s another question.","index":282,"end_time":1186.41,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1185.53,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Is that.","index":283,"end_time":1187.13,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1186.65,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Is that Figma or what''s your tool for creating the LinkedIn ads?","index":284,"end_time":1192.32,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1187.13,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Yeah, yeah.","index":285,"end_time":1193.11,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1192.71,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We do this in Figma so we can share a dot fig file with you.","index":286,"end_time":1195.63,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1193.11,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I think, Max, I shared that in our message.","index":287,"end_time":1197.67,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1195.63,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Because we still need to translate that and it''s probably easiest if we do that in figma directly without.","index":288,"end_time":1203.91,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1199.51,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Yeah, so I can package this up as a dot FIG file and share that with you.","index":289,"end_time":1207.55,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1204.55,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"That''s what I offered to max.","index":290,"end_time":1209.27,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1207.55,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And does Figma have.","index":291,"end_time":1211.75,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1210.39,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"What''s LinkedIn using?","index":292,"end_time":1213.07,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1212.07,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Is that just pictures or do they have their own special format for.","index":293,"end_time":1217.43,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1213.07,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"So we actually have in here, we already have the size.","index":294,"end_time":1221.54,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1217.83,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Everything''s already custom, so you just have to change the text.","index":295,"end_time":1224.1,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1221.54,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So we already have it built out for LinkedIn ad sizes and then the programmatic display ad sizes.","index":296,"end_time":1230.34,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1225.7,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"What is LinkedIn technical?","index":297,"end_time":1232.66,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1231.54,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Is that.","index":298,"end_time":1233.06,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1232.66,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Is that like what other.","index":299,"end_time":1234.58,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1233.06,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"So one of them is a 1200 by 627, the other is a 1080 by 1080 and then this is a 627 by 1200.","index":300,"end_time":1242.1,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1235.78,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"But is it just like pictures or is that like some HTML?","index":301,"end_time":1245.94,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1242.18,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Oh, yeah, these are.","index":302,"end_time":1247.55,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1246.83,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"These are.","index":303,"end_time":1248.11,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1247.55,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"These are display ads that open that will open up into lead generation forms.","index":304,"end_time":1252.31,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1248.19,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"On LinkedIn and you have to provide.","index":305,"end_time":1255.47,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1252.31,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Them with what was input on LinkedIn.","index":306,"end_time":1257.31,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1255.47,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"What, you upload that stuff somehow to LinkedIn or as maybe I''m confused, are.","index":307,"end_time":1263.15,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1257.31,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"You asking about how do you get.","index":308,"end_time":1264.39,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1263.15,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Those things into LinkedIn?","index":309,"end_time":1265.71,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1264.39,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"That''s the question.","index":310,"end_time":1269.07,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1268.43,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"So it''s only Images, basically.","index":311,"end_time":1270.51,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1269.07,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Okay.","index":312,"end_time":1271.27,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1270.91,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":313,"end_time":1271.47,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1271.27,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So we.","index":314,"end_time":1271.79,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1271.47,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Well, there''s several different components to creating a campaign.","index":315,"end_time":1274.27,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1271.79,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So we create.","index":316,"end_time":1275.07,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1274.35,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We''ll create a form on LinkedIn and we''ll upload these images and then we''ll upload the targeting for those are just images.","index":317,"end_time":1280.65,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1275.07,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So the sign up button you really just click on.","index":318,"end_time":1283.29,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1280.65,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Yeah, yeah, you can click anywhere.","index":319,"end_time":1284.53,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1283.29,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, it''s just a design principle.","index":320,"end_time":1286.65,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1284.53,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay.","index":321,"end_time":1286.93,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1286.65,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":322,"end_time":1287.29,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1286.93,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"All right.","index":323,"end_time":1288.33,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1287.77,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Okay.","index":324,"end_time":1289.69,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1289.13,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Yeah, we can share the dot Fig file.","index":325,"end_time":1291.41,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1289.85,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And then I saw that you left just some feedback recently on the landing page.","index":326,"end_time":1296.01,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1291.41,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, I have.","index":327,"end_time":1297.29,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1296.49,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Yeah, I had a few questions.","index":328,"end_time":1298.65,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1297.37,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Like the first one is watch how it works.","index":329,"end_time":1301.21,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1298.89,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Which video is that?","index":330,"end_time":1302.65,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1301.37,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Or is that.","index":331,"end_time":1303.13,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1302.65,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"What is that?","index":332,"end_time":1303.69,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1303.13,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"That''s the video that we''re working on right now.","index":333,"end_time":1305.61,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1303.85,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"It''s the same as as at the bottom.","index":334,"end_time"