ably as.","index":474,"end_time":1688.88,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1687.8,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"We can check what we have.","index":475,"end_time":1690.12,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1688.88,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"So you see also has here all dates.","index":476,"end_time":1695.56,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1690.12,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"I don''t know.","index":477,"end_time":1696.52,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1695.8,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"I mean.","index":478,"end_time":1699.04,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1698.6,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Yeah, over here now someone will be.","index":479,"end_time":1701.08,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1699.04,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Able to answer that.","index":480,"end_time":1703.48,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1701.08,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Yeah, I think we should.","index":481,"end_time":1706.28,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1705.48,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"All right, so you''re doing it in.","index":482,"end_time":1708.12,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1706.28,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Your own WordPress currently or you have some kind of design tool that''s doing it or how do you.","index":483,"end_time":1713,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1708.12,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"WordPress.","index":484,"end_time":1715.68,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1715.2,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Yeah, we''re building this in your WordPress because we''re not doing it on the US subdomain anymore.","index":485,"end_time":1720.24,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1715.68,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"But what we saw the pages, the.","index":486,"end_time":1723.24,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1720.64,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Designs we saw, they''re.","index":487,"end_time":1724.28,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1723.24,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"They''re not.","index":488,"end_time":1724.72,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1724.28,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Oh, we designed that in figma.","index":489,"end_time":1726.12,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1724.72,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, that''s all figma.","index":490,"end_time":1727.28,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1726.12,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"That was my question.","index":491,"end_time":1728.36,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1727.6,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":492,"end_time":1728.8,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1728.36,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"And can you export it from Figma directory or you have to redo that somehow in WordPress.","index":493,"end_time":1734.16,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1730.08,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Oh, our developers like redevelop it.","index":494,"end_time":1736.96,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1734.56,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Figma can export to like Webflow.","index":495,"end_time":1740.96,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1738.88,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"It doesn''t really have much else that it can export into for web development platform.","index":496,"end_time":1745.62,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1741.42,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay.","index":497,"end_time":1745.98,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1745.62,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"So they have to rebuild that somehow.","index":498,"end_time":1748.06,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1745.98,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Okay, good.","index":499,"end_time":1752.22,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1749.02,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"All right.","index":500,"end_time":1753.18,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1752.62,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Okay.","index":501,"end_time":1753.98,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1753.58,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So we''ll send over the FIG files and everything so we can get translations and then we''re pretty much good to go.","index":502,"end_time":1758.78,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1753.98,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Maybe I would have some points if you could open the landing page again.","index":503,"end_time":1764.06,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1759.42,"speaker_name":"MaximilianRabeler"},{"text":"So I tried to make comments, but somehow I got a toaster that something didn''t work, which is a great feedback from the website.","index":504,"end_time":1770.77,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1764.38,"speaker_name":"MaximilianRabeler"},{"text":"So first thing, I don''t know actually what your opinion is, but automated AI consulting operations, minimal business is I think a good catch line.","index":505,"end_time":1782.53,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1773.01,"speaker_name":"MaximilianRabeler"},{"text":"But then we already, in the first sentence we talked about AI.","index":506,"end_time":1786.53,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1782.53,"speaker_name":"MaximilianRabeler"},{"text":"I''m not sure whether that''s smart because first we know that in Germany AI is somehow still scary to many.","index":507,"end_time":1794.45,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1786.85,"speaker_name":"MaximilianRabeler"},{"text":"And also we have A lot of competition.","index":508,"end_time":1797.71,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1795.43,"speaker_name":"MaximilianRabeler"},{"text":"If you say we are an AI automation tool and most of our competition is not working.","index":509,"end_time":1804.39,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1797.71,"speaker_name":"MaximilianRabeler"},{"text":"So I think we have, we are building a more negative picture or image in the head of people reading this.","index":510,"end_time":1814.99,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1804.47,"speaker_name":"MaximilianRabeler"},{"text":"Potentially.","index":511,"end_time":1815.83,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1814.99,"speaker_name":"MaximilianRabeler"},{"text":"Yeah, it''s tricky because one thing.","index":512,"end_time":1821.12,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1817.03,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Yeah, I agree, everyone is AI now.","index":513,"end_time":1823.12,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1821.12,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"And everyone on every software tool on every web page.","index":514,"end_time":1828.4,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1823.12,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"You see, we are AI and AI first and whatever.","index":515,"end_time":1831.4,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1828.4,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"So I think it''s probably not the biggest differentiator.","index":516,"end_time":1835.48,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1831.4,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"But on the other hand, I think.","index":517,"end_time":1836.8,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1835.48,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Everyone is expecting tools to have AI features also.","index":518,"end_time":1841.44,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1836.8,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"And I''m not sure if people will assume that you have AI features if you don''t explicitly put it on your page.","index":519,"end_time":1850.97,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1841.84,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"It''s.","index":520,"end_time":1852.05,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1851.53,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"I, I don''t know what.","index":521,"end_time":1853.73,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1852.05,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"I think we have to have it.","index":522,"end_time":1854.69,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1853.73,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Somewhere that people know, okay, we have AI capabilities.","index":523,"end_time":1859.29,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1854.69,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"But I''m not sure how it''s not.","index":524,"end_time":1863.89,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1860.49,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"I mean it''s not in the header.","index":525,"end_time":1865.17,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1863.89,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"And it''s kind of small.","index":526,"end_time":1866.17,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1865.17,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"You have to, you have to read that admin versus AI command center.","index":527,"end_time":1872.25,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1866.17,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"So you, you don''t want to put it there though.","index":528,"end_time":1878.18,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1876.38,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"I think somewhere we have to have it.","index":529,"end_time":1879.46,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1878.18,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"We have to somehow say, okay, we.","index":530,"end_time":1880.74,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1879.46,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Have these cool AI features too.","index":531,"end_time":1882.46,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1880.74,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Yeah, but maybe, I mean with the place on the bottom where you have the skill management.","index":532,"end_time":1887.58,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1883.02,"speaker_name":"MaximilianRabeler"},{"text":"So where you have this ladder, you know.","index":533,"end_time":1890.14,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1887.98,"speaker_name":"MaximilianRabeler"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":534,"end_time":1892.78,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1892.38,"speaker_name":"MaximilianRabeler"},{"text":"And there we have centralized skill management and I mean our main AI focus is skills management and the inhibit and resource application.","index":535,"end_time":1900.46,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1892.78,"speaker_name":"MaximilianRabeler"},{"text":"Yeah, that would be a place where you, I mean, logically you would put it there.","index":536,"end_time":1906.63,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1901.91,"speaker_name":"MaximilianRabeler"},{"text":"I don''t know whether that''s too far down or not.","index":537,"end_time":1910.39,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1907.19,"speaker_name":"MaximilianRabeler"},{"text":"I just wanted to have a second opinion on putting it directly.","index":538,"end_time":1916.23,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1912.31,"speaker_name":"MaximilianRabeler"},{"text":"I think ii is somehow a must.","index":539,"end_time":1918.19,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1916.389,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Have and, and if it''s a must have, the question is should you lead.","index":540,"end_time":1923.51,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1918.19,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"With it or not?","index":541,"end_time":1924.39,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1923.51,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"And people probably will Google for it like what''s the best AI skill management solution or whatever.","index":542,"end_time":1931.92,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1925.27,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"So they should then find us.","index":543,"end_time":1934.04,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1932.72,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"But I''m, I don''t know Colin, what your, what your take is on that.","index":544,"end_time":1937.88,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1934.04,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Should you lead with it or should you.","index":545,"end_time":1939.6,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1937.88,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Yeah, it''s best to lead with it.","index":546,"end_time":1942.24,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1940.88,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Especially with the, the latest news around how AI like LLMs are reading websites because, you know, like ChatGPT will provide a source is through like the initial text on a page, like a summary almost is what it''s reading.","index":547,"end_time":1955.23,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1942.24,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So the initial text is very important for the LLMs.","index":548,"end_time":1957.59,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1955.23,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay, yeah, makes sense to me then.","index":549,"end_time":1962.07,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1958.15,"speaker_name":"MaximilianRabeler"},{"text":"Second point.","index":550,"end_time":1963.19,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1962.47,"speaker_name":"MaximilianRabeler"},{"text":"Can you scroll up a bit?","index":551,"end_time":1964.31,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1963.19,"speaker_name":"MaximilianRabeler"},{"text":"Yeah, so I mean the testimonial part you already had.","index":552,"end_time":1969.27,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1964.55,"speaker_name":"MaximilianRabeler"},{"text":"So yeah, here, remove the button X.","index":553,"end_time":1971.27,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1969.51,"speaker_name":"MaximilianRabeler"},{"text":"So I think the second text is really great here because in the bold it actually says okay, we want you like it talks to the person reading it.","index":554,"end_time":1982.42,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1971.75,"speaker_name":"MaximilianRabeler"},{"text":"So hey, you have a lot of bench time, you lose revenue, we increase that.","index":555,"end_time":1988.5,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1982.42,"speaker_name":"MaximilianRabeler"},{"text":"But the first and the third one are somehow a bit hanging in there.","index":556,"end_time":1992.78,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1988.82,"speaker_name":"MaximilianRabeler"},{"text":"So for the first one for example I think automate CVM proposal creation is somehow fine but I think the text below is better like respond to RFPS faster.","index":557,"end_time":2005.86,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1992.78,"speaker_name":"MaximilianRabeler"},{"text":"I don''t know if you need to say RFPs.","index":558,"end_time":2007.61,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2005.86,"speaker_name":"MaximilianRabeler"},{"text":"Peace.","index":559,"end_time":2008.24,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2007.84,"speaker_name":"MaximilianRabeler"},{"text":"I''m missing the English word.","index":560,"end_time":2010.48,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2009.28,"speaker_name":"MaximilianRabeler"},{"text":"I don''t know actually.","index":561,"end_time":2011.12,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2010.48,"speaker_name":"MaximilianRabeler"},{"text":"Yeah, that''s probably.","index":562,"end_time":2014,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2012.88,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"That''s.","index":563,"end_time":2014.6,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2014.16,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Yeah, that''s more or less an rfp.","index":564,"end_time":2016.96,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2014.6,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":565,"end_time":2017.92,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2017.52,"speaker_name":"MaximilianRabeler"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":566,"end_time":2018.28,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2017.92,"speaker_name":"MaximilianRabeler"},{"text":"I mean it''s not only public, that''s what I want to.","index":567,"end_time":2020.76,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2018.28,"speaker_name":"MaximilianRabeler"},{"text":"Yeah, it''s.","index":568,"end_time":2021.52,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2020.76,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"But these are not necessarily public.","index":569,"end_time":2023.519,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2021.52,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"They could be private also.","index":570,"end_time":2025.12,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2023.519,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Yeah, but respond faster and win more deals is somehow I think a better catch line because it people are not looking for tool for like I don''t know, for their research management is more than one tool.","index":571,"end_time":2040.81,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2025.6,"speaker_name":"MaximilianRabeler"},{"text":"But they tried to solve a problem or they know they have problem and then they find us by accident.","index":572,"end_time":2050.33,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2041.05,"speaker_name":"MaximilianRabeler"},{"text":"I don''t know.","index":573,"end_time":2051.05,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2050.33,"speaker_name":"MaximilianRabeler"},{"text":"Because they think we can solve it because that''s what we offer.","index":574,"end_time":2055.85,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2051.77,"speaker_name":"MaximilianRabeler"},{"text":"And yeah for the third one, I honestly I don''t know why what this is about get full project visibility.","index":575,"end_time":2066.07,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2056.81,"speaker_name":"MaximilianRabeler"},{"text":"I mean if I was a customer or a potential customer, I don''t.","index":576,"end_time":2073.67,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2067.75,"speaker_name":"MaximilianRabeler"},{"text":"Maybe it''s me, I don''t know.","index":577,"end_time":2077.51,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2076.07,"speaker_name":"MaximilianRabeler"},{"text":"The question is what is what?","index":578,"end_time":2080.67,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2079.43,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Which problem is it addressing?","index":579,"end_time":2082.15,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2080.67,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"It''s not really.","index":580,"end_time":2084.87,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2083.99,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"I mean if lack of transparency could be a problem but it''s somehow a bit of an indirect problem.","index":581,"end_time":2092.49,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2085.67,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"So we have switch this to more of like a skills matrices visibility.","index":582,"end_time":2098.09,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2094.33,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, maybe.","index":583,"end_time":2103.45,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2102.73,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"So we have the bench.","index":584,"end_time":2104.33,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2103.45,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Okay.","index":585,"end_time":2104.61,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2104.33,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"That''s a problem.","index":586,"end_time":2105.13,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2104.61,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"People on the bench.","index":587,"end_time":2106.089,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2105.21,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Then we have the response time and the effort for the proposals.","index":588,"end_time":2109.53,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2106.089,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"That''s a problem.","index":589,"end_time":2111.77,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2110.97,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"And we have.","index":590,"end_time":2113.45,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2112.49,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"I think it might be what we know for example from Natuvion is they came to us and what they really like is the central data management place for everything.","index":591,"end_time":2128.89,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2114.81,"speaker_name":"MaximilianRabeler"},{"text":"Like they have the not.","index":592,"end_time":2132.17,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2129.29,"speaker_name":"MaximilianRabeler"},{"text":"Not personal but all the other data about their people.","index":593,"end_time":2135.85,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2132.89,"speaker_name":"MaximilianRabeler"},{"text":"But what are you doing with what.","index":594,"end_time":2140.57,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2139.21,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"What problem is that solving?","index":595,"end_time":2141.77,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2140.57,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Finding people or.","index":596,"end_time":2143.13,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2141.85,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Yeah, I mean in the end it goes to respond faster obviously.","index":597,"end_time":2149.49,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2144.41,"speaker_name":"MaximilianRabeler"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":598,"end_time":2150.05,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2149.49,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Responding faster will also eliminate your bench if you''re doing it good.","index":599,"end_time":2154.77,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2151.41,"speaker_name":"MaximilianRabeler"},{"text":"So I mean there''s always some overlap.","index":600,"end_time":2158.37,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2154.85,"speaker_name":"MaximilianRabeler"},{"text":"Yes.","index":601,"end_time":2159.49,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2159.01,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Bench and the other.","index":602,"end_time":2160.69,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2159.65,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"So then maybe one could be resource like optimized utilization.","index":603,"end_time":2164.69,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2160.85,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"That is like stuff the right people buy skill.","index":604,"end_time":2168.69,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2164.77,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Don''t, don''t over so don''t stuff the senior on the junior position and stuff like that.","index":605,"end_time":2175.01,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2168.69,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Forecasting, maybe.","index":606,"end_time":2179.59,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2177.71,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"It''s also, I mean, we are talking about companies with, in best case, like, four digits and employee.","index":607,"end_time":2187.95,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2179.59,"speaker_name":"MaximilianRabeler"},{"text":"Employee size.","index":608,"end_time":2190.35,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2189.39,"speaker_name":"MaximilianRabeler"},{"text":"So I don''t know whether we should, like, give some word about APIs here.","index":609,"end_time":2196.51,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2190.83,"speaker_name":"MaximilianRabeler"},{"text":"APIs or skills.","index":610,"end_time":2198.35,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2197.07,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Maybe integrate perfectly.","index":611,"end_time":2200.27,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2198.35,"speaker_name":"MaximilianRabeler"},{"text":"Something that says that we can integrate perfectly, that they don''t have any, I don''t know, information does something.","index":612,"end_time":2207.26,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2200.67,"speaker_name":"MaximilianRabeler"},{"text":"Sorry, just real quick, I''m three minutes late to another meeting.","index":613,"end_time":2212.06,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2209.58,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Do you guys think.","index":614,"end_time":2213.82,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2213.1,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":615,"end_time":2214.66,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2214.3,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Maybe we can talk about this in teams?","index":616,"end_time":2216.06,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2214.66,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":617,"end_time":2217.02,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2216.7,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"We can discuss.","index":618,"end_time":2217.58,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2217.02,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Okay.","index":619,"end_time":2219.02,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2218.62,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I''m so sorry.","index":620,"end_time":2219.9,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2219.02,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I just have to go to that.","index":621,"end_time":2221.34,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2219.98,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"All right, Max, maybe we can have.","index":622,"end_time":2222.82,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2221.34,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"A quick call you on teams.","index":623,"end_time":2225.58,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2222.82,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Thank you both very much.","index":624,"end_time":2227.42,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2226.3,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Thanks.","index":625,"end_time":2227.98,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2227.5,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Bye.","index":626,"end_time":2228.38,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2227.98,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"All right, bye.","index":627,"end_time":2229.1,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2228.38,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"}],"dateString":"2026-01-23T14:00:00.000Z","host_email":"colin.costigan@marketersindemand.com","meeting_link":"https://us02web.zoom.us/j/86344108572?pwd=qdakcUFJbrjywReJlBZ3DxNLrBYqXb.1","participants":["tristan.pelligrino@marketersindemand.com,colin.costigan@marketersindemand.com,joachim.giesen@uni-jena.de,guille.santana@marketersindemand.com,nathalie.mintjens@marketersindemand.com,voelker@data-assessment.com,bebinger@decidalo.com,osbaldeston@data-assessment.com,pollex@data-assessment.com,rabeler@data-assessment.com","tristan.pelligrino@marketersindemand.com","joachim.giesen@uni-jena.de","guille.santana@marketersindemand.com","nathalie.mintjens@marketersindemand.com","voelker@data-assessment.com","bebinger@decidalo.com","osbaldeston@data-assessment.com","pollex@data-assessment.com","rabeler@data-assessment.com"],"transcript_url":"https://app.fireflies.ai/view/01KF3KCYHH05TZQCCXM86V8C5M","organizer_email":"colin.costigan@marketersindemand.com"}'::jsonb,
    '{"label":"positive","confidence":0.95,"bullets":["Highlighted successful rapid prototyping by a student intern using N8N and OpenAI integration.","Compared internal enrichment tools with Axel’s lightweight gender-detection workflow for better data handling.","Colin walked through their full N8N automation flow including Smart Lead, HubSpot, and Supabase integration.","Agreed to share Figma ad files to streamline localization and design translation workflows.","Aligned on SEO and copy positioning for AI features on the landing page for commercial clarity."],"highlights":[{"quote":"He''s done that in a week. It''s pretty cool. It''s a nice little project.","speaker":"Axel Völker"},{"quote":"We''re very, very happy with it. We''re always looking for ways to improve it.","speaker":"Colin Costigan"},{"quote":"Clay is much cheaper... and better data.","speaker":"Colin Costigan"}],"topics":["automation","ai","delivery","tooling","campaign","content"],"model":"openai/gpt-4-1106-preview","version":1,"generated_at":"2026-01-23T14:44:00Z"}'::jsonb,
    '{"fireflies_summary":{"notes":"## **Data Enrichment and Automation Tools**\n\nThe team has developed and compared two advanced tools to enrich contact data and identify gender, streamlining outreach accuracy.\n\n- **Axel Völker shared a new tool developed by a working student that uploads Excel files and enriches them by identifying gender with a confidence threshold set at 70%, batching 500 names in groups of 50 via Azure OpenAI service, delivering updated CSV files within a week** (07:06)  \n    - This local JavaScript/TypeScript tool integrates with an N8N workflow to automate the enrichment process end-to-end.  \n    - Colin Costigan confirmed a similar existing tool using Clay’s enrichment and OpenAI to enrich LinkedIn data and establish salutations.  \n    - The team plans to run a comparison by sharing files on their Teams channel for evaluation.  \n    - This approach aims to improve lead personalization and campaign effectiveness by ensuring higher data quality.  \n\n- **Colin Costigan demonstrated their N8N automation flow that integrates multiple tools such as Smart Lead for cold emails, HubSpot CRM for contact tracking, and OpenAI sentiment analysis to classify replies, all hosted on a self-managed server** (09:39)  \n    - The workflow processes webhooks for actions like email replies, opens, and unsubscribes, updating lead scores and notifying teams via Slack and email.  \n    - This setup reduces manual monitoring and speeds up response time while ensuring compliance by unsubscribing contacts automatically.  \n    - Colin noted the system has been stable for nearly a year with continuous automations running smoothly.  \n    - Axel expressed interest in deeper access and screen sharing is planned to onboard and transfer knowledge.  \n\n## **Lead Data Acquisition and Quality**\n\nThey prioritize Clay over ZoomInfo for lead data due to better accuracy and cost efficiency.\n\n- **Colin confirmed Clay provides superior and more up-to-date company and contact data than ZoomInfo, which they discontinued due to outdated information and high cost** (15:21)  \n    - Clay sources primarily from LinkedIn with enrichment from other signals like Google Maps and CRM data, enabling filtered searches by industry, revenue, and employee count.  \n    - The team uses OpenAI to normalize company names and classify leads into strong, possible, or poor fit categories for targeted outreach.  \n    - They run email address discovery waterfalls across multiple tools within Clay, halting once a valid email is found to optimize costs.  \n    - Cost-wise, Clay is significantly cheaper than ZoomInfo, strengthening their business case for switching fully.  \n\n- **Axel and Maximilian plan to review Clay’s data integration and licensing to replicate similar success in their region, emphasizing the importance of clean, current contact data for campaign ROI** (16:45)  \n    - They discussed the need for API integration and seamless data flow to maintain enriched and normalized records.  \n    - The superior data quality supports faster deal responses and improved lead targeting, directly impacting conversion rates.  \n\n## **Marketing Creative and Messaging Strategy**\n\nThe team is refining LinkedIn ad creatives and landing page messaging to improve engagement and conversion.\n\n- **Colin will share Figma files for LinkedIn ad creatives, pre-sized for platform requirements, enabling direct text edits and translation by Axel’s team** (19:52)  \n    - Ads consist of images linked to lead gen forms on LinkedIn, simplifying campaign setup.  \n    - This approach shortens time to market and ensures brand consistency across regions.  \n    - Axel requested details on LinkedIn’s technical ad specs to optimize future ad formats.  \n\n- **Feedback from Maximilian and Axel recommends adjusting landing page copy to reduce repetitive AI mentions upfront, given mixed market perceptions, while still highlighting AI capabilities in skill management sections to target relevant searches** (29:19)  \n    - They agreed AI should be mentioned but positioned carefully to avoid scaring potential users in Germany.  \n    - Emphasizing benefits like faster RFP responses, bench time reduction, and resource utilization optimization better addresses customer pain points.  \n    - Testimonials should feature well-known client company names instead of lesser-known smaller firms to boost credibility.  \n    - The team plans to experiment with rotating testimonials and company logos to test impact on trust and conversion.  \n\n## **Website Localization and Development Workflow**\n\nThe website supports bilingual content with a WordPress-based translation module, and new designs require redevelopment from Figma.\n\n- **Axel demonstrated the WordPress language switching interface that maintains separate English and German versions for pages, enabling direct translation edits within the CMS** (24:30)  \n    - This setup allows easy content updates but requires manual translation management, which the team will monitor for efficiency.  \n    - The current translation plugin or module details remain unclear but will be investigated further by Axel’s team.  \n\n- **Colin clarified that new website designs are created in Figma and then rebuilt by developers in WordPress, as Figma cannot export directly to WordPress-compatible code** (28:44)  \n    - This redevelopment ensures design fidelity but adds steps and requires developer resources.  \n    - Figma files will be shared to allow Axel’s team to work on translations and text updates before final integration.  \n    - The process aims to maintain quality and consistency while enabling localized content rollout.  \n\n## **Strategic Insights and Next Steps**\n\nThe discussion highlighted the need to balance AI messaging with customer concerns and improve operational collaboration.\n\n- **Maximilian and Axel emphasized the importance of leading with problem-solving messages such as speeding up deal responses and reducing bench time over generic AI buzzwords to better connect with target customers** (29:19)  \n    - They suggested positioning skill management and resource optimization as core AI-powered features in the middle or lower landing page sections to align with buyer intent.  \n    - Colin agreed, noting that LLMs use initial website text for indexing, so AI should be present but not overwhelming upfront.  \n\n- **The team agreed to schedule follow-up screen sharing sessions to review Clay integration, N8N workflows, and landing page translations, with Colin assigning Max and Axel these collaboration tasks for next week** (10:11)  \n    - This will ensure knowledge transfer, system transparency, and coordinated campaign execution.  \n    - Ongoing feedback loops are planned to refine messaging, data enrichment, and automation for measurable improvements in lead quality and response times.","outline":null,"keywords":["N8N Automation","Clay Enrichment","LinkedIn Ads","WordPress Translation","AI Marketing Copy","Gender Identification Tool"],"overview":"- **Data Enrichment Tools:** Team developed a tool that enriches 500 Excel contacts in groups of 50 via Azure OpenAI service.  \n- **N8N Automation:** A workflow integrates multiple tools for automated email responses, improving efficiency and ensuring compliance.  \n- **Lead Data Choice:** Clay outperforms ZoomInfo in data accuracy and cost, sourced mainly from LinkedIn.  \n- **Marketing Messaging:** Focus on problem-solving messages over AI buzzwords in ads and landing pages to engage customers better.  \n- **Website Development:** New designs from Figma are rebuilt in WordPress for better design fidelity, with a bilingual content management workflow.  \n- **Next Steps:** Schedule sessions for Clay integration reviews, N8N workflows, and landing page adjustments to enhance collaboration.","action_items":"\n**Axel Völker**\nSend updated N8N notebook files to Colin Costigan and Maximilian Rabeler for campaign comparison and review (09:30)\nCheck and verify WordPress translation plugin and confirm how multilingual versions are managed to advise on website translation implementation (25:00)\n\n**Colin Costigan**\nShare behind-the-scenes N8N workflow and campaign automation setup with Axel and Max; provide .fig Figma files for LinkedIn ads for translation purposes (09:39)\n\n**Maximilian Rabeler**\nCoordinate translation of LinkedIn ads within Figma directly, and work with Axel on landing page translation management (20:04)\n\n**Colin Costigan & Team**\nIncorporate landing page feedback including replacing testimonial company name with well-known references and optimize marketing copy to balance AI emphasis and client concerns about public perception (22:33)\n\n**All participants**\nSchedule and attend follow-up Teams call to finalize landing page text, translation workflow, and campaign automation refinements (36:58)\n"},"migrated_from":"contract_meetings","original_id":"cc29ef02-0650-47ff-b8a1-50c894c14744","master_marketer":{"status":"migrated"}}'::jsonb,
