    '{"id":"01KFH33KZBCWTB4Q0QP5MQN8H9","title":"Baylee Gunnell and Josh","summary":{"notes":"## **Content and Podcast Performance**\n\nThe team confirmed strong growth in podcast engagement driven by select episodes and planned content rollouts.\n\n- **Episode 15 with Rajiv emerged as the top performer** with most downloads from Apple Podcasts and early traction on YouTube and Spotify, signaling cross-platform interest (01:00)  \n    - Episodes 13 and 14 continue to deliver steady daily downloads, showing consistent listener retention  \n    - Paula shared that the **2025 podcast recap blog is scheduled for release next Thursday**, marking an aligned content push  \n    - This steady performance supports continued investment in podcast content to grow audience reach and engagement  \n\n- **A system for monitoring and responding to public podcast reviews was agreed upon**, focusing on capturing listener feedback across Apple, Spotify, and YouTube (02:47)  \n    - Josh emphasized tracking the impact of calls to action on review volume as a key success metric  \n    - Baylee confirmed the team will flag new feedback weekly during syncs and notify Josh for timely responses  \n    - This approach aims to maintain close audience engagement and quickly address potential concerns or praise  \n\n## **Video Production and Quality Control**\n\nVideo content production is in early stages with clear challenges in quality and workflow that require process improvements to meet deadlines.\n\n- **Josh flagged initial video cuts as rough and expressed concern about meeting timelines due to resource constraints** (04:41)  \n    - The current first cut animation takes about **40 hours**, indicating high effort per version and the need for efficient iteration  \n    - Josh requested better internal review and alignment before videos reach him to avoid bottlenecks and reduce his review load  \n    - Baylee acknowledged her recent absence limited prior reviews but committed to more active internal vetting moving forward  \n    - Prioritizing the **platform overview video over the on-the-job training video** was requested to alleviate immediate pressure  \n\n- **Specific feedback focused on video length, animation style, and visual consistency to improve viewer experience** (07:32)  \n    - Josh noted the need to keep videos near the **three-minute mark** for engagement and pacing  \n    - He requested more subtle animations for product menus, avoiding bouncing effects to maintain a professional look  \n    - Repetitive stock footage should be minimized to keep visuals fresh and relevant  \n    - This detailed feedback will inform internal revisions before Josh’s review to streamline approval  \n\n## **Outreach Campaign Success and Pipeline Development**\n\nThe outreach campaign is generating promising leads with active engagement from potential podcast guests.\n\n- **Two positive responses were received on LinkedIn from podcast guest prospects, with scheduling links already sent** (04:00)  \n    - This indicates that outreach messaging and targeting are effectively driving interest in joining the podcast  \n    - Continued follow-up will confirm conversion of these leads into booked episodes, supporting content growth  \n    - Paula is managing the scheduling process to ensure timely coordination without burdening Josh  \n\n## **Process Improvements for Content Review and Feedback**\n\nThe team agreed on refining internal workflows to reduce delays and improve content quality before executive review.\n\n- **Josh proposed creating a “mind meld” process to align expectations and anticipate his feedback early in video production** (06:28)  \n    - This would involve Baylee and Paula identifying big-picture issues internally before videos reach Josh  \n    - The goal is to reduce his review burden as his availability declines due to new product launches and client visits  \n    - Baylee committed to watching videos and adding notes during her catch-up to support this process  \n    - This approach balances quality control with realistic resource constraints to keep production moving smoothly  \n\n## **Timeline and Prioritization for Upcoming Deliverables**\n\nClear priorities and timelines were set to focus resources on highest-impact content pieces to meet business needs.\n\n- **The product cover video is targeted for first cut completion “very soon,” with the on-the-job training video deprioritized temporarily** (10:11)  \n    - This decision reflects Josh’s need to prioritize content that can reduce pressure and support product launches  \n    - Paula confirmed readiness to proceed with this schedule, aligning team efforts on critical assets  \n    - The timeline supports the broader goal of having polished product videos ready to support upcoming sales and training activities  \n    - This prioritization also guides resource allocation and sets expectations for feedback cycles going forward","outline":null,"keywords":["podcast performance","video review process","outreach campaign","animation timing","listener feedback","priority video production"],"overview":"- **Podcast Growth:** Episode 15 with Rajiv is top performer, driving engagement across Apple Podcasts, YouTube, and Spotify.\n\n- **Listener Feedback System:** New system to monitor podcast reviews agreed; captures feedback weekly to improve audience engagement.\n\n- **Video Production Challenges:** Initial video cuts face quality issues; need faster iterations as first cuts take 40 hours each.\n\n- **Outreach Success:** Positive LinkedIn responses from podcast guests; scheduling underway to convert leads into booked episodes.\n\n- **Workflow Improvement:** Proposed \"mind meld\" process to enhance video feedback, reducing Josh''s review burden during high-pressure periods.\n\n- **Content Prioritization:** Product cover video prioritized for completion soon, on-the-job training video temporarily deprioritized to support launches.","action_items":"\n**Josh Santo**\nReview the mid-roll section Frame link and provide feedback (02:14)\nWatch the full OTG training video and give detailed comments (04:41)\nCollaborate with Baylee and Paula to create a process for earlier internal review before videos are sent to him (06:28)\nPrioritize detailed review and feedback on the platform overview video (09:46)\n\n**Baylee Gunnell**\nReview the OTG training video despite recent absence and add internal feedback before next iteration (09:31)\nWork with Paula to incorporate general standards and feedback cues to streamline video review process with Josh (06:28)\n\n**Paula Ocampo**\nContinue monitoring podcast reviews on all platforms and report flagged listener feedback in weekly syncs (02:47)\nFollow-up on outreach campaign LinkedIn responses and coordinate podcast guest scheduling (04:00)\nPrepare for imminent rollout of product cover video first cut (10:11)\n"},"duration":11.130000114440918,"speakers":[{"id":0,"name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"id":1,"name":"Josh Santo"},{"id":2,"name":"Paula Ocampo"}],"sentences":[{"text":"Been a.","index":0,"end_time":0.88,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":0.08,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"A very crazy week.","index":1,"end_time":2.32,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":0.96,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Yeah, like on site kickoff, all that stuff.","index":2,"end_time":6.56,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2.8,"speaker_name":"Josh Santo"},{"text":"Is this like with a new client?","index":3,"end_time":8.96,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":7.12,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"No.","index":4,"end_time":10.64,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":10.24,"speaker_name":"Josh Santo"},{"text":"So part of it was with a new client and then this is like company.","index":5,"end_time":14.4,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":10.64,"speaker_name":"Josh Santo"},{"text":"Rah, rah.","index":6,"end_time":16.16,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":15.44,"speaker_name":"Josh Santo"},{"text":"Kickoff.","index":7,"end_time":16.88,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":16.16,"speaker_name":"Josh Santo"},{"text":"Okay.","index":8,"end_time":18.16,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":17.6,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":9,"end_time":19.52,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":19.04,"speaker_name":"Josh Santo"},{"text":"How are y''?","index":10,"end_time":20.28,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":19.68,"speaker_name":"Josh Santo"},{"text":"All?","index":11,"end_time":20.48,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":20.28,"speaker_name":"Josh Santo"},{"text":"Yeah, doing good.","index":12,"end_time":23.12,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":21.92,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"I just got back from vacation, so.","index":13,"end_time":25.72,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":23.36,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Oh, yeah, I went.","index":14,"end_time":28.42,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":25.72,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"We drove up the Pacific Coast.","index":15,"end_time":30.42,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":28.5,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Nice.","index":16,"end_time":31.46,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":30.98,"speaker_name":"Josh Santo"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":17,"end_time":32.34,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":31.86,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"How cool.","index":18,"end_time":33.22,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":32.42,"speaker_name":"Paula Ocampo"},{"text":"Nice to unplug for a little bit.","index":19,"end_time":35.06,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":33.38,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"It was very pretty always.","index":20,"end_time":36.9,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":35.06,"speaker_name":"Josh Santo"},{"text":"That''s great.","index":21,"end_time":38.9,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":38.26,"speaker_name":"Josh Santo"},{"text":"How are you father?","index":22,"end_time":40.42,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":39.54,"speaker_name":"Josh Santo"},{"text":"Doing great.","index":23,"end_time":41.74,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":41.14,"speaker_name":"Josh Santo"},{"text":"Doing great, thank you.","index":24,"end_time":43.22,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":41.74,"speaker_name":"Paula Ocampo"},{"text":"Good.","index":25,"end_time":44.1,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":43.7,"speaker_name":"Josh Santo"},{"text":"Awesome.","index":26,"end_time":45.7,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":45.06,"speaker_name":"Paula Ocampo"},{"text":"So I''m gonna start sharing my screen.","index":27,"end_time":48.42,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":46.34,"speaker_name":"Paula Ocampo"},{"text":"Okay.","index":28,"end_time":49.38,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":48.82,"speaker_name":"Josh Santo"},{"text":"So for today we have some content updates.","index":29,"end_time":63.23,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":60.11,"speaker_name":"Paula Ocampo"},{"text":"Also we''re gonna go on some podcast stuff that you requested me last week.","index":30,"end_time":70.27,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":63.87,"speaker_name":"Paula Ocampo"},{"text":"Also we want to talk about the review section, the outreach campaign, and also go through the videos.","index":31,"end_time":79.07,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":70.99,"speaker_name":"Paula Ocampo"},{"text":"So starting with content updates, since where there are current episodes, we have Already shared the 2025 podcast recap blog with Sydney and I think it''s already scheduled to go out next week, next Thursday.","index":32,"end_time":95.89,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":80.37,"speaker_name":"Paula Ocampo"},{"text":"So that''s all complete.","index":33,"end_time":98.05,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":96.21,"speaker_name":"Paula Ocampo"},{"text":"Then we have some podcast stats.","index":34,"end_time":103.17,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":100.85,"speaker_name":"Paula Ocampo"},{"text":"So I have here the latest three episodes.","index":35,"end_time":106.61,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":103.41,"speaker_name":"Paula Ocampo"},{"text":"The episode 15 with Rajiv is the strongest performer so far with most of the downloads coming from Apple podcast and some early traction on YouTube and Spotify.","index":36,"end_time":119.32,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":107.08,"speaker_name":"Paula Ocampo"},{"text":"Episode 13 and 14 are performing daily as well.","index":37,"end_time":124.12,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":119.56,"speaker_name":"Paula Ocampo"},{"text":"So we''re going there.","index":38,"end_time":127.32,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":124.36,"speaker_name":"Paula Ocampo"},{"text":"One sec.","index":39,"end_time":132.44,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":131.8,"speaker_name":"Josh Santo"},{"text":"Okay, so now moving into the review section, I have shared a frame link with Water team created for the mid roll section for the show.","index":40,"end_time":145.34,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":134.7,"speaker_name":"Paula Ocampo"},{"text":"I don''t know if you had a chance to review it, if you have any feedback.","index":41,"end_time":149.26,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":145.34,"speaker_name":"Paula Ocampo"},{"text":"I haven''t taken a look yet.","index":42,"end_time":152.7,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":150.94,"speaker_name":"Josh Santo"},{"text":"Okay.","index":43,"end_time":154.14,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":153.5,"speaker_name":"Paula Ocampo"},{"text":"Okay, that''s good.","index":44,"end_time":155.42,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":154.38,"speaker_name":"Paula Ocampo"},{"text":"No worries.","index":45,"end_time":155.86,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":155.42,"speaker_name":"Paula Ocampo"},{"text":"I know you have a crazy week, so when you have time, just let us know.","index":46,"end_time":159.5,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":155.86,"speaker_name":"Paula Ocampo"},{"text":"What are your thoughts on that?","index":47,"end_time":161.42,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":160.14,"speaker_name":"Paula Ocampo"},{"text":"Will do.","index":48,"end_time":163.26,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":162.62,"speaker_name":"Josh Santo"},{"text":"Perfect.","index":49,"end_time":164.78,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":164.3,"speaker_name":"Josh Santo"},{"text":"And then I know you mentioned about some of the podcast review that you wanna just have like some performance review.","index":50,"end_time":179.9,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":167.34,"speaker_name":"Paula Ocampo"},{"text":"So with Bailey, we discuss this internally and we believe the best way to do it is like each way.","index":51,"end_time":185.86,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":180.3,"speaker_name":"Paula Ocampo"},{"text":"We can monitor public reviews across platforms, across Apple, podcasts, Spotify, YouTube, and we can flag any new listener feedback and share with you during our weekly sync.","index":52,"end_time":197.91,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":185.86,"speaker_name":"Paula Ocampo"},{"text":"And of course, if a response is needed, we''ll let you know.","index":53,"end_time":201.35,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":198.31,"speaker_name":"Paula Ocampo"},{"text":"So you can handle it and reply right away or.","index":54,"end_time":206.23,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":201.51,"speaker_name":"Paula Ocampo"},{"text":"Okay, so.","index":55,"end_time":207.51,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":206.63,"speaker_name":"Paula Ocampo"},{"text":"Yeah, that''s great.","index":56,"end_time":210.39,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":207.99,"speaker_name":"Paula Ocampo"},{"text":"I don''t know, Eli, if you want to something about this.","index":57,"end_time":213.59,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":210.39,"speaker_name":"Paula Ocampo"},{"text":"No, I think you nailed it.","index":58,"end_time":215.96,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":214.96,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"But does that sound okay to you, Josh?","index":59,"end_time":217.92,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":215.96,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":60,"end_time":219.76,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":219.28,"speaker_name":"Josh Santo"},{"text":"The big thing I want to see is if there''s any impact from the call to action for reviews.","index":61,"end_time":225.84,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":219.76,"speaker_name":"Josh Santo"},{"text":"So I''m just going to assume that if we start Seeing reviews after putting it in there, that kind of thing.","index":62,"end_time":233.52,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":226.72,"speaker_name":"Josh Santo"},{"text":"Yeah, that''s the goal.","index":63,"end_time":236,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":234.24,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"So now moving into outreach campaign.","index":64,"end_time":242.97,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":240.97,"speaker_name":"Paula Ocampo"},{"text":"The campaigns are performing great.","index":65,"end_time":245.21,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":243.61,"speaker_name":"Paula Ocampo"},{"text":"We actually received today two responses from LinkedIn and they are really interesting on joining the podcast.","index":66,"end_time":254.09,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":246.09,"speaker_name":"Paula Ocampo"},{"text":"So I already send the schedule link.","index":67,"end_time":256.33,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":254.17,"speaker_name":"Paula Ocampo"},{"text":"These are their names.","index":68,"end_time":258.09,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":257.05,"speaker_name":"Paula Ocampo"},{"text":"So we''ll see if they schedule something with you to be part of the podcast.","index":69,"end_time":262.25,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":258.09,"speaker_name":"Paula Ocampo"},{"text":"But he''s doing great in both platforms right now.","index":70,"end_time":269.54,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":262.33,"speaker_name":"Paula Ocampo"},{"text":"I know you mentioned that you have some feedback about the latest video that I send you, the one for OTG training video.","index":71,"end_time":276.98,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":269.94,"speaker_name":"Paula Ocampo"},{"text":"So, yeah, I don''t know if you want to share your feedback.","index":72,"end_time":280.02,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":277.46,"speaker_name":"Paula Ocampo"},{"text":"What are your.","index":73,"end_time":281.06,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":280.34,"speaker_name":"Paula Ocampo"},{"text":"So far I haven''t been able to watch the whole thing.","index":74,"end_time":284.74,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":281.3,"speaker_name":"Josh Santo"},{"text":"I''ve only gone about maybe halfway, so I''m going to have to look at it hopefully tomorrow.","index":75,"end_time":294.35,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":284.98,"speaker_name":"Josh Santo"},{"text":"But initial impressions are it''s rough and that we''re probably not going to hit like it''s gonna.","index":76,"end_time":307.15,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":294.67,"speaker_name":"Josh Santo"},{"text":"I don''t see it happening.","index":77,"end_time":308.91,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":307.87,"speaker_name":"Josh Santo"},{"text":"I don''t see any of the videos being finished anytime soon.","index":78,"end_time":313.23,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":308.91,"speaker_name":"Josh Santo"},{"text":"So, you know, that''s, it''s kind of like it is what it is.","index":79,"end_time":319.1,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":315.87,"speaker_name":"Josh Santo"},{"text":"Iteration is needed.","index":80,"end_time":320.46,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":319.26,"speaker_name":"Josh Santo"},{"text":"But just in the, in the first kind of minute where I was watching, I did find myself wondering is like, who, who on your side is, is looking at this before it comes to me?","index":81,"end_time":334.54,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":321.34,"speaker_name":"Josh Santo"},{"text":"Is it.","index":82,"end_time":334.94,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":334.54,"speaker_name":"Josh Santo"},{"text":"You get it from the editors and then share it?","index":83,"end_time":337.9,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":334.94,"speaker_name":"Josh Santo"},{"text":"Do you two look at it?","index":84,"end_time":339.62,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":338.22,"speaker_name":"Josh Santo"},{"text":"Is there someone directing?","index":85,"end_time":341.26,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":339.62,"speaker_name":"Josh Santo"},{"text":"How does the process work?","index":86,"end_time":342.54,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":341.26,"speaker_name":"Josh Santo"},{"text":"Yeah, you.","index":87,"end_time":346.15,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":345.51,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Usually we watch these.","index":88,"end_time":347.35,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":346.15,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"I''ve been out the last two weeks, so I didn''t watch these myself.","index":89,"end_time":350.31,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":347.35,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"But one thing to keep in mind is it''s just the first cut.","index":90,"end_time":354.63,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":350.39,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"And the first cut alone, I think takes like 40 hours to animate.","index":91,"end_time":360.87,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":355.27,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"So, like, that''s not including like all the time that our design team has been working on things.","index":92,"end_time":367.43,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":361.27,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"So it is just a first cut and it is really, really helpful to get feedback early on so that we don''t like, sink a ton of time into things and then need to redo stuff.","index":93,"end_time":382.03,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":368.39,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Okay.","index":94,"end_time":388.91,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":388.35,"speaker_name":"Josh Santo"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":95,"end_time":389.63,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":389.23,"speaker_name":"Josh Santo"},{"text":"Because there.","index":96,"end_time":390.11,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":389.63,"speaker_name":"Josh Santo"},{"text":"The example that comes to my mind.","index":97,"end_time":392.11,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":390.67,"speaker_name":"Josh Santo"},{"text":"So there''s, there''s two initial pieces of feedback and I''ll, I''ll come back with more after I get to watch the whole thing and I''ll, I''ll go granularly through each of it.","index":98,"end_time":399.74,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":392.11,"speaker_name":"Josh Santo"},{"text":"Part of it is just my, my time is going to become more and more difficult to be able to provide that type of feedback.","index":99,"end_time":405.34,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":400.14,"speaker_name":"Josh Santo"},{"text":"So the more that I can find some way of kind of doing like a mind meld with the two of you so that there''s, there''s A way to maybe anticipate some of the feedback that I would have.","index":100,"end_time":418.06,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":405.34,"speaker_name":"Josh Santo"},{"text":"I think that that would really help me.","index":101,"end_time":420.3,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":418.06,"speaker_name":"Josh Santo"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":102,"end_time":421.5,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":421.02,"speaker_name":"Josh Santo"},{"text":"Because I''m, I''m worried about becoming a bottleneck for getting these things done because of how intensive this is going to be.","index":103,"end_time":427.76,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":421.82,"speaker_name":"Josh Santo"},{"text":"We''re like working on launching a new product and so like I''m going to be at more customer sites more frequently, that kind of thing.","index":104,"end_time":435.12,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":428.72,"speaker_name":"Josh Santo"},{"text":"So I could use some help, some way of maybe.","index":105,"end_time":438.48,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":435.12,"speaker_name":"Josh Santo"},{"text":"I don''t know if it''s like, I don''t want it to be like defining standards because that would take like a lot of work for us to just get to that point.","index":106,"end_time":448.24,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":439.2,"speaker_name":"Josh Santo"},{"text":"But if we could have some sort of mind meld.","index":107,"end_time":450.24,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":448.24,"speaker_name":"Josh Santo"},{"text":"Okay.","index":108,"end_time":452.08,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":451.44,"speaker_name":"Josh Santo"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":109,"end_time":452.44,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":452.24,"speaker_name":"Josh Santo"},{"text":"If there''s like some big picture things that we can keep an eye out from and we can do internal revisions before we send them to.","index":110,"end_time":458.64,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":452.44,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Yeah, yeah, something like that.","index":111,"end_time":461.36,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":458.64,"speaker_name":"Josh Santo"},{"text":"Like, like.","index":112,"end_time":463.44,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":461.36,"speaker_name":"Josh Santo"},{"text":"So one example is I noticed that the.","index":113,"end_time":468.32,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":464.32,"speaker_name":"Josh Santo"},{"text":"This video is four minutes.","index":114,"end_time":472.32,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":470.64,"speaker_name":"Josh Santo"},{"text":"I think the talk track had ended at like, I don''t know, 3:15, 3:30.","index":115,"end_time":476.64,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":472.56,"speaker_name":"Josh Santo"},{"text":"I think on the job training was the longest one in particular.","index":116,"end_time":479.87,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":476.64,"speaker_name":"Josh Santo"},{"text":"We''re really going to have to make sure it kind of sticks into that three minute mark as much as we can.","index":117,"end_time":487.47,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":480.83,"speaker_name":"Josh Santo"},{"text":"And I think some of that is just going to be helping with the timing of when some of the visuals pop up.","index":118,"end_time":493.07,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":488.99,"speaker_name":"Josh Santo"},{"text":"Etc.","index":119,"end_time":493.55,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":493.07,"speaker_name":"Josh Santo"},{"text":"I noticed some of the stock footage would repeat, you know, like, so you would just see it''s like start over.","index":120,"end_time":504.59,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":495.87,"speaker_name":"Josh Santo"},{"text":"Okay.","index":121,"end_time":505.72,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":505.24,"speaker_name":"Josh Santo"},{"text":"And then the other call out was.","index":122,"end_time":511.24,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":506.68,"speaker_name":"Josh Santo"},{"text":"Oh.","index":123,"end_time":511.72,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":511.24,"speaker_name":"Josh Santo"},{"text":"Whenever it was showing the product and it was like showing menus open.","index":124,"end_time":517.84,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":513.48,"speaker_name":"Josh Santo"},{"text":"It was like a, like a kind of popping, bouncing animation.","index":125,"end_time":522.76,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":517.84,"speaker_name":"Josh Santo"},{"text":"If you take a look at it, you''ll see what I''m talking about.","index":126,"end_time":527.8,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":525.32,"speaker_name":"Josh Santo"},{"text":"And we''ll just need it to be more just like presented, not, not moving as much with the kind of like a bounce to it whenever it shows up on screen.","index":127,"end_time":539.17,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":527.8,"speaker_name":"Josh Santo"},{"text":"So you want something like more subtle.","index":128,"end_time":540.77,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":539.17,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Yeah, just like as if you were opening a menu.","index":129,"end_time":544.45,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":541.41,"speaker_name":"Josh Santo"},{"text":"Okay.","index":130,"end_time":545.37,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":544.93,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"You know, like clicking around, that type of thing.","index":131,"end_time":547.65,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":545.37,"speaker_name":"Josh Santo"},{"text":"And like I said, I''ll go through the actual video and I''ll start putting comments in there.","index":132,"end_time":552.93,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":548.29,"speaker_name":"Josh Santo"},{"text":"But it''s.","index":133,"end_time":554.21,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":553.49,"speaker_name":"Josh Santo"},{"text":"And then you know, as I go through it, if I can think of things of like in general, here''s what I want to be true for all the videos.","index":134,"end_time":562.13,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":555.17,"speaker_name":"Josh Santo"},{"text":"Then have you guys take a look and catch it before, before I look at it.","index":135,"end_time":569.09,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":562.13,"speaker_name":"Josh Santo"},{"text":"It''d be super helpful.","index":136,"end_time":570.37,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":569.17,"speaker_name":"Josh Santo"},{"text":"Yeah, yeah, no, that sounds, sounds great.","index":137,"end_time":574.17,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":571.97,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Well, I haven''t watched this one yet just because I''ve been out.","index":138,"end_time":577.33,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":574.17,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"But I''ll make sure to take a look at it as well.","index":139,"end_time":579.77,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":577.33,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"And so we can also add in our notes and things like that before we get on to the next version.","index":140,"end_time":585.41,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":579.77,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Great, Cool.","index":141,"end_time":589.36,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":586.8,"speaker_name":"Josh Santo"},{"text":"And then, I mean, if I could prioritize anyone, it would be the platform overview one.","index":142,"end_time":596.64,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":589.36,"speaker_name":"Josh Santo"},{"text":"So that would be the one where it''s like, if we have to kind of put on the job training on the back burner so that we get this one done first, that would.","index":143,"end_time":608.12,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":597.36,"speaker_name":"Josh Santo"},{"text":"That would get a little heat off the game.","index":144,"end_time":610.56,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":608.12,"speaker_name":"Josh Santo"},{"text":"Okay, this is good.","index":145,"end_time":612.69,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":611.29,"speaker_name":"Paula Ocampo"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":146,"end_time":613.01,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":612.69,"speaker_name":"Paula Ocampo"},{"text":"I think the product cover video is the next one to be ready, the first cut, so it will be very soon.","index":147,"end_time":618.49,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":613.01,"speaker_name":"Paula Ocampo"},{"text":"Okay, awesome.","index":148,"end_time":622.33,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":621.45,"speaker_name":"Josh Santo"},{"text":"What do y'' all need from me?","index":149,"end_time":625.53,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":624.17,"speaker_name":"Josh Santo"},{"text":"I think that''s all we have on for now.","index":150,"end_time":630.73,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":627.69,"speaker_name":"Paula Ocampo"},{"text":"Okay, cool.","index":151,"end_time":632.57,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":630.73,"speaker_name":"Josh Santo"},{"text":"Well, I appreciate it.","index":152,"end_time":634.25,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":633.13,"speaker_name":"Josh Santo"},{"text":"Thank you for your time.","index":153,"end_time":636.25,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":635.13,"speaker_name":"Paula Ocampo"},{"text":"All right, we''ll see you.","index":154,"end_time":637.7,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":636.9,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Bye.","index":155,"end_time":638.98,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":638.5,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Bye.","index":156,"end_time":639.62,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":639.14,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"}],"dateString":"2026-01-22T21:30:00.000Z","host_email":"baylee.gunnell@marketersindemand.com","meeting_link":"https://us02web.zoom.us/j/87092601638?pwd=zFv07j4yly4HaGL0lOafqcVEf1YWzt.1","participants":["paula.ocampo@marketersindemand.com,baylee.gunnell@marketersindemand.com,josh.santo@ease.io","paula.ocampo@marketersindemand.com","josh.santo@ease.io"],"transcript_url":"https://app.fireflies.ai/view/01KFH33KZBCWTB4Q0QP5MQN8H9","organizer_email":"baylee.gunnell@marketersindemand.com"}'::jsonb,
    '{"label":"neutral","confidence":0.75,"bullets":["Scheduled 2025 podcast recap blog is complete and will publish next Thursday.","Episode 15 outperformed others with strong Apple Podcast traction and early YouTube views.","Outreach campaign yielded two promising responses; scheduling links have been sent.","Josh flagged early video cut concerns; visuals and pacing need revision to hit time target.","Josh requested platform overview video be prioritized ahead of on-the-job training piece."],"highlights":[{"quote":"I don''t see any of the videos being finished anytime soon.","speaker":"Josh Santo"},{"quote":"I''m worried about becoming a bottleneck for getting these things done because of how intensive this is going to be.","speaker":"Josh Santo"}],"topics":["delivery","content","video","outreach"],"model":"openai/gpt-4-1106-preview","version":1,"generated_at":"2026-01-23T00:00:00Z"}'::jsonb,
    '{"fireflies_summary":{"notes":"## **Content and Podcast Performance**\n\nThe team confirmed strong growth in podcast engagement driven by select episodes and planned content rollouts.\n\n- **Episode 15 with Rajiv emerged as the top performer** with most downloads from Apple Podcasts and early traction on YouTube and Spotify, signaling cross-platform interest (01:00)  \n    - Episodes 13 and 14 continue to deliver steady daily downloads, showing consistent listener retention  \n    - Paula shared that the **2025 podcast recap blog is scheduled for release next Thursday**, marking an aligned content push  \n    - This steady performance supports continued investment in podcast content to grow audience reach and engagement  \n\n- **A system for monitoring and responding to public podcast reviews was agreed upon**, focusing on capturing listener feedback across Apple, Spotify, and YouTube (02:47)  \n    - Josh emphasized tracking the impact of calls to action on review volume as a key success metric  \n    - Baylee confirmed the team will flag new feedback weekly during syncs and notify Josh for timely responses  \n    - This approach aims to maintain close audience engagement and quickly address potential concerns or praise  \n\n## **Video Production and Quality Control**\n\nVideo content production is in early stages with clear challenges in quality and workflow that require process improvements to meet deadlines.\n\n- **Josh flagged initial video cuts as rough and expressed concern about meeting timelines due to resource constraints** (04:41)  \n    - The current first cut animation takes about **40 hours**, indicating high effort per version and the need for efficient iteration  \n    - Josh requested better internal review and alignment before videos reach him to avoid bottlenecks and reduce his review load  \n    - Baylee acknowledged her recent absence limited prior reviews but committed to more active internal vetting moving forward  \n    - Prioritizing the **platform overview video over the on-the-job training video** was requested to alleviate immediate pressure  \n\n- **Specific feedback focused on video length, animation style, and visual consistency to improve viewer experience** (07:32)  \n    - Josh noted the need to keep videos near the **three-minute mark** for engagement and pacing  \n    - He requested more subtle animations for product menus, avoiding bouncing effects to maintain a professional look  \n    - Repetitive stock footage should be minimized to keep visuals fresh and relevant  \n    - This detailed feedback will inform internal revisions before Josh’s review to streamline approval  \n\n## **Outreach Campaign Success and Pipeline Development**\n\nThe outreach campaign is generating promising leads with active engagement from potential podcast guests.\n\n- **Two positive responses were received on LinkedIn from podcast guest prospects, with scheduling links already sent** (04:00)  \n    - This indicates that outreach messaging and targeting are effectively driving interest in joining the podcast  \n    - Continued follow-up will confirm conversion of these leads into booked episodes, supporting content growth  \n    - Paula is managing the scheduling process to ensure timely coordination without burdening Josh  \n\n## **Process Improvements for Content Review and Feedback**\n\nThe team agreed on refining internal workflows to reduce delays and improve content quality before executive review.\n\n- **Josh proposed creating a “mind meld” process to align expectations and anticipate his feedback early in video production** (06:28)  \n    - This would involve Baylee and Paula identifying big-picture issues internally before videos reach Josh  \n    - The goal is to reduce his review burden as his availability declines due to new product launches and client visits  \n    - Baylee committed to watching videos and adding notes during her catch-up to support this process  \n    - This approach balances quality control with realistic resource constraints to keep production moving smoothly  \n\n## **Timeline and Prioritization for Upcoming Deliverables**\n\nClear priorities and timelines were set to focus resources on highest-impact content pieces to meet business needs.\n\n- **The product cover video is targeted for first cut completion “very soon,” with the on-the-job training video deprioritized temporarily** (10:11)  \n    - This decision reflects Josh’s need to prioritize content that can reduce pressure and support product launches  \n    - Paula confirmed readiness to proceed with this schedule, aligning team efforts on critical assets  \n    - The timeline supports the broader goal of having polished product videos ready to support upcoming sales and training activities  \n    - This prioritization also guides resource allocation and sets expectations for feedback cycles going forward","outline":null,"keywords":["podcast performance","video review process","outreach campaign","animation timing","listener feedback","priority video production"],"overview":"- **Podcast Growth:** Episode 15 with Rajiv is top performer, driving engagement across Apple Podcasts, YouTube, and Spotify.\n\n- **Listener Feedback System:** New system to monitor podcast reviews agreed; captures feedback weekly to improve audience engagement.\n\n- **Video Production Challenges:** Initial video cuts face quality issues; need faster iterations as first cuts take 40 hours each.\n\n- **Outreach Success:** Positive LinkedIn responses from podcast guests; scheduling underway to convert leads into booked episodes.\n\n- **Workflow Improvement:** Proposed \"mind meld\" process to enhance video feedback, reducing Josh''s review burden during high-pressure periods.\n\n- **Content Prioritization:** Product cover video prioritized for completion soon, on-the-job training video temporarily deprioritized to support launches.","action_items":"\n**Josh Santo**\nReview the mid-roll section Frame link and provide feedback (02:14)\nWatch the full OTG training video and give detailed comments (04:41)\nCollaborate with Baylee and Paula to create a process for earlier internal review before videos are sent to him (06:28)\nPrioritize detailed review and feedback on the platform overview video (09:46)\n\n**Baylee Gunnell**\nReview the OTG training video despite recent absence and add internal feedback before next iteration (09:31)\nWork with Paula to incorporate general standards and feedback cues to streamline video review process with Josh (06:28)\n\n**Paula Ocampo**\nContinue monitoring podcast reviews on all platforms and report flagged listener feedback in weekly syncs (02:47)\nFollow-up on outreach campaign LinkedIn responses and coordinate podcast guest scheduling (04:00)\nPrepare for imminent rollout of product cover video first cut (10:11)\n"},"migrated_from":"contract_meetings","original_id":"cdba0dad-c582-4baa-a6eb-ef4750a2dd06","master_marketer":{"status":"migrated"}}'::jsonb,
