    'https://us02web.zoom.us/j/87477024015?pwd=gVpnKPDuNsoZ0giaFoA7gicVcI6afV.1',
    '{"id":"01KF1JGAJJMDNCHXV16X69WPKH","title":"PTO Exchange // New North Weekly Meeting","summary":{"notes":"## **Marketing Performance and Lead Generation**\n\nMarketing efforts have improved lead quality and cost efficiency, with LinkedIn and programmatic ads showing promising results.\n\n- **LinkedIn lead generation improved cost per lead to $233, a 54% drop from December, generating at least 3 leads this week** (26:16)  \n    - The top-performing ad features a white background with a woman holding a device, driving all current leads  \n    - Plans are to test new creatives and update landing page copy to boost conversion rates further  \n    - The benchmark report page saw a decline in form submissions, prompting a shift to native LinkedIn lead gen forms for easier user completion  \n    - Lower cost per lead and lead volume gains support ongoing investment in LinkedIn campaigns to accelerate pipeline growth  \n\n- **AdRoll programmatic retargeting maintained stable click volume despite a drop in CTR, spending $229 this period** (26:54)  \n    - The best banner highlights \"unused PTO equals hidden costs,\" consistent with LinkedIn’s top creative theme  \n    - AdRoll was chosen over Google retargeting for better audience control and integrated ABM capabilities, per Colin’s agency preference  \n    - New creatives are planned to rotate in to improve engagement and sustain retargeting effectiveness  \n    - This retargeting keeps prospects engaged after website visits, supporting brand recall and funnel re-entry  \n\n## **Sales and Lead Nurturing Strategy**\n\nThe team agreed on streamlining and refreshing drip campaigns to improve follow-up efficiency and engagement with inbound leads.\n\n- **A new automated drip campaign will enroll leads who show interest but don’t respond within one week, replacing the existing engaged sequence** (14:11)  \n    - Leads enter the sequence after failing to book meetings despite initial outreach by Dan or Stephanie  \n    - The campaign is segmented by four primary industries, with plans to add more (e.g., higher ed) later  \n    - Dan prefers a one-week follow-up window to maintain momentum and capitalize on recent engagement  \n    - Josh emphasized varying drip frequency based on prospect behavior, distinguishing between demo requests and content downloads  \n\n- **Sales reps currently perform personalized outreach including calls and LinkedIn connections, but no texting is involved** (17:00)  \n    - Demo requests receive customized emails with local hospital examples, while white paper downloads get fully automated sequences  \n    - The new drip campaign targets those who have taken action but remain unresponsive to personalized outreach  \n    - Automating this follow-up reduces manual work and ensures consistent contact without overburdening reps  \n    - This approach balances personalization with scalability to improve meeting booking rates  \n\n## **HubSpot Audit and System Optimization**\n\nA comprehensive HubSpot audit revealed substantial cleanup opportunities to improve CRM efficiency and data clarity.\n\n- **Audit uncovered over 95% of properties unused, with 417 contact, 318 deal properties, and 234 workflows reviewed** (11:04)  \n    - Many workflows overlap or contradict, creating inefficiencies and confusion in lead handling  \n    - Multiple source fields track the same data differently, complicating attribution and reporting  \n    - Colin will add company object analysis to the audit per Carmen’s request to enhance data completeness  \n    - Cleanup aims to streamline automation, unify processes, and ensure consistent campaign tracking  \n\n- **Recommendations include automating removal of contacts from drip sequences upon receiving an email reply** (13:30)  \n    - This reduces manual updates and prevents over-contacting engaged leads  \n    - Industry-specific sequences will be clearly defined to better tailor messaging  \n    - The audit deliverables will be shared with the team for review and further questions  \n    - Josh expects follow-up queries as he digs deeper into the audit findings  \n\n## **Content and Asset Development**\n\nThe team plans to create targeted content and tools to support lead engagement and demonstrate PTO Exchange’s value.\n\n- **Infographics and lead magnets will be developed based on segmentation insights from the “Time To” research white paper** (18:30)  \n    - The content will highlight differing benefit preferences across age groups and professions like registered nurses  \n    - A PTO liability calculator tool is planned to provide personalized cost-saving insights during lead conversations  \n    - Josh will coordinate with Rob to gather baseline metrics such as employee counts and PTO accrual rates to fuel customization  \n    - Social proof and landing page integration will support credibility and conversion  \n\n- **The 2026 State of Employee Benefits report is envisioned as a longer-term white paper to establish subject matter expertise** (22:20)  \n    - Carmen and Natalie expressed interest in collaborating on strategy and content refinement  \n    - This asset aims to support account-based marketing efforts and elevate the brand in the financial wellness space  \n    - The project will combine proprietary PTO Exchange data with external research for a comprehensive view  \n    - Its development is planned as a multi-phase initiative aligned with broader marketing goals  \n\n## **Team Collaboration and Meeting Cadence**\n\nThe group discussed optimizing meeting schedules and coordination to improve marketing and sales alignment.\n\n- **A dedicated marketing meeting combining PTO Exchange, New North, and Kristen’s teams is proposed for messaging and campaign orchestration** (28:51)  \n    - Rob suggested this meeting replace or complement current Wednesday and Monday sessions to centralize marketing efforts  \n    - Carmen indicated Monday midday conflicts but is open to alternate times to ensure presence  \n    - Josh will explore options and coordinate timing to maximize attendance and effectiveness  \n    - Colin will assist in adjusting schedules and sharing audit documents promptly  \n\n- **Colin committed to delivering segmented campaign performance stats by Monday to support reporting clarity** (30:26)  \n    - This will enable the team to monitor spend and results separately for New North and other initiatives  \n    - Faster access to detailed data supports informed decision-making and campaign optimization  \n    - Carmen plans to engage with wider team members as she ramps up in her new role  \n    - The group is aligned on strengthening cross-team communication and visibility for smoother execution","outline":null,"keywords":["HubSpot Audit","Drip Campaigns","PTO Liability","Marketing Strategy","Lead Generation","Campaign Reporting"],"overview":"- **LinkedIn Success:** Cost per lead dropped to $233, generating at least 3 leads this week, prompting more investment in campaigns.  \n- **AdRoll Stability:** Spent $229 with stable click volume; new creatives planned to enhance engagement and audience control.  \n- **Drip Campaign Revamp:** New automated campaign targets unresponsive leads within a week, improving follow-up efficiency across industries.  \n- **HubSpot Audit Insights:** Cleaned up over 95% of unused properties, optimizing workflows and enhancing data clarity for better lead tracking.  \n- **Content Development:** Infographics and tools planned to demonstrate PTO Exchange''s value; collaboration on a long-term white paper initiated.  \n- **Meeting Coordination:** Proposed dedicated marketing meeting to improve alignment; Colin will provide segmented campaign performance stats by Monday.","action_items":"\n**Colin Costigan**\nUpdate HubSpot audit report with company-specific data as per Carmen’s questions and send to Josh Reinhard (31:20)\nPrepare and deliver segregated campaign reporting showing New North-specific metrics by Monday to aid marketing optimization (31:10)\n\n**Josh Reinhard**\nReview updated HubSpot audit report upon receipt and prepare questions or clarifications (31:38)\nCoordinate internally (likely with Rob Whalen) to gather baseline PTO liability and financial metrics data required for new marketing assets and PTO liability tool development (19:37)\nProvide Carmen with access and review new website pages for feedback and alignment on messaging and marketing assets (24:52)\n\n**Carmen Williams**\nEngage with Nathan and Nina to collaborate on strategic input and marketing recommendations as she familiarizes with account (23:54)\nProvide feedback on new website marketing pages once access is granted (24:52)\nCommunicate scheduling constraints for marketing meetings; follow up on meeting time proposals (30:47)\n"},"duration":32.540000915527344,"speakers":[{"id":0,"name":"Colin Costigan"},{"id":1,"name":"Dan Igo"},{"id":2,"name":"Colin Costigan"},{"id":3,"name":"Colin Costigan"},{"id":4,"name":"Carmen Williams"},{"id":5,"name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"id":6,"name":"Rob Whalen"},{"id":7,"name":"Josh Reinhard"}],"sentences":[{"text":"Hey, Dan.","index":0,"end_time":226,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":225.36,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Colin.","index":1,"end_time":226.56,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":226,"speaker_name":"Dan Igo"},{"text":"What''s up, man?","index":2,"end_time":227.28,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":226.56,"speaker_name":"Dan Igo"},{"text":"How''s it going?","index":3,"end_time":228.32,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":227.6,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Good.","index":4,"end_time":229.78,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":229.52,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"How you doing?","index":5,"end_time":230.49,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":229.93,"speaker_name":"Dan Igo"},{"text":"Surviving, Dan.","index":6,"end_time":232.57,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":231.37,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"It''s a four day week, but still.","index":7,"end_time":234.65,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":232.97,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Five days worth of meetings.","index":8,"end_time":235.93,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":234.65,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Oh, is that.","index":9,"end_time":237.69,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":236.41,"speaker_name":"Dan Igo"},{"text":"Is.","index":10,"end_time":237.89,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":237.69,"speaker_name":"Dan Igo"},{"text":"Do you.","index":11,"end_time":238.21,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":237.89,"speaker_name":"Dan Igo"},{"text":"Do you always work four days?","index":12,"end_time":239.29,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":238.21,"speaker_name":"Dan Igo"},{"text":"No, it''s just we had the government holiday on Monday.","index":13,"end_time":242.73,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":239.77,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Oh, that''s right.","index":14,"end_time":243.69,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":242.81,"speaker_name":"Dan Igo"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":15,"end_time":244.21,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":243.85,"speaker_name":"Dan Igo"},{"text":"We didn''t have Martin Luther King Day.","index":16,"end_time":245.53,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":244.21,"speaker_name":"Dan Igo"},{"text":"I don''t know why we have President''s Day.","index":17,"end_time":246.81,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":245.53,"speaker_name":"Dan Igo"},{"text":"It''s kind of weird.","index":18,"end_time":247.61,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":246.81,"speaker_name":"Dan Igo"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":19,"end_time":248.41,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":247.85,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"How''s your weekend going so far?","index":20,"end_time":252.97,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":251.53,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"It''s busy, man.","index":21,"end_time":254.61,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":253.77,"speaker_name":"Dan Igo"},{"text":"We''re picking up.","index":22,"end_time":255.21,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":254.61,"speaker_name":"Dan Igo"},{"text":"It''s good.","index":23,"end_time":255.65,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":255.21,"speaker_name":"Dan Igo"},{"text":"Things are getting.","index":24,"end_time":256.33,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":255.65,"speaker_name":"Dan Igo"},{"text":"Things are getting really busy.","index":25,"end_time":258.42,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":257.34,"speaker_name":"Dan Igo"},{"text":"It''s like.","index":26,"end_time":259.02,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":258.42,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Open enrollment through, like, January 1st are, like, kind of dead for us because everyone''s doing like benefit planning and stuff.","index":27,"end_time":267.06,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":261.5,"speaker_name":"Dan Igo"},{"text":"But, like, we just start.","index":28,"end_time":269.62,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":267.06,"speaker_name":"Dan Igo"},{"text":"We just started taking off this past week.","index":29,"end_time":271.5,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":269.62,"speaker_name":"Dan Igo"},{"text":"It''s awesome.","index":30,"end_time":272.54,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":271.74,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":31,"end_time":273.18,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":272.86,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And I know a few more conversions came through from LinkedIn as well.","index":32,"end_time":275.5,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":273.18,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So you and Steph have tasks?","index":33,"end_time":277.82,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":275.58,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, I was joking with her.","index":34,"end_time":280.54,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":279.42,"speaker_name":"Dan Igo"},{"text":"I''m like, is she paying y''?","index":35,"end_time":281.54,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":280.54,"speaker_name":"Dan Igo"},{"text":"All?","index":36,"end_time":281.66,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":281.54,"speaker_name":"Dan Igo"},{"text":"Because she''s getting like 20 of them.","index":37,"end_time":283.36,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":281.66,"speaker_name":"Dan Igo"},{"text":"I got like one.","index":38,"end_time":284.16,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":283.36,"speaker_name":"Dan Igo"},{"text":"I never know what it is.","index":39,"end_time":286.56,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":285.2,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":40,"end_time":288,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":287.44,"speaker_name":"Dan Igo"},{"text":"Hey, Steph, how''s it going?","index":41,"end_time":297.92,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":296.72,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I can''t hear you.","index":42,"end_time":301.76,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":300.88,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"For some reason.","index":43,"end_time":302.4,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":301.76,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"It doesn''t show.","index":44,"end_time":304.48,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":303.68,"speaker_name":"Dan Igo"},{"text":"She''s on mute, but I can''t hear her.","index":45,"end_time":306,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":304.48,"speaker_name":"Dan Igo"},{"text":"How about now?","index":46,"end_time":310.33,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":309.69,"speaker_name":"Carmen Williams"},{"text":"Now we can magically.","index":47,"end_time":311.81,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":310.81,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yes.","index":48,"end_time":312.25,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":311.81,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Because I didn''t press OK to the meeting being recorded.","index":49,"end_time":315.77,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":313.05,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Gotcha.","index":50,"end_time":317.05,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":316.33,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And is Josh joining?","index":51,"end_time":319.77,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":318.41,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Should be.","index":52,"end_time":320.97,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":320.41,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"All right, we''ll give him a minute here.","index":53,"end_time":324.41,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":322.97,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"But Carmen, I know we just got to introduce ourselves to each other, but.","index":54,"end_time":327.49,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":324.41,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I also want to give Natalie and Nina from our team the opportunity to do so.","index":55,"end_time":331.41,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":327.49,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"They''re both awesome strategists on our side.","index":56,"end_time":333.77,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":331.41,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Amazing.","index":57,"end_time":335.27,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":334.83,"speaker_name":"Carmen Williams"},{"text":"I''m looking forward to working with you both.","index":58,"end_time":337.07,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":335.27,"speaker_name":"Carmen Williams"},{"text":"Happy to work with you as well.","index":59,"end_time":340.27,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":338.75,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Yeah, me too.","index":60,"end_time":342.79,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":341.87,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Like Colin said, I''m a marketing strategist.","index":61,"end_time":345.15,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":342.79,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"I''m also new on the account here.","index":62,"end_time":346.59,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":345.15,"speaker_name":"Carmen Williams"},{"text":"Looking forward to working together.","index":63,"end_time":348.75,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":347.47,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Excellent.","index":64,"end_time":350.35,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":349.55,"speaker_name":"Carmen Williams"},{"text":"Um, and I mean, both.","index":65,"end_time":362.2,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":359.56,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"And me and Natalie are marketing strategists.","index":66,"end_time":364.48,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":362.2,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"But currently we''re both helping out and hopefully in the future, Natalie will be helping calling a little bit more.","index":67,"end_time":372.44,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":364.48,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":68,"end_time":374.2,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":373.8,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Awesome.","index":69,"end_time":374.76,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":374.2,"speaker_name":"Dan Igo"},{"text":"See, Rob joined.","index":70,"end_time":377.32,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":376.52,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"How you doing, Rob?","index":71,"end_time":378.12,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":377.32,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Good, good.","index":72,"end_time":379.72,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":378.84,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"How is everyone doing?","index":73,"end_time":381.12,"speaker_id":6,"start_time":379.72,"speaker_name":"Rob Whalen"},{"text":"Well, it''s Thursday.","index":74,"end_time":382.52,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":381.12,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Friday.","index":75,"end_time":384.32,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":383.96,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Junior.","index":76,"end_time":384.84,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":384.32,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Give Josh another minute or so.","index":77,"end_time":391.71,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":389.79,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Any big plans for the weekend?","index":78,"end_time":395.87,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":394.11,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I know you guys are probably not.","index":79,"end_time":397.47,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":395.87,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Getting hit with this major snowstorm.","index":80,"end_time":399.31,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":397.47,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I am.","index":81,"end_time":401.67,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":401.069,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"I''m in Boston.","index":82,"end_time":402.51,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":401.67,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"I''m gonna get crushed.","index":83,"end_time":403.95,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":402.67,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"I don''t think we''re gonna get snow as far south as I am, but it''s gonna be cold.","index":84,"end_time":409.83,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":405.23,"speaker_name":"Dan Igo"},{"text":"I think 29 degrees forecasted for Sunday overnight.","index":85,"end_time":414.83,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":409.83,"speaker_name":"Dan Igo"},{"text":"So I''m gonna be.","index":86,"end_time":416.59,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":415.23,"speaker_name":"Dan Igo"},{"text":"Do you own long sleeves?","index":87,"end_time":417.87,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":416.67,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"I do, yeah.","index":88,"end_time":420.07,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":419.23,"speaker_name":"Dan Igo"},{"text":"But I gotta.","index":89,"end_time":421.03,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":420.07,"speaker_name":"Dan Igo"},{"text":"I''m more concerned about.","index":90,"end_time":422.11,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":421.03,"speaker_name":"Dan Igo"},{"text":"I''m from Minnesota, so the cold doesn''t bother me.","index":91,"end_time":424.31,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":422.11,"speaker_name":"Dan Igo"},{"text":"I''m more concerned about wrapping up my plants and my spigots and my pool equipment.","index":92,"end_time":431.07,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":424.31,"speaker_name":"Dan Igo"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":93,"end_time":431.71,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":431.23,"speaker_name":"Dan Igo"},{"text":"But people run around like crazy down here.","index":94,"end_time":436.83,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":434.83,"speaker_name":"Dan Igo"},{"text":"Like grocery stores crazy.","index":95,"end_time":438.69,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":437.17,"speaker_name":"Dan Igo"},{"text":"Like 30 degrees is what we call Monday in Minnesota.","index":96,"end_time":443.41,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":438.93,"speaker_name":"Dan Igo"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":97,"end_time":444.21,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":443.73,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Yeah, no kidding.","index":98,"end_time":446.29,"speaker_id":6,"start_time":445.01,"speaker_name":"Rob Whalen"},{"text":"It''s almost like Covid, you know, when you go to the grocery store and it''s no paper towels and toilet paper.","index":99,"end_time":452.85,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":447.01,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"For some reason, everyone had to load up on those.","index":100,"end_time":454.77,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":452.929,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"All right, guys.","index":101,"end_time":458.77,"speaker_id":7,"start_time":458.05,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Hey, Josh.","index":102,"end_time":459.65,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":458.85,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"What''s up?","index":103,"end_time":461.33,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":460.61,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We''re just getting the party started.","index":104,"end_time":463.25,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":461.81,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"How are you doing?","index":105,"end_time":463.89,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":463.25,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Doing good.","index":106,"end_time":465,"speaker_id":7,"start_time":464.44,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Awesome.","index":107,"end_time":466.36,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":465.8,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Well, we''ve all gotten introduced to Carmen.","index":108,"end_time":469.6,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":467.64,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Carmen and I actually just also had a nice like 25 minute meeting.","index":109,"end_time":473.16,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":469.6,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Getting introduced to each other.","index":110,"end_time":474.44,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":473.16,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So very excited.","index":111,"end_time":475.72,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":474.44,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":112,"end_time":478.52,"speaker_id":6,"start_time":478.04,"speaker_name":"Rob Whalen"},{"text":"Hopefully this will, this will be a good little partnership.","index":113,"end_time":480.92,"speaker_id":6,"start_time":478.6,"speaker_name":"Rob Whalen"},{"text":"Yeah, absolutely.","index":114,"end_time":481.8,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":481,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"That''s what we''re excited about.","index":115,"end_time":483.16,"speaker_id":6,"start_time":481.96,"speaker_name":"Rob Whalen"},{"text":"So helping drive.","index":116,"end_time":484.68,"speaker_id":6,"start_time":483.24,"speaker_name":"Rob Whalen"},{"text":"Drive some new business and more awareness out there about us, so.","index":117,"end_time":489.16,"speaker_id":6,"start_time":485,"speaker_name":"Rob Whalen"},{"text":"A hundred percent.","index":118,"end_time":489.72,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":489.16,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":119,"end_time":490.08,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":489.72,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And Dan was just giving me a heads up that things have been moving.","index":120,"end_time":493.16,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":490.08,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Pretty well this week.","index":121,"end_time":493.96,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":493.16,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":122,"end_time":495.39,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":495.07,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":123,"end_time":496.19,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":495.87,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We''re off to a really good start.","index":124,"end_time":497.39,"speaker_id":6,"start_time":496.19,"speaker_name":"Rob Whalen"},{"text":"I mean, we really are.","index":125,"end_time":498.55,"speaker_id":6,"start_time":497.63,"speaker_name":"Rob Whalen"},{"text":"And we just had our board meeting yesterday was.","index":126,"end_time":500.59,"speaker_id":6,"start_time":498.55,"speaker_name":"Rob Whalen"},{"text":"The board was really excited.","index":127,"end_time":502.95,"speaker_id":6,"start_time":501.63,"speaker_name":"Rob Whalen"},{"text":"They were really, really, really pleased with the.","index":128,"end_time":505.39,"speaker_id":6,"start_time":502.95,"speaker_name":"Rob Whalen"},{"text":"The progress we made over the year.","index":129,"end_time":508.03,"speaker_id":6,"start_time":505.79,"speaker_name":"Rob Whalen"},{"text":"I mean, the goal to getting to profitability.","index":130,"end_time":510.83,"speaker_id":6,"start_time":508.99,"speaker_name":"Rob Whalen"},{"text":"As you can imagine, if you''re, if you''re a board member or shareholder and you''ve been investing in the company, to know that it''s going to be successful, whether you put more money in or not, is a really, really great place to be.","index":131,"end_time":524.06,"speaker_id":6,"start_time":512.43,"speaker_name":"Rob Whalen"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":132,"end_time":524.66,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":524.22,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And so, you know, and if we can continue to grow 25 to 30% a year, this thing will continue to have an impact.","index":133,"end_time":534.94,"speaker_id":6,"start_time":524.66,"speaker_name":"Rob Whalen"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":134,"end_time":535.66,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":535.18,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":135,"end_time":536.42,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":536.06,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We''re excited to support Kerosene on that impact.","index":136,"end_time":538.46,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":536.42,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":137,"end_time":539.5,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":539.02,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And that''s why we''re hoping that you and Carmen and everyone is going to help us get there.","index":138,"end_time":544.7,"speaker_id":6,"start_time":540.78,"speaker_name":"Rob Whalen"},{"text":"Yeah, absolutely.","index":139,"end_time":545.98,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":544.94,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":140,"end_time":546.46,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":545.98,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Like I said, Carmen and I just met and had a great conversation.","index":141,"end_time":549.02,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":546.62,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I''m going to send over every document, Josh, that you''ve seen in your life.","index":142,"end_time":552.46,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":549.02,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"With New north, which you know is heavy, but Carmen seems more than up to the task and looking forward to our healthy relationship.","index":143,"end_time":561.47,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":552.46,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Perfect.","index":144,"end_time":563.39,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":562.83,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So to start out, what I do have is, is a bit in the weeds items to go through, Josh.","index":145,"end_time":569.63,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":564.99,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So like the audit and website pages for review and things like that.","index":146,"end_time":573.63,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":569.63,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Was there anywhere else you wanted to.","index":147,"end_time":575.39,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":573.79,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Start higher up just as a conversation for the group?","index":148,"end_time":577.55,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":575.39,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I don''t think so.","index":149,"end_time":580.12,"speaker_id":7,"start_time":579.32,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Like let''s, let''s start with where you''re going.","index":150,"end_time":584.08,"speaker_id":7,"start_time":580.2,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"One of the things that we do need to talk about at some point is like what I know part of the audit and part of what you were doing was like we''re also going to be looking at the sequences.","index":151,"end_time":592.44,"speaker_id":7,"start_time":584.08,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"One of like the very specific things that we want to change is the process for the inbound LinkedIn connection acceptance things.","index":152,"end_time":600.76,"speaker_id":7,"start_time":592.68,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"I think we talked about this the other day as a team.","index":153,"end_time":603.4,"speaker_id":7,"start_time":600.76,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"The work manual work being put in the way the sequence is running now is not worth the time for the results that we''re seeing.","index":154,"end_time":611.53,"speaker_id":7,"start_time":605.01,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"So we.","index":155,"end_time":611.85,"speaker_id":7,"start_time":611.53,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"So that''s a specific change, but that might be part of a bigger conversation.","index":156,"end_time":616.45,"speaker_id":7,"start_time":611.85,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Yeah, yeah, we could definitely automate that.","index":157,"end_time":618.21,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":616.53,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"All right, perfect.","index":158,"end_time":621.09,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":620.29,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"All right, well I''ll hop in.","index":159,"end_time":623.61,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":622.69,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And then you see an opportunity where you want to.","index":160,"end_time":625.81,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":623.61,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Something reminds you of something else you wanted to go through, just let me know.","index":161,"end_time":628.21,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":625.81,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"All right.","index":162,"end_time":631.42,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":630.86,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So diving in, go through our usual agenda, project updates, things we''re working on, items on your side to.","index":163,"end_time":641.02,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":635.82,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Be reviewed and then going through some.","index":164,"end_time":642.54,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":641.02,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Of our metrics and always ending with.","index":165,"end_time":644.1,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":642.54,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"What are our action items.","index":166,"end_time":645.42,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":644.1,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So we do have our HubSpot audit.","index":167,"end_time":648.62,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":646.3,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We have in here that it''s complete.","index":168,"end_time":650.06,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":648.62,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Carmen, after talking to you, there''s a few more things that I do want.","index":169,"end_time":652.94,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":650.14,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"To add in here just from your questions around like how companies are being added through different tools from the sales.","index":170,"end_time":658.2,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":652.94,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Side and things like that.","index":171,"end_time":658.92,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":658.2,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So I''m going to add that in here right now.","index":172,"end_time":661.44,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":658.92,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"This is about a 24 page document that goes through all of the different object types from deals, contacts and companies.","index":173,"end_time":669.24,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":661.44,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Found some pretty stark issues like 95%.","index":174,"end_time":673.64,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":670.36,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Of properties not being utilized at all.","index":175,"end_time":675.88,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":673.64,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So a pretty large amount of wasted space that we can clean up multiple source fields.","index":176,"end_time":681.2,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":676.36,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And Carmen, I know that even ties.","index":177,"end_time":682.64,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":681.2,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"To one of your questions of like.","index":178,"end_time":683.6,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":682.64,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Why are we tracking New north in.","index":179,"end_time":684.84,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":683.6,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"This versus email or versus it was this, this exact campaign.","index":180,"end_time":688.02,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":684.84,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"It''s because there''s like 10 different sources or source fields that are that are happening and being tracked there.","index":181,"end_time":692.94,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":688.18,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So a lot of recommendations for cleanup in here.","index":182,"end_time":695.5,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":692.94,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We also dove into the workflows.","index":183,"end_time":697.38,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":695.5,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"There are over 240 workflows that have been built over the years of you guys using HubSpot.","index":184,"end_time":703.3,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":698.02,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Some of them cancel each other out.","index":185,"end_time":706.06,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":704.1,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"A lot of them happen right when a contact comes into the system and they''re just duplicative or completely unnecessary to what I''ve come to understand as your guys process.","index":186,"end_time":714.74,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":706.06,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So we make a lot of recommendations for cleanup.","index":187,"end_time":717.3,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":715.3,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I don''t want to read 24 pages of a document to you guys on.","index":188,"end_time":719.76,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":717.3,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"This call, but it''s all broken down.","index":189,"end_time":721.32,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":719.76,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"In this table of contents, so you can quite easily jump to whatever section you''re looking for.","index":190,"end_time":725.36,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":721.32,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So, yeah, 234 workflows, 417 different contact properties, and 318 deal properties were what were analyzed so far in this audit.","index":191,"end_time":733.8,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":726.8,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"But I''m going to add in the company piece that Carmen had asked about in our call previously.","index":192,"end_time":737.6,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":733.8,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Any questions around this?","index":193,"end_time":740.4,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":738.96,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"No questions, but, I mean, that''s somewhat shocking.","index":194,"end_time":748.01,"speaker_id":7,"start_time":743.76,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"I knew it was going to be bad.","index":195,"end_time":749.05,"speaker_id":7,"start_time":748.01,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"I didn''t know it was going to be that bad.","index":196,"end_time":751.01,"speaker_id":7,"start_time":749.05,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"I almost just think we give Colin a reciprocating saw and say, go to work.","index":197,"end_time":755.09,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":751.49,"speaker_name":"Dan Igo"},{"text":"Rob said something.","index":198,"end_time":758.77,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":757.97,"speaker_name":"Dan Igo"},{"text":"I think you''re on mute, Rob.","index":199,"end_time":759.81,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":758.77,"speaker_name":"Dan Igo"},{"text":"Yeah, I said, you guys can really make a fricking mess.","index":200,"end_time":763.09,"speaker_id":6,"start_time":759.89,"speaker_name":"Rob Whalen"},{"text":"No, this is where we throw Sam on the bottom.","index":201,"end_time":767.65,"speaker_id":7,"start_time":765.81,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Steph, you don''t belong to that crew.","index":202,"end_time":770.69,"speaker_id":6,"start_time":768.29,"speaker_name":"Rob Whalen"},{"text":"That crew way before you don''t loop.","index":203,"end_time":773.57,"speaker_id":6,"start_time":770.69,"speaker_name":"Rob Whalen"},{"text":"Me into this mess.","index":204,"end_time":774.53,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":773.57,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Right.","index":205,"end_time":776.82,"speaker_id":6,"start_time":776.58,"speaker_name":"Rob Whalen"},{"text":"But you know when you find a message, just an opportunity for cleanup and realignment and get everyone operating in one motion.","index":206,"end_time":785.94,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":778.66,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And then I know we also talked about updating.","index":207,"end_time":790.42,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":787.94,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So anytime Steph, you or Dan or whoever''s assigned as the contact owner, anytime you get an email through changing the.","index":208,"end_time":797.74,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":790.5,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Automation so they get taken out of the drip sequence that they were going into automatically.","index":209,"end_time":802.42,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":797.74,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And then we''ve also written Josh, we talked about the four main industries or primary industries we wanted to start with.","index":210,"end_time":810.31,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":804.39,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"From a drip campaign perspective as well as a general.","index":211,"end_time":812.63,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":810.31,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So we have that bucket, you know, for the.","index":212,"end_time":815.47,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":812.79,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Like, we didn''t do a higher ed, for example.","index":213,"end_time":817.11,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":815.47,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We can do that here soon and loop that in.","index":214,"end_time":819.95,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":817.11,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"They can have their own sequence, but we didn''t start with those.","index":215,"end_time":822.23,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":819.95,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So they would fall into a general.","index":216,"end_time":823.43,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":822.23,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So this is what we are recommending.","index":217,"end_time":826.11,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":824.55,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And it''s a bunch of different documents that we''ll share, broken out by industry as the drip sequences.","index":218,"end_time":831.59,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":826.11,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"That.","index":219,"end_time":831.99,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":831.59,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So someone comes in, they''ve.","index":220,"end_time":834.11,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":832.91,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"They''ve raised their hand, showing their interest in PTO exchange.","index":221,"end_time":837.07,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":834.11,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"They''re not responding to Steph or Dan about booking a meeting very quickly.","index":222,"end_time":841.79,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":837.55,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So within that, like one to two.","index":223,"end_time":842.99,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":841.79,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Weeks, and I want everyone to come to a consensus here on that exact timeline.","index":224,"end_time":846.03,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":842.99,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Then they would get enrolled into the sequence that we can keep adding more content to as we go.","index":225,"end_time":851.47,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":846.75,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We started out with just a few emails to start over a couple of weeks.","index":226,"end_time":854.59,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":851.47,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Any questions here about what we put together?","index":227,"end_time":861.16,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":859.48,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"No.","index":228,"end_time":863.24,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":862.84,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Great.","index":229,"end_time":864.68,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":864.28,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Awesome.","index":230,"end_time":866.28,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":865.72,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":231,"end_time":866.64,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":866.28,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I know that Dan and Steph, you guys especially were Saying that the drip campaigns have just been in place for.","index":232,"end_time":872.44,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":866.64,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"A while and needed a refresh.","index":233,"end_time":873.88,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":872.44,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":234,"end_time":875.24,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":874.92,"speaker_name":"Dan Igo"},{"text":"And I lean more towards one week as opposed to two, but that''s just my thought.","index":235,"end_time":879.48,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":875.24,"speaker_name":"Dan Igo"},{"text":"Well, I think some of this depends on who is receiving the drip campaign.","index":236,"end_time":886.22,"speaker_id":7,"start_time":880.84,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"It would be the contact that had raised their hand, whether it''s from a LinkedIn lead gen ad or they filled.","index":237,"end_time":890.94,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":886.94,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Out like a benchmark report form on the website to get their benchmark report if they''re not responding.","index":238,"end_time":895.9,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":890.94,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So that''s the trigger that we talked.","index":239,"end_time":897.5,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":896.22,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"About for the lead status of Dan and Steph.","index":240,"end_time":900.26,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":897.5,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"All they have to do is just flip lead status to like cold or nurture.","index":241,"end_time":904.9,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":900.26,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We can add a new one if we need and then they would automatically get enrolled in the sequence.","index":242,"end_time":909.98,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":904.9,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So these are folks that have already been through another sequence of us trying to set a meeting with them.","index":243,"end_time":914.74,"speaker_id":7,"start_time":910.58,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"They were non responsive to that outreach and now we''re getting it.","index":244,"end_time":919.14,"speaker_id":7,"start_time":915.06,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"So in that case, I think like a longer break between the emails probably makes more.","index":245,"end_time":922.9,"speaker_id":7,"start_time":919.14,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Makes a little more sense, but.","index":246,"end_time":924.34,"speaker_id":7,"start_time":923.06,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Well, it wasn''t that they were non responsive.","index":247,"end_time":925.94,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":924.5,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I mean, they have raised their.","index":248,"end_time":926.9,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":925.94,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"They filled out a form on like.","index":249,"end_time":928.54,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":926.9,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"The benchmark report on the website or.","index":250,"end_time":929.94,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":928.54,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"They filled out a form on LinkedIn.","index":251,"end_time":931.22,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":929.94,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So they''ve shown interest or they''ve responded to Steph and Dan on LinkedIn, know, things like that.","index":252,"end_time":936.51,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":931.22,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So if you guys want to think through, I think a week or two weeks would work.","index":253,"end_time":944.91,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":941.47,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"You guys move pretty quickly.","index":254,"end_time":947.51,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":946.35,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So a week.","index":255,"end_time":948.07,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":947.51,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I mean, I''m sure Steph and Dan have already sent more than two emails and tried a few phone calls.","index":256,"end_time":951.71,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":948.07,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":257,"end_time":952.19,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":951.87,"speaker_name":"Dan Igo"},{"text":"My thought is if, if we''ve reached out and try to book a first meeting, if it''s gone beyond a week that I just think a week is.","index":258,"end_time":961.55,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":952.19,"speaker_name":"Dan Igo"},{"text":"We, we can talk about it.","index":259,"end_time":962.93,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":961.89,"speaker_name":"Dan Igo"},{"text":"Josh.","index":260,"end_time":963.33,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":962.93,"speaker_name":"Dan Igo"},{"text":"Yeah, because what just.","index":261,"end_time":965.65,"speaker_id":7,"start_time":963.65,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"I''m sure you saw this in the audit that you did in HubSpot, but we were treating people who are downloading white papers differently than people that are requesting a demo.","index":262,"end_time":977.49,"speaker_id":7,"start_time":966.05,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"There''s like a much more aggressive approach than someone that''s like just downloading a white paper.","index":263,"end_time":984.21,"speaker_id":7,"start_time":977.649,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"This feels to me more like what we would be doing with someone that''s downloading a white paper as opposed to someone that''s requesting a demo or like the benchmark report or something that''s a little more active, but carbon, that''s probably stuff we need to do.","index":264,"end_time":1003.11,"speaker_id":7,"start_time":986.77,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Well, I have a question.","index":265,"end_time":1003.95,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1003.11,"speaker_name":"Carmen Williams"},{"text":"Sorry, dumb questions at the beginning.","index":266,"end_time":1006.35,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1004.75,"speaker_name":"Carmen Williams"},{"text":"Right.","index":267,"end_time":1006.55,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1006.35,"speaker_name":"Carmen Williams"},{"text":"Because I''m just trying to figure it out.","index":268,"end_time":1007.63,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1006.55,"speaker_name":"Carmen Williams"},{"text":"But are Dan, Stephanie, are the sales reps doing their own outreach?","index":269,"end_time":1013.51,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1007.63,"speaker_name":"Carmen Williams"},{"text":"To these inbound leads or is it all marketing?","index":270,"end_time":1017.39,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1013.51,"speaker_name":"Carmen Williams"},{"text":"Like, is there any one off personalized or is it these automated?","index":271,"end_time":1022.6,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1017.47,"speaker_name":"Carmen Williams"},{"text":"Like, is there both things happening or just this?","index":272,"end_time":1025.56,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1023.24,"speaker_name":"Carmen Williams"},{"text":"So I.","index":273,"end_time":1028.84,"speaker_id":7,"start_time":1027.64,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"So for.","index":274,"end_time":1029.96,"speaker_id":7,"start_time":1029.32,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"It''s a different approach depending on what, what the trigger is.","index":275,"end_time":1033.24,"speaker_id":7,"start_time":1030.28,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"So if it''s, if it''s like a request for demo, we have a sequence that''s created, but part of the sequence is they should be going in and customizing it and trying to find like some other hospital that we work with that''s in the region and they''re personalizing it.","index":276,"end_time":1049.48,"speaker_id":7,"start_time":1033.32,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"But 75% of the email is written for the step of the sequence.","index":277,"end_time":1055.79,"speaker_id":7,"start_time":1049.87,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"For the white papers that people are downloading.","index":278,"end_time":1059.15,"speaker_id":7,"start_time":1056.51,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"It''s all automated.","index":279,"end_time":1060.43,"speaker_id":7,"start_time":1059.23,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Matthew Shaughnessy enrolls them in a sequence as they come in.","index":280,"end_time":1065.71,"speaker_id":7,"start_time":1061.07,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":281,"end_time":1066.35,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1065.87,"speaker_name":"Carmen Williams"},{"text":"And with the requested demo follow up, that has the high touch with the personalization from the rep, are you also doing texting, calling, other things or.","index":282,"end_time":1079.15,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1068.11,"speaker_name":"Carmen Williams"},{"text":"We''re not doing texting, but we''re doing calling and we''re doing LinkedIn connections.","index":283,"end_time":1082.31,"speaker_id":7,"start_time":1079.15,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Text.","index":284,"end_time":1083.43,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1082.95,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":285,"end_time":1083.99,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1083.51,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So this is to go to those that just didn''t respond.","index":286,"end_time":1091.35,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1087.59,"speaker_name":"Carmen Williams"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":287,"end_time":1093.07,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1092.71,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"That have, like have done.","index":288,"end_time":1093.91,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1093.07,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Have taken some sort of action but.","index":289,"end_time":1095.39,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1093.91,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Are not signing that meeting.","index":290,"end_time":1096.63,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1095.39,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Signing up for that meeting.","index":291,"end_time":1097.91,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1096.87,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So that I see this as replacing our engaged sequence.","index":292,"end_time":1101.51,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1097.91,"speaker_name":"Dan Igo"},{"text":"Yeah, yeah, absolutely.","index":293,"end_time":1105.93,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1103.45,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Great.","index":294,"end_time":1108.73,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1108.33,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Awesome.","index":295,"end_time":1109.41,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1108.97,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I will send those over for review.","index":296,"end_time":1110.77,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1109.41,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"As well for the ideas that we pitched last week.","index":297,"end_time":1114.65,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1110.77,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So we''re working on infographics and assets.","index":298,"end_time":1116.65,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1114.65,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And Josh, I know that you said that we could heavily pull from the time to.","index":299,"end_time":1122.01,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1117.45,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I can''t remember the exact title.","index":300,"end_time":1123.33,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1122.01,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"You know, the research white paper that I''m talking about.","index":301,"end_time":1126.29,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1123.33,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"The time to.","index":302,"end_time":1127.61,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1126.29,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":303,"end_time":1128.11,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1127.91,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yes.","index":304,"end_time":1128.47,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1128.11,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":305,"end_time":1128.79,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1128.47,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"That goes through like, this is what the younger population likes to see as.","index":306,"end_time":1131.79,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1128.79,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Far as their benefits is what the older population likes to see.","index":307,"end_time":1134.23,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1131.79,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Registered nurses need X, Y and Z.","index":308,"end_time":1136.95,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1135.03,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"You know, all of those who are developing infographics and other lead magnets to try and drive more traffic to those as well.","index":309,"end_time":1144.87,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1137.19,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Right.","index":310,"end_time":1147.03,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1146.63,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"As well as the tool that we.","index":311,"end_time":1150.03,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1148.39,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Talked about for the financial liability angle that we want to play.","index":312,"end_time":1153.75,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1150.03,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And so for that you had brought up like that, you guys have some.","index":313,"end_time":1158.94,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1154.71,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Metrics behind the scenes that we might be able to utilize there.","index":314,"end_time":1162.18,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1158.94,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So I wanted to ask if you''ve had any time to have conversations around those.","index":315,"end_time":1165.62,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1162.18,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I. I haven''t, but just because it totally slipped off my radar.","index":316,"end_time":1170.74,"speaker_id":7,"start_time":1165.94,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"So I can get with Rob probably on that.","index":317,"end_time":1176.58,"speaker_id":7,"start_time":1170.74,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Awesome.","index":318,"end_time":1177.62,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1177.06,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":319,"end_time":1178.26,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1177.78,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":320,"end_time":1178.82,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1178.5,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I think we just need to collect a few baseline metrics.","index":321,"end_time":1181.58,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1178.82,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"You know, I know that you''ve shown me a few times kind of like.","index":322,"end_time":1184.06,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1181.58,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Your spreadsheet and what you''re pulling up and plugging in to be able to give them some customized numbers or even.","index":323,"end_time":1189.63,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1184.06,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Just if we can streamline it.","index":324,"end_time":1191.35,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1189.63,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And it''s just like, you know, how many employees, what''s your average accrual rate for one year, three or five year.","index":325,"end_time":1195.87,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1191.35,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Or whatever, or roughly how, what''s your headcount and what''s your salary ranges?","index":326,"end_time":1200.35,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1195.87,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"You know, there''s a few things that we can try and make it a little bit easier or more range based versus them having to have that all on hand.","index":327,"end_time":1207.23,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1200.35,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":328,"end_time":1208.19,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1207.63,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I have to go back to our last week''s chat to figure out like what were the, what were the data points that you needed me to look up?","index":329,"end_time":1215.69,"speaker_id":7,"start_time":1209.39,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"I don''t know if you have that easily accessible, but if not, I can.","index":330,"end_time":1219.33,"speaker_id":7,"start_time":1215.69,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Yeah, I can pull that up.","index":331,"end_time":1221.21,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1220.13,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Give me one second.","index":332,"end_time":1222.29,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1221.21,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":333,"end_time":1254.42,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1254.14,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So we''re starting out with asking if they even know their PTO liability, if.","index":334,"end_time":1259.62,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1254.42,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"They''Re aware of that number or not, and then going from there like a branch.","index":335,"end_time":1264.14,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1259.62,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So if they do know it, enter.","index":336,"end_time":1265.66,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1264.38,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"The amount, then we would follow up.","index":337,"end_time":1268.3,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1265.66,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"With like some insights on what that means and drive them towards that first meeting.","index":338,"end_time":1271.58,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1268.3,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"If they''re unaware of their PTO liability, it''d be a different set of questions that we would need to work with you on.","index":339,"end_time":1276.58,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1271.58,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And again, ultimately driving them to that.","index":340,"end_time":1279.74,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1277.94,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"First meeting.","index":341,"end_time":1280.26,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1279.74,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And the things that we would be asking for was like the number of employees they have, average PTO balance, average pay rate.","index":342,"end_time":1291.46,"speaker_id":7,"start_time":1282.5,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":343,"end_time":1292.26,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1291.78,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Then we would take that to estimate their overall PTO liability and we could show them that.","index":344,"end_time":1305.53,"speaker_id":7,"start_time":1299.61,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Would you be interested in reducing a million dollars of that PTO liability at the cost of $800,000?","index":345,"end_time":1313.69,"speaker_id":7,"start_time":1305.77,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Right.","index":346,"end_time":1314.41,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1314.01,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"With social proof of the companies you''ve done it for and all of the landing page items.","index":347,"end_time":1320.56,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1315.53,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":348,"end_time":1322.12,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1321.68,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"That calculator we would build straight into the site.","index":349,"end_time":1324.32,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1322.12,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Awesome.","index":350,"end_time":1329.92,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1329.28,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And then the 2026 state of employee benefits report.","index":351,"end_time":1332.96,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1329.92,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So we kind of had a question.","index":352,"end_time":1335.8,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1334.56,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Mark around this one too of like, what data we can utilize.","index":353,"end_time":1338.32,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1335.8,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I think that we can combine some research with some proprietary data that PTO Exchange has.","index":354,"end_time":1342.88,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1338.32,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And you wanted to think about that a little bit more.","index":355,"end_time":1345.2,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1343.44,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":356,"end_time":1346.29,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1345.89,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And like, I mean, to me this is part of a fairly big project that we would be working on.","index":357,"end_time":1353.97,"speaker_id":7,"start_time":1346.93,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"So Carmen, I think this is a longer term play for us, but it would essentially be like us owning some kind of white paper that, you know, legitimizes us as experts in the employee benefits, financial wellness space is kind of like the way we were envisioning this.","index":358,"end_time":1379.1,"speaker_id":7,"start_time":1353.97,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"So the account based marketing for me I think is going to be likely I''m just still day three or whatever, most key initiatives.","index":359,"end_time":1393.66,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1383.9,"speaker_name":"Carmen Williams"},{"text":"And at this point it''s too early for me to accept that.","index":360,"end_time":1396.9,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1393.74,"speaker_name":"Carmen Williams"},{"text":"It''s.","index":361,"end_time":1397.25,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1396.9,"speaker_name":"Carmen Williams"},{"text":"What I''m seeing is it''s a different.","index":362,"end_time":1398.76,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1397.4,"speaker_name":"Carmen Williams"},{"text":"You''re looking at it differently than I would look at it, which is fine.","index":363,"end_time":1402.04,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1399.08,"speaker_name":"Carmen Williams"},{"text":"Curious with your team, Natalie?","index":364,"end_time":1406.64,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1402.92,"speaker_name":"Carmen Williams"},{"text":"Nina, what are you available to collaborate as I kind of work through and come up with some strategy and recommendations.","index":365,"end_time":1415.4,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1406.64,"speaker_name":"Carmen Williams"},{"text":"How.","index":366,"end_time":1415.76,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1415.4,"speaker_name":"Carmen Williams"},{"text":"How we don''t have to talk about this now, but I.","index":367,"end_time":1418.56,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1415.76,"speaker_name":"Carmen Williams"},{"text":"It''s too early for me to even chime in other than I''m trying to get up to speed.","index":368,"end_time":1424.04,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1418.56,"speaker_name":"Carmen Williams"},{"text":"And then I have some different ways of looking at it that we can kind of consider as well.","index":369,"end_time":1430.16,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1424.04,"speaker_name":"Carmen Williams"},{"text":"So thoughts on?","index":370,"end_time":1432.32,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1430.24,"speaker_name":"Carmen Williams"},{"text":"Of course.","index":371,"end_time":1434.64,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":1434.16,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"It would be great to bounce off ideas and see, you know, what can be improved.","index":372,"end_time":1439.44,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":1434.64,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Cool.","index":373,"end_time":1441.76,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1441.36,"speaker_name":"Carmen Williams"},{"text":"So.","index":374,"end_time":1442,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1441.76,"speaker_name":"Carmen Williams"},{"text":"So you''re accessible.","index":375,"end_time":1442.88,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1442,"speaker_name":"Carmen Williams"},{"text":"In other words, if I want out and we could.","index":376,"end_time":1445.16,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1442.88,"speaker_name":"Carmen Williams"},{"text":"Okay, good.","index":377,"end_time":1445.92,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":1445.16,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Perfect.","index":378,"end_time":1446.64,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1446,"speaker_name":"Carmen Williams"},{"text":"Sorry I don''t have more at this point.","index":379,"end_time":1450.17,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1448.73,"speaker_name":"Carmen Williams"},{"text":"Yeah, yeah, totally get it.","index":380,"end_time":1452.97,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1451.61,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"All right, Josh.","index":381,"end_time":1455.37,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1454.73,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So yeah, I agree.","index":382,"end_time":1457.01,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1455.37,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"That can be a longer term thing.","index":383,"end_time":1458.49,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1457.01,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"That''s why I didn''t want to have.","index":384,"end_time":1459.61,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1458.57,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"That as the only campaign pitch because I think we can launch these other ones much quicker with our segmentation and have those emails going out.","index":385,"end_time":1466.01,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1459.61,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Awesome.","index":386,"end_time":1469.53,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1468.97,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We''ll send the links again if you need them for the webpage.","index":387,"end_time":1474.09,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1471.21,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I imagine you''ve been very busy and haven''t had a chance to look at these.","index":388,"end_time":1476.81,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1474.09,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Correct.","index":389,"end_time":1478.61,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1478.21,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"But that is going to be on the high priority agenda for us.","index":390,"end_time":1484.93,"speaker_id":7,"start_time":1478.69,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Carmen, do you have those?","index":391,"end_time":1488.37,"speaker_id":7,"start_time":1487.01,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Probably not.","index":392,"end_time":1490.29,"speaker_id":7,"start_time":1489.41,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"No.","index":393,"end_time":1492.53,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1492.13,"speaker_name":"Carmen Williams"},{"text":"Okay, so these are new web, new pages to add to the website that they created.","index":394,"end_time":1497.41,"speaker_id":7,"start_time":1492.929,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Glad to see that.","index":395,"end_time":1498.85,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1497.73,"speaker_name":"Carmen Williams"},{"text":"Yes.","index":396,"end_time":1499.73,"speaker_id":7,"start_time":1499.25,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"So, well, I''ll make sure you have access to these links so that you can start going through and making comments.","index":397,"end_time":1505.51,"speaker_id":7,"start_time":1499.73,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"All that.","index":398,"end_time":1506.39,"speaker_id":7,"start_time":1505.83,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":399,"end_time":1507.11,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1506.55,"speaker_name":"Carmen Williams"},{"text":"Awesome.","index":400,"end_time":1508.71,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1508.15,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"All right.","index":401,"end_time":1511.51,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1511.03,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And then diving into performance, looking at a week over week.","index":402,"end_time":1515.31,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1511.51,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So we did increase spend as we''re still bouncing back from the drop in spend on the holidays.","index":403,"end_time":1519.99,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1515.31,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Generated three leads.","index":404,"end_time":1521.39,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1520.15,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I think actually even more came through since we made this deck yesterday.","index":405,"end_time":1524.15,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1521.39,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I saw a few more this morning.","index":406,"end_time":1525.43,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1524.23,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"The cost per lead when we looked.","index":407,"end_time":1527.19,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1526.07,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"At it was $233, which is a significant improvement versus what we were seeing in the month of December.","index":408,"end_time":1532.23,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1527.19,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"54% to be more precise.","index":409,"end_time":1534.55,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1532.71,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"As far as the creative that''s performing best.","index":410,"end_time":1538.21,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1536.45,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"It is the reimagine your PTO program ad.","index":411,"end_time":1541.05,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1538.21,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"It''s got the white background, the woman with her device on the right side that''s actually generated all of the ads.","index":412,"end_time":1547.81,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1541.05,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So what we''re going to use from that data is that is our champion.","index":413,"end_time":1550.73,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1547.81,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We''re Going to sub in a new B test and see what we can get as a new champion.","index":414,"end_time":1554.53,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1550.73,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And we want to also test changing some of the landing page copy again, ultimately reaching that goal.","index":415,"end_time":1561.97,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1555.73,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Rob, I know we''ve had conversations.","index":416,"end_time":1563.25,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1561.97,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"First meeting is everything.","index":417,"end_time":1564.53,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1563.25,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So continuing to push towards that.","index":418,"end_time":1566.89,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1564.61,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And then for the benchmark report, we''ve.","index":419,"end_time":1569.49,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1567.45,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Seen a dip in the amount of form submissions coming from that page.","index":420,"end_time":1574.65,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1569.49,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So we want to switch and test running sort of a native lead gen form on LinkedIn.","index":421,"end_time":1580.37,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1575.77,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Getting a bit more interest there, more buy in because we just see higher performance and high results when someone doesn''t have to fill out all their information on a website.","index":422,"end_time":1588.57,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1580.37,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And it''s already all filled in on LinkedIn.","index":423,"end_time":1590.41,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1588.57,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Any questions around?","index":424,"end_time":1592.82,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1592.1,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Anything for LinkedIn ads?","index":425,"end_time":1594.02,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1592.82,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"On the Adroll side, again, this is the programmatic play.","index":426,"end_time":1600.5,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1597.78,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"It''s much more on the awareness portion of the funnel.","index":427,"end_time":1603.86,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1600.5,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Not a large budget.","index":428,"end_time":1604.9,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1604.02,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"The spend was $229.","index":429,"end_time":1606.5,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1604.9,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Clicks did drop, so we''re looking at rotating Ad Creative there as well.","index":430,"end_time":1612.58,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1606.98,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"The one that''s performing the best is very similar to the one that''s performing the best on LinkedIn, which is interesting to see.","index":431,"end_time":1618.02,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1612.58,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"It is the unused PTO equals hidden costs banner.","index":432,"end_time":1621.3,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1618.26,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And Carmen, I''m not sure if you''ve used AdRoll specifically or some other programmatic display tool.","index":433,"end_time":1626.68,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1622.84,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Questions we can talk about another time.","index":434,"end_time":1631.16,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1629.48,"speaker_name":"Carmen Williams"},{"text":"Yeah, yeah, yeah.","index":435,"end_time":1631.92,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1631.16,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Perfect.","index":436,"end_time":1632.28,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1631.92,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And the click through rate did drop while impressions rose.","index":437,"end_time":1636.12,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1633.4,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So technically that means the clicks kind of stayed at a volume stabilization.","index":438,"end_time":1640.68,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1636.2,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"But still looking for new creative that will build and rotate into that.","index":439,"end_time":1644.84,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1640.68,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"This is a retargeting play.","index":440,"end_time":1646.64,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1645.08,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So people that have been visiting the website and trying to get them back.","index":441,"end_time":1648.84,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1646.64,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Question on using the Adroll versus Google Retargeting.","index":442,"end_time":1653.59,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1650.03,"speaker_name":"Carmen Williams"},{"text":"Just.","index":443,"end_time":1653.95,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1653.59,"speaker_name":"Carmen Williams"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":444,"end_time":1655.23,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1654.91,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So Adrolls, it''s a pixel that we''re.","index":445,"end_time":1656.75,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1655.23,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Able to put onto the website for simple retargeting.","index":446,"end_time":1659.79,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1656.75,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So it sticks with them.","index":447,"end_time":1660.79,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1659.79,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"It''s IP based and follows them like through Wall Street Journal.","index":448,"end_time":1664.27,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1660.79,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, yeah, totally.","index":449,"end_time":1665.35,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1664.27,"speaker_name":"Carmen Williams"},{"text":"But why did you use AdRoll versus Google retargeting?","index":450,"end_time":1669.75,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1665.35,"speaker_name":"Carmen Williams"},{"text":"I was just curious if there was.","index":451,"end_time":1670.79,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1669.75,"speaker_name":"Carmen Williams"},{"text":"A. Yeah, I mean, historically it''s just our agency''s preference.","index":452,"end_time":1673.59,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1670.79,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"That''s what we found more success with.","index":453,"end_time":1675.15,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1673.59,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"No worries.","index":454,"end_time":1675.99,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1675.51,"speaker_name":"Carmen Williams"},{"text":"Cool.","index":455,"end_time":1678.23,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1677.83,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, more audience control as well.","index":456,"end_time":1679.87,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1678.23,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"They also have an ABM portion to their tool.","index":457,"end_time":1681.67,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1679.87,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay, awesome.","index":458,"end_time":1685.91,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1681.75,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Josh, did anything spark in your mind of other things you needed to bring up or.","index":459,"end_time":1690.31,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1686.63,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I mean, not immediately.","index":460,"end_time":1694.99,"speaker_id":7,"start_time":1693.91,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"I think kind of separate from all the stuff that we''re talking about.","index":461,"end_time":1699.43,"speaker_id":7,"start_time":1694.99,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"I think we just need to figure out what once Carmen gets settled, like what''s our cadence, what''s our schedule yeah.","index":462,"end_time":1705.87,"speaker_id":7,"start_time":1699.43,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Carmen joined our first Wednesday meeting, which is our marketing and sales meeting that we have.","index":463,"end_time":1713.23,"speaker_id":7,"start_time":1707.87,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Probably makes sense to have you on that meeting if you can, but.","index":464,"end_time":1720.35,"speaker_id":7,"start_time":1714.27,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"But I don''t know.","index":465,"end_time":1723.31,"speaker_id":7,"start_time":1722.51,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"You know, again, I don''t know if that replaces another meeting.","index":466,"end_time":1725.39,"speaker_id":7,"start_time":1723.31,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"If it''s necessary to have you on that meeting.","index":467,"end_time":1727.47,"speaker_id":7,"start_time":1725.39,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"We just have to figure all that, all that out.","index":468,"end_time":1730.61,"speaker_id":7,"start_time":1728.89,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"This is all new, so.","index":469,"end_time":1731.69,"speaker_id":7,"start_time":1730.61,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Well, Josh, I''m thinking that on the Wednesday meeting, we, we don''t have New North.","index":470,"end_time":1737.41,"speaker_id":6,"start_time":1731.85,"speaker_name":"Rob Whalen"},{"text":"I, I think we have a whole separate marketing meeting like we had, you know, going with Sam and Kristen.","index":471,"end_time":1745.17,"speaker_id":6,"start_time":1737.41,"speaker_name":"Rob Whalen"},{"text":"And it would be great if we had Carmen, New North, Kristen.","index":472,"end_time":1749.29,"speaker_id":6,"start_time":1745.17,"speaker_name":"Rob Whalen"},{"text":"Yeah, yeah.","index":473,"end_time":1750.29,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1749.61,"speaker_name":"Carmen Williams"},{"text":"All together.","index":474,"end_time":1750.81,"speaker_id":6,"start_time":1750.29,"speaker_name":"Rob Whalen"},{"text":"Marketing focused.","index":475,"end_time":1752.05,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1751.05,"speaker_name":"Carmen Williams"},{"text":"Yeah, marketing focused, messaging focused, blog focused, PR focused.","index":476,"end_time":1757.52,"speaker_id":6,"start_time":1752.05,"speaker_name":"Rob Whalen"},{"text":"So that Carmen can actually, you know.","index":477,"end_time":1760.72,"speaker_id":6,"start_time":1757.92,"speaker_name":"Rob Whalen"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":478,"end_time":1761.28,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1760.8,"speaker_name":"Carmen Williams"},{"text":"Tell everyone what to do, orchestrate what her.","index":479,"end_time":1763.6,"speaker_id":6,"start_time":1761.28,"speaker_name":"Rob Whalen"},{"text":"What she''s thinking about.","index":480,"end_time":1764.64,"speaker_id":6,"start_time":1763.6,"speaker_name":"Rob Whalen"},{"text":"So I talked to Colin about that because, you know, we always used to do that on Mondays when.","index":481,"end_time":1769.92,"speaker_id":7,"start_time":1764.96,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"With Sam.","index":482,"end_time":1770.72,"speaker_id":7,"start_time":1769.92,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":483,"end_time":1771.68,"speaker_id":6,"start_time":1771.2,"speaker_name":"Rob Whalen"},{"text":"And we have our standing Monday with New north from 12:30 to 1.","index":484,"end_time":1778.08,"speaker_id":7,"start_time":1772.56,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"But Colin also has a meeting from 12 to 12:30.","index":485,"end_time":1780.88,"speaker_id":7,"start_time":1778.24,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"So what I was thinking was maybe if we wanted to have like a 45 minute meeting, maybe we start at 12:15.","index":486,"end_time":1787.58,"speaker_id":7,"start_time":1781.52,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"If Colin''s other call ends early, he jumps on at 12:15.","index":487,"end_time":1791.1,"speaker_id":7,"start_time":1787.98,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"But then he joins at 12:30 and he''s on from 12:30 to 1 and covering the stuff that he needs to be there for.","index":488,"end_time":1797.26,"speaker_id":7,"start_time":1791.42,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"I''m gonna have a hard time with that time slot.","index":489,"end_time":1800.42,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1798.3,"speaker_name":"Carmen Williams"},{"text":"But we, can, we, can we get back on that?","index":490,"end_time":1804.22,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1800.42,"speaker_name":"Carmen Williams"},{"text":"I have.","index":491,"end_time":1804.62,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1804.22,"speaker_name":"Carmen Williams"},{"text":"Is, Is it okay if we solve that?","index":492,"end_time":1807.42,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1804.62,"speaker_name":"Carmen Williams"},{"text":"Sorry to jump in with another thing because I actually think would be urgent.","index":493,"end_time":1810.87,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1808.15,"speaker_name":"Carmen Williams"},{"text":"Colin, how quickly can you change the stats so we know rather than a big chunk is New north rather than.","index":494,"end_time":1817.99,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1810.87,"speaker_name":"Carmen Williams"},{"text":"Can we get the stats specifically on, you know, the different media and campaigns?","index":495,"end_time":1822.83,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1817.99,"speaker_name":"Carmen Williams"},{"text":"How quickly is it to get that reporting sorted out?","index":496,"end_time":1825.83,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1822.83,"speaker_name":"Carmen Williams"},{"text":"I mean, I could have that ready on Monday.","index":497,"end_time":1827.99,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1826.55,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay, so it''s quick.","index":498,"end_time":1829.55,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1828.63,"speaker_name":"Carmen Williams"},{"text":"Great.","index":499,"end_time":1829.87,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1829.55,"speaker_name":"Carmen Williams"},{"text":"Yeah, perfect.","index":500,"end_time":1830.63,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1829.87,"speaker_name":"Carmen Williams"},{"text":"So maybe by the time we have this meeting, whether it''s Monday or.","index":501,"end_time":1833.59,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1830.63,"speaker_name":"Carmen Williams"},{"text":"And curious.","index":502,"end_time":1835.42,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1834.82,"speaker_name":"Carmen Williams"},{"text":"Josh, may I ask, like this, this time spot right now, this meeting right now, would it, would it make sense to kind of either combine or have it kind of one and then the other?","index":503,"end_time":1845.86,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1835.42,"speaker_name":"Carmen Williams"},{"text":"Yeah, I mean, that''s what I''m trying to figure.","index":504,"end_time":1849.18,"speaker_id":7,"start_time":1847.62,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"We have this set up so that we were meeting with New York twice a week.","index":505,"end_time":1851.94,"speaker_id":7,"start_time":1849.18,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":506,"end_time":1852.62,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1852.18,"speaker_name":"Carmen Williams"},{"text":"The two times can be any times that work for everybody.","index":507,"end_time":1855.78,"speaker_id":7,"start_time":1852.62,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"This was just like what we had initially.","index":508,"end_time":1858.66,"speaker_id":7,"start_time":1856.34,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":509,"end_time":1859.5,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1859.14,"speaker_name":"Carmen Williams"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":510,"end_time":1859.74,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1859.5,"speaker_name":"Carmen Williams"},{"text":"Cool.","index":511,"end_time":1860.1,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1859.74,"speaker_name":"Carmen Williams"},{"text":"So sorry that Monday midday is, is, is the.","index":512,"end_time":1864.66,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1860.62,"speaker_name":"Carmen Williams"},{"text":"Yeah, I''m committed.","index":513,"end_time":1865.9,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1864.66,"speaker_name":"Carmen Williams"},{"text":"So no worries.","index":514,"end_time":1867.34,"speaker_id":6,"start_time":1865.9,"speaker_name":"Rob Whalen"},{"text":"Yeah, we''ll just find it.","index":515,"end_time":1868.42,"speaker_id":6,"start_time":1867.42,"speaker_name":"Rob Whalen"},{"text":"We''ll find another time.","index":516,"end_time":1869.34,"speaker_id":6,"start_time":1868.42,"speaker_name":"Rob Whalen"},{"text":"So.","index":517,"end_time":1870.22,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1869.82,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":518,"end_time":1871.02,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1870.46,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Awesome.","index":519,"end_time":1872.38,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1871.74,"speaker_name":"Carmen Williams"},{"text":"Fantastic.","index":520,"end_time":1874.58,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1873.82,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, Josh, just let me know in.","index":521,"end_time":1876.1,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1874.58,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text"