iming to maximize attendance and effectiveness  \n    - Colin will assist in adjusting schedules and sharing audit documents promptly  \n\n- **Colin committed to delivering segmented campaign performance stats by Monday to support reporting clarity** (30:26)  \n    - This will enable the team to monitor spend and results separately for New North and other initiatives  \n    - Faster access to detailed data supports informed decision-making and campaign optimization  \n    - Carmen plans to engage with wider team members as she ramps up in her new role  \n    - The group is aligned on strengthening cross-team communication and visibility for smoother execution","outline":null,"keywords":["HubSpot Audit","Drip Campaigns","PTO Liability","Marketing Strategy","Lead Generation","Campaign Reporting"],"overview":"- **LinkedIn Success:** Cost per lead dropped to $233, generating at least 3 leads this week, prompting more investment in campaigns.  \n- **AdRoll Stability:** Spent $229 with stable click volume; new creatives planned to enhance engagement and audience control.  \n- **Drip Campaign Revamp:** New automated campaign targets unresponsive leads within a week, improving follow-up efficiency across industries.  \n- **HubSpot Audit Insights:** Cleaned up over 95% of unused properties, optimizing workflows and enhancing data clarity for better lead tracking.  \n- **Content Development:** Infographics and tools planned to demonstrate PTO Exchange''s value; collaboration on a long-term white paper initiated.  \n- **Meeting Coordination:** Proposed dedicated marketing meeting to improve alignment; Colin will provide segmented campaign performance stats by Monday.","action_items":"\n**Colin Costigan**\nUpdate HubSpot audit report with company-specific data as per Carmen’s questions and send to Josh Reinhard (31:20)\nPrepare and deliver segregated campaign reporting showing New North-specific metrics by Monday to aid marketing optimization (31:10)\n\n**Josh Reinhard**\nReview updated HubSpot audit report upon receipt and prepare questions or clarifications (31:38)\nCoordinate internally (likely with Rob Whalen) to gather baseline PTO liability and financial metrics data required for new marketing assets and PTO liability tool development (19:37)\nProvide Carmen with access and review new website pages for feedback and alignment on messaging and marketing assets (24:52)\n\n**Carmen Williams**\nEngage with Nathan and Nina to collaborate on strategic input and marketing recommendations as she familiarizes with account (23:54)\nProvide feedback on new website marketing pages once access is granted (24:52)\nCommunicate scheduling constraints for marketing meetings; follow up on meeting time proposals (30:47)\n"},"migrated_from":"contract_meetings","original_id":"c5183f9d-28e1-441c-8790-ae73139c0b0e","master_marketer":{"status":"migrated"}}'::jsonb,
