  'Meeting Notes: PTO Exchange // New North Weekly Meeting',
  '## **Marketing Performance and Lead Generation**

Marketing efforts have improved lead quality and cost efficiency, with LinkedIn and programmatic ads showing promising results.

- **LinkedIn lead generation improved cost per lead to $233, a 54% drop from December, generating at least 3 leads this week** (26:16)  
    - The top-performing ad features a white background with a woman holding a device, driving all current leads  
    - Plans are to test new creatives and update landing page copy to boost conversion rates further  
    - The benchmark report page saw a decline in form submissions, prompting a shift to native LinkedIn lead gen forms for easier user completion  
    - Lower cost per lead and lead volume gains support ongoing investment in LinkedIn campaigns to accelerate pipeline growth  

- **AdRoll programmatic retargeting maintained stable click volume despite a drop in CTR, spending $229 this period** (26:54)  
    - The best banner highlights "unused PTO equals hidden costs," consistent with LinkedIn’s top creative theme  
    - AdRoll was chosen over Google retargeting for better audience control and integrated ABM capabilities, per Colin’s agency preference  
    - New creatives are planned to rotate in to improve engagement and sustain retargeting effectiveness  
    - This retargeting keeps prospects engaged after website visits, supporting brand recall and funnel re-entry  

## **Sales and Lead Nurturing Strategy**

The team agreed on streamlining and refreshing drip campaigns to improve follow-up efficiency and engagement with inbound leads.

- **A new automated drip campaign will enroll leads who show interest but don’t respond within one week, replacing the existing engaged sequence** (14:11)  
    - Leads enter the sequence after failing to book meetings despite initial outreach by Dan or Stephanie  
    - The campaign is segmented by four primary industries, with plans to add more (e.g., higher ed) later  
    - Dan prefers a one-week follow-up window to maintain momentum and capitalize on recent engagement  
    - Josh emphasized varying drip frequency based on prospect behavior, distinguishing between demo requests and content downloads  

- **Sales reps currently perform personalized outreach including calls and LinkedIn connections, but no texting is involved** (17:00)  
    - Demo requests receive customized emails with local hospital examples, while white paper downloads get fully automated sequences  
    - The new drip campaign targets those who have taken action but remain unresponsive to personalized outreach  
    - Automating this follow-up reduces manual work and ensures consistent contact without overburdening reps  
    - This approach balances personalization with scalability to improve meeting booking rates  

## **HubSpot Audit and System Optimization**

A comprehensive HubSpot audit revealed substantial cleanup opportunities to improve CRM efficiency and data clarity.

- **Audit uncovered over 95% of properties unused, with 417 contact, 318 deal properties, and 234 workflows reviewed** (11:04)  
    - Many workflows overlap or contradict, creating inefficiencies and confusion in lead handling  
    - Multiple source fields track the same data differently, complicating attribution and reporting  
    - Colin will add company object analysis to the audit per Carmen’s request to enhance data completeness  
    - Cleanup aims to streamline automation, unify processes, and ensure consistent campaign tracking  

- **Recommendations include automating removal of contacts from drip sequences upon receiving an email reply** (13:30)  
    - This reduces manual updates and prevents over-contacting engaged leads  
    - Industry-specific sequences will be clearly defined to better tailor messaging  
    - The audit deliverables will be shared with the team for review and further questions  
    - Josh expects follow-up queries as he digs deeper into the audit findings  

## **Content and Asset Development**

The team plans to create targeted content and tools to support lead engagement and demonstrate PTO Exchange’s value.

- **Infographics and lead magnets will be developed based on segmentation insights from the “Time To” research white paper** (18:30)  
    - The content will highlight differing benefit preferences across age groups and professions like registered nurses  
    - A PTO liability calculator tool is planned to provide personalized cost-saving insights during lead conversations  
    - Josh will coordinate with Rob to gather baseline metrics such as employee counts and PTO accrual rates to fuel customization  
    - Social proof and landing page integration will support credibility and conversion  

- **The 2026 State of Employee Benefits report is envisioned as a longer-term white paper to establish subject matter expertise** (22:20)  
    - Carmen and Natalie expressed interest in collaborating on strategy and content refinement  
    - This asset aims to support account-based marketing efforts and elevate the brand in the financial wellness space  
    - The project will combine proprietary PTO Exchange data with external research for a comprehensive view  
    - Its development is planned as a multi-phase initiative aligned with broader marketing goals  

## **Team Collaboration and Meeting Cadence**

The group discussed optimizing meeting schedules and coordination to improve marketing and sales alignment.

- **A dedicated marketing meeting combining PTO Exchange, New North, and Kristen’s teams is proposed for messaging and campaign orchestration** (28:51)  
    - Rob suggested this meeting replace or complement current Wednesday and Monday sessions to centralize marketing efforts  
    - Carmen indicated Monday midday conflicts but is open to alternate times to ensure presence  
    - Josh will explore options and coordinate timing to maximize attendance and effectiveness  
    - Colin will assist in adjusting schedules and sharing audit documents promptly  

- **Colin committed to delivering segmented campaign performance stats by Monday to support reporting clarity** (30:26)  
    - This will enable the team to monitor spend and results separately for New North and other initiatives  
    - Faster access to detailed data supports informed decision-making and campaign optimization  
    - Carmen plans to engage with wider team members as she ramps up in her new role  
    - The group is aligned on strengthening cross-team communication and visibility for smoother execution',
  '2026-01-22 18:30:00+00',
  'published',
  '[{"text":"Update HubSpot audit report with company-specific data as per Carmen’s questions and send to Josh Reinhard (31:20)","completed":false},{"text":"Prepare and deliver segregated campaign reporting showing New North-specific metrics by Monday to aid marketing optimization (31:10)","completed":false},{"text":"Review updated HubSpot audit report upon receipt and prepare questions or clarifications (31:38)","completed":false},{"text":"Coordinate internally (likely with Rob Whalen) to gather baseline PTO liability and financial metrics data required for new marketing assets and PTO liability tool development (19:37)","completed":false},{"text":"Provide Carmen with access and review new website pages for feedback and alignment on messaging and marketing assets (24:52)","completed":false},{"text":"Engage with Nathan and Nina to collaborate on strategic input and marketing recommendations as she familiarizes with account (23:54)","completed":false},{"text":"Provide feedback on new website marketing pages once access is granted (24:52)","completed":false},{"text":"Communicate scheduling constraints for marketing meetings; follow up on meeting time proposals (30:47)","completed":false}]'::jsonb,
  true
