-- Meeting: Colin Costigan and Carmen Williams (2026-01-22 18:00:00+00)
WITH new_meeting AS (
  INSERT INTO compass_meetings (contract_id, meeting_date, source, external_id, title, participants, duration_seconds, recording_url, transcript, sentiment, raw_metadata, created_at, updated_at)
  VALUES (
    '3f032f15-833e-4d7d-9347-381febf6d953',
    '2026-01-22 18:00:00+00',
    'fireflies',
    '01KFERZMY9M9H1JJT8S3SF8XR2',
    'Colin Costigan and Carmen Williams',
    '{"Carmen Williams","Colin Costigan"}'::text[],
    1440,
    'https://us02web.zoom.us/j/84520841876?pwd=ou1EAHiZfSDoYnxjUsawbnFk1lcJtL.1',
    '{"id":"01KFERZMY9M9H1JJT8S3SF8XR2","title":"Colin Costigan and Carmen Williams","summary":{"notes":"## **Agency Structure and Collaboration**\n\nThe marketing efforts for **PTO Exchange** are managed by **Marketers In Demand**, which owns **four agencies** specializing in performance marketing, content, AI-driven automation, and web development, all working collaboratively within a unified project management and communication system (00:58).\n\n- **Colin Costigan**, as **Head of Client Operations**, leads system and process development while supported by strategists and account directors managing day-to-day client communications.\n- Clients gain access to capabilities across all agencies simultaneously, streamlining service delivery and cross-functional expertise.\n- This structure allows faster onboarding and integrated campaign execution across channels, improving agility and resource use.\n- The collaborative approach is designed to deliver cohesive marketing strategies rather than fragmented agency efforts.\n\n## **Current Marketing Strategy and Campaign Development**\n\nThe team focuses on **account-based marketing (ABM)** using cost-effective automation tools outside of HubSpot to target cold outreach and track engagement, emphasizing first meeting bookings as the primary sales conversion goal (03:08).\n\n- The strategy heavily leverages **PTO Exchange’s benchmark report data** for industry-specific targeting over 1-, 3-, and 5-year periods.\n- Four new **industry-focused campaign ideas** were pitched and approved in the prior week, with landing pages and email content currently in development, aiming to expand beyond healthcare and HR sectors (12:27).\n- Campaign assets include lead magnets like infographics and playbooks designed to increase lead engagement and nurture prospects.\n- Web pages optimized with AI and SEO are written but remain unpublished pending final review by **Josh**, limiting current campaign activation (05:19).\n\n## **HubSpot Usage and Audit Findings**\n\nThe current **HubSpot instance** spans Marketing Hub Enterprise, Sales Hub Professional, Service Hub Professional, and CMS but suffers from significant data quality and process issues, with **95% of properties not filled**, causing misinformation and inefficiency (09:51, 10:44).\n\n- The audit highlights convoluted source tracking with multiple properties for the same data, complicating accurate attribution and reporting.\n- Lead management processes appear disconnected from sales pipeline progression, with unclear handoffs between marketing-sourced leads and sales-qualified opportunities (10:57, 11:27).\n- The database contains **238,000 contact records**, but only **fewer than 100 deals** in the sales pipeline, indicating a large volume of unqualified or stale data (17:29).\n- Colin and Carmen agreed that cleaning the database and implementing a clear funnel with measurable conversion points from contact to opportunity is critical.\n- HubSpot’s limitation on cold outreach requires outside tools for ABM cold emails, reinforcing the hybrid tool strategy.\n\n## **Lead Management and Sales Alignment**\n\nMarketing’s primary objective is to deliver **first meetings** for sales, but converting interest into booked appointments remains a challenge across industries, with many leads showing initial engagement but failing to respond to calls (16:47).\n\n- Colin clarified that marketing executes campaigns and lead generation but does not currently own lead management or sales process alignment.\n- Sales teams add contacts from external sources like ZoomInfo, adding volume but complicating funnel clarity (18:31).\n- Carmen emphasized the need to define and potentially redesign lead management processes within HubSpot to ensure smooth lead qualification and follow-up.\n- The team plans to collaborate closely with **Josh** to align marketing campaigns and lead handling with sales workflows.\n\n## **Next Steps and Onboarding**\n\nCarmen will be invited to the **client portal (Pulse)** containing all strategic documents, campaign plans, and reporting to get up to speed and begin driving strategy development (07:48).\n\n- Weekly reporting meetings occur on Thursdays where campaign performance and ad metrics are reviewed.\n- Carmen aims to conduct a strategic audit and develop a recommended marketing plan within **6 to 9 weeks**, focusing on business understanding, personas, positioning, and ABM enhancement.\n- Colin will provide selective documentation and access to reports from tools like **Factors AI** and **RB2B** used for website traffic de-anonymization.\n- The team agreed to establish a cadence for ongoing knowledge sharing and collaboration to refine the marketing and lead management approach.\n\n## **Strategic Perspectives and Challenges**\n\nCarmen’s core focus is on understanding **PTO Exchange’s market, personas, and unique positioning** to build a more outbound, targeted approach that complements existing inbound efforts (14:54).\n\n- She sees potential in shifting more effort to outbound ABM but recognizes HubSpot’s cold outreach limits, requiring creative integrations.\n- Colin expressed openness to process and system redesigns in HubSpot to better fit strategic needs and operational preferences.\n- Both emphasized partnership and alignment to improve campaign focus, measurement, and ultimately, appointment setting rates.\n- The urgency of cleaning and organizing the large contact database was highlighted as foundational to improving marketing effectiveness and sales funnel clarity.","outline":null,"keywords":["HubSpot","Account-Based Marketing","PTO Exchange","Lead Management","Campaign Strategy","Client Portal"],"overview":"- **Agency Collaboration:** Marketing managed by four specialized agencies enhances service delivery and accelerates campaign execution.  \n- **ABM Strategy:** Focused on cost-effective automation tools for cold outreach; aims for first meeting bookings as key sales goal.  \n- **HubSpot Issues:** 95% of HubSpot data properties are unfilled, complicating reporting and lead tracking.  \n- **Lead Management Challenges:** Marketing generates leads but lacks ownership over lead management and sales processes.  \n- **Next Steps:** Carmen will conduct a strategic audit and develop a marketing plan within 6 to 9 weeks.  \n- **Strategic Focus:** Emphasizing outbound ABM while addressing HubSpot’s limitations; improving database organization is urgent.","action_items":"\n**Colin Costigan**\nInvite Carmen to the client portal named Pulse with access to all strategic documents and campaign details (08:10)\nShare access to campaign proposals and scope of work documentation to help Carmen understand current and planned initiatives (14:09)\nProvide Carmen with reports from external tools (factors AI, RB2B), though direct access may not be possible (22:11)\nContinue weekly reporting on ad campaign performance and prepare to share updates in upcoming internal calls on Mondays or Thursdays (08:35)\n\n**Carmen Williams**\nReview all materials and client portal access once provided to familiarize herself with strategy, campaigns, and reporting (08:25)\nConduct deeper discussions with Josh about sales lead management and internal processes to identify gaps between marketing efforts and sales conversions (15:59)\nDevelop her own strategic audit and recommended plan for PTO Exchange marketing within the next 6-9 weeks and ensure alignment with Colin’s team (20:01)\nAssess the use of HubSpot and related tools for target account marketing and lead management processes (20:39)\nProbe existing lead database quality and segmentation during upcoming audits or meetings (17:40)\n"},"duration":24,"speakers":[{"id":0,"name":"Carmen Williams"},{"id":1,"name":"Colin Costigan"}],"sentences":[{"text":"Hey, Colin.","index":0,"end_time":32.81,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":32.01,"speaker_name":"Carmen Williams"},{"text":"Hey.","index":1,"end_time":33.69,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":33.21,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"How''s it going?","index":2,"end_time":34.25,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":33.69,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Carmen?","index":3,"end_time":34.77,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":34.25,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Good.","index":4,"end_time":35.09,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":34.77,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Nice to meet you.","index":5,"end_time":36.01,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":35.09,"speaker_name":"Carmen Williams"},{"text":"You as well.","index":6,"end_time":36.97,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":36.17,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"How are you doing?","index":7,"end_time":38.89,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":38.17,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I''m drinking from a fire hose.","index":8,"end_time":41.37,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":39.45,"speaker_name":"Carmen Williams"},{"text":"I can''t imagine.","index":9,"end_time":43.37,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":42.17,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Give me the background.","index":10,"end_time":46.21,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":45.05,"speaker_name":"Carmen Williams"},{"text":"Like how long have you been with the company and PTO Exchange?","index":11,"end_time":50.53,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":46.21,"speaker_name":"Carmen Williams"},{"text":"How did this come about?","index":12,"end_time":51.61,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":50.53,"speaker_name":"Carmen Williams"},{"text":"What.","index":13,"end_time":52.69,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":52.33,"speaker_name":"Carmen Williams"},{"text":"How does it work over there?","index":14,"end_time":54.05,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":52.69,"speaker_name":"Carmen Williams"},{"text":"Are you like the front person and there''s a team behind you or what?","index":15,"end_time":57.37,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":54.05,"speaker_name":"Carmen Williams"},{"text":"Just give me.","index":16,"end_time":58.11,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":57.67,"speaker_name":"Carmen Williams"},{"text":"I''d love to.","index":17,"end_time":58.71,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":58.11,"speaker_name":"Carmen Williams"},{"text":"Yeah, yeah, yeah, absolutely.","index":18,"end_time":60.79,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":58.87,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So a lot of background here.","index":19,"end_time":63.07,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":60.79,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"It might even start to help to start with the company structure.","index":20,"end_time":65.59,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":63.07,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So you see my email.","index":21,"end_time":66.79,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":65.59,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Marketers in Demand.","index":22,"end_time":67.75,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":66.79,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Marketers In Demand owns four different marketing agencies.","index":23,"end_time":71.11,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":68.15,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So one of those is New north, that is the performance marketing agency.","index":24,"end_time":75.55,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":71.43,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Another is Motion, that is a content and podcasting agency.","index":25,"end_time":79.03,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":75.55,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Another one is Spoke, which is a content, more AI driven workflow automation agency.","index":26,"end_time":84.71,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":79.19,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And then Ideometry is a web design and development agency.","index":27,"end_time":87.88,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":85.28,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So over the years we''ve acquired agencies with a skill set that we don''t currently have because it''s better to do that than like bolting on just a person.","index":28,"end_time":95.08,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":87.88,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"You know, there''s a proven process, et cetera.","index":29,"end_time":96.88,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":95.08,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So those acquisitions have been made over the course of several years.","index":30,"end_time":100.76,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":98.16,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I started at New north before Marketers in Demand was a thing.","index":31,"end_time":104,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":100.76,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Worked there for a few years.","index":32,"end_time":105.56,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":104.4,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"The acquisition happened.","index":33,"end_time":106.88,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":105.56,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I stayed on for a bit.","index":34,"end_time":108.12,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":107.12,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I actually then went and left and ran another agency for a little over a year and then came back just because they were looking for more leadership help, someone to come in on the.","index":35,"end_time":117.82,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":108.12,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"My title is head of client operations.","index":36,"end_time":119.82,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":118.06,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So I build a lot of the systems and structures and everything that we use from a marketing perspective.","index":37,"end_time":125.18,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":120.54,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And then we have an account management team, so strategists and account directors that hop on to.","index":38,"end_time":130.22,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":125.66,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And, and when you start joining our calls, you''ll meet those, those people as well that help facilitate everything from a.","index":39,"end_time":136.42,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":130.94,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"A week to week basis communications, everything that''s happening with our team.","index":40,"end_time":139.42,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":136.42,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"The cool thing about the, the agencies that we have is it''s all in one project management system.","index":41,"end_time":143.98,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":139.74,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We all use one slack.","index":42,"end_time":145.14,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":143.98,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We.","index":43,"end_time":145.38,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":145.14,"speaker_name":"Carmen Williams"},{"text":"When you sign on with any of the agencies, you get all of the capabilities of any agency we have.","index":44,"end_time":149.77,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":145.45,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Got it.","index":45,"end_time":150.81,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":150.17,"speaker_name":"Carmen Williams"},{"text":"And so, so the meeting that''s after this is the wider group meeting.","index":46,"end_time":155.93,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":151.21,"speaker_name":"Carmen Williams"},{"text":"Okay.","index":47,"end_time":157.33,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":156.81,"speaker_name":"Carmen Williams"},{"text":"Because it used to be Monday, but now it''s Thursday, is that right?","index":48,"end_time":159.93,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":157.33,"speaker_name":"Carmen Williams"},{"text":"We.","index":49,"end_time":160.37,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":160.01,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We actually have both.","index":50,"end_time":161.17,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":160.37,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We have Monday and Thursday sessions, but Josh was looking for us to start joining some internal calls on Monday.","index":51,"end_time":167.85,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":161.17,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So I think we''re going to replace the Monday call with maybe me joining that for like 15 to 30 minutes.","index":52,"end_time":171.61,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":167.85,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Just give an update.","index":53,"end_time":172.49,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":171.61,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Got it.","index":54,"end_time":173.43,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":173.03,"speaker_name":"Carmen Williams"},{"text":"Okay.","index":55,"end_time":173.91,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":173.43,"speaker_name":"Carmen Williams"},{"text":"And what.","index":56,"end_time":177.43,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":174.47,"speaker_name":"Carmen Williams"},{"text":"Okay, so let me understand about strategy.","index":57,"end_time":181.75,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":177.43,"speaker_name":"Carmen Williams"},{"text":"Like, have we incorporated your strategy?","index":58,"end_time":184.99,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":181.75,"speaker_name":"Carmen Williams"},{"text":"Like we have.","index":59,"end_time":185.47,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":184.99,"speaker_name":"Carmen Williams"},{"text":"We worked with your strategy team.","index":60,"end_time":186.67,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":185.47,"speaker_name":"Carmen Williams"},{"text":"Is there, is there a strategy?","index":61,"end_time":188.15,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":186.67,"speaker_name":"Carmen Williams"},{"text":"Yeah, there is a strategy.","index":62,"end_time":190.63,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":188.629,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":63,"end_time":190.87,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":190.63,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We have a lot of documents and everything that we can dive into or I can share as well.","index":64,"end_time":194.07,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":190.87,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We do a lot through account based marketing and we don''t run that through HubSpot.","index":65,"end_time":199.27,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":195.43,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I know that was one of your questions about the capabilities there.","index":66,"end_time":201.59,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":199.27,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We actually set up, we work with scrappy teams, so not the teams that can afford dream data for $100,000 a year, but we pair together and stitch together a bunch of tools that are more cost effective so that we can send cold emails, we can de anonymize website traffic, we can track all of this in your CRM and all of this done through automation.","index":67,"end_time":221.07,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":202.23,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So our strategy, you know, we started by building a strong offer where we work with PTO Exchange very heavily in building what is called the benchmark report.","index":68,"end_time":229.55,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":221.31,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So used a lot of their data to establish what the benchmarks are per industries for, you know, like over one year, three years, five years.","index":69,"end_time":238.9,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":230.43,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"How does PTO accrue?","index":70,"end_time":240.38,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":238.9,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"What types of, you know, all of the PTO things that you can ask.","index":71,"end_time":244.14,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":240.94,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Do you want to show me where the plan is?","index":72,"end_time":247.46,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":245.5,"speaker_name":"Carmen Williams"},{"text":"Like the strategy and the plan?","index":73,"end_time":249.02,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":247.46,"speaker_name":"Carmen Williams"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":74,"end_time":249.82,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":249.42,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And then are you guys also doing, did you do the AI stuff?","index":75,"end_time":254.26,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":249.82,"speaker_name":"Carmen Williams"},{"text":"Like, because it sounds like they''ve dabbled in AI.","index":76,"end_time":256.74,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":254.26,"speaker_name":"Carmen Williams"},{"text":"It sounds like, as in like AI optimization.","index":77,"end_time":259.42,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":256.74,"speaker_name":"Carmen Williams"},{"text":"It sounds like they''ve dabbled in digital ads or this is where.","index":78,"end_time":264.2,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":259.66,"speaker_name":"Carmen Williams"},{"text":"I don''t know because I''m like just trying to piece it together kind of thing.","index":79,"end_time":267.44,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":264.2,"speaker_name":"Carmen Williams"},{"text":"Yeah, yeah.","index":80,"end_time":269,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":267.44,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So one thing that may be getting confused here, you might be thinking of 11x that does the AI enrichment and enablement components.","index":81,"end_time":276.96,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":269,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Josh was actually just showing me that on Monday.","index":82,"end_time":278.64,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":276.96,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Well, I looked at their website.","index":83,"end_time":281.2,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":278.8,"speaker_name":"Carmen Williams"},{"text":"It sounds more like they''re like agents.","index":84,"end_time":284.08,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":281.36,"speaker_name":"Carmen Williams"},{"text":"Whereas I''m talking about search engine optimization.","index":85,"end_time":286.96,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":284.32,"speaker_name":"Carmen Williams"},{"text":"Oh yeah, yeah.","index":86,"end_time":288.24,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":287.36,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And AI optimization as in rankings.","index":87,"end_time":292.12,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":288.4,"speaker_name":"Carmen Williams"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":88,"end_time":293.2,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":292.84,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We actually haven''t historically done organic work for PTO exchange.","index":89,"end_time":296.52,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":293.2,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"That is something that we do have in house as a capability is SEO and AI optimization for websites.","index":90,"end_time":301.96,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":296.68,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And that''s something that we.","index":91,"end_time":303.32,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":302.28,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Not to the PTO Exchange website, but that''s something that we baked in when we rewrote.","index":92,"end_time":307.96,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":303.64,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I know that you also asked about web pages.","index":93,"end_time":309.8,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":308.04,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So we wrote.","index":94,"end_time":310.88,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":310.12,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"There''s no existing industry pages or anything on the site.","index":95,"end_time":313.52,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":310.88,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So we wrote those with AI and SEO in mind as well as new homepage and all these things.","index":96,"end_time":318.27,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":313.52,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"They just haven''t Been published.","index":97,"end_time":319.07,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":318.27,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"They''re being reviewed.","index":98,"end_time":319.79,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":319.07,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay.","index":99,"end_time":320.39,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":319.79,"speaker_name":"Carmen Williams"},{"text":"Okay, that''s good.","index":100,"end_time":322.31,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":320.63,"speaker_name":"Carmen Williams"},{"text":"Okay.","index":101,"end_time":322.67,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":322.31,"speaker_name":"Carmen Williams"},{"text":"But.","index":102,"end_time":322.95,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":322.67,"speaker_name":"Carmen Williams"},{"text":"But they.","index":103,"end_time":323.75,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":323.1