gular cadence where we''re really digging into this because the goal is in.","index":475,"end_time":1224.9,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1218.66,"speaker_name":"Carmen Williams"},{"text":"In about six, eight, nine weeks or so.","index":476,"end_time":1228.42,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1225.22,"speaker_name":"Carmen Williams"},{"text":"I want to have a recommended strategy and plan like my own kind of audit with the start.","index":477,"end_time":1233.18,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1228.42,"speaker_name":"Carmen Williams"},{"text":"You know what I''m saying?","index":478,"end_time":1233.94,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1233.18,"speaker_name":"Carmen Williams"},{"text":"Sure.","index":479,"end_time":1234.38,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1234.1,"speaker_name":"Carmen Williams"},{"text":"They are in agreement and I want you to.","index":480,"end_time":1236.24,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1234.38,"speaker_name":"Carmen Williams"},{"text":"To include you so that we''re aligned.","index":481,"end_time":1238.47,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1236.47,"speaker_name":"Carmen Williams"},{"text":"I don''t want to have, you know.","index":482,"end_time":1239.75,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1238.47,"speaker_name":"Carmen Williams"},{"text":"Okay, yeah, absolutely.","index":483,"end_time":1240.95,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1239.99,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":484,"end_time":1241.19,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1240.95,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"With HubSpot target accounts.","index":485,"end_time":1242.31,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1241.19,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"The one caveat there is that HubSpot doesn''t allow like cold communication.","index":486,"end_time":1245.67,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1242.31,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"People have to opt in.","index":487,"end_time":1247.19,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1246.23,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So that would have to be the account based marketing approach.","index":488,"end_time":1249.07,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1247.19,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"They would have had to opted in.","index":489,"end_time":1250.75,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1249.07,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Opt in somewhere else.","index":490,"end_time":1251.99,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1250.75,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, the account based marketing that we run is purely cold.","index":491,"end_time":1255.35,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1252.07,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We set up emails on different domains, things like that.","index":492,"end_time":1257.67,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1255.35,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Totally, totally get it and that''s good.","index":493,"end_time":1260.71,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1258.23,"speaker_name":"Carmen Williams"},{"text":"But there''s ways to.","index":494,"end_time":1262.79,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1261.27,"speaker_name":"Carmen Williams"},{"text":"Yeah, so there''s ways to opt in and get.","index":495,"end_time":1265.63,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1263.11,"speaker_name":"Carmen Williams"},{"text":"But you can still have that target list because at the end of the day you want to work that target list and get them to engage so you can then nurture.","index":496,"end_time":1272.25,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1265.63,"speaker_name":"Carmen Williams"},{"text":"So what you''re just saying though is that for that particular functionality you''ve got to use it nurturing, not co. Yeah, I''m with you.","index":497,"end_time":1280.25,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1272.25,"speaker_name":"Carmen Williams"},{"text":"Right, thank you.","index":498,"end_time":1281.41,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1280.25,"speaker_name":"Carmen Williams"},{"text":"Is there anything else you think I should point me, you know, because I want to.","index":499,"end_time":1286.93,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1282.93,"speaker_name":"Carmen Williams"},{"text":"I want to be efficient and get up to speed quickly.","index":500,"end_time":1289.09,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1286.93,"speaker_name":"Carmen Williams"},{"text":"What do you recommend I focus on or do to really kind of just send slack lit with links or something if you want.","index":501,"end_time":1297.42,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1289.09,"speaker_name":"Carmen Williams"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":502,"end_time":1297.7,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1297.42,"speaker_name":"Carmen Williams"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":503,"end_time":1297.9,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1297.7,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Well, I''ll get you invited into our client portal.","index":504,"end_time":1299.78,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1297.9,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"It''s called Pulse.","index":505,"end_time":1300.34,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1299.78,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So you''ll get an email for that.","index":506,"end_time":1301.42,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1300.34,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I think we went through everything on your list.","index":507,"end_time":1304.86,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1302.86,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I''m just reviewing that to make sure.","index":508,"end_time":1307.02,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1305.18,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Sounds like you''ve used Pearl Diver.","index":509,"end_time":1308.46,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1307.1,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I''ve used that in the past as well.","index":510,"end_time":1309.74,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1308.46,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Are you telling me how this works?","index":511,"end_time":1313.02,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1311.5,"speaker_name":"Carmen Williams"},{"text":"I''ve had mixed results too.","index":512,"end_time":1315.1,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1313.5,"speaker_name":"Carmen Williams"},{"text":"So it sounds like HubSpot has all that baked in.","index":513,"end_time":1317.58,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1315.34,"speaker_name":"Carmen Williams"},{"text":"HubSpot does, but we also have.","index":514,"end_time":1319.82,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1318.22,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We use tools like factors AI and RB2B to DE.","index":515,"end_time":1323.62,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1319.9,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Anonymize website traffic.","index":516,"end_time":1324.84,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1323.62,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Cool.","index":517,"end_time":1325.67,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1325.47,"speaker_name":"Carmen Williams"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":518,"end_time":1325.91,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1325.67,"speaker_name":"Carmen Williams"},{"text":"So I''d love to get access to any of those things that.","index":519,"end_time":1328.59,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1325.91,"speaker_name":"Carmen Williams"},{"text":"If we''re using it.","index":520,"end_time":1329.63,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1328.59,"speaker_name":"Carmen Williams"},{"text":"Yeah, like.","index":521,"end_time":1331.23,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1330.03,"speaker_name":"Carmen Williams"},{"text":"Well, yeah, it''s all set up through our AT account.","index":522,"end_time":1333.47,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1331.39,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So I can give you, like, reports.","index":523,"end_time":1334.47,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1333.47,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I can''t give you access.","index":524,"end_time":1335.39,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1334.47,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Cool, cool.","index":525,"end_time":1336.71,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1335.79,"speaker_name":"Carmen Williams"},{"text":"Okay.","index":526,"end_time":1337.15,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1336.71,"speaker_name":"Carmen Williams"},{"text":"Amazing.","index":527,"end_time":1337.71,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1337.15,"speaker_name":"Carmen Williams"},{"text":"Okay.","index":528,"end_time":1339.23,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1338.59,"speaker_name":"Carmen Williams"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":529,"end_time":1339.99,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1339.63,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And.","index":530,"end_time":1340.23,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1339.99,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And I. I just.","index":531,"end_time":1341.47,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1340.23,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I totally hear you on the.","index":532,"end_time":1342.43,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1341.47,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Drinking through a fire hose.","index":533,"end_time":1343.35,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1342.43,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So I. I do want to be, like, strategic about how I''m passing through the information because all at once I feel like is.","index":534,"end_time":1348.75,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1343.35,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Is overwhelming and.","index":535,"end_time":1350.43,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1348.75,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And may.","index":536,"end_time":1351.58,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1351.22,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"May produce, like, a cloudy image of what we''re doing.","index":537,"end_time":1354.26,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1351.58,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We have a lot of documents of everything that we do.","index":538,"end_time":1356.78,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1354.82,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay, let me just set this record straight.","index":539,"end_time":1358.66,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1356.78,"speaker_name":"Carmen Williams"},{"text":"I''m not here to cut you guys out.","index":540,"end_time":1360.82,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1358.66,"speaker_name":"Carmen Williams"},{"text":"I''m not here to evaluate you.","index":541,"end_time":1362.26,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1360.82,"speaker_name":"Carmen Williams"},{"text":"I don''t have any.","index":542,"end_time":1363.3,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1362.26,"speaker_name":"Carmen Williams"},{"text":"I.","index":543,"end_time":1363.7,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1363.38,"speaker_name":"Carmen Williams"},{"text":"That''s what I told Josh and Rob is I work like.","index":544,"end_time":1366.62,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1363.7,"speaker_name":"Carmen Williams"},{"text":"I''m not someone who brings my posse with me, adaptable and work with.","index":545,"end_time":1371.18,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1366.62,"speaker_name":"Carmen Williams"},{"text":"So please do not worry about that.","index":546,"end_time":1373.38,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1371.18,"speaker_name":"Carmen Williams"},{"text":"Give me as much as I can, because I want to get up to speed so I can be useful and.","index":547,"end_time":1379.62,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1373.7,"speaker_name":"Carmen Williams"},{"text":"And make what you''re doing better.","index":548,"end_time":1381.46,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1379.7,"speaker_name":"Carmen Williams"},{"text":"But I don''t want it stuck together in a.","index":549,"end_time":1384.5,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1382.26,"speaker_name":"Carmen Williams"},{"text":"It needs to be broken apart by campaigns, not by a big chunk called New North.","index":550,"end_time":1390.74,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1385.22,"speaker_name":"Carmen Williams"},{"text":"Yeah, Yeah, I agree with that.","index":551,"end_time":1392.5,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1391.06,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Because we''re working together and we have to have media channels and campaigns that are performing together, not.","index":552,"end_time":1401.14,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1394.42,"speaker_name":"Carmen Williams"},{"text":"You know what I mean?","index":553,"end_time":1402.1,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1401.3,"speaker_name":"Carmen Williams"},{"text":"Yeah, absolutely.","index":554,"end_time":1403.14,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1402.26,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay.","index":555,"end_time":1404,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1403.72,"speaker_name":"Carmen Williams"},{"text":"Amazing.","index":556,"end_time":1404.44,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1404,"speaker_name":"Carmen Williams"},{"text":"Thank you so much.","index":557,"end_time":1405.32,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1404.44,"speaker_name":"Carmen Williams"},{"text":"Yeah, it was great to meet you.","index":558,"end_time":1406.68,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1405.48,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Send as much over as you can.","index":559,"end_time":1408.52,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1407.08,"speaker_name":"Carmen Williams"},{"text":"And don''t worry, I''ll.","index":560,"end_time":1409.48,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1408.52,"speaker_name":"Carmen Williams"},{"text":"I''ll survive the drinking from the fire hose.","index":561,"end_time":1412.68,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1409.48,"speaker_name":"Carmen Williams"},{"text":"All right, Sounds good.","index":562,"end_time":1413.8,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1412.76,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Great to meet you, Carmen.","index":563,"end_time":1414.84,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1413.8,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Thank you.","index":564,"end_time":1415.2,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1414.84,"speaker_name":"Carmen Williams"},{"text":"Take care.","index":565,"end_time":1415.64,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1415.2,"speaker_name":"Carmen Williams"},{"text":"Bye.","index":566,"end_time":1416.6,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1416.12,"speaker_name":"Carmen Williams"}],"dateString":"2026-01-22T18:00:00.000Z","host_email":"colin.costigan@marketersindemand.com","meeting_link":"https://us02web.zoom.us/j/84520841876?pwd=ou1EAHiZfSDoYnxjUsawbnFk1lcJtL.1","participants":["carmen@ptoexchange.com,colin.costigan@marketersindemand.com","carmen@ptoexchange.com"],"transcript_url":"https://app.fireflies.ai/view/01KFERZMY9M9H1JJT8S3SF8XR2","organizer_email":"colin.costigan@marketersindemand.com"}'::jsonb,
    '{"label":"neutral","confidence":0.84,"bullets":["Clarified scope of agency work includes SEO, AI optimization, and ABM but no lead management.","Carmen requested access to client portal and campaign documentation to ramp up strategic oversight.","Colin confirmed new campaigns and content are underway but not yet deployed or live.","Audit revealed 95% of HubSpot properties unused and major CRM data issues spanning multiple years.","Agreed to align strategy deliverables and streamline metrics for funnel and campaign performance."],"highlights":[{"quote":"95% of properties are not even being filled in.","speaker":"Colin Costigan"},{"quote":"I believe the goal is for me to take over and drive and direct this stuff.","speaker":"Carmen Williams"},{"quote":"Everything that I''m pitching from the audit is just a recommendation.","speaker":"Colin Costigan"}],"topics":["CRM","strategy","audit","ABM","HubSpot","campaigns"],"model":"openai/gpt-4-vision","version":1,"generated_at":"2026-01-22T00:00:00Z"}'::jsonb,
    '{"fireflies_summary":{"notes":"## **Agency Structure and Collaboration**\n\nThe marketing efforts for **PTO Exchange** are managed by **Marketers In Demand**, which owns **four agencies** specializing in performance marketing, content, AI-driven automation, and web development, all working collaboratively within a unified project management and communication system (00:58).\n\n- **Colin Costigan**, as **Head of Client Operations**, leads system and process development while supported by strategists and account directors managing day-to-day client communications.\n- Clients gain access to capabilities across all agencies simultaneously, streamlining service delivery and cross-functional expertise.\n- This structure allows faster onboarding and integrated campaign execution across channels, improving agility and resource use.\n- The collaborative approach is designed to deliver cohesive marketing strategies rather than fragmented agency efforts.\n\n## **Current Marketing Strategy and Campaign Development**\n\nThe team focuses on **account-based marketing (ABM)** using cost-effective automation tools outside of HubSpot to target cold outreach and track engagement, emphasizing first meeting bookings as the primary sales conversion goal (03:08).\n\n- The strategy heavily leverages **PTO Exchange’s benchmark report data** for industry-specific targeting over 1-, 3-, and 5-year periods.\n- Four new **industry-focused campaign ideas** were pitched and approved in the prior week, with landing pages and email content currently in development, aiming to expand beyond healthcare and HR sectors (12:27).\n- Campaign assets include lead magnets like infographics and playbooks designed to increase lead engagement and nurture prospects.\n- Web pages optimized with AI and SEO are written but remain unpublished pending final review by **Josh**, limiting current campaign activation (05:19).\n\n## **HubSpot Usage and Audit Findings**\n\nThe current **HubSpot instance** spans Marketing Hub Enterprise, Sales Hub Professional, Service Hub Professional, and CMS but suffers from significant data quality and process issues, with **95% of properties not filled**, causing misinformation and inefficiency (09:51, 10:44).\n\n- The audit highlights convoluted source tracking with multiple properties for the same data, complicating accurate attribution and reporting.\n- Lead management processes appear disconnected from sales pipeline progression, with unclear handoffs between marketing-sourced leads and sales-qualified opportunities (10:57, 11:27).\n- The database contains **238,000 contact records**, but only **fewer than 100 deals** in the sales pipeline, indicating a large volume of unqualified or stale data (17:29).\n- Colin and Carmen agreed that cleaning the database and implementing a clear funnel with measurable conversion points from contact to opportunity is critical.\n- HubSpot’s limitation on cold outreach requires outside tools for ABM cold emails, reinforcing the hybrid tool strategy.\n\n## **Lead Management and Sales Alignment**\n\nMarketing’s primary objective is to deliver **first meetings** for sales, but converting interest into booked appointments remains a challenge across industries, with many leads showing initial engagement but failing to respond to calls (16:47).\n\n- Colin clarified that marketing executes campaigns and lead generation but does not currently own lead management or sales process alignment.\n- Sales teams add contacts from external sources like ZoomInfo, adding volume but complicating funnel clarity (18:31).\n- Carmen emphasized the need to define and potentially redesign lead management processes within HubSpot to ensure smooth lead qualification and follow-up.\n- The team plans to collaborate closely with **Josh** to align marketing campaigns and lead handling with sales workflows.\n\n## **Next Steps and Onboarding**\n\nCarmen will be invited to the **client portal (Pulse)** containing all strategic documents, campaign plans, and reporting to get up to speed and begin driving strategy development (07:48).\n\n- Weekly reporting meetings occur on Thursdays where campaign performance and ad metrics are reviewed.\n- Carmen aims to conduct a strategic audit and develop a recommended marketing plan within **6 to 9 weeks**, focusing on business understanding, personas, positioning, and ABM enhancement.\n- Colin will provide selective documentation and access to reports from tools like **Factors AI** and **RB2B** used for website traffic de-anonymization.\n- The team agreed to establish a cadence for ongoing knowledge sharing and collaboration to refine the marketing and lead management approach.\n\n## **Strategic Perspectives and Challenges**\n\nCarmen’s core focus is on understanding **PTO Exchange’s market, personas, and unique positioning** to build a more outbound, targeted approach that complements existing inbound efforts (14:54).\n\n- She sees potential in shifting more effort to outbound ABM but recognizes HubSpot’s cold outreach limits, requiring creative integrations.\n- Colin expressed openness to process and system redesigns in HubSpot to better fit strategic needs and operational preferences.\n- Both emphasized partnership and alignment to improve campaign focus, measurement, and ultimately, appointment setting rates.\n- The urgency of cleaning and organizing the large contact database was highlighted as foundational to improving marketing effectiveness and sales funnel clarity.","outline":null,"keywords":["HubSpot","Account-Based Marketing","PTO Exchange","Lead Management","Campaign Strategy","Client Portal"],"overview":"- **Agency Collaboration:** Marketing managed by four specialized agencies enhances service delivery and accelerates campaign execution.  \n- **ABM Strategy:** Focused on cost-effective automation tools for cold outreach; aims for first meeting bookings as key sales goal.  \n- **HubSpot Issues:** 95% of HubSpot data properties are unfilled, complicating reporting and lead tracking.  \n- **Lead Management Challenges:** Marketing generates leads but lacks ownership over lead management and sales processes.  \n- **Next Steps:** Carmen will conduct a strategic audit and develop a marketing plan within 6 to 9 weeks.  \n- **Strategic Focus:** Emphasizing outbound ABM while addressing HubSpot’s limitations; improving database organization is urgent.","action_items":"\n**Colin Costigan**\nInvite Carmen to the client portal named Pulse with access to all strategic documents and campaign details (08:10)\nShare access to campaign proposals and scope of work documentation to help Carmen understand current and planned initiatives (14:09)\nProvide Carmen with reports from external tools (factors AI, RB2B), though direct access may not be possible (22:11)\nContinue weekly reporting on ad campaign performance and prepare to share updates in upcoming internal calls on Mondays or Thursdays (08:35)\n\n**Carmen Williams**\nReview all materials and client portal access once provided to familiarize herself with strategy, campaigns, and reporting (08:25)\nConduct deeper discussions with Josh about sales lead management and internal processes to identify gaps between marketing efforts and sales conversions (15:59)\nDevelop her own strategic audit and recommended plan for PTO Exchange marketing within the next 6-9 weeks and ensure alignment with Colin’s team (20:01)\nAssess the use of HubSpot and related tools for target account marketing and lead management processes (20:39)\nProbe existing lead database quality and segmentation during upcoming audits or meetings (17:40)\n"},"migrated_from":"contract_meetings","original_id":"6d52c840-93c5-4c87-bffe-39439e5b8172","master_marketer":{"status":"migrated"}}'::jsonb,
