-- Meeting: Aligned Growth Engine | Alignment Meeting (2026-01-22 14:00:00+00)
WITH new_meeting AS (
  INSERT INTO compass_meetings (contract_id, meeting_date, source, external_id, title, participants, duration_seconds, recording_url, transcript, sentiment, raw_metadata, created_at, updated_at)
  VALUES (
    'ae79e392-17c6-477b-8c36-88db208d3b12',
    '2026-01-22 14:00:00+00',
    'fireflies',
    '01KF3KCYHMX1K6JD5KTR17QBYH',
    'Aligned Growth Engine | Alignment Meeting',
    '{"Dan Rényi","Matt Forkas","Justin Brown","Colin Costigan","Len Forkas","oswaldoreyes-chica","Tristan"}'::text[],
    4216,
    'https://us02web.zoom.us/j/88208688412?pwd=Ccbr4IbNbprAsghGj1Gu2f61wjMpcV.1',
    '{"id":"01KF3KCYHMX1K6JD5KTR17QBYH","title":"Aligned Growth Engine | Alignment Meeting","summary":{"notes":"## **Lead Generation and Qualification**\n\nThe main focus is to increase the number of high-quality inquiries from carriers to about **20 per month**, shifting from the current rate of approximately **4 to 5 inquiries monthly** (14:47).\n\n- **Matt Forkas** explained that inquiries primarily come via direct relationships rather than forms or online submissions, with most leads entering through personal emails and manual Salesforce entry.\n- There are two main lead types: **soft inquiries**, usually low quality or unviable leads, and **inquiries**, which represent active, promising projects; qualification is based mostly on manual evaluation and factors like property size and proximity to towers.\n- Salesforce is currently used more as a project management tool than a marketing or lead-tracking system, with manual input for contacts and project statuses, limiting automated tracking and source attribution.\n- Increasing monthly inquiries to **20** is seen as critical, with a strong emphasis on maintaining lead quality rather than just volume, as **Matt** highlighted that inquiries from carriers themselves are almost always solid leads.\n\n## **Market Relationships and Regional Growth**\n\nThe business depends heavily on strong carrier and site acquisition firm relationships, particularly with **Verizon and Mastec in the Bawa market**, which drive most active inquiries (32:05).\n\n- This relationship model is considered the \"golden ticket\" because carriers provide early access to search rings and opportunities, enabling Milestone to onboard multiple municipal properties efficiently.\n- Expansion into new markets relies on replicating these relationships, especially focusing on **municipal landowners** who often control multiple properties, creating more efficient growth opportunities.\n- **Matt** identified challenges in other markets, such as North Carolina, where lower land quality and easier alternatives for carriers reduce the attractiveness of sites compared to the DMV region.\n- The strategy prioritizes onboarding high-quality land in new markets to secure carrier interest before scaling outreach and marketing efforts.\n\n## **Sales and Outreach Strategy**\n\nOutreach messaging is tailored based on the audience, with **service needs and revenue sharing** being the most effective hooks for engagement (38:42).\n\n- Municipal property owners respond well to service and revenue opportunities, with public safety needs sometimes outweighing financial incentives.\n- Private landowners mostly focus on revenue potential, and outreach to them is limited due to lower conversion rates and less strategic value.\n- The **existing reputation** and track record of Milestone Towers play a key role in differentiating from competitors and gaining trust with both carriers and landowners.\n- Outreach relies on personal contacts and calls rather than mass marketing, reflecting the niche and relationship-driven nature of the business.\n\n## **Technology and Process Automation**\n\nCurrent systems lack automation, with manual data entry and limited use of analytics; automation will become necessary when lead volume exceeds about **20 inquiries per month** (53:41).\n\n- Salesforce fields often lack consistent data entry, requiring clearer definitions and processes to ensure quality and uniform reporting.\n- Email and outreach activity are not currently tracked for performance metrics such as response or meeting rates.\n- The team recognizes a need for process improvements, including possible AI or automation tools to validate and input data more efficiently without sacrificing the personalized attention required for these leads.\n- Investment in automation or additional staff will be considered as inquiry volume grows to maintain quality and responsiveness.\n\n## **Marketing Budget and Investment Strategy**\n\nThere is cautiousness around committing to large ad spend, with an initial budget discussion centering around **$8,000 to $10,000 per month** for agency and campaign costs, with ad spend considered supplemental (01:01:16).\n\n- **Justin Brown** and **Oswaldo Reyes-Chica** emphasized the importance of testing with a pilot campaign to prove value before scaling investment, given past experiences with limited results and concerns over budget risk.\n- Paid advertising directly targeting carriers is seen as unlikely to be effective; instead, campaigns would support existing outreach efforts with tailored content and multiple touchpoints.\n- The team stressed that marketing must be outcome-driven, focusing on measurable lead quality and pipeline progression rather than superficial metrics.\n- The roadmap for marketing spend and activities will be refined to balance investment size with expected results, avoiding underfunding that could yield no meaningful returns.\n\n## **Next Steps and Timeline**\n\nThe upcoming meeting will present a detailed **roadmap and financial model** for marketing strategy and budget allocation, targeting **Friday at 9:10 AM** to accommodate carrier meeting schedules (01:09:08).\n\n- Colin Costigan will coordinate calendar invites and follow-ups to finalize scheduling.\n- The roadmap session will define clear goals, budget scenarios, and expected outcomes to guide decision-making.\n- Deliverables will include case studies, presentations, and potentially video content designed to support outreach and relationship-building efforts.\n- The focus will be on replicating successful relationship models in new markets and supplementing outreach with strategic marketing materials.","outline":null,"keywords":["Salesforce","Lead Management","Carrier Relationships","Marketing Budget","Municipal Landowners","Inquiry Qualification"],"overview":"- **Increased Inquiries Goal:** Aim for **20 high-quality inquiries monthly**, up from 4-5; quality over quantity remains key.  \n- **Carrier Relationships Crucial:** Strong ties with **Verizon and Mastec** drive inquiries; they offer early access to opportunities.  \n- **Tailored Outreach Messaging:** Focus on service and revenue appeals for municipal owners; private landowners prefer revenue potential.  \n- **Need for Automation:** Current manual processes limit efficiency; improvements essential as inquiry volume grows past 20 monthly.  \n- **Cautious Marketing Budget:** Proposed **$8,000 to $10,000/month**; need pilot campaigns to evaluate before scaling investment.  \n- **Upcoming Financial Roadmap Meeting:** A session on **budget allocation** scheduled for **Friday** to set clear goals and expected outcomes.","action_items":"\n**Matt Forkas**\nProvide any available carrier build plan numbers for the upcoming year to assist with forecasting and marketing strategy (46:47)\nShare existing key contact and project data from Salesforce to support deeper pipeline analysis and marketing alignment (00:00)\nConfirm internal preferences and realities around inquiry volume and process automation threshold (estimated 20/month) (53:41)\nCollaborate with marketing team to specify marketing collateral needs (case studies, presentations, videos) to support new market entry (56:36)\n\n**Colin Costigan**\nFollow up with scheduling a roadmap presentation meeting, offering booking links and accommodating Friday preference (01:08:44)\nDevelop standard definitions for development stages (soft inquiry, inquiry, candidate, etc.) to align data tracking and reporting (27:02)\nPrepare financial and marketing strategy roadmap based on client feedback for next meeting (00:00)\n\n**Justin Brown**\nLead creation of financial model and initial budget recommendations for marketing investment based on desired inquiry growth and realistic pilot scopes (8-10k suggested) (01:01:16)\nDevelop proposal for test campaigns balancing risk tolerance and expected outcomes, to build confidence and demonstrate value (01:03:48)\n\n**Oswaldo Reyes-Chica**\nProvide input on internal budget comfort level and feasibility of marketing spend to guide strategy development (01:02:17)\n\n**Dan Rényi**\nSupport discussion and modeling of automation needs triggered by inquiry volume growth (53:37)\n\n**Tristan Pelligrino**\nAssist with detailed review and analysis of historic marketing agency work outcomes vs expectations (22:06)\n"},"duration":70.26000213623047,"speakers":[{"id":0,"name":"Dan Rényi"},{"id":1,"name":"Matt Forkas"},{"id":2,"name":"Justin Brown"},{"id":3,"name":"Colin Costigan"},{"id":4,"name":"Len Forkas"},{"id":5,"name":"oswaldoreyes-chica"},{"id":6,"name":"Tristan"}],"sentences":[{"text":"Hey.","index":0,"end_time":10.2,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":9.92,"speaker_name":"Dan Rényi"},{"text":"Hey.","index":1,"end_time":10.64,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":10.2,"speaker_name":"Dan Rényi"},{"text":"Hey, Len.","index":2,"end_time":12.96,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":12.08,"speaker_name":"Dan Rényi"},{"text":"Hey, good morning.","index":3,"end_time":14.08,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":13.28,"speaker_name":"Matt Forkas"},{"text":"Yeah, Justin''s here.","index":4,"end_time":19.12,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":16.48,"speaker_name":"Dan Rényi"},{"text":"You stocked up on all your eggs and toilet paper lens?","index":5,"end_time":26.74,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":22.4,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"Not really.","index":6,"end_time":28.85,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":28.41,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I''m in the Dominican Republic.","index":7,"end_time":30.33,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":28.85,"speaker_name":"Len Forkas"},{"text":"Okay.","index":8,"end_time":31.29,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":30.89,"speaker_name":"oswaldoreyes-chica"},{"text":"So you''re not gonna get hit by the snowstorm there.","index":9,"end_time":33.29,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":31.29,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"Yeah, just the opposite.","index":10,"end_time":34.73,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":33.45,"speaker_name":"Len Forkas"},{"text":"You might get.","index":11,"end_time":35.49,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":34.81,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"You might just get unfortunately stranded in.","index":12,"end_time":38.33,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":35.49,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"In the Caribbean while we all are digging out.","index":13,"end_time":41.93,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":39.29,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"Yeah, that''s.","index":14,"end_time":43.21,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":42.25,"speaker_name":"Len Forkas"},{"text":"I know.","index":15,"end_time":43.85,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":43.29,"speaker_name":"oswaldoreyes-chica"},{"text":"I''ve been lamenting that.","index":16,"end_time":45.21,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":43.85,"speaker_name":"Len Forkas"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":17,"end_time":45.93,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":45.45,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"How much snow are you supposed to be getting?","index":18,"end_time":50.33,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":48.41,"speaker_name":"Dan Rényi"},{"text":"They''re saying could be.","index":19,"end_time":54.13,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":51.37,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"It could be five inches.","index":20,"end_time":55.37,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":54.21,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"It could be 22 inches.","index":21,"end_time":56.85,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":55.37,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":22,"end_time":57.65,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":57.09,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"So.","index":23,"end_time":58.21,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":57.81,"speaker_name":"Dan Rényi"},{"text":"So one to two feet is like basically what they''re saying where I live and where Tristan lives because we live pretty close to each other.","index":24,"end_time":67.33,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":58.93,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"Not exactly.","index":25,"end_time":69.009,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":68.29,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"Like a ton of snowplows down here.","index":26,"end_time":70.73,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":69.009,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"So, like when we get hit it, it.","index":27,"end_time":73.17,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":70.73,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"It''s.","index":28,"end_time":73.73,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":73.17,"speaker_name":"Matt Forkas"},{"text":"His kids will probably be out of school for like.","index":29,"end_time":75.97,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":73.89,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"Yeah, it''s like spring break.","index":30,"end_time":78.37,"speaker_id":6,"start_time":76.69,"speaker_name":"Tristan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":31,"end_time":79.11,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":78.79,"speaker_name":"Dan Rényi"},{"text":"And it''s funny.","index":32,"end_time":82.83,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":82.07,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"It''s not because, you know, everybody jokes that it''s like everybody freaks out in the south when there''s snow.","index":33,"end_time":88.99,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":82.83,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"It''s like, well, we just don''t have the infrastructure and like the actual ability to clean the roads.","index":34,"end_time":95.39,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":88.99,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"So it is interesting.","index":35,"end_time":97.43,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":95.39,"speaker_name":"Dan Rényi"},{"text":"All right, so is this going to be everybody today, Lynn?","index":36,"end_time":101.59,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":98.07,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"I think so, yeah.","index":37,"end_time":103.91,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":103.11,"speaker_name":"Len Forkas"},{"text":"We got Matt and I''m not sure if Oswaldo is joining us.","index":38,"end_time":106.59,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":103.91,"speaker_name":"Len Forkas"},{"text":"Let me check.","index":39,"end_time":107.19,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":106.59,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"Yeah, that was what I was wondering.","index":40,"end_time":108.71,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":107.19,"speaker_name":"Matt Forkas"},{"text":"It''s on his calend.","index":41,"end_time":109.99,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":108.95,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I assume they''ll be popping in.","index":42,"end_time":113.73,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":112.05,"speaker_name":"Len Forkas"},{"text":"Did you guys have a chance to take a peek at the work that.","index":43,"end_time":123.01,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":120.21,"speaker_name":"Len Forkas"},{"text":"Yes.","index":44,"end_time":124.25,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":123.81,"speaker_name":"Len Forkas"},{"text":"And had done in priority last year?","index":45,"end_time":128.77,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":124.25,"speaker_name":"Len Forkas"},{"text":"Yes, we did.","index":46,"end_time":130.29,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":129.41,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We have that slide deck as well.","index":47,"end_time":133.01,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":130.69,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Hopefully that''ll get.","index":48,"end_time":134.69,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":133.73,"speaker_name":"Len Forkas"},{"text":"That''ll move things forward a little bit faster for you guys.","index":49,"end_time":137.73,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":134.77,"speaker_name":"Len Forkas"},{"text":"Yeah, absolutely.","index":50,"end_time":139.15,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":138.11,"speaker_name":"Dan Rényi"},{"text":"Colin.","index":51,"end_time":139.99,"speaker_id":6,"start_time":139.55,"speaker_name":"Tristan"},{"text":"I think we can get rolling and if and when Ozzy jumps in, he''ll jump in.","index":52,"end_time":144.27,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":139.99,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"Sounds like a plan.","index":53,"end_time":145.63,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":144.75,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"All right, well, thanks, Matt and Len for joining today''s call and making time for this.","index":54,"end_time":152.03,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":146.75,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So this is the second meeting in our three step aligned growth engine process.","index":55,"end_time":155.87,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":152.03,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Last time we got really, really great context from you guys on your business.","index":56,"end_time":160.11,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":156.99,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Your goals around, you know, location and geographical expansion, your desire to differentiate, you know, from really expanding like the.","index":57,"end_time":168.85,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":160.59,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"The builders that you''re working with Today we''re going to get a lot more tactical.","index":58,"end_time":172.49,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":168.85,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Matt, I know in your email you mentioned not wanting to share access to.","index":59,"end_time":176.61,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":173.37,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"To Salesforce but being willing to do some screen sharing today and I think that would be a really strong use of our time.","index":60,"end_time":182.65,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":176.61,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So we, We''re.","index":61,"end_time":185.01,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":184.25,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I want to dive in, understand the data, understand, you know, the.","index":62,"end_time":187.77,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":185.01,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"The properties in Place the current flow of information, how it''s moving from one place to another, how someone knows exactly what their next step is.","index":63,"end_time":195.61,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":187.77,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So I''m going to ask a lot of questions.","index":64,"end_time":198.97,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":197.37,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Some of them might feel repetitive, but one thing is I''m going to be upfront.","index":65,"end_time":204.09,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":198.97,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So, you know, when we land on, like, what metrics we need to align on for how marketing is going to best assist, milestone.","index":66,"end_time":210.81,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":204.09,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"It can''t just be more leads, right?","index":67,"end_time":213.25,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":211.77,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"It needs to be what number of leads.","index":68,"end_time":215.13,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":213.25,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"If you say, like, we need to focus on quality, okay, well, what are the quality benchmarks?","index":69,"end_time":220.21,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":215.77,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"What is the criteria that we''re establishing for quality?","index":70,"end_time":222.61,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":220.21,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So we really need to dive into those and have strong definitions.","index":71,"end_time":225.36,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":222.61,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And then that leads to a really productive third meeting, which is our roadmap, where we go through and present what we propose as your marketing strategy.","index":72,"end_time":232.95,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":225.91,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Does that sound like a game plan?","index":73,"end_time":234.31,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":233.03,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Sure.","index":74,"end_time":235.11,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":234.71,"speaker_name":"Matt Forkas"},{"text":"All right, so kind of want to start with the basics and hop into Salesforce and we can talk about lead flow and conversion points.","index":75,"end_time":245.67,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":236.71,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I know that you mentioned Salesforce isn''t currently being used maybe as intentionally as it should be.","index":76,"end_time":252.15,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":246.23,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So I just want to understand, like, what data lives in there, what''s living in Matt''s head, What''s living in Matt''s inbox, You know, where.","index":77,"end_time":259.93,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":252.87,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Where are these things living right now?","index":78,"end_time":261.81,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":259.93,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":79,"end_time":265.17,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":264.69,"speaker_name":"oswaldoreyes-chica"},{"text":"So right now, Salesforce is being used as a project management tool.","index":80,"end_time":269.81,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":265.25,"speaker_name":"Matt Forkas"},{"text":"When a new lead come.","index":81,"end_time":271.41,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":269.89,"speaker_name":"Matt Forkas"},{"text":"Well, yeah, when a new lead comes in, it''s coming directly into the mailbox, into one of our mailboxes.","index":82,"end_time":277.37,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":271.49,"speaker_name":"Matt Forkas"},{"text":"Usually mine, or sometimes it''s lens, or sometimes it''s Aussie, but predominantly it''s mine.","index":83,"end_time":282.53,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":277.37,"speaker_name":"Matt Forkas"},{"text":"And then that will get.","index":84,"end_time":287.26,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":285.1,"speaker_name":"Matt Forkas"},{"text":"Well, let me just share my screen.","index":85,"end_time":288.9,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":287.82,"speaker_name":"Dan Rényi"},{"text":"Hold on.","index":86,"end_time":289.42,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":288.9,"speaker_name":"Dan Rényi"},{"text":"Yep.","index":87,"end_time":290.3,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":289.74,"speaker_name":"Dan Rényi"},{"text":"Sorry.","index":88,"end_time":305.26,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":304.78,"speaker_name":"Matt Forkas"},{"text":"I go old school on Salesforce.","index":89,"end_time":307.1,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":305.42,"speaker_name":"Matt Forkas"},{"text":"You know, I see more, I think, Tristan, we''ve joked about this before.","index":90,"end_time":310.98,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":307.9,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"More and more people turn the lightning experience off than ever actually use it.","index":91,"end_time":314.38,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":310.98,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Like the first thing you do.","index":92,"end_time":315.74,"speaker_id":6,"start_time":314.82,"speaker_name":"Tristan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":93,"end_time":316.18,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":315.74,"speaker_name":"Len Forkas"},{"text":"Thank you.","index":94,"end_time":316.7,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":316.18,"speaker_name":"oswaldoreyes-chica"},{"text":"Thank you.","index":95,"end_time":317.3,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":316.7,"speaker_name":"Matt Forkas"},{"text":"At least a gets very bothered by that.","index":96,"end_time":319.82,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":317.3,"speaker_name":"Matt Forkas"},{"text":"I''m like, dude, it''s just.","index":97,"end_time":320.98,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":319.82,"speaker_name":"Matt Forkas"},{"text":"It just works, man.","index":98,"end_time":322.34,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":321.14,"speaker_name":"Matt Forkas"},{"text":"So we didn''t.","index":99,"end_time":327.14,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":325.46,"speaker_name":"Matt Forkas"},{"text":"I did not build this.","index":100,"end_time":328.14,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":327.14,"speaker_name":"Matt Forkas"},{"text":"I think the person that built this was previous employee a long time ago.","index":101,"end_time":333.06,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":328.14,"speaker_name":"Matt Forkas"},{"text":"I don''t know if they.","index":102,"end_time":333.86,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":333.06,"speaker_name":"Matt Forkas"},{"text":"Did we hire someone to build this?","index":103,"end_time":336.02,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":334.26,"speaker_name":"Matt Forkas"},{"text":"No, it was the Chris.","index":104,"end_time":339.38,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":337.3,"speaker_name":"Len Forkas"},{"text":"Chris.","index":105,"end_time":340.1,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":339.7,"speaker_name":"Matt Forkas"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":106,"end_time":340.48,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":340.1,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"So we have this broken down yet into our contacts, into our projects, and then our leases with the.","index":107,"end_time":351.99,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":343.19,"speaker_name":"Matt Forkas"},{"text":"With the carriers.","index":108,"end_time":352.87,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":351.99,"speaker_name":"Matt Forkas"},{"text":"So typically when a new site comes in from email from the carrier or sad act firm or potentially a landowner, it gets added in as a. Technically, as a candidate, it''s called Ms. Site.","index":109,"end_time":370.65,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":352.95,"speaker_name":"Matt Forkas"},{"text":"And then from there we just add more details on what the, what the status of the project is.","index":110,"end_time":380.65,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":370.89,"speaker_name":"Matt Forkas"},{"text":"And then we have these two differentiators, soft inquiry and inquiry.","index":111,"end_time":385.93,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":380.97,"speaker_name":"Matt Forkas"},{"text":"I would consider soft inquiry like a less quality lead.","index":112,"end_time":393.22,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":386.17,"speaker_name":"Matt Forkas"},{"text":"Then an inquiry would actually be like an active, a more active project.","index":113,"end_time":397.3,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":393.3,"speaker_name":"Matt Forkas"},{"text":"So that''s really the only two tiers.","index":114,"end_time":400.02,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":398.34,"speaker_name":"Matt Forkas"},{"text":"If it''s anything else, I won''t really input it.","index":115,"end_time":402.74,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":400.02,"speaker_name":"Matt Forkas"},{"text":"And you''re doing all of that manually.","index":116,"end_time":405.26,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":403.62,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So you''re checking in on like the, the site name.","index":117,"end_time":407.7,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":405.26,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Is all this coming through the form, you know, pretty consistently as far as information or there''s no form.","index":118,"end_time":413.14,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":407.78,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Oh, there''s no form.","index":119,"end_time":414.5,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":413.62,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"They''re just sending a straight email.","index":120,"end_time":415.78,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":414.5,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"There is no.","index":121,"end_time":416.9,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":416.02,"speaker_name":"Matt Forkas"},{"text":"The, the carriers don''t like, they wouldn''t.","index":122,"end_time":421.18,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":416.98,"speaker_name":"Matt Forkas"},{"text":"I''ve yet to hear any carrier using someone''s website to submit a, an inquiry.","index":123,"end_time":429.14,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":422.22,"speaker_name":"Matt Forkas"},{"text":"I mean it''s all these relationships are very interpersonal.","index":124,"end_time":432.62,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":429.14,"speaker_name":"Matt Forkas"},{"text":"You know, we''re talking to these guys every week.","index":125,"end_time":435.98,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":433.9,"speaker_name":"Matt Forkas"},{"text":"We don''t.","index":126,"end_time":437.02,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":436.38,"speaker_name":"Matt Forkas"},{"text":"The, the, the on the carrier end, the pool of people to really talk to, to get business is very small.","index":127,"end_time":443.02,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":437.02,"speaker_name":"Matt Forkas"},{"text":"So you know, outbound marketing to drive more track to the website to get more leads there.","index":128,"end_time":449.07,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":443.66,"speaker_name":"Matt Forkas"},{"text":"We already, we already know who to talk to and we''re already talking to them, at least in this market.","index":129,"end_time":454.43,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":450.99,"speaker_name":"Matt Forkas"},{"text":"And we can talk a little bit more about what we need to do to get into new markets.","index":130,"end_time":459.27,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":454.91,"speaker_name":"Matt Forkas"},{"text":"But it certainly wouldn''t be involved with filling out a form on our website.","index":131,"end_time":462.99,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":459.27,"speaker_name":"Matt Forkas"},{"text":"The only thing that would make sense.","index":132,"end_time":465.55,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":463.87,"speaker_name":"Matt Forkas"},{"text":"Well, I think what we do is host our site list on our website and they can download that there.","index":133,"end_time":474.36,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":467.15,"speaker_name":"Matt Forkas"},{"text":"But yeah, it''s just, it''s old school.","index":134,"end_time":476.92,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":474.36,"speaker_name":"Matt Forkas"},{"text":"I mean it''s just straight into my inbox and then I''ll fill it in here.","index":135,"end_time":479.76,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":476.92,"speaker_name":"Matt Forkas"},{"text":"Gotcha.","index":136,"end_time":480.96,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":480.32,"speaker_name":"Dan Rényi"},{"text":"Okay, sorry and I, and I interrupted you with that question.","index":137,"end_time":484.72,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":482.32,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So continue.","index":138,"end_time":485.32,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":484.72,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"No, you''re good.","index":139,"end_time":486,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":485.32,"speaker_name":"oswaldoreyes-chica"},{"text":"No, so I''ll just fill out the pertinent information and then we, you know, you can sort of.","index":140,"end_time":494.24,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":486.72,"speaker_name":"Matt Forkas"},{"text":"Look at different projects at different stage of the development process.","index":141,"end_time":503.61,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":498.81,"speaker_name":"Matt Forkas"},{"text":"So these are all like our active inquiries that are sites that have not gone into zoning yet.","index":142,"end_time":510.49,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":503.85,"speaker_name":"Matt Forkas"},{"text":"And this would be for before I''ve made contact with the specific landowner.","index":143,"end_time":517.53,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":510.81,"speaker_name":"Matt Forkas"},{"text":"It would go until we finish our concept plans, our survey work or title reports and then we get pushed into, into zoning and then we have a different view for that, we have a different view for construction, we have a different view for the collocation management, modification management.","index":144,"end_time":536.08,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":519.61,"speaker_name":"Matt Forkas"},{"text":"So yeah, it''s pretty much just a PM tool that has been stapled together.","index":145,"end_time":543.12,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":538.64,"speaker_name":"Matt Forkas"},{"text":"But at the same time We''ve still got most of our key contacts in here.","index":146,"end_time":547.88,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":544,"speaker_name":"Matt Forkas"},{"text":"So Salesforce is like the only place to build something like this?","index":147,"end_time":551.56,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":547.88,"speaker_name":"Dan Rényi"},{"text":"I guess.","index":148,"end_time":552,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":551.56,"speaker_name":"Dan Rényi"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":149,"end_time":552.64,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":552.44,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And how are contacts coming in right now?","index":150,"end_time":554.44,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":552.64,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Manually.","index":151,"end_time":556.28,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":555.64,"speaker_name":"Matt Forkas"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":152,"end_time":557.32,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":556.84,"speaker_name":"Matt Forkas"},{"text":"Okay, so you get an inquiry via email or start a conversation with someone, you create them as a contact manually in Salesforce, if a.","index":153,"end_time":565.32,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":558.04,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"If a.","index":154,"end_time":566.04,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":565.4,"speaker_name":"Matt Forkas"},{"text":"If a set acquisition member or a carrier rep reaches out to me directly, nine times out of 10, they''re already in the system.","index":155,"end_time":575.8,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":566.6,"speaker_name":"Matt Forkas"},{"text":"If they''re not, and they have been in the system, if not, then y''.","index":156,"end_time":579.52,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":576.6,"speaker_name":"Matt Forkas"},{"text":"All have to manually add them.","index":157,"end_time":581.15,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":579.52,"speaker_name":"Dan Rényi"},{"text":"But that happens like maybe like once a.","index":158,"end_time":585.71,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":583.47,"speaker_name":"Matt Forkas"},{"text":"Once or twice a quarter.","index":159,"end_time":586.99,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":585.95,"speaker_name":"Matt Forkas"},{"text":"I''ll meet someone new.","index":160,"end_time":588.11,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":587.07,"speaker_name":"Matt Forkas"},{"text":"Okay.","index":161,"end_time":589.23,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":588.75,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And so, so this project management portion here is really how you''re tracking, like what we would consider opportunities or what Salesforce would typically refer to as an opportunity object.","index":162,"end_time":596.99,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":589.23,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I guess, like deals almost.","index":163,"end_time":600.59,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":598.51,"speaker_name":"Matt Forkas"},{"text":"Yeah, yeah, I guess.","index":164,"end_time":603.75,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":602.11,"speaker_name":"Matt Forkas"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":165,"end_time":604.11,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":603.75,"speaker_name":"Matt Forkas"},{"text":"Okay, so, yeah, you know, if we try to run, let''s just say, for example, a comparison of like, performance in 2024, performance in 2023, 2025.","index":166,"end_time":614.14,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":604.35,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Is there anything here that like, is there a field that designates so for development stage?","index":167,"end_time":621.9,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":615.1,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Is that what the second column is?","index":168,"end_time":623.82,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":621.9,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":169,"end_time":625.5,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":625.1,"speaker_name":"Matt Forkas"},{"text":"Dev status.","index":170,"end_time":626.1,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":625.5,"speaker_name":"Matt Forkas"},{"text":"Yep.","index":171,"end_time":626.5,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":626.1,"speaker_name":"Matt Forkas"},{"text":"Okay.","index":172,"end_time":626.82,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":626.5,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Dev status.","index":173,"end_time":627.54,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":626.82,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So what are the.","index":174,"end_time":629.38,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":627.54,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So it''s.","index":175,"end_time":629.78,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":629.38,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I know it''s soft inquiry and inquiry.","index":176,"end_time":631.5,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":629.78,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"What other statuses live there to kind of show, like where the deal currently sits?","index":177,"end_time":636.06,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":631.5,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yep.","index":178,"end_time":639.47,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":639.11,"speaker_name":"Matt Forkas"},{"text":"So inquiry to candidate.","index":179,"end_time":640.83,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":639.47,"speaker_name":"Matt Forkas"},{"text":"Candidate means that it''s been.","index":180,"end_time":642.15,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":640.83,"speaker_name":"Matt Forkas"},{"text":"This was a little loose, but candidate technically means that it''s been RF approved by the.","index":181,"end_time":649.27,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":643.91,"speaker_name":"Matt Forkas"},{"text":"By the carrier market.","index":182,"end_time":651.19,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":649.99,"speaker_name":"Matt Forkas"},{"text":"No candidate.","index":183,"end_time":654.55,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":653.51,"speaker_name":"Matt Forkas"},{"text":"Yeah, I guess technically inquiry to candidate.","index":184,"end_time":661.15,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":656.47,"speaker_name":"Matt Forkas"},{"text":"Candidate means that the landowner has been onboarded formally and that the carriers want to move forward.","index":185,"end_time":668.68,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":661.15,"speaker_name":"Matt Forkas"},{"text":"RF approval is a completely different stage.","index":186,"end_time":670.72,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":668.68,"speaker_name":"Matt Forkas"},{"text":"And then pre zoning would be collecting more due diligence and getting the required package for submitting the zoning application.","index":187,"end_time":679.52,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":672.48,"speaker_name":"Matt Forkas"},{"text":"Zoning is just currently in that zoning process.","index":188,"end_time":682.48,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":680,"speaker_name":"Matt Forkas"},{"text":"Pre construction, self explanatory, active construction, in service and then in service is when the.","index":189,"end_time":691.28,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":683.36,"speaker_name":"Matt Forkas"},{"text":"The journey''s over.","index":190,"end_time":692.24,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":691.28,"speaker_name":"Matt Forkas"},{"text":"And if the site''s killed for whatever reason or put on hold, then we.","index":191,"end_time":696.76,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":692.72,"speaker_name":"Matt Forkas"},{"text":"Just put either of these two.","index":192,"end_time":698.24,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":696.76,"speaker_name":"Dan Rényi"},{"text":"Gotcha.","index":193,"end_time":699.2,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":698.48,"speaker_name":"Dan Rényi"},{"text":"Earlier you said the difference between soft inquiry and inquiry was.","index":194,"end_time":702.88,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":699.84,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Soft inquiry is less quality.","index":195,"end_time":704.56,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":703.04,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Can we dive into exactly what you mean there or how you''re determining that?","index":196,"end_time":707.2,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":704.56,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Is that all manual gut feeling?","index":197,"end_time":709.12,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":707.2,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Is there like a baseline number?","index":198,"end_time":710.48,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":709.12,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, I mean, I think with the.","index":199,"end_time":713.2,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":711.68,"speaker_name":"Matt Forkas"},{"text":"Like, I''ll look at any.","index":200,"end_time":718.05,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":715.41,"speaker_name":"Matt Forkas"},{"text":"I''ll input any inquiry we get, right.","index":201,"end_time":721.13,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":718.05,"speaker_name":"Matt Forkas"},{"text":"Whether it''s bad or good, and then I. I determine whether it''s bad or good based on A few set of criteria.","index":202,"end_time":726.29,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":721.13,"speaker_name":"Matt Forkas"},{"text":"So, one, what the objective of that particular search ring is.","index":203,"end_time":731.49,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":726.29,"speaker_name":"Matt Forkas"},{"text":"For example, a lot of the Verizon work the past couple years has been high rent, relocation program, and those typically are not likely to go through.","index":204,"end_time":748.49,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":733.65,"speaker_name":"Matt Forkas"},{"text":"I''ll still look at them, but I wouldn''t call them a real.","index":205,"end_time":751.05,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":748.57,"speaker_name":"Matt Forkas"},{"text":"A real winner.","index":206,"end_time":752.97,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":751.93,"speaker_name":"Matt Forkas"},{"text":"And then if I get.","index":207,"end_time":756.09,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":754.73,"speaker_name":"Matt Forkas"},{"text":"And this happens quite a bit where a landowner.","index":208,"end_time":760.25,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":756.41,"speaker_name":"Matt Forkas"},{"text":"A landowner will reach out to us directly saying, hey, I want a tower on my land, and then he sends me his coordinates, I look at it, and I''ll input it in as an inquiry, a soft inquiry, and then I''ll.","index":209,"end_time":771.96,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":760.41,"speaker_name":"Matt Forkas"},{"text":"I''ll just look at the parcel really quick.","index":210,"end_time":773.96,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":771.96,"speaker_name":"Matt Forkas"},{"text":"If it''s three acres and, you know, if it''s really close to an existing tower, if the coverage looks good in that area, then I''ll just.","index":211,"end_time":784.32,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":773.96,"speaker_name":"Matt Forkas"},{"text":"I''ll just kill it from there.","index":212,"end_time":786.96,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":785.52,"speaker_name":"Matt Forkas"},{"text":"Inquiry requires a little bit more.","index":213,"end_time":790.88,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":788.8,"speaker_name":"Matt Forkas"},{"text":"You know, do we.","index":214,"end_time":792.08,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":791.2,"speaker_name":"Matt Forkas"},{"text":"Do we actually have a place to place it?","index":215,"end_time":795.68,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":794.2,"speaker_name":"Matt Forkas"},{"text":"Does it competitively look good?","index":216,"end_time":797.16,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":795.68,"speaker_name":"Matt Forkas"},{"text":"Does access look good?","index":217,"end_time":799.72,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":798.36,"speaker_name":"Matt Forkas"},{"text":"Yeah, I''d say baseline.","index":218,"end_time":803.44,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":802.2,"speaker_name":"Matt Forkas"},{"text":"It''s just acreage of the property would be the easiest one.","index":219,"end_time":806.28,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":803.44,"speaker_name":"Matt Forkas"},{"text":"And B, are there towers nearby?","index":220,"end_time":809,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":806.6,"speaker_name":"Matt Forkas"},{"text":"Okay.","index":221,"end_time":810.52,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":809.96,"speaker_name":"Dan Rényi"},{"text":"And I don''t see a column for, like, create data in here.","index":222,"end_time":814.44,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":811.4,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Is that something that you guys are doing is checking, like, you know, this year we''ve had this many soft inquiries.","index":223,"end_time":819.4,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":814.44,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"This year we had this many inquiries.","index":224,"end_time":821.78,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":819.4,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay.","index":225,"end_time":822.98,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":822.34,"speaker_name":"Matt Forkas"},{"text":"It''s in there.","index":226,"end_time":827.78,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":826.9,"speaker_name":"Dan Rényi"},{"text":"I don''t know if it''s always getting put.","index":227,"end_time":829.7,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":828.1,"speaker_name":"Dan Rényi"},{"text":"Looks like there was a timestamp at the bottom.","index":228,"end_time":833.22,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":831.38,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, it should be in here.","index":229,"end_time":834.9,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":833.38,"speaker_name":"Dan Rényi"},{"text":"Okay, so maybe that''s not even consistently being filled out.","index":230,"end_time":839.06,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":836.42,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"No.","index":231,"end_time":840.34,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":839.94,"speaker_name":"Matt Forkas"},{"text":"Okay.","index":232,"end_time":841.54,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":840.9,"speaker_name":"Matt Forkas"},{"text":"Sometimes it is, but.","index":233,"end_time":842.58,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":841.54,"speaker_name":"Dan Rényi"},{"text":"Yeah, gotcha.","index":234,"end_time":845.58,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":844.18,"speaker_name":"Dan Rényi"},{"text":"All right, well, last time we were talking, you mentioned that you''re not really creating context until you''re kind of in conversation.","index":235,"end_time":852.5,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":845.58,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Well, so help me understand, like, what''s happening at the top of the funnel currently.","index":236,"end_time":856.44,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":852.88,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"How many prospects are you currently doing outreach to?","index":237,"end_time":859.12,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":856.44,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Let''s just say, like, right now.","index":238,"end_time":860.32,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":859.12,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, I mean, I think right now the flow''s been pretty inconsistent.","index":239,"end_time":872.08,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":865.28,"speaker_name":"Matt Forkas"},{"text":"So per month, I mean, maybe we''re getting, I don''t know, a handful.","index":240,"end_time":878.48,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":872.24,"speaker_name":"Matt Forkas"},{"text":"Four or five maybe, which is not where we want to be.","index":241,"end_time":882.66,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":878.64,"speaker_name":"Matt Forkas"},{"text":"I mean, the number we want to be at is roughly about 20 per month.","index":242,"end_time":887.82,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":882.66,"speaker_name":"Matt Forkas"},{"text":"Right.","index":243,"end_time":888.38,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":887.98,"speaker_name":"Dan Rényi"},{"text":"And at that point, it could be any inquiry.","index":244,"end_time":892.14,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":889.26,"speaker_name":"Matt Forkas"},{"text":"I think.","index":245,"end_time":892.7,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":892.3,"speaker_name":"Matt Forkas"},{"text":"I think if we could use a metric to even hit a percentage of stuff that could get qualified, that''d be fine, but 20 would be great, and that''s where we kind of need to be and.","index":246,"end_time":903.66,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":892.7,"speaker_name":"Matt Forkas"},{"text":"Sorry, the first question you asked was top of the funnel when I start to input stuff.","index":247,"end_time":910.79,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":904.38,"speaker_name":"Matt Forkas"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":248,"end_time":911.55,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":911.19,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So like just getting an understanding of like how many people you''re currently tracking at inquiry or at soft inquiry and like what your pace of reaching back out to them at a regular period is.","index":249,"end_time":919.75,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":911.55,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, I mean, so if it''s an inquiry, it typically means that I''ve made contact and that there is some interest.","index":250,"end_time":930.39,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":921.43,"speaker_name":"Matt Forkas"},{"text":"I follow up with everyone pretty much once a week just to keep the project moving along.","index":251,"end_time":938.33,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":932.33,"speaker_name":"Matt Forkas"},{"text":"I''m asking for site walks, I''m asking for lease reviews, I''m asking for plans, I''m, you know, whatever.","index":252,"end_time":943.81,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":938.33,"speaker_name":"Matt Forkas"},{"text":"Whatever pertains to the project I''m asking for.","index":253,"end_time":946.01,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":943.81,"speaker_name":"Matt Forkas"},{"text":"So, Yeah, when a new site comes in, if I get a new search ring, I''ll usually.","index":254,"end_time":959.97,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":948.73,"speaker_name":"Matt Forkas"},{"text":"Well, I''ll just.","index":255,"end_time":962.05,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":961.17,"speaker_name":"Matt Forkas"},{"text":"I''ll just show you what I do.","index":256,"end_time":963.41,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":962.05,"speaker_name":"Dan Rényi"},{"text":"So I''ll get like a specific search ring in.","index":257,"end_time":978.77,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":976.37,"speaker_name":"Matt Forkas"},{"text":"I just pick anywhere.","index":258,"end_time":983.89,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":982.77,"speaker_name":"Dan Rényi"},{"text":"And this search ring will be, you know, X miles.","index":259,"end_time":992.32,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":989.04,"speaker_name":"Matt Forkas"},{"text":"The radius will be like a half a mile or a full mile.","index":260,"end_time":995.2,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":992.56,"speaker_name":"Matt Forkas"},{"text":"And so in certain cases I''ll only be allowed to engage with certain property owners, but in the case where I''m not, I would just identify potential properties that look more viable.","index":261,"end_time":1006.16,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":995.44,"speaker_name":"Matt Forkas"},{"text":"So like these schools, obviously pretty straightforward.","index":262,"end_time":1008.4,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1006.24,"speaker_name":"Matt Forkas"},{"text":"But if they were raw land owners like this one, I would mark these as down.","index":263,"end_time":1015.55,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1008.88,"speaker_name":"Matt Forkas"},{"text":"I would make a really just.","index":264,"end_time":1018.27,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1015.55,"speaker_name":"Matt Forkas"},{"text":"I write them down internally just for myself until I can actually make a lead.","index":265,"end_time":1023.39,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1018.35,"speaker_name":"Matt Forkas"},{"text":"And whatever lead I make, those will get inputted into.","index":266,"end_time":1027.63,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1023.79,"speaker_name":"Matt Forkas"},{"text":"Into Salesforce.","index":267,"end_time":1028.75,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1027.79,"speaker_name":"Matt Forkas"},{"text":"And oftentimes there''s only one or two people that become active prospects.","index":268,"end_time":1034.27,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1028.75,"speaker_name":"Matt Forkas"},{"text":"And.","index":269,"end_time":1035.79,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1035.39,"speaker_name":"Dan Rényi"},{"text":"But most of our sites, we already have existing mla, so I don''t have to do any of this.","index":270,"end_time":1040.919,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1036.679,"speaker_name":"Matt Forkas"},{"text":"But in the case where I am searching for new property owners, I''m not inputting every single one.","index":271,"end_time":1048.239,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1042.039,"speaker_name":"Matt Forkas"},{"text":"I just have a personal tracker that I use that goes site by site before just bloating up Salesforce with names of people I''ll never talk to again.","index":272,"end_time":1058.039,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1048.239,"speaker_name":"Matt Forkas"},{"text":"Gotcha.","index":273,"end_time":1059.719,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1058.999,"speaker_name":"Dan Rényi"},{"text":"Okay, so not a vast amount of data as far as marketing activities happening in Salesforce right now.","index":274,"end_time":1066.439,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1060.119,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Probably something that we''ll have to establish, understand, you know, source attribution and things like that.","index":275,"end_time":1070.5,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1066.679,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Because I imagine that it''s kind of like, I mean really your main source is you, you know, or someone kind of reaching directly out to you.","index":276,"end_time":1077.34,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1070.98,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So it''s not like you need to understand like it was this ad or this, and they''re not filling out a form.","index":277,"end_time":1082.46,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1077.34,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So it''s really just one source that''s been happening historically.","index":278,"end_time":1084.98,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1082.46,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Is that correct?","index":279,"end_time":1085.78,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1084.98,"speaker_name":"Dan Rényi"},{"text":"From the set acquisition side?","index":280,"end_time":1087.86,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1086.5,"speaker_name":"Matt Forkas"},{"text":"Yeah, I think in the.","index":281,"end_time":1090.66,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1087.86,"speaker_name":"Matt Forkas"},{"text":"In a conversation about getting new leads of, you know, let''s just say landowners.","index":282,"end_time":1096.15,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1090.9,"speaker_name":"Matt Forkas"},{"text":"If I wanted to make a campaign to attract new landowners, that''s a completely different thing because that, that just means that there''s no active site.","index":283,"end_time":1103.15,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1096.15,"speaker_name":"Matt Forkas"},{"text":"So we''re working backwards, which is fine and it''s something I like to explore.","index":284,"end_time":1107.87,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1103.63,"speaker_name":"Matt Forkas"},{"text":"But it''s certainly not.","index":285,"end_time":1109.15,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1107.87,"speaker_name":"Matt Forkas"},{"text":"We''re not actively reaching out to private property owners.","index":286,"end_time":1113.03,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1109.15,"speaker_name":"Matt Forkas"},{"text":"We''re not actively reaching out to schools right now.","index":287,"end_time":1114.91,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1113.03,"speaker_name":"Matt Forkas"},{"text":"I think for at least our plan to grow the ML, the, the landowner management portion is going to be predominantly focused on schools.","index":288,"end_time":1125.53,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1116.67,"speaker_name":"Matt Forkas"},{"text":"Those are just going to be direct reach outs.","index":289,"end_time":1128.93,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1127.37,"speaker_name":"Matt Forkas"},{"text":"There''s, you know, paid ads or ad spend online or direct mailers really won''t work for them.","index":290,"end_time":1135.53,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1128.93,"speaker_name":"Matt Forkas"},{"text":"I think maybe we talked about it last time was just the materials that we can send during that cold outreach part.","index":291,"end_time":1142.49,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1135.69,"speaker_name":"Matt Forkas"},{"text":"I think it is what we need.","index":292,"end_time":1143.89,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1142.73,"speaker_name":"Matt Forkas"},{"text":"But if we did decide to explore like advertising to private property owners, real estate developers, then I think that more like traditional flow of, you know, having a landing page, collecting emails and, and whatnot would make a lot of sense.","index":293,"end_time":1160.82,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1143.89,"speaker_name":"Matt Forkas"},{"text":"But I don''t think it''s going to be the focus for at least this next couple months.","index":294,"end_time":1165.9,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1160.82,"speaker_name":"Matt Forkas"},{"text":"Yeah, I totally agree.","index":295,"end_time":1167.74,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1166.86,"speaker_name":"Dan Rényi"},{"text":"Tristan, I saw you on me.","index":296,"end_time":1168.98,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1167.98,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Was there something you were jumping in with?","index":297,"end_time":1171.42,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1168.98,"speaker_name":"Dan Rényi"},{"text":"Yeah, I''m off mute now.","index":298,"end_time":1174.77,"speaker_id":6,"start_time":1173.05,"speaker_name":"Tristan"},{"text":"I was going to ask Matt, like the, the number of leads that you mentioned or inquiries, that 20 number, like what, what does that look like, you know, as far as like across the different segments of customers.","index":299,"end_time":1189.37,"speaker_id":6,"start_time":1174.77,"speaker_name":"Tristan"},{"text":"So I think the dream situation would be we''re getting 20 inquiries or inbound leads from the carriers or the site positions themselves.","index":300,"end_time":1203.76,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1190.81,"speaker_name":"Matt Forkas"},{"text":"So they''re bringing us the sites, which is, you know, typically what we experience.","index":301,"end_time":1209.12,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1204.24,"speaker_name":"Matt Forkas"},{"text":"Very rarely will we get a property owner to reach out to us directly and have that site be aligned with the carrier''s needs.","index":302,"end_time":1219.68,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1210.56,"speaker_name":"Matt Forkas"},{"text":"That very rarely happens.","index":303,"end_time":1221.52,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1219.68,"speaker_name":"Matt Forkas"},{"text":"It does happen, but it''s very rare.","index":304,"end_time":1223.6,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1221.52,"speaker_name":"Matt Forkas"},{"text":"And so in that case we have to work backwards.","index":305,"end_time":1225.52,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1223.84,"speaker_name":"Matt Forkas"},{"text":"Okay, this guy reaches out to us, he wants a tower on his property.","index":306,"end_time":1228,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1225.52,"speaker_name":"Matt Forkas"},{"text":"We look at it, we think it looks good, and then we take it to the carriers and say, okay, now it''s active and then it becomes a real project.","index":307,"end_time":1234.38,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1228.7,"speaker_name":"Matt Forkas"},{"text":"But what we''d like to grow is the carrier, the carriers reaching out to us directly with new opportunities that that number growing to 20amonth.","index":308,"end_time":1247.42,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1236.38,"speaker_name":"Matt Forkas"},{"text":"Okay, got it.","index":309,"end_time":1249.38,"speaker_id":6,"start_time":1248.22,"speaker_name":"Tristan"},{"text":"And in those historical numbers, is there a way, like how do you track those in Salesforce?","index":310,"end_time":1254.66,"speaker_id":6,"start_time":1249.38,"speaker_name":"Tristan"},{"text":"Like that flavor of inbound inquiry, like, is there a data field or something that.","index":311,"end_time":1259.1,"speaker_id":6,"start_time":1254.66,"speaker_name":"Tristan"},{"text":"Yeah, I think that''s Just the baseline, I mean, of what we consider an inquiry.","index":312,"end_time":1268.75,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1259.63,"speaker_name":"Matt Forkas"},{"text":"I think they have like a.","index":313,"end_time":1271.31,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1270.11,"speaker_name":"Dan Rényi"},{"text":"Yeah, so.","index":314,"end_time":1291.64,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1291.08,"speaker_name":"Matt Forkas"},{"text":"I have to rerun this, but yeah.","index":315,"end_time":1311,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1309.08,"speaker_name":"Matt Forkas"},{"text":"It''S, that''s, it looks like that''s the report.","index":316,"end_time":1314.22,"speaker_id":6,"start_time":1311,"speaker_name":"Tristan"},{"text":"You just have it for January and then we could run that for a time span.","index":317,"end_time":1318.3,"speaker_id":6,"start_time":1314.38,"speaker_name":"Tristan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":318,"end_time":1319.1,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1318.62,"speaker_name":"Dan Rényi"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":319,"end_time":1322.06,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1321.66,"speaker_name":"Matt Forkas"},{"text":"So January has been very quiet so.","index":320,"end_time":1324.1,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1322.06,"speaker_name":"Matt Forkas"},{"text":"Far.","index":321,"end_time":1324.38,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1324.1,"speaker_name":"Dan Rényi"},{"text":"And the, the past couple months, I''d say six.","index":322,"end_time":1330.94,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1326.3,"speaker_name":"Matt Forkas"},{"text":"Six months.","index":323,"end_time":1332.46,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1331.74,"speaker_name":"Dan Rényi"},{"text":"That''s been pretty dry and it''s a big reason why we, we decided to.","index":324,"end_time":1339.26,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1334.14,"speaker_name":"Matt Forkas"},{"text":"Talk to you guys too.","index":325,"end_time":1340.18,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1339.26,"speaker_name":"Dan Rényi"},{"text":"So.","index":326,"end_time":1340.54,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1340.18,"speaker_name":"Matt Forkas"},{"text":"And Matt, with some of the work when we were looking at.","index":327,"end_time":1348.17,"speaker_id":6,"start_time":1345.45,"speaker_name":"Tristan"},{"text":"Yes.","index":328,"end_time":1348.73,"speaker_id":6,"start_time":1348.25,"speaker_name":"Tristan"},{"text":"And the, the proposals there, because we, we saw like the, the documentation that they provided as far as what would be done, how much of that was, was done, because I know you weren''t necessarily happy with, you know, the, the results there that transpired.","index":329,"end_time":1368.33,"speaker_id":6,"start_time":1348.73,"speaker_name":"Tristan"},{"text":"Like, how much of a gap was it?","index":330,"end_time":1370.47,"speaker_id":6,"start_time":1368.33,"speaker_name":"Tristan"},{"text":"Was it the fact that a lot of that work wasn''t done and it didn''t drive results or like, how, how does that, like, correlate with some of the, the leads that you saw coming through?","index":331,"end_time":1381.75,"speaker_id":6,"start_time":1370.79,"speaker_name":"Tristan"},{"text":"I don''t think we got that far, to be honest.","index":332,"end_time":1385.59,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1383.59,"speaker_name":"Matt Forkas"},{"text":"And I wasn''t as deeply entrenched in.","index":333,"end_time":1389.67,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1387.11,"speaker_name":"Matt Forkas"},{"text":"In with them as I am with you guys, so I''d let Islan even still here.","index":334,"end_time":1396.15,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1389.83,"speaker_name":"Matt Forkas"},{"text":"You talk on that.","index":335,"end_time":1397.26,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1396.5,"speaker_name":"Dan Rényi"},{"text":"I think he just dropped off.","index":336,"end_time":1398.74,"speaker_id":6,"start_time":1397.26,"speaker_name":"Tristan"},{"text":"Right, Colin?","index":337,"end_time":1399.34,"speaker_id":6,"start_time":1398.74,"speaker_name":"Tristan"},{"text":"I think I said.","index":338,"end_time":1399.82,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1399.34,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, he said he had to go to another call.","index":339,"end_time":1401.46,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1399.82,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":340,"end_time":1401.94,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1401.46,"speaker_name":"Dan Rényi"},{"text":"Oh, yeah.","index":341,"end_time":1404.34,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1402.02,"speaker_name":"Dan Rényi"},{"text":"So, yeah, I, I can''t remember.","index":342,"end_time":1408.7,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1404.5,"speaker_name":"Matt Forkas"},{"text":"I mean, that whole relationship was really started because, I mean, frankly, they had a really good sales guy that was pulling all the cards and I think they were referred to us by a friend and.","index":343,"end_time":1425.85,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1408.7,"speaker_name":"Matt Forkas"},{"text":"But I don''t think we were as targeted in terms of, like, what the ROI would look like, really hunkering down on like this inquiry piece and that being the primary focus of what we need to grow in order to grow the business.","index":344,"end_time":1440.33,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1426.89,"speaker_name":"Matt Forkas"},{"text":"And they were like, I think they were just billing out of control and it just got to a point where, you know, every week we were joining a call with, you know, a dozen people on this call.","index":345,"end_time":1453.86,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1443.29,"speaker_name":"Matt Forkas"},{"text":"Like there''s some, like Fortune 500 company or something, and their, their output was just really making decks for us, talking about maybe what they wanted to do.","index":346,"end_time":1463.54,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1454.34,"speaker_name":"Matt Forkas"},{"text":"And I don''t really believe we even started most of the implementation just because it just got so expensive.","index":347,"end_time":1470.74,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1463.54,"speaker_name":"Matt Forkas"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":348,"end_time":1471.94,"speaker_id":6,"start_time":1471.46,"speaker_name":"Tristan"},{"text":"But I, I won''t speak much to it because I, I wasn''t really invited to a lot of those conversations.","index":349,"end_time":1479.42,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1472.5,"speaker_name":"Matt Forkas"},{"text":"I just remember I saw the bill once one month, and then it just Kind of blew up.","index":350,"end_time":1484.38,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1479.82,"speaker_name":"Matt Forkas"},{"text":"Got it right.","index":351,"end_time":1485.98,"speaker_id":6,"start_time":1484.62,"speaker_name":"Tristan"},{"text":"Colin, we''ll make sure to bring 12 other people on next week.","index":352,"end_time":1488.94,"speaker_id":6,"start_time":1485.98,"speaker_name":"Tristan"},{"text":"Yeah, we need to double our numbers.","index":353,"end_time":1491.34,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1489.42,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":354,"end_time":1491.98,"speaker_id":6,"start_time":1491.5,"speaker_name":"Tristan"},{"text":"Now Matt, I think that that''s one thing.","index":355,"end_time":1494.54,"speaker_id":6,"start_time":1492.38,"speaker_name":"Tristan"},{"text":"Just when Colin and I were looking at this, we were wondering how much traction you did get with what was in the.","index":356,"end_time":1501.5,"speaker_id":6,"start_time":1494.54,"speaker_name":"Tristan"},{"text":"Because it''s not like there are some, you know, good approaches here, but it''s also all about execution too.","index":357,"end_time":1508.83,"speaker_id":6,"start_time":1501.5,"speaker_name":"Tristan"},{"text":"So we weren''t sure, you know, what actually transpired there.","index":358,"end_time":1512.79,"speaker_id":6,"start_time":1508.83,"speaker_name":"Tristan"},{"text":"So that, that does help us a little bit and that like what do you think, you know, based on what was written up here?","index":359,"end_time":1521.39,"speaker_id":6,"start_time":1512.79,"speaker_name":"Tristan"},{"text":"I know you weren''t in a lot of those conversations, but how did you feel about the approach going in and I guess when you turned it off, was there any impact up or down from your inquiries?","index":360,"end_time":1535.77,"speaker_id":6,"start_time":1521.39,"speaker_name":"Tristan"},{"text":"Like was there any.","index":361,"end_time":1536.57,"speaker_id":6,"start_time":1535.77,"speaker_name":"Tristan"},{"text":"Yeah, like I said, we did not get, we didn''t even get there.","index":362,"end_time":1539.37,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1536.89,"speaker_name":"Matt Forkas"},{"text":"They didn''t implement any, they didn''t implement anything.","index":363,"end_time":1541.69,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1539.37,"speaker_name":"Matt Forkas"},{"text":"I mean I, I, yeah.","index":364,"end_time":1547.25,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1542.81,"speaker_name":"Matt Forkas"},{"text":"So there is no effect.","index":365,"end_time":1548.33,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1547.25,"speaker_name":"Matt Forkas"},{"text":"Gotcha.","index":366,"end_time":1549.69,"speaker_id":6,"start_time":1549.05,"speaker_name":"Tristan"},{"text":"It''s just decks.","index":367,"end_time":1550.85,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1549.93,"speaker_name":"Matt Forkas"},{"text":"It''s just decks and decks and presentations.","index":368,"end_time":1552.97,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1550.85,"speaker_name":"Matt Forkas"},{"text":"And.","index":369,"end_time":1553.37,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1552.97,"speaker_name":"Dan Rényi"},{"text":"Yeah, I don''t believe they, I could be wrong but it was a very short engagement.","index":370,"end_time":1560.74,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1555.94,"speaker_name":"Matt Forkas"},{"text":"They built like crazy and if Ozzy and Len were on the call they could probably speak more to it and in terms of how, how far they got into this.","index":371,"end_time":1569.78,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1561.3,"speaker_name":"Matt Forkas"},{"text":"But from my end I don''t think they got far at all.","index":372,"end_time":1573.14,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1569.78,"speaker_name":"Matt Forkas"},{"text":"And I think there was also a big misunderstanding of just who was going to be taking ownership of the implementation and yeah, so there''s good stuff in here and it''s, I think it''s a lot of, it''s just kind of basic stuff.","index":373,"end_time":1592.67,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1575.06,"speaker_name":"Matt Forkas"},{"text":"I mean we''re not really a complicated business.","index":374,"end_time":1594.79,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1592.67,"speaker_name":"Matt Forkas"},{"text":"So.","index":375,"end_time":1596.55,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1596.15,"speaker_name":"Matt Forkas"},{"text":"Yeah, I got, I mean 61 page.","index":376,"end_time":1600.35,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1598.47,"speaker_name":"Matt Forkas"},{"text":"Deck is just crazy.","index":377,"end_time":1602.79,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1600.35,"speaker_name":"Dan Rényi"},{"text":"So.","index":378,"end_time":1603.11,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1602.79,"speaker_name":"Matt Forkas"},{"text":"Yeah, all right.","index":379,"end_time":1604.79,"speaker_id":6,"start_time":1603.51,"speaker_name":"Tristan"},{"text":"Yeah, that helps.","index":380,"end_time":1605.47,"speaker_id":6,"start_time":1604.79,"speaker_name":"Tristan"},{"text":"Sorry Kyle, I just want to jump in and get some like how, like correlation between, you know, those, the numbers that you''re, you''re mentioning, Matt?","index":381,"end_time":1612.2,"speaker_id":6,"start_time":1605.47,"speaker_name":"Tristan"},{"text":"Anywhere from it looks like two to five inquiries per month and then you know where you want to get to on that side.","index":382,"end_time":1620.2,"speaker_id":6,"start_time":1612.2,"speaker_name":"Tristan"},{"text":"Yeah, yeah.","index":383,"end_time":1622,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1620.68,"speaker_name":"Dan Rényi"},{"text":"And I think early on we need to establish like strong definitions for each of those development statuses as well.","index":384,"end_time":1629.88,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1622,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"You know, we need to know exactly what soft inquiry is, what inquiry is pre construction, all of those things.","index":385,"end_time":1635.24,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1630.2,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Because even as you were going through your like kind of adjusting as you were going.","index":386,"end_time":1638.93,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1635.32,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So I think we need just some true definition so we''re all speaking the same language there.","index":387,"end_time":1643.01,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1639.57,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, I want to look through a different lens too because you Know, we talked about 20 inquiries per month from site acquisition, but you know, if we land 20 that don''t move through, then I have to imagine Milestone''s not happy with performance.","index":388,"end_time":1655.81,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1643.33,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So I wanna, I wanna talk about like the ones that have brought in the most consistent revenue.","index":389,"end_time":1660.13,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1655.81,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"What were the similarities between those deals?","index":390,"end_time":1664.37,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1660.93,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"How quickly did they move?","index":391,"end_time":1666.42,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1665.3,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"What was the velocity?","index":392,"end_time":1667.54,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1666.42,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Can we dive into that a little bit?","index":393,"end_time":1669.06,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1667.7,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":394,"end_time":1677.62,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1677.06,"speaker_name":"Matt Forkas"},{"text":"You know, even just ones that have moved from like in, into in service in 2025, you know what, what are the similarities between those companies?","index":395,"end_time":1686.34,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1679.62,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, I think you get the.","index":396,"end_time":1690.58,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1688.66,"speaker_name":"Matt Forkas"},{"text":"There''s only three companies.","index":397,"end_time":1695.81,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1694.77,"speaker_name":"Matt Forkas"},{"text":"So.","index":398,"end_time":1696.69,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1696.29,"speaker_name":"Matt Forkas"},{"text":"Every project is, I mean simply what Len would say is that every project''s a snowflake.","index":399,"end_time":1705.73,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1701.01,"speaker_name":"Matt Forkas"},{"text":"So it''s really hard to figure out what in, in terms of the, like, I''m not looking at this as like, as a customer journey, I''m looking at this as a project journey.","index":400,"end_time":1716.29,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1705.73,"speaker_name":"Matt Forkas"},{"text":"So every project is different.","index":401,"end_time":1717.81,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1716.65,"speaker_name":"Matt Forkas"},{"text":"It''s very hard to, you know, figure out what we can replicate.","index":402,"end_time":1722.61,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1717.81,"speaker_name":"Matt Forkas"},{"text":"I mean certain landowners definitely perform better or take more agency over others.","index":403,"end_time":1727.29,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1722.61,"speaker_name":"Matt Forkas"},{"text":"You know, if you''re dealing with a farmer in West Virginia, he wants his money as fast as he can get it, he''s going to pick up the phone immediately and do everything he can to make the project move forward.","index":404,"end_time":1740.89,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1730.01,"speaker_name":"Matt Forkas"},{"text":"So I think if we''re going to talk about this, I just want to make sure we''re, we''re going to talk about the same, I guess, characteristics.","index":405,"end_time":1749.23,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1741.45,"speaker_name":"Matt Forkas"},{"text":"Are you asking on the carrier side and you talk about the project side with the, the landowner?","index":406,"end_time":1753.67,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1749.23,"speaker_name":"Matt Forkas"},{"text":"Yeah, yeah.","index":407,"end_time":1758.71,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1758.07,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I mean I need to get an understanding of really all of them and, and what is kind of the end to end process.","index":408,"end_time":1764.95,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1758.71,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Because understanding these similarities helps us with, with targeting, you know, on the landowner side for a campaign where we can start to drop, drum up some interest and really get more awareness for who Milestone Towers is.","index":409,"end_time":1775.7,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1765.51,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"But also your guys, new locations that you guys are expanding into and getting more depth and familiarity with the carriers in those regions as well as the municipality.","index":410,"end_time":1785.86,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1776.1,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So just need to kind of want to have a broad conversation around how those are flowing through currently and what similarities we can kind of attribute to each other.","index":411,"end_time":1794.81,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1785.86,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Segment.","index":412,"end_time":1795.6,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1795.12,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, okay, let me see if I can share this.","index":413,"end_time":1798.64,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1796,"speaker_name":"Matt Forkas"},{"text":"I just want to.","index":414,"end_time":1799.36,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1798.64,"speaker_name":"Matt Forkas"},{"text":"Just brain dump because I think there''s a lot.","index":415,"end_time":1807.36,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1803.6,"speaker_name":"Matt Forkas"},{"text":"So I think on the carrier side we have the, the RF teams and then we have the real estate teams and then same goes for the site acquisition firms.","index":416,"end_time":1834.57,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1817.76,"speaker_name":"Matt Forkas"},{"text":"They just typically have a real estate arm that they, that we work with and we have our landown, We have MLA partners And then we have, I don''t know, just one offs.","index":417,"end_time":1854.58,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1836.249,"speaker_name":"Matt Forkas"},{"text":"We''ll just have a single, you know, they just have a single piece of land and we just happen to build a tower there.","index":418,"end_time":1862.34,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1856.66,"speaker_name":"Matt Forkas"},{"text":"And so these would be the two groups where inquiries are coming from.","index":419,"end_time":1870.38,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1865.22,"speaker_name":"Matt Forkas"},{"text":"And that''s ultimately it.","index":420,"end_time":1871.78,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1870.38,"speaker_name":"Matt Forkas"},{"text":"Right now the, the, the majority, if not all, is coming directly from the carrier end.","index":421,"end_time":1878.67,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1873.15,"speaker_name":"Matt Forkas"},{"text":"And these two buckets are in the, these two organizations are in the same carrier bucket.","index":422,"end_time":1884.35,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1878.75,"speaker_name":"Matt Forkas"},{"text":"The, the carriers hire the psyduck firms which are typically the ones reaching out to us directly as opposed to the carriers reaching out to us directly.","index":423,"end_time":1893.79,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1884.99,"speaker_name":"Matt Forkas"},{"text":"That''s why they hire these guys to begin with.","index":424,"end_time":1896.19,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1894.11,"speaker_name":"Matt Forkas"},{"text":"So yeah, these would be the two, the two buckets, I''d say the things that we want to replicate and the things that work very well from the getting those inquiries in, in this market, the relationship that we want to copy that works the best is Verizon in the Bawa market, Mass Tech, which is their PSYDAC firm in the Bawa market.","index":425,"end_time":1924.93,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1896.51,"speaker_name":"Matt Forkas"},{"text":"And so we have this.","index":426,"end_time":1928.37,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1925.73,"speaker_name":"Matt Forkas"},{"text":"What drives a lot of the inquiries in this region actually, and this is when I started noticing the pattern is that these guys, without these two entities, our inquiries would be way more dried up.","index":427,"end_time":1943.89,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1929.25,"speaker_name":"Matt Forkas"},{"text":"I mean almost like one a month would be nice if, if we didn''t have these guys.","index":428,"end_time":1952.73,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1943.89,"speaker_name":"Matt Forkas"},{"text":"They are driving so much of our business at least the past year or so.","index":429,"end_time":1957.73,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1952.73,"speaker_name":"Matt Forkas"},{"text":"And you know, there''s been years that this hasn''t been the case.","index":430,"end_time":1960.93,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1958.45,"speaker_name":"Matt Forkas"},{"text":"I mean, there''s industry changes, there''s been turnover, there''s been massive reorgs.","index":431,"end_time":1966.37,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1960.93,"speaker_name":"Matt Forkas"},{"text":"I mean, and then the, the industry itself is just getting fairly mature and the carriers are getting so much more power and so much more control and blah, blah, blah.","index":432,"end_time":1977.44,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1966.37,"speaker_name":"Matt Forkas"},{"text":"But this particular situation we have with Verizon and Mastec is golden.","index":433,"end_time":1984.44,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1977.44,"speaker_name":"Matt Forkas"},{"text":"So they, we have a relationship with them from the, in terms of the psychosis piece that they''ll give us the, they''ll give us eyes on a. Searching that they''re working on and they''ll let us look at that ring to see if we can find any municipal focused projects that we can.","index":434,"end_time":2005.22,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1985.08,"speaker_name":"Matt Forkas"},{"text":"Or doors that we can open.","index":435,"end_time":2007.62,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2006.26,"speaker_name":"Matt Forkas"},{"text":"Ideally in most cases we already have the mla, we already have the option for that land in place.","index":436,"end_time":2016.34,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2008.5,"speaker_name":"Matt Forkas"},{"text":"So there''s no resistance.","index":437,"end_time":2018.5,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2017.06,"speaker_name":"Matt Forkas"},{"text":"It''s this.","index":438,"end_time":2019.02,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2018.5,"speaker_name":"Matt Forkas"},{"text":"I call the facilities director at the parks or at the, at the county or at the schools and I say, hey, this came in.","index":439,"end_time":2026.74,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2019.02,"speaker_name":"Matt Forkas"},{"text":"Verizon needs service here.","index":440,"end_time":2027.74,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2026.74,"speaker_name":"Matt Forkas"},{"text":"You guys interested?","index":441,"end_time":2028.54,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2027.74,"speaker_name":"Matt Forkas"},{"text":"And then more times than not they say yes, we go walk the site and we, we go through the process.","index":442,"end_time":2033.22,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2028.54,"speaker_name":"Matt Forkas"},{"text":"If we don''t have an MLA or an option in place, then Mass tech will give us the opportunity to, to do the outreach to open up a door with a new relationship.","index":443,"end_time":2043.54,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2033.7,"speaker_name":"Matt Forkas"},{"text":"Most most recently, that was.","index":444,"end_time":2045.94,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2044.26,"speaker_name":"Matt Forkas"},{"text":"And I''ll just show you.","index":445,"end_time":2048.82,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2047.54,"speaker_name":"Matt Forkas"},{"text":"I was going to show you how I did that, but literally Mastek gave me a set of coordinates.","index":446,"end_time":2059.369,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2053.7,"speaker_name":"Matt Forkas"},{"text":"He said, matt, the search ring is half a mile wide.","index":447,"end_time":2062.609,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2059.369,"speaker_name":"Matt Forkas"},{"text":"We can see that there''s a VRE VDOT station that looks good.","index":448,"end_time":2070.529,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2063.569,"speaker_name":"Matt Forkas"},{"text":"We know that you guys work with vdot.","index":449,"end_time":2072.369,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2070.689,"speaker_name":"Matt Forkas"},{"text":"Can you try them?","index":450,"end_time":2073.489,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2072.529,"speaker_name":"Matt Forkas"},{"text":"And then he said, look around.","index":451,"end_time":2075.849,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2074.449,"speaker_name":"Matt Forkas"},{"text":"If you see anything else that looks good, let me know.","index":452,"end_time":2077.809,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2075.849,"speaker_name":"Matt Forkas"},{"text":"And then I identified a church and I identified a Spotsylvania county site, which we did not have an active option with.","index":453,"end_time":2085.57,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2077.969,"speaker_name":"Matt Forkas"},{"text":"But he said, you know, go for it.","index":454,"end_time":2088.29,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2086.53,"speaker_name":"Matt Forkas"},{"text":"See if you can open the door.","index":455,"end_time":2089.57,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2088.37,"speaker_name":"Matt Forkas"},{"text":"And then I did.","index":456,"end_time":2090.37,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2089.57,"speaker_name":"Matt Forkas"},{"text":"And then we onboarded Spotsylvania county and we onboarded all of the county facilities parks for a new option to build newts towers on other, you know, for different rings.","index":457,"end_time":2103.41,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2090.53,"speaker_name":"Matt Forkas"},{"text":"So that''s like the perfect.","index":458,"end_time":2105.33,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2103.89,"speaker_name":"Matt Forkas"},{"text":"That is the perfect situation, right?","index":459,"end_time":2107.25,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2105.49,"speaker_name":"Matt Forkas"},{"text":"We have active interest in one site.","index":460,"end_time":2109.17,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2107.33,"speaker_name":"Matt Forkas"},{"text":"That''s like our pilot site with the county.","index":461,"end_time":2111.85,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2110.25,"speaker_name":"Matt Forkas"},{"text":"We onboard them and then we onboard the rest of their land.","index":462,"end_time":2114.65,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2112.09,"speaker_name":"Matt Forkas"},{"text":"Then we take the rest of the land and then start actively marketing it to the carriers to generate interest for new towers.","index":463,"end_time":2120.17,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2114.65,"speaker_name":"Matt Forkas"},{"text":"Right?","index":464,"end_time":2120.73,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2120.33,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So just the ability to look at that ring so early on into the process to identify new opportunities is huge.","index":465,"end_time":2128.01,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2120.73,"speaker_name":"Matt Forkas"},{"text":"And we do not get that privilege virtually in any other market.","index":466,"end_time":2131.29,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2128.17,"speaker_name":"Matt Forkas"},{"text":"And we''ve earned that privilege through time.","index":467,"end_time":2134.65,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2132.25,"speaker_name":"Matt Forkas"},{"text":"By.","index":468,"end_time":2135.63,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2135.39,"speaker_name":"Dan Rényi"},{"text":"Proving ourselves and actually getting the work done.","index":469,"end_time":2139.79,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2137.47,"speaker_name":"Matt Forkas"},{"text":"But that just, that alone only happened because we have land under option that is extremely high quality, right?","index":470,"end_time":2149.27,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2140.51,"speaker_name":"Matt Forkas"},{"text":"So when we have the land under management and it''s good quality land, this whole process runs so much smoother.","index":471,"end_time":2156.11,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2149.27,"speaker_name":"Matt Forkas"},{"text":"I mean, there''s still roadblocks, there''s still challenges, whatever, but that''s when things move super smooth.","index":472,"end_time":2162.69,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2156.11,"speaker_name":"Matt Forkas"},{"text":"You''ve got a good carrier, you''ve got a good sight act, you''ve got a good landowner, you got a good piece of property.","index":473,"end_time":2168.33,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2163.09,"speaker_name":"Matt Forkas"},{"text":"That''s like the golden ticket, you know, that''s what we.","index":474,"end_time":2170.69,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2168.33,"speaker_name":"Matt Forkas"},{"text":"That''s what we want to replicate.","index":475,"end_time":2172.29,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2170.69,"speaker_name":"Matt Forkas"},{"text":"And certain laners certainly move faster than others.","index":476,"end_time":2180.33,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2174.45,"speaker_name":"Matt Forkas"},{"text":"I mean, I think we kind of talked about it last time where it''s like their characteristics would be, you know, just them being generally interested in and they want this to succeed, they want to move forward, they want to move fast.","index":477,"end_time":2192.33,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2180.33,"speaker_name":"Matt Forkas"},{"text":"You know, I''d say from first contact, when I reach out with Verizon''s, needs, you know, from first contact to actually walking the site in certain cases can take, I don''t know, a month, a month, a month and a half of legislative, not legislative but like bureaucratic back end conversations after having first and that''s not ideal.","index":478,"end_time":2230.139,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2194.49,"speaker_name":"Matt Forkas"},{"text":"Where I could think of the most recent example would be Alachua county in Florida.","index":479,"end_time":2234.34,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2230.139,"speaker_name":"Matt Forkas"},{"text":"Verizon gave us a ring.","index":480,"end_time":2236.34,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2234.98,"speaker_name":"Matt Forkas"},{"text":"I, I brought it to the facilities director and within two days he''s like let''s get out there, let''s just go.","index":481,"end_time":2243.24,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2237.3,"speaker_name":"Matt Forkas"},{"text":"Like we need the service.","index":482,"end_time":2244.24,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2243.24,"speaker_name":"Matt Forkas"},{"text":"Let''s go, let''s go, let''s go, let''s go, let''s go.","index":483,"end_time":2246.12,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2244.24,"speaker_name":"Matt Forkas"},{"text":"And we just.","index":484,"end_time":2247.8,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2246.92,"speaker_name":"Matt Forkas"},{"text":"That was like the fastest, you know, from start to finish I''ve ever experienced been since I''ve been at the company.","index":485,"end_time":2254.04,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2247.96,"speaker_name":"Matt Forkas"},{"text":"But that''s something very hard to replicate because even if there are stakeholders within the organization that are interested, they''re typically met with more bureaucratic backend or getting approvals internally.","index":486,"end_time":2267.8,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2255.08,"speaker_name":"Matt Forkas"},{"text":"So it''s hard to develop a. I could make a list of things that I like about certain landowners that want to do business but it''s very hard to identify, you know, especially when we start looking at prospects like how we can replicate that because we just don''t know.","index":487,"end_time":2282.65,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2267.8,"speaker_name":"Matt Forkas"},{"text":"It''s really hard until you start to develop that relationship.","index":488,"end_time":2285.37,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2282.81,"speaker_name":"Matt Forkas"},{"text":"And yeah, there''s other ones too that we have very good, we''ve got very good leads on their end of the program.","index":489,"end_time":2293.69,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2285.37,"speaker_name":"Matt Forkas"},{"text":"I can think of another one like Loudoun county or contact their Gretchen is awesome.","index":490,"end_time":2299.94,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2294.73,"speaker_name":"Matt Forkas"},{"text":"She picks up the phone every time she calls me back.","index":491,"end_time":2302.7,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2299.94,"speaker_name":"Matt Forkas"},{"text":"She responds.","index":492,"end_time":2303.98,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2302.94,"speaker_name":"Matt Forkas"},{"text":"She gets me answers within like a couple days.","index":493,"end_time":2306.3,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2304.06,"speaker_name":"Matt Forkas"},{"text":"She''s great.","index":494,"end_time":2307.34,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2306.62,"speaker_name":"Matt Forkas"},{"text":"That''s really tough to, to replicate.","index":495,"end_time":2310.06,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2307.9,"speaker_name":"Matt Forkas"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":496,"end_time":2310.62,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2310.14,"speaker_name":"Dan Rényi"},{"text":"And, and when you''re making first contact, whether it''s via phone or via email, what are you leading with?","index":497,"end_time":2317.66,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2312.86,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"You know, what is, what is.","index":498,"end_time":2319.14,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2317.9,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"How are you drumming their interest right away to stay even on the phone with you?","index":499,"end_time":2322.3,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2319.14,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, well I would have to like break that down.","index":500,"end_time":2328.41,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2322.62,"speaker_name":"Matt Forkas"},{"text":"So it''s like if we have MLA option land that isn''t an issue.","index":501,"end_time":2335.97,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2328.41,"speaker_name":"Matt Forkas"},{"text":"We already have the landowner management.","index":502,"end_time":2338.69,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2337.17,"speaker_name":"Matt Forkas"},{"text":"I, I just lead with why I''m even calling.","index":503,"end_time":2343.41,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2338.93,"speaker_name":"Matt Forkas"},{"text":"So we are experiencing coverage gaps in the area.","index":504,"end_time":2347.01,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2343.65,"speaker_name":"Matt Forkas"},{"text":"Your prop this property came up and they''d like to explore it.","index":505,"end_time":2351.17,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2347.73,"speaker_name":"Matt Forkas"},{"text":"Can we walk it?","index":506,"end_time":2352.06,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2351.26,"speaker_name":"Matt Forkas"},{"text":"And that''s the pretty much the nature of the conversation.","index":507,"end_time":2355.1,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2352.3,"speaker_name":"Matt Forkas"},{"text":"There''s very little sales I have to do on that end.","index":508,"end_time":2358.3,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2355.1,"speaker_name":"Matt Forkas"},{"text":"And then for.","index":509,"end_time":2361.34,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2360.46,"speaker_name":"Matt Forkas"},{"text":"New property owners I am leading with the same.","index":510,"end_time":2370.86,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2365.5,"speaker_name":"Matt Forkas"},{"text":"So it would be.","index":511,"end_time":2371.66,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2370.86,"speaker_name":"Matt Forkas"},{"text":"That pitch is pretty much the same service needs revenue in certain cases.","index":512,"end_time":2389.27,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2380.39,"speaker_name":"Matt Forkas"},{"text":"I''ll Also leave with public safety and yeah, our reputation.","index":513,"end_time":2396.15,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2389.35,"speaker_name":"Matt Forkas"},{"text":"So that would include like our existing partnerships in adjacent counties or successful programs we have elsewhere.","index":514,"end_time":2404.42,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2397.91,"speaker_name":"Matt Forkas"},{"text":"And when you say sometimes I''ll lead with what''s making the determination, is it like a gut feeling?","index":515,"end_time":2410.74,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2406.26,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Is it any data backed decision?","index":516,"end_time":2413.06,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2411.06,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"No, it''s, it''s typically the audience.","index":517,"end_time":2415.78,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2413.54,"speaker_name":"Matt Forkas"},{"text":"So if I''m reaching out to the facilities director or in some, some jurisdictions they have, they literally have a, you know, a director of emergency safety.","index":518,"end_time":2423.78,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2415.86,"speaker_name":"Matt Forkas"},{"text":"So yeah, or from reaching out to a fire station, I mean public safety, that''s all they, they don''t care about the money, they just want those, they want the coverage for public safety read for public safety needs.","index":519,"end_time":2435.91,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2424.26,"speaker_name":"Matt Forkas"},{"text":"And yeah, so it''s really just audience.","index":520,"end_time":2438.43,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2435.91,"speaker_name":"Matt Forkas"},{"text":"If I do talk about all these things, but I''ll emphasize certain ones just depending on who I''m talking to.","index":521,"end_time":2444.51,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2438.43,"speaker_name":"Matt Forkas"},{"text":"Really it''s the, the service need and the revenue that, that resonate most with the, the broad spectrum of who I''m talking to at these organizations.","index":522,"end_time":2457.9,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2445.39,"speaker_name":"Matt Forkas"},{"text":"And they in most cases really react positively towards the, the revenue stream that we can bring them.","index":523,"end_time":2465.82,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2459.26,"speaker_name":"Matt Forkas"},{"text":"I think the, the service need, in some cases the service is more important than the money.","index":524,"end_time":2472.82,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2466.46,"speaker_name":"Matt Forkas"},{"text":"I mean that certainly happens too.","index":525,"end_time":2474.62,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2472.82,"speaker_name":"Matt Forkas"},{"text":"And, but they want to hear about what, you know, why we''re different than anyone else calling too.","index":526,"end_time":2480.54,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2474.62,"speaker_name":"Matt Forkas"},{"text":"So our reputation really and those go kind of hand in hand.","index":527,"end_time":2485.06,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2480.54,"speaker_name":"Matt Forkas"},{"text":"Like the revenue structure that we can offer is typically different than what a traditional developer can offer.","index":528,"end_time":2491.3,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2485.06,"speaker_name":"Matt Forkas"},{"text":"We have a really what I would consider more, a little bit of more unique program offering the revenue share with the, with the municipal sites.","index":529,"end_time":2501.06,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2493.3,"speaker_name":"Matt Forkas"},{"text":"And this would be this, this conversation.","index":530,"end_time":2505.3,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2501.3,"speaker_name":"Matt Forkas"},{"text":"This is getting messy here, but I''m following.","index":531,"end_time":2511.69,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2509.13,"speaker_name":"Matt Forkas"},{"text":"No, I gotcha.","index":532,"end_time":2512.49,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2511.69,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, this is municipal, Regular property owners.","index":533,"end_time":2521.53,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2512.57,"speaker_name":"Matt Forkas"},{"text":"And I would even further distinguish these, I would say like municipal or.","index":534,"end_time":2526.57,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2522.01,"speaker_name":"Matt Forkas"},{"text":"So elected.","index":535,"end_time":2535.06,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2534.42,"speaker_name":"Matt Forkas"},{"text":"Meaning like if they have a, if this particular property owner has a board that''s been elected, like an HOA or a church.","index":536,"end_time":2543.46,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2535.06,"speaker_name":"Matt Forkas"},{"text":"We do a lot of churches.","index":537,"end_time":2545.94,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2544.58,"speaker_name":"Matt Forkas"},{"text":"They all have boards and chairmans and whatnot.","index":538,"end_time":2550.38,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2546.42,"speaker_name":"Matt Forkas"},{"text":"So the nature of this conversation is kind of the same where if I''m talking to a private property owner that just has a single site or maybe has a couple, you know, acres for farming or some commercial use, all they care about is.","index":539,"end_time":2570.62,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2550.38,"speaker_name":"Matt Forkas"},{"text":"Yeah, I would imagine revenue.","index":540,"end_time":2574.46,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2573.18,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yep, that tracks.","index":541,"end_time":2576.54,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2574.46,"speaker_name":"Dan Rényi"},{"text":"And they do like, let''s say I''m reaching out to like a storage facility or a, some property owner that has a commercial use on their property, the service does, does matter to them.","index":542,"end_time":2588.98,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2577.02,"speaker_name":"Matt Forkas"},{"text":"I mean if, if, because they want it too.","index":543,"end_time":2592.02,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2588.98,"speaker_name":"Matt Forkas"},{"text":"But typically the revenues, how much Am I getting paid and.","index":544,"end_time":2595.22,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2592.02,"speaker_name":"Matt Forkas"},{"text":"Yeah, yeah.","index":545,"end_time":2598.42,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2597.54,"speaker_name":"Dan Rényi"},{"text":"What do I get out of this?","index":546,"end_time":2599.22,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2598.42,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Right, exactly.","index":547,"end_time":2600.34,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2599.22,"speaker_name":"Matt Forkas"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":548,"end_time":2600.82,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2600.42,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay, great.","index":549,"end_time":2601.46,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2600.82,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So, and I want to come back to the Verizon Bawa and Mastec Bawa.","index":550,"end_time":2605.5,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2601.46,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So you know, this to me opens up a few buckets with probably a lot of sub buckets under them.","index":551,"end_time":2609.86,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2605.5,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"One of those is how do we replicate this not only with a different carrier, so T Mobile for example, in Bawa region, Verizon in the Florida Carolinas, you know, the regions you guys have expanded into the last few years with, with buying up more real estate.","index":552,"end_time":2626.72,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2610.58,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And then the other side of it is, is there opportunity to expand even more of what we''re doing with Verizon and Mastect in the Bawa region or are we kind of fully maxed out there?","index":553,"end_time":2636.56,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2627.04,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, good question.","index":554,"end_time":2639.84,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2638.88,"speaker_name":"Matt Forkas"},{"text":"I do not believe, let''s see.","index":555,"end_time":2643.36,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2640.32,"speaker_name":"Matt Forkas"},{"text":"I do not believe that we''re maxed out in this region.","index":556,"end_time":2653.77,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2651.61,"speaker_name":"Matt Forkas"},{"text":"I think there is a lot more opportunity.","index":557,"end_time":2658.01,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2653.77,"speaker_name":"Matt Forkas"},{"text":"I think as, as the, As newer markets start to grow with population.","index":558,"end_time":2668.73,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2658.17,"speaker_name":"Matt Forkas"},{"text":"I mean we''re seeing that right now.","index":559,"end_time":2670.53,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2669.37,"speaker_name":"Matt Forkas"},{"text":"I just talked a little bit about spots of county 10 years, five, 10 years ago that wouldn''t have been a priority.","index":560,"end_time":2675.53,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2670.53,"speaker_name":"Matt Forkas"},{"text":"People are clearly moving out further west, south, whatever, you know, whatever it is north to find more affordable properties, buy homes.","index":561,"end_time":2685.63,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2676.15,"speaker_name":"Matt Forkas"},{"text":"And so we''re seeing a lot of markets grow and the shift will start to happen and they''ll start to invest in these markets.","index":562,"end_time":2691.989,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2685.63,"speaker_name":"Matt Forkas"},{"text":"So I think there''s going to be a lot in this particular region that they manage.","index":563,"end_time":2698.87,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2691.989,"speaker_name":"Matt Forkas"},{"text":"There is going to be a lot more growth with, with, with new, with new MLA partners on municipal land.","index":564,"end_time":2708,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2699.11,"speaker_name":"Matt Forkas"},{"text":"The same could be said for, for private.","index":565,"end_time":2710.24,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2708.32,"speaker_name":"Matt Forkas"},{"text":"But I really, I know the team really wants to just hunker down at least initially on the municipal side because it grows the land bank in a more efficient way I believe.","index":566,"end_time":2723.92,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2710.24,"speaker_name":"Matt Forkas"},{"text":"Or at least with property owners that have multiple different types of property that we can actively market to the carriers.","index":567,"end_time":2732.41,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2725.68,"speaker_name":"Matt Forkas"},{"text":"Right.","index":568,"end_time":2733.09,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2732.81,"speaker_name":"Dan Rényi"},{"text":"Rather than being limited to a private landowner with one piece of land.","index":569,"end_time":2736.25,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2733.09,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Exactly.","index":570,"end_time":2737.09,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2736.41,"speaker_name":"Matt Forkas"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":571,"end_time":2737.41,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2737.09,"speaker_name":"Matt Forkas"},{"text":"I think having those would be nice, but I don''t think we''ve done the, the leg work to determine, you know, if we did make a campaign for that, what''s.","index":572,"end_time":2748.81,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2737.41,"speaker_name":"Matt Forkas"},{"text":"How many of those sites are actually going to be solid.","index":573,"end_time":2752.09,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2748.97,"speaker_name":"Matt Forkas"},{"text":"You know, must.","index":574,"end_time":2752.97,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2752.09,"speaker_name":"Dan Rényi"},{"text":"I think, yeah, the, the one offs are pretty tough, but I wouldn''t knock out a, a master plan developer that''s got, you know, 40 commercial properties in the DMV.","index":575,"end_time":2765.98,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2754.7,"speaker_name":"Matt Forkas"},{"text":"He wants a tower on them.","index":576,"end_time":2767.66,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2766.3,"speaker_name":"Matt Forkas"},{"text":"Like that would be an ideal partnership too.","index":577,"end_time":2769.62,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2767.74,"speaker_name":"Matt Forkas"},{"text":"Like for sure.","index":578,"end_time":2770.3,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2769.62,"speaker_name":"Matt Forkas"},{"text":"So I do think I Don''t know, you know, if I have a metric to say how much more growth there is in Baba, but I do believe as the markets go further out, there''s going to be opportunity.","index":579,"end_time":2783.39,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2772.3,"speaker_name":"Matt Forkas"},{"text":"I can, I can ask.","index":580,"end_time":2785.99,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2784.11,"speaker_name":"Matt Forkas"},{"text":"I don''t know if I have the numbers.","index":581,"end_time":2787.51,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2785.99,"speaker_name":"Matt Forkas"},{"text":"Sometimes they share with us what their build plan is for the year, saying what they expect, how many towers they''ll actually construct in the new year, or how many towers they''ll, how many installs they''ll put up for the year.","index":582,"end_time":2800.03,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2787.51,"speaker_name":"Matt Forkas"},{"text":"So I don''t have that for, for this year yet, but I can certainly try to get that.","index":583,"end_time":2806.99,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2802.91,"speaker_name":"Matt Forkas"},{"text":"Yeah, if they''re willing to share that, that''d be, you know, great insight for us.","index":584,"end_time":2810.25,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2807.45,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, for us too.","index":585,"end_time":2812.09,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2810.57,"speaker_name":"Matt Forkas"},{"text":"Yeah, yeah, yeah.","index":586,"end_time":2813.61,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2812.41,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay, great.","index":587,"end_time":2815.13,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2814.41,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So, yeah, that I do say Baba for sure.","index":588,"end_time":2818.81,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2815.77,"speaker_name":"Matt Forkas"},{"text":"And in terms of.","index":589,"end_time":2820.49,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2819.53,"speaker_name":"Matt Forkas"},{"text":"I wanted to.","index":590,"end_time":2821.41,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2820.73,"speaker_name":"Matt Forkas"},{"text":"I''m sorry, I was pausing because I was trying to find this thing I made.","index":591,"end_time":2825.05,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2821.41,"speaker_name":"Matt Forkas"},{"text":"It''s pretty crude.","index":592,"end_time":2832.97,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2831.37,"speaker_name":"Matt Forkas"},{"text":"Just give me a second.","index":593,"end_time":2837.8,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2836.92,"speaker_name":"Dan Rényi"},{"text":"Okay, so.","index":594,"end_time":2848.36,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2846.04,"speaker_name":"Dan Rényi"},{"text":"This is how I perceived inquiries coming in altogether.","index":595,"end_time":2856.68,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2852.84,"speaker_name":"Matt Forkas"},{"text":"So like I said, it really starts with just two buckets.","index":596,"end_time":2861.62,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2857.64,"speaker_name":"Matt Forkas"},{"text":"Landowners and carriers.","index":597,"end_time":2863.02,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2861.62,"speaker_name":"Matt Forkas"},{"text":"Very rarely do we get landowners reaching out to us directly and.","index":598,"end_time":2867.1,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2863.42,"speaker_name":"Matt Forkas"},{"text":"Sorry, very rarely do we get a landowner to reach out to us with a site that actually makes sense for the carrier.","index":599,"end_time":2873.58,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2867.34,"speaker_name":"Matt Forkas"},{"text":"That very rarely happens.","index":600,"end_time":2875.26,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2873.74,"speaker_name":"Matt Forkas"},{"text":"Would I like more of that?","index":601,"end_time":2878.3,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2877.1,"speaker_name":"Matt Forkas"},{"text":"Sure.","index":602,"end_time":2878.78,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2878.38,"speaker_name":"Matt Forkas"},{"text":"But the impact doesn''t seem, the priority.","index":603,"end_time":2883.5,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2880.78,"speaker_name":"Matt Forkas"},{"text":"Doesn''T seem as not worth the squeeze.","index":604,"end_time":2886.1,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2883.5,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, I think if there''s a way to.","index":605,"end_time":2888.7,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2886.1,"speaker_name":"Matt Forkas"},{"text":"Can I approach that in a more passive sense or just, you know, something on the back end?","index":606,"end_time":2894.64,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2889.56,"speaker_name":"Matt Forkas"},{"text":"Sure.","index":607,"end_time":2894.96,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2894.64,"speaker_name":"Matt Forkas"},{"text":"I, I do, I do want to grow that piece of the business in.","index":608,"end_time":2898.6,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2894.96,"speaker_name":"Matt Forkas"},{"text":"Stronger like automatic qualifications for them to understand how they can even move forward.","index":609,"end_time":2905.08,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2898.6,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Exactly.","index":610,"end_time":2905.88,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2905.32,"speaker_name":"Matt Forkas"},{"text":"Like if we had, you know, if we decided eventually to do a campaign, you know, spend a couple thousand bucks a month on, on ads or whatever it looks like.","index":611,"end_time":2914.72,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2905.88,"speaker_name":"Matt Forkas"},{"text":"I don''t know.","index":612,"end_time":2915.24,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2914.72,"speaker_name":"Matt Forkas"},{"text":"And we have filtering mechanism.","index":613,"end_time":2917.72,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2915.96,"speaker_name":"Matt Forkas"},{"text":"I think that''d be ideal.","index":614,"end_time":2919.57,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2918.45,"speaker_name":"Matt Forkas"},{"text":"But I, I do believe the, the majority is just coming through this more traditional form.","index":615,"end_time":2926.05,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2919.57,"speaker_name":"Matt Forkas"},{"text":"So we have our carriers and site acts the way they know what sites we have under option is through our kmz, which is just a Google Earth file that has nodes of all of our sites and then they plug that into their software and then they can see where the coverage gaps are and then they can see, oh no, milestone''s got a property here.","index":616,"end_time":2951.98,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2927.49,"speaker_name":"Matt Forkas"},{"text":"Let''s reach out to them.","index":617,"end_time":2953.18,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2952.06,"speaker_name":"Matt Forkas"},{"text":"We pop up and that''s one way or this other way is the carriers giving us the rings directly where we don''t have an active Property owner under management.","index":618,"end_time":2967.9,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2953.34,"speaker_name":"Matt Forkas"},{"text":"And that''s kind of what I was talking about with the Bawa Mass Tech Verizon relationship.","index":619,"end_time":2973.18,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2968.7,"speaker_name":"Matt Forkas"},{"text":"I mean, that''s a really very unique one.","index":620,"end_time":2975.15,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2973.18,"speaker_name":"Matt Forkas"},{"text":"And that comes.","index":621,"end_time":2976.51,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2975.71,"speaker_name":"Matt Forkas"},{"text":"That''s born out of our reputation.","index":622,"end_time":2978.03,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2976.59,"speaker_name":"Matt Forkas"},{"text":"It''s born out of our performance.","index":623,"end_time":2979.23,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2978.03,"speaker_name":"Matt Forkas"},{"text":"But furthermore, like I said, that''s born out of actually having sites that they''re interested in to begin with to perform on.","index":624,"end_time":2986.67,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2980.11,"speaker_name":"Matt Forkas"},{"text":"So it just so happens to be that.","index":625,"end_time":2988.91,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2987.31,"speaker_name":"Matt Forkas"},{"text":"And I think we talked about a little bit last time was.","index":626,"end_time":2991.79,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2989.55,"speaker_name":"Matt Forkas"},{"text":"I don''t think there was any, like, methodology back then when he.","index":627,"end_time":2997.67,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2993.07,"speaker_name":"Matt Forkas"},{"text":"When.","index":628,"end_time":2997.95,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2997.67,"speaker_name":"Dan Rényi"},{"text":"When Len started the business to say, I''m going to target Fairfax county because they have the best land, it''s like, no, he targeted Fairfax County.","index":629,"end_time":3006.72,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2997.95,"speaker_name":"Matt Forkas"},{"text":"This is where he lives.","index":630,"end_time":3007.64,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":3006.72,"speaker_name":"Matt Forkas"},{"text":"Yeah, it''s.","index":631,"end_time":3009.08,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":3008.28,"speaker_name":"Matt Forkas"},{"text":"They''re.","index":632,"end_time":3009.36,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":3009.08,"speaker_name":"Matt Forkas"},{"text":"They''re.","index":633,"end_time":3009.64,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":3009.36,"speaker_name":"Matt Forkas"},{"text":"It worked out.","index":634,"end_time":3010.36,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":3009.64,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Or neighbors.","index":635,"end_time":3011.12,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":3010.44,"speaker_name":"Matt Forkas"},{"text":"It worked out okay.","index":636,"end_time":3012.12,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":3011.12,"speaker_name":"Matt Forkas"},{"text":"We just so happen to live in the dmv, which is an extraordinary area in the country.","index":637,"end_time":3017.96,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":3012.28,"speaker_name":"Matt Forkas"},{"text":"So, yeah, Prince William would make sense.","index":638,"end_time":3020.24,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":3018.52,"speaker_name":"Matt Forkas"},{"text":"Louden would make sense.","index":639,"end_time":3021.48,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":3020.24,"speaker_name":"Matt Forkas"},{"text":"All these counties in Maryland, Montgomery, all these counties, Potomac, like, these are awesome areas.","index":640,"end_time":3030.42,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":3023.88,"speaker_name":"Matt Forkas"},{"text":"This is where people live.","index":641,"end_time":3031.58,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":3030.42,"speaker_name":"Matt Forkas"},{"text":"I mean, this is a huge hub.","index":642,"end_time":3033.26,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":3031.58,"speaker_name":"Matt Forkas"},{"text":"So it.","index":643,"end_time":3034.22,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":3033.66,"speaker_name":"Matt Forkas"},{"text":"It just so happens to work.","index":644,"end_time":3035.82,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":3034.22,"speaker_name":"Matt Forkas"},{"text":"Right.","index":645,"end_time":3036.38,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":3035.98,"speaker_name":"Matt Forkas"},{"text":"We''re in this cert.","index":646,"end_time":3037.5,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":3036.38,"speaker_name":"Matt Forkas"},{"text":"We live in this area.","index":647,"end_time":3038.54,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":3037.5,"speaker_name":"Matt Forkas"},{"text":"You start a business in this area, you start to fragment that out to North Carolina.","index":648,"end_time":3043.26,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":3038.78,"speaker_name":"Matt Forkas"},{"text":"Okay, how do we know that, you know, certain counties are.","index":649,"end_time":3048.3,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":3044.22,"speaker_name":"Matt Forkas"},{"text":"We might know that they''re high growth, but we may not know that.","index":650,"end_time":3053.66,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":3049.26,"speaker_name":"Matt Forkas"},{"text":"What''s a good example?","index":651,"end_time":3057.13,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":3056.17,"speaker_name":"Matt Forkas"},{"text":"They onboarded, like, New Hanover County.","index":652,"end_time":3059.61,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":3057.53,"speaker_name":"Matt Forkas"},{"text":"We spent a lot of time and resources onboarding New New Hanover, Hanover county in North Carolina through this cold outreach approach.","index":653,"end_time":3066.89,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":3059.61,"speaker_name":"Matt Forkas"},{"text":"We approached them, we said, hey, there may have been one site, a pilot site that T Mobile gave us, and we said, hey, the school looks good.","index":654,"end_time":3074.73,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":3067.05,"speaker_name":"Matt Forkas"},{"text":"Can we make it work?","index":655,"end_time":3076.25,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":3075.21,"speaker_name":"Matt Forkas"},{"text":"Yes, we got it built.","index":656,"end_time":3077.85,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":3076.41,"speaker_name":"Matt Forkas"},{"text":"Great.","index":657,"end_time":3078.49,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":3078.17,"speaker_name":"Matt Forkas"},{"text":"But then they also gave us 60 other properties to market, and we built maybe one other property.","index":658,"end_time":3084.49,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":3078.49,"speaker_name":"Matt Forkas"},{"text":"So we spent all this time and effort onboarding these guys.","index":659,"end_time":3088.77,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":3084.81,"speaker_name":"Matt Forkas"},{"text":"Why aren''t we getting other sites like we experienced in Fairfax or in Prince William or in Loudon and now in Spotsylvania?","index":660,"end_time":3096.49,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":3088.77,"speaker_name":"Matt Forkas"},{"text":"And I think the short answer is that in other markets, we don''t experience it here.","index":661,"end_time":3104.97,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":3096.97,"speaker_name":"Matt Forkas"},{"text":"But those.","index":662,"end_time":3106.41,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":3105.37,"speaker_name":"Matt Forkas"},{"text":"The land that we have here is so high quality in the sense that there''s nowhere else to build.","index":663,"end_time":3111.29,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":3106.81,"speaker_name":"Matt Forkas"},{"text":"Right?","index":664,"end_time":3111.93,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":3111.53,"speaker_name":"Dan Rényi"},{"text":"There''s nowhere else to build.","index":665,"end_time":3113.37,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":3112.09,"speaker_name":"Matt Forkas"},{"text":"We got a school in rural North Carolina.","index":666,"end_time":3115.53,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":3113.53,"speaker_name":"Matt Forkas"},{"text":"Most likely, they.","index":667,"end_time":3117.69,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":3116.09,"speaker_name":"Matt Forkas"},{"text":"You got Joe Schmo across the street that''ll take a tower deal for 600 bucks a month in rent.","index":668,"end_time":3121.85,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":3117.69,"speaker_name":"Matt Forkas"},{"text":"And he''ll take that and be happy.","index":669,"end_time":3123.45,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":3122.01,"speaker_name":"Matt Forkas"},{"text":"So that''s what we definitely want to avoid.","index":670,"end_time":3126.49,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":3124.09,"speaker_name":"Matt Forkas"},{"text":"And I know that''s not an easy task, but anyways, like rambling, but that''s great.","index":671,"end_time":3135.37,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":3128.41,"speaker_name":"Matt Forkas"},{"text":"So we have eight minutes left and I have a few questions that I want to get through kind of, kind of rapidly from a technology standpoint.","index":672,"end_time":3144.33,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":3136.89,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I know you guys mentioned that, you know, the website isn''t a high traffic site.","index":673,"end_time":3147.61,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":3144.33,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"You''re not seeing a lot of activity through it.","index":674,"end_time":3149.49,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":3147.61,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Do you have like, I just want to understand from a foundational perspective, like, do you have like Google Analytics and technology like that already installed and tracking things?","index":675,"end_time":3157.53,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":3149.49,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, there''s an, yeah, there''s an analytics, but it''s not reviewed or gotcha.","index":676,"end_time":3163.86,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":3157.77,"speaker_name":"Matt Forkas"},{"text":"10, 10 clicks a month, maybe.","index":677,"end_time":3166.06,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":3164.26,"speaker_name":"Matt Forkas"},{"text":"I don''t know.","index":678,"end_time":3166.58,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":3166.06,"speaker_name":"Matt Forkas"},{"text":"Yeah, okay, I gotcha.","index":679,"end_time":3168.02,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":3166.66,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Are you tracking for your email performance, like response rates or anything like that, or how many meetings you''re getting versus how many emails you''re sending?","index":680,"end_time":3176.58,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":3168.74,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"No, I don''t have an issue with that.","index":681,"end_time":3179.179,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":3178.02,"speaker_name":"Matt Forkas"},{"text":"I mean, I, I typically get meetings at least with an active inquiry.","index":682,"end_time":3183.38,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":3179.179,"speaker_name":"Matt Forkas"},{"text":"I, I''ll drill it into the ground until I get a meeting.","index":683,"end_time":3186.42,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":3183.38,"speaker_name":"Matt Forkas"},{"text":"I don''t.","index":684,"end_time":3186.9,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":3186.42,"speaker_name":"Matt Forkas"},{"text":"The volume''s not there.","index":685,"end_time":3189.38,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":3188.26,"speaker_name":"Matt Forkas"},{"text":"It may be a metric worth tracking, but again, the, the pool of who I''m reaching out to is so, so small.","index":686,"end_time":3197.41,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":3190.21,"speaker_name":"Matt Forkas"},{"text":"Yeah, yeah, yeah.","index":687,"end_time":3199.37,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":3197.73,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And one thing on that volume, you know, I know we talked about automating processes and you said last meeting, that side of volume that needs to be automated yet is that the current like 4 or 5 volume?","index":688,"end_time":3210.09,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":3199.37,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And if we get to 20, the process needs to be a bit more automated or what''s that kind of clip that you''re looking for?","index":689,"end_time":3215.41,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":3210.09,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"What number do we need to hit before it''s like, all right, we need to automate this because I do not have time to handle this manually.","index":690,"end_time":3220.87,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":3215.91,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I think.","index":691,"end_time":3221.99,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":3221.43,"speaker_name":"Matt Forkas"},{"text":"Yeah, automation having a hard time envisioning what that would look like.","index":692,"end_time":3229.31,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":3225.19,"speaker_name":"Matt Forkas"},{"text":"But I would say, you know, anything over, you know, 20, 20amonth would have to probably entertain a conversation like that or we''d have to hire someone.","index":693,"end_time":3238.47,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":3229.31,"speaker_name":"Matt Forkas"},{"text":"I mean, so, so much of this is just so much attention to detail and care.","index":694,"end_time":3244.48,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":3238.79,"speaker_name":"Matt Forkas"},{"text":"Right.","index":695,"end_time":3245.2,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":3244.8,"speaker_name":"Dan Rényi"},{"text":"But yeah, probably, probably 20 would be my breaking point where it''s just too much to manage.","index":696,"end_time":3253.04,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":3247.04,"speaker_name":"Matt Forkas"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":697,"end_time":3253.76,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":3253.44,"speaker_name":"Dan Rényi"},{"text":"And I''m just thinking about, you know, all of those custom fields that you were going through, making sure that we have, you know, those consistently filled out, that we''re all telling the same story across the board and where we can, you know, maybe even utilize like some AI researcher to pull those numbers and put that in or maybe it''s sending them an email to confirm our research and then that''s what gets entered.","index":698,"end_time":3272.92,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":3253.76,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"You know, there''s, there''s a few different ways that we can go there.","index":699,"end_time":3274.94,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":3272.92,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, definitely.","index":700,"end_time":3275.9,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":3275.1,"speaker_name":"Matt Forkas"},{"text":"Awesome.","index":701,"end_time":3276.54,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":3275.98,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"All right.","index":702,"end_time":3276.98,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":3276.54,"speaker_name":"Dan Rényi"},{"text":"And then, you know, as we''re building out, like I said, this next meeting is our roadmap.","index":703,"end_time":3280.98,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":3276.98,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So as we''re building out what possible goals we feel confident in achieving, a lot of it''s going to be based on like financial models.","index":704,"end_time":3288.06,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":3280.98,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"You mentioned spending, you know, just a few minutes ago, like if we spend a couple thousand dollars on ads, blah, blah, blah.","index":705,"end_time":3293.1,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":3288.06,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Do you have numbers in mind already for your agency and your, your ad spend per month?","index":706,"end_time":3299.1,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":3293.18,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"No, no, I, I think the only way to get something like that approved would be to have a really well thought out campaign to and, and really understand the, the results we would expect.","index":707,"end_time":3310.83,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":3299.79,"speaker_name":"Matt Forkas"},{"text":"And honestly, I don''t even think they would be interested in entertaining that right now.","index":708,"end_time":3314.83,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":3311.15,"speaker_name":"Matt Forkas"},{"text":"I think the, the main focus from our experience to drive those inquiries, qualified, decent inquiries, is doing everything we can initially to replicate what we have in this market into new markets.","index":709,"end_time":3329.11,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":3315.149,"speaker_name":"Matt Forkas"},{"text":"And maybe next time we can just dive deeper into that.","index":710,"end_time":3331.87,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":3329.35,"speaker_name":"Matt Forkas"},{"text":"But the, the, the, the, from my, my perception, the answer to that is getting more land under management in those new markets that we want to grow into good quality land that the carriers want.","index":711,"end_time":3346.47,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":3331.87,"speaker_name":"Matt Forkas"},{"text":"And that''s just going to be more traditional form of cold outreach.","index":712,"end_time":3351.99,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":3346.79,"speaker_name":"Matt Forkas"},{"text":"But then what, what, what we need to staple onto that outreach, I think is where we want to see where we need help.","index":713,"end_time":3359.49,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":3352.37,"speaker_name":"Matt Forkas"},{"text":"I mean, case studies are just really fully fleshed out.","index":714,"end_time":3364.85,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":3359.49,"speaker_name":"Matt Forkas"},{"text":"Presentations, maybe video, I don''t know.","index":715,"end_time":3369.81,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":3366.13,"speaker_name":"Matt Forkas"},{"text":"But we really need to have the decks, decks ready for every type of customer that we talk to.","index":716,"end_time":3376.69,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":3369.81,"speaker_name":"Matt Forkas"},{"text":"And I think it''s, it''s just a lot of work.","index":717,"end_time":3380.28,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":3377.17,"speaker_name":"Matt Forkas"},{"text":"And that''s what we, I think the main goal, main focus right now in this first piece in terms of the strategies, how can we grow and replicate the relationships we have in this market into new markets?","index":718,"end_time":3394.68,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":3380.36,"speaker_name":"Matt Forkas"},{"text":"And then, you know, what, what do we need to supplement that?","index":719,"end_time":3399.92,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":3396.28,"speaker_name":"Matt Forkas"},{"text":"I mean, right, it, you know, whatever.","index":720,"end_time":3402.48,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":3399.92,"speaker_name":"Dan Rényi"},{"text":"So, yeah, and we''re looking for growth in quality, not, I mean, we are looking for quantity increase too, but not like going from 5 to 150 leads per month.","index":721,"end_time":3409.94,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":3402.48,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"That''s a mixed bag of quality.","index":722,"end_time":3411.69,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":3410.33,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We''re looking for 20 very high quality or solid leads that can, you know, either move forward quickly with some velocity or sit in the pipeline with an evolving conversation.","index":723,"end_time":3420.49,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":3411.69,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, and I''ll quickly add, if we''re getting an inquiry from the carrier themselves, that is nine times maybe 9.5 times out of 10.","index":724,"end_time":3430.73,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":3420.81,"speaker_name":"Matt Forkas"},{"text":"That is a solid lead.","index":725,"end_time":3432.41,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":3430.97,"speaker_name":"Matt Forkas"},{"text":"That is a good lead.","index":726,"end_time":3433.69,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":3432.49,"speaker_name":"Matt Forkas"},{"text":"Those that come in, even if they''re high rent relos or those are real projects that they need help with that they need to solve.","index":727,"end_time":3442.05,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":3433.93,"speaker_name":"Matt Forkas"},{"text":"Right.","index":728,"end_time":3442.45,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":3442.13,"speaker_name":"Dan Rényi"},{"text":"So we will, we''ll do everything we can to, to vet it into the ground.","index":729,"end_time":3445.65,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":3442.45,"speaker_name":"Matt Forkas"},{"text":"Those are really good, solid leads.","index":730,"end_time":3449.41,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":3446.61,"speaker_name":"Matt Forkas"},{"text":"So those 20, if they turn, if those 20 don''t turn over into the next phase, that''s not necessarily on the quality of the ring.","index":731,"end_time":3457.69,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":3449.41,"speaker_name":"Matt Forkas"},{"text":"It''s just the, you know, the, the, the, the, the project constraints on finding the right property owner or, or whatnot.","index":732,"end_time":3465.26,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":3457.69,"speaker_name":"Matt Forkas"},{"text":"But those are from, from our end.","index":733,"end_time":3467.02,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":3465.26,"speaker_name":"Matt Forkas"},{"text":"If we''re getting 20, that''s gold.","index":734,"end_time":3468.82,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":3467.1,"speaker_name":"Matt Forkas"},{"text":"I mean that''s what we want.","index":735,"end_time":3469.7,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":3468.82,"speaker_name":"Matt Forkas"},{"text":"If those are coming from the carrier themselves at least.","index":736,"end_time":3472.14,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":3469.7,"speaker_name":"Matt Forkas"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":737,"end_time":3472.54,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":3472.14,"speaker_name":"Matt Forkas"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":738,"end_time":3473.02,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":3472.62,"speaker_name":"Dan Rényi"},{"text":"Okay.","index":739,"end_time":3473.58,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":3473.02,"speaker_name":"Dan Rényi"},{"text":"All right.","index":740,"end_time":3474.26,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":3473.82,"speaker_name":"Dan Rényi"},{"text":"I totally hear you.","index":741,"end_time":3475.02,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":3474.26,"speaker_name":"Dan Rényi"},{"text":"Awesome.","index":742,"end_time":3476.18,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":3475.74,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I think, I think, I think what we''ll do there is we''ll work backwards from that goal and try and see what we can do on the budget side.","index":743,"end_time":3485.5,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":3476.18,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"I think that, you know, Matt, that''s what we''re trying to figure out as we move into the roadmap is what type of investment is going to be required to hit the goals.","index":744,"end_time":3495.57,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":3485.5,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"So.","index":745,"end_time":3496.29,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":3495.89,"speaker_name":"oswaldoreyes-chica"},{"text":"Yeah, yeah.","index":746,"end_time":3500.29,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":3497.41,"speaker_name":"Matt Forkas"},{"text":"No.","index":747,"end_time":3501.09,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":3500.77,"speaker_name":"Matt Forkas"},{"text":"And yeah.","index":748,"end_time":3501.97,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":3501.09,"speaker_name":"Matt Forkas"},{"text":"I do not think, you know, a paid advertising campaign to the carriers would work at all.","index":749,"end_time":3509.65,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":3501.97,"speaker_name":"Matt Forkas"},{"text":"I don''t think it would work at all.","index":750,"end_time":3511.17,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":3509.81,"speaker_name":"Matt Forkas"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":751,"end_time":3513.33,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":3512.93,"speaker_name":"Dan Rényi"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":752,"end_time":3513.65,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":3513.33,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And that wasn''t like me pitching a strategy.","index":753,"end_time":3515.05,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":3513.65,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"It was just because we, we have agency spend and then any ad spend is on top.","index":754,"end_time":3518.93,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":3515.05,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So I just wanted to get a flavor of like, you know, I know that we''re at the beginning of the year.","index":755,"end_time":3522.79,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":3519.41,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"You guys just went through eos.","index":756,"end_time":3523.87,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":3522.79,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I wasn''t sure if that was like a topic of conversation of like budget we''ve set aside for this activity.","index":757,"end_time":3528.43,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":3523.87,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"No.","index":758,"end_time":3529.47,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":3529.07,"speaker_name":"Matt Forkas"},{"text":"And historically I don''t think we''ve ever, if we ever have done an ad campaign or any type of ad spend, I don''t think it was actually targeted enough or worked at all.","index":759,"end_time":3541.07,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":3529.47,"speaker_name":"Matt Forkas"},{"text":"I honestly don''t even think we''ve spent a dollar on LinkedIn.","index":760,"end_time":3544.23,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":3541.63,"speaker_name":"Matt Forkas"},{"text":"I don''t think we''ve spent a dollar on Google Ads just because it''s.","index":761,"end_time":3548.84,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":3544.23,"speaker_name":"Matt Forkas"},{"text":"We, we know where the business is, so.","index":762,"end_time":3551.48,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":3549.56,"speaker_name":"Matt Forkas"},{"text":"Right.","index":763,"end_time":3551.88,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":3551.56,"speaker_name":"Dan Rényi"},{"text":"And it''s been historically just all relationship based.","index":764,"end_time":3554.36,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":3551.88,"speaker_name":"Matt Forkas"},{"text":"Got it.","index":765,"end_time":3556.2,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":3555.64,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":766,"end_time":3556.6,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":3556.2,"speaker_name":"Matt Forkas"},{"text":"So then, so one of the things that we''re probably going to do.","index":767,"end_time":3559,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":3556.6,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":768,"end_time":3559.28,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":3559,"speaker_name":"oswaldoreyes-chica"},{"text":"We''re going to run very, I envision.","index":769,"end_time":3561.88,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":3559.28,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"I got to talk to Colin.","index":770,"end_time":3563.16,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":3561.88,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"We''re going to run targeted campaigns and paid media might be supplemental to that, but it would be in a different way than just like running Google Ads.","index":771,"end_time":3573.17,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":3563.56,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"In terms of just the overall budget for this initiative, did you have a chance to sync with the team on that?","index":772,"end_time":3580.45,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":3573.49,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"Well, I think that''s kind of the big question mark.","index":773,"end_time":3584.45,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":3582.45,"speaker_name":"Matt Forkas"},{"text":"It''s, it''s, what do you, what are the deliverables that you guys perceive that we need to supplement our growth into new markets and then kind of starting from there.","index":774,"end_time":3596.05,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":3584.45,"speaker_name":"Matt Forkas"},{"text":"So I mean we, I, we saw, we all saw the ranges of what a typical customer reviewers spends and that''s fine but we just want to make sure that''s actually going to drive results and it''s, it''s worth our time.","index":775,"end_time":3607.68,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":3596.21,"speaker_name":"Matt Forkas"},{"text":"So yeah, just to take a step back, it''s important to note that like there''s just a couple of ways to do this right.","index":776,"end_time":3613.84,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":3607.68,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"So we have clients who say, hey, Justin, Colin, Tristan, Dan, you know, here''s what budget I have.","index":777,"end_time":3622.48,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":3613.84,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"What outcomes do you think you can get from that?","index":778,"end_time":3625.68,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":3623.12,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"And then, and then we work through that financial model or there is, you know, hey, here are the goals that I''m trying to drive towards.","index":779,"end_time":3636.06,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":3626.08,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"How much is that going to cost?","index":780,"end_time":3638.14,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":3636.46,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"And then there''s, I''m not 100 sure on either.","index":781,"end_time":3642.54,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":3638.86,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"Can you help put something together so I can start to take a look at something that is modeled out based on industry benchmarks, historical data, what you guys think, etc.","index":782,"end_time":3653.9,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":3642.62,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"And so my guess is it falls somewhere between the second and third option there, which is, you know, we''re not 100 sure what the budget is.","index":783,"end_time":3662.94,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":3654.46,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"We''re comfortable with what we saw on your site, what Tristan told us want to see from you.","index":784,"end_time":3667.82,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":3662.94,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"And then I think what we''re going to do is we''ll put together something along the lines of like, I don''t know, what do you think, Colin?","index":785,"end_time":3674.7,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":3667.98,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"Like 8 to 10k?","index":786,"end_time":3676.264,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":3674.7,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"8 to 10.","index":787,"end_time":3677.02,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":3676.336,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, that''s exactly what I had in mind.","index":788,"end_time":3678.38,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":3677.02,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And then maybe some light ad spend on top.","index":789,"end_time":3681.73,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":3678.54,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"That''s different type of ad spend, Matt, than maybe what you''re thinking where it will be supplemental to a campaign that we''re running versus we''re running paid media campaigns.","index":790,"end_time":3691.85,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":3681.73,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"And if that doesn''t make sense, this.","index":791,"end_time":3693.49,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":3691.85,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Is just a couple of thoughts here on this because you know, ultimately we are pretty shy in terms of setting a budget on this because we haven''t seen results.","index":792,"end_time":3706.41,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":3693.49,"speaker_name":"oswaldoreyes-chica"},{"text":"Right.","index":793,"end_time":3706.73,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":3706.41,"speaker_name":"oswaldoreyes-chica"},{"text":"And I think indicated that at the end of the day, you know, it''s not, you know, the biggest bang is really the, the relationships that you build with the carriers themselves.","index":794,"end_time":3720.2,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":3706.73,"speaker_name":"oswaldoreyes-chica"},{"text":"As you pointed out, 95 point, 99.5% or whatever is the, the value of that one lead coming from the carrier versus coming from a side acquisition firm.","index":795,"end_time":3731.56,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":3720.92,"speaker_name":"oswaldoreyes-chica"},{"text":"So we know that''s where we need to get to.","index":796,"end_time":3736.2,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":3733.72,"speaker_name":"oswaldoreyes-chica"},{"text":"And I think what Matt is looking for is, okay, what are the materials that will help him, help us get there faster.","index":797,"end_time":3744.11,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":3736.2,"speaker_name":"oswaldoreyes-chica"},{"text":"Right?","index":798,"end_time":3744.59,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":3744.19,"speaker_name":"oswaldoreyes-chica"},{"text":"Yes.","index":799,"end_time":3745.91,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":3745.55,"speaker_name":"oswaldoreyes-chica"},{"text":"There''s some need for landowners as well.","index":800,"end_time":3749.23,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":3745.91,"speaker_name":"oswaldoreyes-chica"},{"text":"And some of that material is, you know, obviously tailored differently.","index":801,"end_time":3753.79,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":3749.31,"speaker_name":"oswaldoreyes-chica"},{"text":"But I would say, you know, the better approach to take on this for us to be able to consume would be to think about how do we test this in a way that shows us the results will be, they''ll be worth it.","index":802,"end_time":3772.52,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":3755.39,"speaker_name":"oswaldoreyes-chica"},{"text":"Right.","index":803,"end_time":3773.08,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":3772.76,"speaker_name":"Matt Forkas"},{"text":"Because I can tell you that a ten thousand dollar spend for the month, it''s not gonna, that''s just not gonna feel right.","index":804,"end_time":3781.48,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":3773.08,"speaker_name":"oswaldoreyes-chica"},{"text":"We''re gonna.","index":805,"end_time":3782.6,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":3781.96,"speaker_name":"oswaldoreyes-chica"},{"text":"Okay, that''s what I was trying to get.","index":806,"end_time":3784.08,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":3782.6,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"Yeah, that''s where I was trying.","index":807,"end_time":3785.4,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":3784.08,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"I don''t want to put something in front of you that you''re like, yeah.","index":808,"end_time":3787.8,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":3785.4,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"It''S not gonna work.","index":809,"end_time":3789,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":3788.04,"speaker_name":"oswaldoreyes-chica"},{"text":"Right.","index":810,"end_time":3789.36,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":3789,"speaker_name":"oswaldoreyes-chica"},{"text":"So we need to feel, well, also it works unless it works.","index":811,"end_time":3793.94,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":3789.36,"speaker_name":"oswaldoreyes-chica"},{"text":"Right, Exactly.","index":812,"end_time":3794.66,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":3793.94,"speaker_name":"oswaldoreyes-chica"},{"text":"But you know, again, it''s a big deal to put in $10,000 is my point.","index":813,"end_time":3798.26,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":3794.66,"speaker_name":"oswaldoreyes-chica"},{"text":"100.","index":814,"end_time":3798.98,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":3798.42,"speaker_name":"Matt Forkas"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":815,"end_time":3799.5,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":3799.06,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"Right.","index":816,"end_time":3799.86,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":3799.5,"speaker_name":"oswaldoreyes-chica"},{"text":"So I, I think, you know, I want to know that.","index":817,"end_time":3803.78,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":3799.86,"speaker_name":"oswaldoreyes-chica"},{"text":"Let''s test out, let''s do a pilot, right.","index":818,"end_time":3807.14,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":3804.26,"speaker_name":"oswaldoreyes-chica"},{"text":"And see how that mechanic, how the other mechanics works and see whether we get, we may not get the results that you would envision on a tradition, on a typical campaign that you guys run for other clients.","index":819,"end_time":3820.64,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":3807.38,"speaker_name":"oswaldoreyes-chica"},{"text":"But I think you help us build confidence.","index":820,"end_time":3824.16,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":3820.72,"speaker_name":"oswaldoreyes-chica"},{"text":"Right.","index":821,"end_time":3824.48,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":3824.16,"speaker_name":"oswaldoreyes-chica"},{"text":"And that''s what I think that''s ultimately what we need to be able to see.","index":822,"end_time":3827.44,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":3824.48,"speaker_name":"oswaldoreyes-chica"},{"text":"Yeah, I think there''s two sides to this.","index":823,"end_time":3829.76,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":3828.08,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"So one is we can try and build something out that we can certainly test with less risk.","index":824,"end_time":3836,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":3829.92,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"And pretty much everything you said, there''s the other side of this that is to have good marketing, it does require investment and it requires, I''m trying not to like use a bunch of analogies, but, you know, snowball down a hill.","index":825,"end_time":3852.44,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":3836.08,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"If I roll, you know, tiny little snowball, it''s not going to turn into a big snowball.","index":826,"end_time":3856.04,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":3852.44,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"And so our fear always is if we shortchange the start, you''re not going to get a flavor for what it could look like.","index":827,"end_time":3863,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":3856.04,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"And so what we have to balance on our side is like if it was just like sending a couple emails out for relatively low everything and we''re gonna get a bunch of results, you''re gonna be like, this is great, let''s jump kerosene on this.","index":828,"end_time":3875.84,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":3863,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"And I''ll give, you know, I''m putting in one And I''m getting two out.","index":829,"end_time":3878.88,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":3875.84,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"It''s amazing.","index":830,"end_time":3879.56,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":3878.88,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"We''d have a line, you know, out the door and around the block and to the next block of people who wanted to do that.","index":831,"end_time":3887.88,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":3880.36,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"The reality is that you have to build out these financial models.","index":832,"end_time":3891.24,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":3888.04,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"You have to say, here''s what we''re setting out to do.","index":833,"end_time":3893.04,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":3891.24,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"And then you need to run the different pieces of it.","index":834,"end_time":3896.28,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":3893.04,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"You need content that''s going to resonate with an audience.","index":835,"end_time":3899.29,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":3896.28,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"You need to be able to ensure that they are going to see it, hear it, engage with it.","index":836,"end_time":3904.37,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":3899.29,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"You have to have multiple touch points.","index":837,"end_time":3905.89,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":3904.37,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"You''re going to have to be able to track all of this.","index":838,"end_time":3907.53,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":3905.89,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"You''re going to have to be able to send signals to a sales team or to members of your team to say, here''s what we''re seeing.","index":839,"end_time":3913.05,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":3907.53,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"So it takes.","index":840,"end_time":3914.01,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":3913.05,"speaker_name":"Matt Forkas"},{"text":"It takes a lot.","index":841,"end_time":3915.29,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":3914.33,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"I totally understand.","index":842,"end_time":3917.53,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":3916.41,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"And we won''t go to that level if that''s not something you''re comfortable with.","index":843,"end_time":3921.85,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":3917.61,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"So we''ll just have to figure out what''s possible.","index":844,"end_time":3923.53,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":3921.85,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"Because what I don''t want.","index":845,"end_time":3924.85,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":3923.61,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"My biggest fear always, Ozzy, is we do too little, and then you get nothing.","index":846,"end_time":3932.88,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":3924.85,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"And so I''d rather say let''s do a little bit more than too little.","index":847,"end_time":3937.08,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":3933.52,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"Let''s get.","index":848,"end_time":3937.6,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":3937.08,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"Versus let''s say you spend.","index":849,"end_time":3940.08,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":3937.92,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"We''re not going to put this out there, but I tell you, hey, we''re going to do a pilot.","index":850,"end_time":3945.48,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":3941.28,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"You''re going to spend $2,000 a month for three months.","index":851,"end_time":3948.24,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":3945.48,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"Odds are you''re going to get nothing from that.","index":852,"end_time":3951.4,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":3948.72,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"And then you just wasted $6,000.","index":853,"end_time":3953.6,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":3951.4,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"So we have to find that, like, inflection point of where we can try some things out.","index":854,"end_time":3959.06,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":3953.76,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"But there actually still will be results that come along with it.","index":855,"end_time":3962.54,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":3959.06,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"And there''s a threshold for that that I''m just gonna have to work with Colin and Tristan and Dan to figure out what that is so that everybody can be comfortable.","index":856,"end_time":3970.42,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":3962.54,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"I hope that makes sense.","index":857,"end_time":3971.34,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":3970.42,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"And I''m not just, like, talking myself in circles here.","index":858,"end_time":3974.02,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":3971.34,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"Yep.","index":859,"end_time":3975.86,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":3975.38,"speaker_name":"oswaldoreyes-chica"},{"text":"No, I understand.","index":860,"end_time":3976.5,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":3975.86,"speaker_name":"oswaldoreyes-chica"},{"text":"I certainly understand, you know, the.","index":861,"end_time":3979.26,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":3976.82,"speaker_name":"oswaldoreyes-chica"},{"text":"The.","index":862,"end_time":3979.62,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":3979.26,"speaker_name":"Matt Forkas"},{"text":"The full breath and.","index":863,"end_time":3981.14,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":3979.7,"speaker_name":"oswaldoreyes-chica"},{"text":"And, you know, it''d be great to be able to do that, Right?","index":864,"end_time":3984.18,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":3981.14,"speaker_name":"oswaldoreyes-chica"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":865,"end_time":3984.9,"speaker_id":6,"start_time":3984.42,"speaker_name":"Tristan"},{"text":"But, yeah, that''s just not where we are.","index":866,"end_time":3988.5,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":3985.74,"speaker_name":"oswaldoreyes-chica"},{"text":"And just, you know, we.","index":867,"end_time":3990.18,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":3988.5,"speaker_name":"oswaldoreyes-chica"},{"text":"We got to.","index":868,"end_time":3990.94,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":3990.18,"speaker_name":"oswaldoreyes-chica"},{"text":"It''s got to be right size for us, I think.","index":869,"end_time":3994.78,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":3991.82,"speaker_name":"oswaldoreyes-chica"},{"text":"And, you know, demonstrating value, it''s obviously important.","index":870,"end_time":3997.98,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":3995.02,"speaker_name":"oswaldoreyes-chica"},{"text":"So everything that we''re going to propose is going to be demonstrating value.","index":871,"end_time":4002.5,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":3998.22,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"I mean, that is what this entire engagement is, which is starting with outcomes not focused on, hey, you know, let''s get some.","index":872,"end_time":4010.62,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":4002.5,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"Some views and some Social media likes this is what are the most important outcomes to your business and how can we drive towards them?","index":873,"end_time":4018.95,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":4010.7,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"And what, how can we track all of that and then attribute it to the return on investment?","index":874,"end_time":4025.59,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":4019.27,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"We''re going to have to come up with what that can be at the, you know, where''s that inflection point of what we don''t believe will work?","index":875,"end_time":4034.59,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":4026.31,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"And that that''s just something we''re not.","index":876,"end_time":4036.15,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":4034.59,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"We won''t take a dollar if we don''t feel like you''re going to put it into a place that''s going to drive results.","index":877,"end_time":4043.09,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":4036.47,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"So we have to come back to you and say, here''s the inflection point.","index":878,"end_time":4047.25,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":4043.49,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"If we go lower than this, at that point, at that clip, we feel like you''re going to be wasting your money and you''re going to get nothing back.","index":879,"end_time":4055.17,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":4047.41,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"And then, and, and we don''t want to be a part of that because I don''t like having to have calls with clients that say we didn''t get anything.","index":880,"end_time":4064.21,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":4055.89,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"And that''s why we rolled out this engagement the way that we did a couple of years ago, which was instead of having people come to us, hey, I want to spend $3,000 a month.","index":881,"end_time":4071.94,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":4064.53,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"We''re like, cool, we''ll take it and we''ll see how it goes.","index":882,"end_time":4074.54,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":4071.94,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"And then three months later, nothing comes back.","index":883,"end_time":4077.26,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":4074.7,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"And then I''m like, I have to have a conversation.","index":884,"end_time":4079.82,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":4078.3,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"Well, you didn''t spend.","index":885,"end_time":4080.54,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":4079.82,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"You know, if you don''t spend, you don''t get.","index":886,"end_time":4082.22,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":4080.54,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"And that''s a lot more difficult to do after the fact.","index":887,"end_time":4085.66,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":4082.62,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"And so we try to do it before and say, based on our projections, Ozzy, Matt, Len, here''s what we think you need to spend.","index":888,"end_time":4092.94,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":4086.22,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"Here''s what we think the outcomes are going to be and how do you feel about it?","index":889,"end_time":4096.99,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":4093.1,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"And then we have that conversation, which is going to take place in the upcoming roadmap.","index":890,"end_time":4101.11,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":4096.99,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"And so we just wanted to make sure we''re, you know, we build something right size here for you guys.","index":891,"end_time":4106.15,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":4101.11,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"And so I''m glad we asked because we would have come back with $10,000 a month.","index":892,"end_time":4110.59,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":4106.31,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"You guys would have been like, we''re not starting there.","index":893,"end_time":4113.51,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":4110.59,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"So I, I think that that''s a good conversation.","index":894,"end_time":4117.43,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":4113.75,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"And we''ll keep this conversation going in the next meeting.","index":895,"end_time":4120.63,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":4117.43,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"That''s great.","index":896,"end_time":4122.67,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":4122.19,"speaker_name":"Matt Forkas"},{"text":"Just because we''re, we''re 10 minutes over.","index":897,"end_time":4125.91,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":4124.59,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I''m sure everyone''s pressed maybe to get another meeting or maybe a bathroom break because we''ve been here for an hour.","index":898,"end_time":4129.71,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":4125.91,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"But I''ll follow up with a booking link so that we can get time on the calendar, hopefully for next week for this roadmap presentation.","index":899,"end_time":4137.07,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":4129.71,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"But really appreciate your time, Ozzy.","index":900,"end_time":4140.35,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":4137.71,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Sorry, I did not notice when he joined so I did not say hello.","index":901,"end_time":4142.59,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":4140.35,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Otherwise I would have taken a minute to do.","index":902,"end_time":4144.23,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":4142.59,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Sorry I was joined late.","index":903,"end_time":4145.55,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":4144.23,"speaker_name":"oswaldoreyes-chica"},{"text":"Apologies for that.","index":904,"end_time":4146.43,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":4145.55,"speaker_name":"oswaldoreyes-chica"},{"text":"No worries at all.","index":905,"end_time":4147.39,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":4146.43,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"FYI, next Thursdays won''t be a good day for us.","index":906,"end_time":4152.01,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":4148.33,"speaker_name":"oswaldoreyes-chica"},{"text":"We have meetings all day with carriers so it probably Friday.","index":907,"end_time":4158.33,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":4152.65,"speaker_name":"oswaldoreyes-chica"},{"text":"Probably be better.","index":908,"end_time":4159.29,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":4158.33,"speaker_name":"oswaldoreyes-chica"},{"text":"Okay, that''s good busy, Ozzy.","index":909,"end_time":4161.97,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":4159.53,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"Yeah, that''s good busy.","index":910,"end_time":4163.09,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":4161.97,"speaker_name":"oswaldoreyes-chica"},{"text":"So 9, I think 9:10am Looks like would be a reasonable time.","index":911,"end_time":4169.21,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":4163.09,"speaker_name":"oswaldoreyes-chica"},{"text":"Yeah, I''ll.","index":912,"end_time":4170.93,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":4170.17,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I''ll match up all our calendars over here and then we''ll send over a link that you guys can book directly on for whatever works for you.","index":913,"end_time":4175.96,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":4170.93,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Sounds great.","index":914,"end_time":4176.71,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":4176.27,"speaker_name":"oswaldoreyes-chica"},{"text":"Thanks.","index":915,"end_time":4177.15,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":4176.71,"speaker_name":"oswaldoreyes-chica"},{"text":"Awesome.","index":916,"end_time":4177.95,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":4177.39,"speaker_name":"Matt Forkas"},{"text":"All right, thanks guys.","index":917,"end_time":4179.43,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":4178.03,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"We''ll talk next week.","index":918,"end_time":4180.27,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":4179.43,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"Take care.","index":919,"end_time":4180.99,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":4180.51,"speaker_name":"oswaldoreyes-chica"},{"text":"Bye.","index":920,"end_time":4181.39,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":4180.99,"speaker_name":"oswaldoreyes-chica"},{"text":"Thanks.","index":921,"end_time":4182.27,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":4181.87,"speaker_name":"Matt Forkas"},{"text":"Bye.","index":922,"end_time":4182.67,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":4182.27,"speaker_name":"Dan Rényi"}],"dateString":"2026-01-22T14:00:00.000Z","host_email":"colin.costigan@marketersindemand.com","meeting_link":"https://us02web.zoom.us/j/88208688412?pwd=Ccbr4IbNbprAsghGj1Gu2f61wjMpcV.1","participants":["colin.costigan@marketersindemand.com,dan.renyi@marketersindemand.com,justin.brown@marketersindemand.com,tristan.pelligrino@marketersindemand.com,len@milestonetowers.com,matthew@milestonetowers.com,oswaldo@milestonetowers.com","dan.renyi@marketersindemand.com","justin.brown@marketersindemand.com","tristan.pelligrino@marketersindemand.com","len@milestonetowers.com","matthew@milestonetowers.com","oswaldo@milestonetowers.com"],"transcript_url":"https://app.fireflies.ai/view/01KF3KCYHMX1K6JD5KTR17QBYH","organizer_email":"colin.costigan@marketersindemand.com"}'::jsonb,
    '{"label":"positive","confidence":0.9,"bullets":["Defined target of 20 high‑quality carrier inquiries per month to drive sustainable growth.","Matt explained current lead intake is manual; most data originates from direct carrier contact.","Colin emphasized need to formalize definitions for lead quality and development stages.","Team agreed success depends on replicating strong Verizon-Mastec partnerships in new regions.","Ozzy requested phased pilot showing value before scaling; full $10K/month not yet feasible."],"highlights":[{"quote":"If we''re getting 20, that''s gold. I mean that''s what we want.","speaker":"Matt Forkas"},{"quote":"We need just some true definition so we''re all speaking the same language there.","speaker":"Colin Costigan"},{"quote":"Let''s test out, let''s do a pilot, and see how the mechanics work.","speaker":"oswaldoreyes-chica"}],"topics":["lead_quality","CRM","partnerships","growth","budget"],"model":"openai/gpt-4-1106-preview","version":1,"generated_at":"2026-01-22T00:00:00Z"}'::jsonb,
    '{"fireflies_summary":{"notes":"## **Lead Generation and Qualification**\n\nThe main focus is to increase the number of high-quality inquiries from carriers to about **20 per month**, shifting from the current rate of approximately **4 to 5 inquiries monthly** (14:47).\n\n- **Matt Forkas** explained that inquiries primarily come via direct relationships rather than forms or online submissions, with most leads entering through personal emails and manual Salesforce entry.\n- There are two main lead types: **soft inquiries**, usually low quality or unviable leads, and **inquiries**, which represent active, promising projects; qualification is based mostly on manual evaluation and factors like property size and proximity to towers.\n- Salesforce is currently used more as a project management tool than a marketing or lead-tracking system, with manual input for contacts and project statuses, limiting automated tracking and source attribution.\n- Increasing monthly inquiries to **20** is seen as critical, with a strong emphasis on maintaining lead quality rather than just volume, as **Matt** highlighted that inquiries from carriers themselves are almost always solid leads.\n\n## **Market Relationships and Regional Growth**\n\nThe business depends heavily on strong carrier and site acquisition firm relationships, particularly with **Verizon and Mastec in the Bawa market**, which drive most active inquiries (32:05).\n\n- This relationship model is considered the \"golden ticket\" because carriers provide early access to search rings and opportunities, enabling Milestone to onboard multiple municipal properties efficiently.\n- Expansion into new markets relies on replicating these relationships, especially focusing on **municipal landowners** who often control multiple properties, creating more efficient growth opportunities.\n- **Matt** identified challenges in other markets, such as North Carolina, where lower land quality and easier alternatives for carriers reduce the attractiveness of sites compared to the DMV region.\n- The strategy prioritizes onboarding high-quality land in new markets to secure carrier interest before scaling outreach and marketing efforts.\n\n## **Sales and Outreach Strategy**\n\nOutreach messaging is tailored based on the audience, with **service needs and revenue sharing** being the most effective hooks for engagement (38:42).\n\n- Municipal property owners respond well to service and revenue opportunities, with public safety needs sometimes outweighing financial incentives.\n- Private landowners mostly focus on revenue potential, and outreach to them is limited due to lower conversion rates and less strategic value.\n- The **existing reputation** and track record of Milestone Towers play a key role in differentiating from competitors and gaining trust with both carriers and landowners.\n- Outreach relies on personal contacts and calls rather than mass marketing, reflecting the niche and relationship-driven nature of the business.\n\n## **Technology and Process Automation**\n\nCurrent systems lack automation, with manual data entry and limited use of analytics; automation will become necessary when lead volume exceeds about **20 inquiries per month** (53:41).\n\n- Salesforce fields often lack consistent data entry, requiring clearer definitions and processes to ensure quality and uniform reporting.\n- Email and outreach activity are not currently tracked for performance metrics such as response or meeting rates.\n- The team recognizes a need for process improvements, including possible AI or automation tools to validate and input data more efficiently without sacrificing the personalized attention required for these leads.\n- Investment in automation or additional staff will be considered as inquiry volume grows to maintain quality and responsiveness.\n\n## **Marketing Budget and Investment Strategy**\n\nThere is cautiousness around committing to large ad spend, with an initial budget discussion centering around **$8,000 to $10,000 per month** for agency and campaign costs, with ad spend considered supplemental (01:01:16).\n\n- **Justin Brown** and **Oswaldo Reyes-Chica** emphasized the importance of testing with a pilot campaign to prove value before scaling investment, given past experiences with limited results and concerns over budget risk.\n- Paid advertising directly targeting carriers is seen as unlikely to be effective; instead, campaigns would support existing outreach efforts with tailored content and multiple touchpoints.\n- The team stressed that marketing must be outcome-driven, focusing on measurable lead quality and pipeline progression rather than superficial metrics.\n- The roadmap for marketing spend and activities will be refined to balance investment size with expected results, avoiding underfunding that could yield no meaningful returns.\n\n## **Next Steps and Timeline**\n\nThe upcoming meeting will present a detailed **roadmap and financial model** for marketing strategy and budget allocation, targeting **Friday at 9:10 AM** to accommodate carrier meeting schedules (01:09:08).\n\n- Colin Costigan will coordinate calendar invites and follow-ups to finalize scheduling.\n- The roadmap session will define clear goals, budget scenarios, and expected outcomes to guide decision-making.\n- Deliverables will include case studies, presentations, and potentially video content designed to support outreach and relationship-building efforts.\n- The focus will be on replicating successful relationship models in new markets and supplementing outreach with strategic marketing materials.","outline":null,"keywords":["Salesforce","Lead Management","Carrier Relationships","Marketing Budget","Municipal Landowners","Inquiry Qualification"],"overview":"- **Increased Inquiries Goal:** Aim for **20 high-quality inquiries monthly**, up from 4-5; quality over quantity remains key.  \n- **Carrier Relationships Crucial:** Strong ties with **Verizon and Mastec** drive inquiries; they offer early access to opportunities.  \n- **Tailored Outreach Messaging:** Focus on service and revenue appeals for municipal owners; private landowners prefer revenue potential.  \n- **Need for Automation:** Current manual processes limit efficiency; improvements essential as inquiry volume grows past 20 monthly.  \n- **Cautious Marketing Budget:** Proposed **$8,000 to $10,000/month**; need pilot campaigns to evaluate before scaling investment.  \n- **Upcoming Financial Roadmap Meeting:** A session on **budget allocation** scheduled for **Friday** to set clear goals and expected outcomes.","action_items":"\n**Matt Forkas**\nProvide any available carrier build plan numbers for the upcoming year to assist with forecasting and marketing strategy (46:47)\nShare existing key contact and project data from Salesforce to support deeper pipeline analysis and marketing alignment (00:00)\nConfirm internal preferences and realities around inquiry volume and process automation threshold (estimated 20/month) (53:41)\nCollaborate with marketing team to specify marketing collateral needs (case studies, presentations, videos) to support new market entry (56:36)\n\n**Colin Costigan**\nFollow up with scheduling a roadmap presentation meeting, offering booking links and accommodating Friday preference (01:08:44)\nDevelop standard definitions for development stages (soft inquiry, inquiry, candidate, etc.) to align data tracking and reporting (27:02)\nPrepare financial and marketing strategy roadmap based on client feedback for next meeting (00:00)\n\n**Justin Brown**\nLead creation of financial model and initial budget recommendations for marketing investment based on desired inquiry growth and realistic pilot scopes (8-10k suggested) (01:01:16)\nDevelop proposal for test campaigns balancing risk tolerance and expected outcomes, to build confidence and demonstrate value (01:03:48)\n\n**Oswaldo Reyes-Chica**\nProvide input on internal budget comfort level and feasibility of marketing spend to guide strategy development (01:02:17)\n\n**Dan Rényi**\nSupport discussion and modeling of automation needs triggered by inquiry volume growth (53:37)\n\n**Tristan Pelligrino**\nAssist with detailed review and analysis of historic marketing agency work outcomes vs expectations (22:06)\n"},"migrated_from":"contract_meetings","original_id":"e4755d92-56f3-4cbf-ad16-09fc401f8595","master_marketer":{"status":"migrated"}}'::jsonb,
