    '{"Colin Costigan","Justin Brown","Joe Ragno","Joe Ragno","timot","Nathalie Mintjens"}'::text[],
    2756,
    'https://us02web.zoom.us/j/89661160528?pwd=KQASOzvolzWNcOxmA0hA2mfi1J6peZ.1',
    '{"id":"01KEYJNFJ5A480TR8EEP8XGTVE","title":"Aligned Growth Engine | Roadmap Meeting","summary":{"notes":"## **Target Market Definition and Segmentation**\n\nThe team finalized three target market segments to focus initial outreach and platform growth efforts effectively (03:50).\n\n- **Behavioral health and substance use treatment centers** were identified as the primary onboarding target, with firms generating between **$2 million and $30 million in revenue** and employing **25 to 500 people** (08:11).\n    - These centers typically hold titles like Chief Operating Officer or Admissions Director, facing challenges such as poor lead flow and underutilized bed capacity.\n    - Onboarding these centers first ensures there is a robust network for employers and employees to engage with once outreach begins.\n    - Joe Ragno confirmed alignment with this segment based on his existing network and outreach efforts.\n    - Integration opportunities with EMR systems like Kaipu were noted to enhance platform value.\n\n- **Mid-market employers** represent the second segment, targeting industries such as manufacturing, construction, healthcare, and hospitality, with revenue between **$20 million and $500 million** and employee counts from **100 to 1,000** (11:58).\n    - These employers may bolt Treatment Navigator onto existing Employee Assistance Programs (EAPs), emphasizing recruiting, retention, and employee wellbeing.\n    - The focus is on executive HR roles such as Chief People Officer and HR managers, who need scalable mental health and addiction solutions.\n    - This wide net ensures no early market share is missed, with plans to build credibility through early proof points from smaller companies.\n\n- The third segment targets **fast-growing technology, SaaS, and professional services companies** with revenues ranging from **$100 million to $2 billion** and employee headcounts between **1,000 and 5,000** (13:41).\n    - These companies require quick deployment of affordable, comprehensive mental health solutions to support rapid recruiting.\n    - Outreach will focus on CHRO-level executives who demand volume discounts and smooth onboarding.\n    - Joe Ragno confirmed readiness to offer volume-based pricing to accommodate this segment''s needs.\n  \n- Additionally, insurance brokerages, benefits consulting, and human capital firms were segmented separately to tailor messaging and proof points, distinguishing them from EAP providers (14:45).\n\n## **Brand Positioning and Messaging Framework**\n\nThe team developed a brand story positioning both treatment centers and employers as heroes, emphasizing the platform’s role in simplifying access to mental health and substance use treatment (16:19).\n\n- Treatment centers are positioned as mission-driven heroes receiving qualified leads without traditional advertising pressure, enhancing bed utilization and patient intake efficiency.\n- Employers are portrayed as champions providing quick, anonymous access to treatment options for employees, reducing administrative burdens and compliance risks.\n- Joe Ragno advised shifting messaging focus from substance use to broader mental health to avoid advertising restrictions and expand appeal (20:01).\n- The brand story is designed to be dynamic and evolve as product development and marketing campaigns progress, ensuring ongoing alignment with market feedback.\n- Colin emphasized that this foundational messaging will drive subsequent website content, sales materials, and outreach campaigns.\n\n## **Competitive Landscape and Market Opportunity**\n\nThe competitive analysis revealed a fragmented market with no direct competitor fully addressing the niche Treatment Navigator targets, offering a strong opportunity for differentiation (20:56).\n\n- Spring Health boasts a strong brand with a **9 out of 10 score** in key marketing categories but lacks paid advertising and organic social presence outside of YouTube (22:09).\n    - Their focus is more on substance use and mental health combined, with a large YouTube library but limited paid media.\n- Lira targets enterprise clients with **over 268,000 LinkedIn followers**, emphasizing thought leadership and paid social campaigns but less direct mental health messaging (23:38).\n- Pelago shows minimal presence, low domain authority, and limited SEO or social media activity, acting as a gatekeeper with a referral-first model (24:58).\n- Treatment Navigator currently has no presence but fills a clear market gap by combining targeted lead generation for treatment centers with streamlined employer engagement.\n- Colin reassured Joe that while competitors exist, none fully cover the market needs Treatment Navigator addresses, particularly at the mid-market and employer integration level (39:39).\n\n## **Roadmap and Quarterly Priorities**\n\nThe immediate focus is on building a solid foundation with website launch, sales materials, and campaign infrastructure in the first two quarters (26:59).\n\n- A **three-page website** will be drafted, designed, and developed with tracking to monitor visitor behavior and engagement (29:02).\n- Sales enablement materials, including a **one-pager or slide deck**, will be created promptly to support outreach and address prospects’ self-education needs (31:20).\n- The team plans to launch a **content series** named tentatively \"Agnostic Advisor,\" producing video episodes featuring conversations with treatment centers, employers, and industry guests (29:02).\n- Social media presence will be established primarily on LinkedIn and potentially Meta platforms to build brand awareness and engagement (30:12).\n- Treatment center outreach campaigns will target **500,000 qualified centers across key states** like California, Florida, Texas, New York, New Jersey, Maryland, and Pennsylvania, focusing on COOs and admissions directors (30:28).\n- ABM campaign architecture will leverage advanced tools such as **RB2B and Factors** for website visitor de-anonymization and lead enrichment, integrated with N8N workflows and Supabase databases to generate actionable reports (33:14).\n- Metrics and engagement data will inform ongoing campaign optimization, with baseline data collected to time shifts from treatment centers to employer focus (28:34).\n\n## **Technology Stack and Process Enhancements**\n\nThe marketing tech stack is enhanced with new tools to improve lead identification, data enrichment, and campaign management, enabling precise targeting and reporting (33:14).\n\n- RB2B and Factors tools provide granular de-anonymization of website visitors on a person or account level, improving lead qualification and outreach accuracy.\n- N8N automates data collection and processing, storing interactions in Supabase for clean reporting and campaign adjustments.\n- Slack integrations alert the team in real-time about high-value visitors, enabling timely personalized follow-ups.\n- Colin explained the website will integrate with Lovable as the front end UI, backed by a database (potentially Supabase), to maintain a lightweight and scalable platform supporting blog posts and custom content (43:00).\n- The system architecture supports easy content updates and future integrations, ensuring agility as marketing and product strategies evolve.\n\n## **Budgeting, Resource Allocation, and Meeting Cadence**\n\nThe team agreed to front-load effort and budget in the first quarter to establish brand and infrastructure, borrowing points from future months to cover initial scope (35:12).\n\n- **Monthly points** total **70 points** (40 base plus 30 additional), with **210 points over three months** allocated primarily toward website, brand guidelines, campaign plans, and content production.\n- Colin clarified that heavier investment in initial months will be balanced by maintenance phases in later months to manage budget and effort.\n- Joe confirmed no additional capital is required beyond this scope, easing financial planning (37:37).\n- Weekly meetings will be scheduled to maintain momentum, with Colin to send availability links to coordinate times accommodating Joe and Tim’s schedules (44:40).\n- Justin emphasized that the website launch and sales collateral are the highest priority immediate actions to establish market presence and support sales conversations (42:06).","outline":null,"keywords":["Treatment Navigator","Marketing Roadmap","Target Market","Competitive Analysis","Account-Based Marketing","Brand Storytelling"],"overview":"- **Target Market Focus:** Three segments identified: behavioral health centers, mid-market employers, and fast-growing tech firms for outreach.\n\n- **Market Segment Details:** Treatment centers; $2-$30M revenue, 25-500 employees. Mid-markets; $20-$500M revenue, 100-1,000 employees. Tech firms; $100M-$2B revenue, 1,000-5,000 employees.\n\n- **Brand Messaging Strategy:** Position treatment centers as heroes simplifying mental health access, while employers champion employee wellbeing and compliance.\n\n- **Competitive Analysis Insight:** Fragmented market with no direct competitor fully addressing Treatment Navigator''s niche, highlighting strong differentiation opportunity.\n\n- **Quarterly Priorities:** Focus on website, sales materials, and outreach campaigns in Q1, targeting 500,000 qualified treatment centers across key states. \n\n- **Tech Enhancements:** New tools for lead identification and data management to improve outreach and campaign reporting, integrating real-time alerts for high-value visitors.","action_items":"\n**Colin Costigan**\nSend full 140-page marketing research document and roadmap presentation to Joe for review (07:23)\nShare availability link to schedule weekly meetings coordinating between all parties (44:49)\nBegin drafting, designing, and developing three-page website including basic tracking (35:00)\nDevelop brand guidelines including logo, messaging framework, and sales enablement materials (slide deck or one-pager) (35:00)\nBuild ABM plan document with full campaign assets (image creatives, email templates, paid media setup) (36:00)\nSet up and manage marketing technology stack (Clay, Smart Lead, Heyreach, RB2B, Factors, N8N, Supabase) (33:30)\nInitiate treatment center outreach campaign targeting identified priority states via LinkedIn, email, and advertising (31:30)\nEstablish Thought Leadership Content Engine branding and production plan, including hosting format (with Joe and Tim) (36:50)\n\n**Joe Ragno**\nReview and provide feedback on marketing research document, brand story, and roadmap presentation (07:23)\nCoordinate with Colin and Tim on scheduling weekly alignment meetings (44:55)\nContinue outreach to treatment centers and communicate feedback on campaign progress and sales materials needed (09:00)\nFinalize decision and input on Salesforce integration with marketing campaigns (27:30)\n\n**Tim**\nParticipate in strategy meetings and provide input as available, balancing work with family obligations (04:01)\nSupport content series participation and campaign execution as decided (16:13)\n"},"duration":45.939998626708984,"speakers":[{"id":0,"name":"Colin Costigan"},{"id":1,"name":"Justin Brown"},{"id":2,"name":"Joe Ragno"},{"id":3,"name":"Joe Ragno"},{"id":4,"name":"timot"},{"id":5,"name":"Nathalie Mintjens"}],"sentences":[{"text":"Here we''re talking about this crazy storm that''s coming.","index":0,"end_time":2.64,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":0.08,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I told you about the Blob like two months ago.","index":1,"end_time":7.76,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":4.88,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"You didn''t, you didn''t believe me, Colin.","index":2,"end_time":9.92,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":8,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"I didn''t heed your warning.","index":3,"end_time":11.24,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":10.08,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"No.","index":4,"end_time":11.52,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":11.24,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Joe''s said he''s going to Aruba or scheduled to at least try to tell everybody.","index":5,"end_time":16.36,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":11.52,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Joe, what''s the Blob?","index":6,"end_time":18.72,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":16.36,"speaker_name":"Joe Ragno"},{"text":"So like earlier this year, so there''s like this big like arctic polar vortex that''s supposed to come from the west, the like Pacific.","index":7,"end_time":34.17,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":19.52,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"It''s supposed to go north up into Canada and just go into, you know, the North Pole type area and they get all their annual snow and whatever and it missed and went south.","index":8,"end_time":47.93,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":34.65,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"And so this like Arctic Blob, you can look it up.","index":9,"end_time":55,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":48.81,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"I''m not making up the Blob.","index":10,"end_time":56.28,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":55,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"It''s just been sitting over the like the US for this entire winter and we''re just going to get destroyed all winter there will be snow like all the time that we don''t usually get.","index":11,"end_time":69.16,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":57.08,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"I told columnists two months ago about the Blob.","index":12,"end_time":72.44,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":69.64,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"He didn''t believe me.","index":13,"end_time":74.44,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":73.4,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Now here we are, we''re getting two feet of snow.","index":14,"end_time":76.44,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":74.52,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"That''s true.","index":15,"end_time":78.29,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":77.97,"speaker_name":"Joe Ragno"},{"text":"I mean it''s been what, since like 96, since we got snow like this?","index":16,"end_time":83.49,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":78.29,"speaker_name":"Joe Ragno"},{"text":"Yeah, I''m not looking forward to it.","index":17,"end_time":85.65,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":83.81,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"No, my like.","index":18,"end_time":87.17,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":86.13,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"So Colin and I both have young daughters.","index":19,"end_time":90.37,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":87.49,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"My daughter''s like, I don''t know, probably yours too, Colin.","index":20,"end_time":94.21,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":90.61,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"Like too young for it to be fun or exciting in any way.","index":21,"end_time":100.77,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":94.37,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"Like next year this would be awesome.","index":22,"end_time":103.17,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":101.33,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"Or even the following.","index":23,"end_time":104.39,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":103.51,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"Like my daughter can''t even crawl yet.","index":24,"end_time":106.95,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":104.95,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"I''m put her in snow face down.","index":25,"end_time":108.67,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":106.95,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"She''d be like, thanks.","index":26,"end_time":109.75,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":108.67,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"She''s got tears and a cold baby.","index":27,"end_time":112.15,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":109.99,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"So all I get is a, a driveway filled with snow.","index":28,"end_time":117.03,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":113.67,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"Sweet.","index":29,"end_time":117.59,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":117.03,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"And it''s not like it''s, it''s light snow.","index":30,"end_time":120.27,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":118.15,"speaker_name":"Joe Ragno"},{"text":"It''s that wet, heavy snow and freezing light snow overnight.","index":31,"end_time":124.23,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":120.27,"speaker_name":"Joe Ragno"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":32,"end_time":125.11,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":124.55,"speaker_name":"Joe Ragno"},{"text":"At least if it was like light or whatever wouldn''t be such a pain in the ass to draw shovel.","index":33,"end_time":130.19,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":125.43,"speaker_name":"Joe Ragno"},{"text":"But super heavy and useless.","index":34,"end_time":133.72,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":130.19,"speaker_name":"Joe Ragno"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":35,"end_time":134.68,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":134.12,"speaker_name":"timot"},{"text":"And it''s not an Aruba trip, but my daughter''s first birthday party Saturday.","index":36,"end_time":139.24,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":134.84,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And so that is leaning towards possibly canceled.","index":37,"end_time":144.84,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":139.4,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":38,"end_time":145.88,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":145.4,"speaker_name":"Joe Ragno"},{"text":"Unfortunate.","index":39,"end_time":146.84,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":145.88,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"But no.","index":40,"end_time":149.32,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":148.2,"speaker_name":"Joe Ragno"},{"text":"The great news is we can still do marketing.","index":41,"end_time":151.4,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":149.4,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"So yes, here we are.","index":42,"end_time":153.32,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":151.64,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"Yeah, I work.","index":43,"end_time":155.16,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":153.64,"speaker_name":"Joe Ragno"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":44,"end_time":156.04,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":155.56,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I was saying that is, that is definitely one of the downsides, I guess upsides as a business owner.","index":45,"end_time":161.94,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":156.12,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"But that''s like the capitalist side of me.","index":46,"end_time":163.78,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":161.94,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"But the, the human side of me is like at least once upon a time when you would go into an Office.","index":47,"end_time":170.18,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":163.78,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"It was like, oh, there''s a snow day.","index":48,"end_time":171.74,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":170.18,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"Can''t make it in.","index":49,"end_time":172.66,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":171.74,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"Like, kind of adult snow day.","index":50,"end_time":174.74,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":172.66,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"Nope.","index":51,"end_time":176.3,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":175.86,"speaker_name":"timot"},{"text":"I work for my house.","index":52,"end_time":177.14,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":176.3,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"So is everybody.","index":53,"end_time":178.9,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":177.7,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"We all work in different locations, so there''s not really a such thing as snow days anymore, unfortunately.","index":54,"end_time":184.9,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":179.54,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"No, no.","index":55,"end_time":187.31,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":185.7,"speaker_name":"Joe Ragno"},{"text":"It was very nice, though.","index":56,"end_time":188.43,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":187.31,"speaker_name":"Joe Ragno"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":57,"end_time":189.39,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":188.91,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":58,"end_time":190.03,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":189.55,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"I worked in, like, inside sales to start my career.","index":59,"end_time":193.23,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":190.43,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":60,"end_time":194.27,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":193.79,"speaker_name":"Joe Ragno"},{"text":"Dial from your phone at your desk.","index":61,"end_time":196.11,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":194.27,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"Couldn''t make it in.","index":62,"end_time":197.23,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":196.27,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"Guess we''re not making calls today.","index":63,"end_time":199.55,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":197.95,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":64,"end_time":200.59,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":200.11,"speaker_name":"Joe Ragno"},{"text":"All right, Colin, I''ll let you take it away.","index":65,"end_time":203.55,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":201.87,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":66,"end_time":204.43,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":203.95,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Well, thank you, Joe and Tim, for joining.","index":67,"end_time":208.27,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":204.43,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Talking last week was awesome.","index":68,"end_time":209.87,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":208.51,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We''ve done a lot of research between our last meeting and this one, and we''ve also put together our roadmap, which is our marketing strategy in the first three months of work that we recommend getting started on right away.","index":69,"end_time":220.4,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":209.87,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I also want to let Natalie introduce herself.","index":70,"end_time":223.68,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":220.8,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Joe, you know Natalie, but Tim, this is Natalie, strategist on our team.","index":71,"end_time":229,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":223.76,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So I''ll kick it over to her.","index":72,"end_time":230.32,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":229,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":73,"end_time":231.32,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":230.96,"speaker_name":"Joe Ragno"},{"text":"Nice to meet you, Tim.","index":74,"end_time":232.32,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":231.32,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"I''m a strategist here.","index":75,"end_time":233.88,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":232.64,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"I worked closely with Joe before the holidays and looking forward to working together.","index":76,"end_time":238.96,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":233.88,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Nice.","index":77,"end_time":241.6,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":241.12,"speaker_name":"Joe Ragno"},{"text":"Nice to meet you guys.","index":78,"end_time":243.72,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":241.84,"speaker_name":"timot"},{"text":"I just wanted to let you know I''m actually going to mute my audio and possibly my video.","index":79,"end_time":247.92,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":243.72,"speaker_name":"timot"},{"text":"My.","index":80,"end_time":248.32,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":247.92,"speaker_name":"timot"},{"text":"My daughter stayed home from school sick today, so she''s in her room right next to my office.","index":81,"end_time":254.77,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":249.01,"speaker_name":"timot"},{"text":"So I might be, like, jumping up and running, but I will be here for the duration, hopefully.","index":82,"end_time":260.45,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":254.77,"speaker_name":"timot"},{"text":"Totally get it.","index":83,"end_time":262.37,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":261.57,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"All good.","index":84,"end_time":262.85,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":262.37,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And we can even send over a recording and we''ll send you over all the documents afterwards as well.","index":85,"end_time":267.33,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":262.85,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Thank you.","index":86,"end_time":268.61,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":267.89,"speaker_name":"timot"},{"text":"All right, so I''m going to share my screen.","index":87,"end_time":271.97,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":269.81,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We''re going to go ahead and get started.","index":88,"end_time":274.21,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":272.77,"speaker_name":"Joe Ragno"},{"text":"If my zoom will line up.","index":89,"end_time":279.7,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":277.18,"speaker_name":"Joe Ragno"},{"text":"Here we go.","index":90,"end_time":280.22,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":279.7,"speaker_name":"Joe Ragno"},{"text":"All right, so this is the final session of our line growth engine process.","index":91,"end_time":284.86,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":280.7,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So we''ve had kickoff and alignment, and now this is our roadmap presentation.","index":92,"end_time":289.02,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":285.02,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So this is really where we combine all of the knowledge that you have provided of, like, this is the tool that I want to build.","index":93,"end_time":299.38,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":289.1,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"This is who I want to talk to, and this is what I need from a marketing standpoint with the marketing research that we''ve conducted, seeing from a competitor analysis standpoint and from just a market opportunity standpoint, what we need to do.","index":94,"end_time":311.88,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":299.38,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"But of course, we need to pour the concrete into the foundation before we can start to build some stilts.","index":95,"end_time":315.96,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":311.96,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Right.","index":96,"end_time":316.28,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":315.96,"speaker_name":"Joe Ragno"},{"text":"So in order to do that, we''re going to identify our target market, our brand positioning and messaging.","index":97,"end_time":323.56,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":316.76,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"You obviously are very familiar with the product and solution.","index":98,"end_time":326.28,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":323.64,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Then we''ve gone through competitors that you''ve outlined.","index":99,"end_time":329.32,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":326.52,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"There''s not a 100% direct competitor, as you''re aware, but with lira and Spring health and a few other ones, there are similar offerings where we can start to, to see how they''re positioning themselves in the market.","index":100,"end_time":340.58,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":329.32,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Then we''ll get into the roadmap, outline our goals and what we feel is vital to get started on for the next three months.","index":101,"end_time":347.38,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":340.82,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Sound like a plan?","index":102,"end_time":348.66,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":347.78,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Sounds good.","index":103,"end_time":349.94,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":349.3,"speaker_name":"Joe Ragno"},{"text":"Awesome.","index":104,"end_time":350.98,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":350.34,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"All right.","index":105,"end_time":352.02,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":351.46,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So you know Joe, you''ve, you''ve seen these presentations before.","index":106,"end_time":355.94,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":352.1,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"This is us explaining kind of how we work.","index":107,"end_time":358.58,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":356.18,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So if there''s any questions, and Tim, this may be more for you if there''s any questions about how we work.","index":108,"end_time":363.46,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":358.9,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I''m just going to do a really quick overview of our six step process.","index":109,"end_time":366.82,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":363.54,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So we follow this six step model in all of our engagements and you can see we start with research and alignment and roadmap.","index":110,"end_time":374.88,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":368.2,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So that is the, the meetings that we have had to date.","index":111,"end_time":377.4,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":374.88,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Then we go into our foundation.","index":112,"end_time":381.32,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":379,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So towards the end of this meeting, I''ll pull up the next three months of all the work that we have planned out.","index":113,"end_time":386.44,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":381.56,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"You will see plan documents in there.","index":114,"end_time":388.4,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":386.52,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"The reason that we do that is because we need a source of truth for everything that we''re doing.","index":115,"end_time":392.04,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":388.4,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So if we''re making a website, we need a website plan.","index":116,"end_time":395.57,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":392.04,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"If we''re making ABM campaign, we need an ABM plan.","index":117,"end_time":400.17,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":395.57,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"That way we are all aligned on exactly what we''re doing, why we''re doing it, who we''re doing it for and who we''re doing it with.","index":118,"end_time":406.73,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":400.57,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Then we go into execution.","index":119,"end_time":408.81,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":407.45,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So that''s running the actual campaigns, building the website, standing up a content series, things like that, and in a constant evolution on a weekly, monthly and quarterly period.","index":120,"end_time":421.45,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":408.889,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We are analyzing all of the data coming through so that we know from a data back perspective what changes or enhancements to make to everything that we are doing.","index":121,"end_time":430.55,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":421.53,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I know Tim is probably bouncing back and forth between his daughter and his office as well.","index":122,"end_time":438.03,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":433.27,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So if he has any questions.","index":123,"end_time":440.15,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":438.03,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"No, so far so good.","index":124,"end_time":442.07,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":440.79,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Thank you.","index":125,"end_time":443.03,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":442.39,"speaker_name":"timot"},{"text":"Awesome.","index":126,"end_time":443.91,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":443.27,"speaker_name":"Joe Ragno"},{"text":"And then we''ve also put together a very large marketing research document, Joe.","index":127,"end_time":448.99,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":443.99,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So I''ll send this over.","index":128,"end_time":449.99,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":448.99,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"This is about 140 pages.","index":129,"end_time":451.67,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":449.99,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"It''s a very in depth analysis into the industry, the technology, customer insights that we''ve uncovered.","index":130,"end_time":459.14,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":452.9,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We go into the competitor overviews, how they look across SEO, social media, paid media, what their overall brand and positioning and messaging are and really how they put themselves out into the market which opens up opportunities for treatment navigator.","index":131,"end_time":477.62,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":459.22,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So I''m not going to go through 140 pages here.","index":132,"end_time":482.83,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":480.67,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I''ll send this over to you and you can review in your own time.","index":133,"end_time":485.31,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":482.99,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"But we have everything up in this table of contents for anything you want to quickly jump to.","index":134,"end_time":490.59,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":485.79,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Great, thank you.","index":135,"end_time":492.91,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":491.79,"speaker_name":"Joe Ragno"},{"text":"Yeah, of course.","index":136,"end_time":493.71,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":492.99,"speaker_name":"Joe Ragno"},{"text":"All right, so then getting into our target market, we''ve put together a few different target markets and each target market has or target account has also a target Persona.","index":137,"end_time":503.55,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":494.59,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So we''re starting with Treatment Navigator.","index":138,"end_time":506.83,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":504.15,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We need to get treatment centers onboarded onto this platform so that when we start reaching out to employers, they actually have a network that they can start to have their employees sign up with, filling out their forms and getting the help that they need.","index":139,"end_time":520.149,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":506.83,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So Joe, what we''ve named this segment is Behavioral health and substance use treatment Centers.","index":140,"end_time":526.03,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":520.71,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Pretty pretty straightforward, no kind of fun name there.","index":141,"end_time":529.43,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":526.03,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"But with the industries that we''ve seen with even Autobytes outreach, I think there''s some opportunity to expand in.","index":142,"end_time":535.39,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":529.43,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Exactly, exactly like how these treatment centers refer to themselves from an industry standpoint.","index":143,"end_time":539.01,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":535.39,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So you can see we have behavioral health treatment, substance abuse treatment, mental health services and addiction medicine.","index":144,"end_time":544.37,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":539.01,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Just different ways that they''ve classified themselves in the tools that we use to find these contacts.","index":145,"end_time":549.57,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":544.37,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"From a revenue standpoint, probably doing about 2 million to 30 million.","index":146,"end_time":555.01,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":551.49,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And from the employee headcount, probably 25 to 500.","index":147,"end_time":558.13,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":555.09,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And with this, do you feel like this is aligned to the treatment centers?","index":148,"end_time":563.97,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":559.33,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"That one that you have in your network already you want to do some outreach with or that you are already have.","index":149,"end_time":568.07,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":563.97,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I know that you sent that message last week of some outreach you started or is there any range difference that you see here?","index":150,"end_time":575.47,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":568.07,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"No, everything I see here looks pretty much on par.","index":151,"end_time":579.63,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":576.27,"speaker_name":"Joe Ragno"},{"text":"Okay, great then I know you mentioned Kaipu and a few other EMR systems that you may be able to integrate with in the future.","index":152,"end_time":586.43,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":579.87,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So definitely want to have content around that.","index":153,"end_time":588.67,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":586.51,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And then one question I did want to ask is if you do develop this relationship between treatment center with Treatment Navigator or are you I assume you would be open to like if they have Salesforce issues coming in as Salesforce consultant.","index":154,"end_time":604.1,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":589.55,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":155,"end_time":605.14,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":604.58,"speaker_name":"Joe Ragno"},{"text":"Okay, great.","index":156,"end_time":607.06,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":605.22,"speaker_name":"Joe Ragno"},{"text":"So just some additive services that we can talk through as well.","index":157,"end_time":610.74,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":607.3,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So for the ideal customer this would be the chief operating officer at a treatment center or a range of titles really.","index":158,"end_time":618.9,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":611.46,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"They''re finding that their team is wasting time in their systems.","index":159,"end_time":623.06,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":619.06,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"They don''t have a good lead flow really.","index":160,"end_time":626.53,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":623.06,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"It''s around getting more utilization and having more of their their beds filled on a regular basis with pre approved from an insurance perspective, already have their forms filled out and they could basically easily See who wants to book with them from this employee use of the app.","index":161,"end_time":643.13,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":626.53,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Right.","index":162,"end_time":644.25,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":643.85,"speaker_name":"Joe Ragno"},{"text":"Then we get into the mid market employer.","index":163,"end_time":647.89,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":645.69,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So switching, you know, looking down the road, we''ve got 50 to 100 treatment centers signed up inside the platform as a resource.","index":164,"end_time":655.44,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":647.89,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We are starting now to target employers.","index":165,"end_time":658.24,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":656.08,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Hey, we''ve built this network, this is something that you should add on or it''s kind of a carve out of your EAP if you have something existing already.","index":166,"end_time":666.24,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":658.24,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So a few of these, I mean we''re kind of going across the gamut of industries.","index":167,"end_time":671.84,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":667.04,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I mean manufacturing, construction, healthcare, hospitality, you can see a big range here.","index":168,"end_time":675.76,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":672,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We didn''t want to limit our options of who we can reach out to.","index":169,"end_time":679.16,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":676.32,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And we tend to see in these industries a higher headcount of employees as well, which in turn would provide more revenue for Treatment Navigator.","index":170,"end_time":688.7,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":679.16,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Looking at the 20 to 500 million revenue range and 100 to 1,000 employees.","index":171,"end_time":695.98,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":691.42,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So again, kind of a big umbrella there.","index":172,"end_time":697.98,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":695.98,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"But we don''t want to miss out on any market share that we can gain here and there.","index":173,"end_time":702.34,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":697.98,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"There will likely be some proof that we need to establish with some of the smaller companies early on and then we start to have the credibility to show here''s what we''ve done for other companies, obviously not from a, not invading any HIPAA compliance or anything like that, but here''s what we''re able to provide.","index":174,"end_time":718.03,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":702.34,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And then you know, working with HRIS systems probably in their, in their solution stack and they may also have an existing EAP and then this could be bolted on to that service.","index":175,"end_time":729.55,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":718.91,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Right.","index":176,"end_time":730.83,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":730.43,"speaker_name":"timot"},{"text":"So Director of benefits here is, or anyone really with the realm of HR titles.","index":177,"end_time":740.47,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":734.03,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I mean there''s Chief People Officer, there''s people success, there''s hr, there''s Chro, there''s, there''s really any mix of these, but looking for that executive level HR person at these companies or even a manager here where we can start a conversation and give them some information about Treatment Navigator, how it''s going to help them across the board.","index":178,"end_time":761.61,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":740.47,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Right.","index":179,"end_time":761.85,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":761.61,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"There''s employee retention, there''s recruiting benefits, and then there''s just the solace of being able to provide your employees with better solutions if they are struggling with mental health, with addictions, with really anything that runs a gambit and they''re not able to find those solutions currently.","index":180,"end_time":778.14,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":761.85,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"All right, getting into this last target account, I''m sorry, the third target account here.","index":181,"end_time":787.66,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":781.98,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So aiding a little bit more towards companies that are growing really fast and really need to bolt on these types of solutions.","index":182,"end_time":794.46,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":787.74,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So they are typically in the technology or SAS or Professional services space growing very quickly, increasing headcount very quickly and need need to bolt on a, an affordable but also comprehensive solution to their EAP or non existent EAP stack already.","index":183,"end_time":813.64,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":794.62,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So looking at 100 million to 2 billion in revenue, a thousand to 5,000 employees, again a pretty big range here.","index":184,"end_time":821.24,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":815.56,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Don''t want to limit ourselves on who we''re reaching out to, but through our research we found that these companies are signing on solutions very quickly from an HR perspective because they need a lot of recruiting very quickly as they are growing very quickly.","index":185,"end_time":835.09,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":821.96,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Great.","index":186,"end_time":838.6,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":838.36,"speaker_name":"timot"},{"text":"So here more of a chro that we would reach out to.","index":187,"end_time":843.56,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":839.96,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Again they''re experiencing, you know, they''re, they''re getting quotes from vendors at a high clip.","index":188,"end_time":849.56,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":843.56,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"It might be five to eight dollars for a PEPM.","index":189,"end_time":853,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":849.56,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"That could be, you know, 200, $300,000 a year depending on the employee headcount that they have.","index":190,"end_time":859.56,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":853.4,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"They''re experiencing delays with maybe teams that they''ve tried onboarding with.","index":191,"end_time":864.04,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":860.28,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"They want to secure, you know, a solution that offers volume discounts.","index":192,"end_time":869.04,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":864.68,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And I know in our last conversation you said, you know, if we start to see companies come in with several hundred people in their head count or a thousand people in their headcount, we can lower that charge so that it makes more sense for them and that is a volume discount that they are looking for.","index":193,"end_time":881.44,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":869.04,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Right.","index":194,"end_time":882.639,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":882.24,"speaker_name":"Joe Ragno"},{"text":"All right.","index":195,"end_time":885.56,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":885.2,"speaker_name":"Joe Ragno"},{"text":"And then getting into the last one, again more of a employer center here.","index":196,"end_time":891.2,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":885.56,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So insurance brokerages, benefits consulting, human capital, again, fast growing companies, a large employee range here, large revenue range, but they''re typically using a few different tools for their, their eap.","index":197,"end_time":907.15,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":891.28,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And we want to tap in and basically say how this can be a carve out or just an additional service that they can provide to their employees.","index":198,"end_time":914.19,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":907.55,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And it''s pretty similar to honestly the last ideal account, but with different industries they''re going to want some different jargon, some different conversation, different proof points.","index":199,"end_time":924.83,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":914.75,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So that''s why we wanted to split this out.","index":200,"end_time":926.59,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":924.99,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Sort of a different Persona.","index":201,"end_time":927.93,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":926.81,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay.","index":202,"end_time":929.01,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":928.57,"speaker_name":"Joe Ragno"},{"text":"And this is considered different than like EAP providers, right?","index":203,"end_time":933.21,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":929.01,"speaker_name":"Joe Ragno"},{"text":"Yes.","index":204,"end_time":933.85,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":933.37,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay.","index":205,"end_time":934.73,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":934.17,"speaker_name":"Joe Ragno"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":206,"end_time":936.57,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":936.09,"speaker_name":"Joe Ragno"},{"text":"And so really what they''re looking for is having a few different solutions that some people can, you know, that they can provide to their employees and having you know, these solutions really just again for recruiting, for retention, for all of the pain points that employers are experiencing and want to be able to provide to their team.","index":207,"end_time":955.7,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":937.45,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So I''m going to take a pause there.","index":208,"end_time":957.94,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":956.58,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Any questions around the target accounts or ideal Personas that we have set up?","index":209,"end_time":961.62,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":958.18,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"No, I think that made make sense.","index":210,"end_time":966.26,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":963.62,"speaker_name":"Joe Ragno"},{"text":"There are some on there that I Didn''t even anticipate.","index":211,"end_time":969.98,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":967.3,"speaker_name":"Joe Ragno"},{"text":"So just glad to see that.","index":212,"end_time":971.7,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":969.98,"speaker_name":"Joe Ragno"},{"text":"Yeah, yeah, of course.","index":213,"end_time":972.82,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":971.7,"speaker_name":"Joe Ragno"},{"text":"All right, so then.","index":214,"end_time":974.66,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":973.7,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Oh, sorry, go ahead.","index":215,"end_time":975.86,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":974.98,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"No, I was just saying everything looks good.","index":216,"end_time":977.9,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":976.26,"speaker_name":"timot"},{"text":"I dig it.","index":217,"end_time":978.86,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":977.9,"speaker_name":"timot"},{"text":"Awesome.","index":218,"end_time":979.97,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":979.57,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"All right, so then we''ve also built, what we do here is a brand story development.","index":219,"end_time":986.05,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":981.33,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So this is a brand story framework.","index":220,"end_time":987.97,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":986.29,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"What this does is positions your customers or end users as the hero.","index":221,"end_time":993.33,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":988.37,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And how does Treatment Navigator by Autobytes help them reach their goals, experience success?","index":222,"end_time":998.85,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":993.57,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So there''s, there''s two main folds to what Treatment Navigator is working with.","index":223,"end_time":1003.45,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":998.93,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"That is one, treatment centers, they, they need leads, but it''s not in a lead farming sort of way.","index":224,"end_time":1009,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1003.45,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So we''re able to facilitate, we''re able to facilitate leads for them, but not in a way that other services are like, you can advertise here, you get favorite treatment here, etc.","index":225,"end_time":1021.24,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1009.56,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"But we need to build a network with them and position and show them basically why signing up for Treatment Navigator and being listed on the platform is a no brainer.","index":226,"end_time":1029.48,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1021.48,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So we need to position them as the hero, make sure that they understand looking to, it''s not even increase like their revenue or anything like that.","index":227,"end_time":1038.87,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1029.88,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We''re looking to really solve a mission here of helping employees who don''t have an option right now for that substance abuse, for mental health, for anything like that.","index":228,"end_time":1050.11,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1038.87,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Thus in turn helping treatment centers who provide that service and so serving as that middleman to help both sides.","index":229,"end_time":1057.15,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1050.51,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"The other side of this as a customer hero is the employers.","index":230,"end_time":1061.87,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1058.19,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So I''ve talked a lot about the points that they''re experiencing, but really we want to help them give their employees access to treatment in a very quick turnaround.","index":231,"end_time":1071.1,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1062.38,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Hey, you know, you don''t have to, you no longer have to fill out a form for every different treatment center that you''re looking at.","index":232,"end_time":1076.7,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1071.26,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"You don''t have to fill out your insurance form multiple times.","index":233,"end_time":1079.58,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1077.02,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"You can fill out this one.","index":234,"end_time":1081.42,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1080.06,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"It''ll bring up a list of options that are available to you and you can quickly and easily and anonymously sign up for these solutions and get help very quickly.","index":235,"end_time":1091.99,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1081.5,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And so this in turn can help them possibly get rid of another EAP solution if they see some overlap between anything, avoid losing their headcount, avoid any compliance violations and avoid really the biggest risk of employee retention, failure being burnout and mental health issues and things like that and not having a solution for them.","index":236,"end_time":1115.87,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1094.31,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Any question about this brand story?","index":237,"end_time":1119.78,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1116.98,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"No, I don''t think so.","index":238,"end_time":1124.74,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1123.14,"speaker_name":"Joe Ragno"},{"text":"Awesome.","index":239,"end_time":1125.86,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1125.22,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Like I said, I''ll send this over for review.","index":240,"end_time":1129.06,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1126.5,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So really what this does is everything that I''ve gone over so far pours the foundation of who are we talking to, what is the story and how are we talking to them.","index":241,"end_time":1140.5,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1129.3,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So this is all very, very critical to everything that we''ll build from here on out.","index":242,"end_time":1145.06,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1140.74,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We may naturally see some development and change in this as the product comes to fruition, as a website is built, as we start to get campaigns out there and live.","index":243,"end_time":1154.73,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1145.22,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So we will update that if anything changes.","index":244,"end_time":1156.77,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1154.73,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"But this is where we see things based on our research and based on our conversations so far.","index":245,"end_time":1161.01,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1157.25,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Great.","index":246,"end_time":1163.33,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1162.93,"speaker_name":"Joe Ragno"},{"text":"No, this looks awesome.","index":247,"end_time":1164.73,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1163.65,"speaker_name":"Joe Ragno"},{"text":"This is better than anything I could ever thought of.","index":248,"end_time":1167.97,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1164.73,"speaker_name":"Joe Ragno"},{"text":"I love to hear that.","index":249,"end_time":1169.89,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1168.85,"speaker_name":"Joe Ragno"},{"text":"I think this is probably the slide that you will not need to read through as you are very familiar with the product that you have built.","index":250,"end_time":1176.69,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1170.37,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"But as we''ve laid this out, it''s.","index":251,"end_time":1180.14,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1177.82,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"It''s a product and solutions matrix.","index":252,"end_time":1181.98,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1180.14,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So one of the reasons I asked about the salesforce side of things or even like bringing Autobytes back into the conversation possibly is if we add that into like this sort of matrix or even have a link on the new website that we''re building back to Autobytes, if someone''s looking for that type of solution.","index":253,"end_time":1196.62,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1183.26,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Great.","index":254,"end_time":1197.66,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1197.26,"speaker_name":"Joe Ragno"},{"text":"It may also come up organically, you know, through conversation.","index":255,"end_time":1201.58,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1198.86,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":256,"end_time":1202.46,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1201.98,"speaker_name":"Joe Ragno"},{"text":"The one thing that I would note here, not even with this slide in particular, but with most of the slides, is there''s a lot of reference to substance use that could potentially block us out from certain types of advertising, depending upon, you know, who we''re trying to reach out to because of that legit script certification.","index":257,"end_time":1224.3,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1202.46,"speaker_name":"Joe Ragno"},{"text":"Right.","index":258,"end_time":1224.9,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1224.54,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So we want to put the focus on mental health in general with substance abuse, substance use and abuse being a downstream thing of mental health.","index":259,"end_time":1234.71,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1224.9,"speaker_name":"Joe Ragno"},{"text":"That way it doesn''t kind of block us out from that.","index":260,"end_time":1237.27,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1234.71,"speaker_name":"Joe Ragno"},{"text":"And I think it''ll be, it''ll resonate more with the, with the employers simply because it''s not just a substance use or abuse solution.","index":261,"end_time":1246.75,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1237.27,"speaker_name":"Joe Ragno"},{"text":"It is a mental health overall solution.","index":262,"end_time":1248.99,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1246.75,"speaker_name":"Joe Ragno"},{"text":"Yeah, yeah, totally hear you there.","index":263,"end_time":1251.07,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1249.31,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I agree.","index":264,"end_time":1251.71,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1251.07,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Awesome.","index":265,"end_time":1254.83,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1254.19,"speaker_name":"Joe Ragno"},{"text":"All right, then we hop into a competitive analysis.","index":266,"end_time":1258.83,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1256.11,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Again.","index":267,"end_time":1259.07,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1258.83,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"The, the much more thorough one is in the, the research document that I showed, but going through SP health, so we have a mock up here of where their data points fall for the five main categories that we do this competitive analysis based on.","index":268,"end_time":1272.73,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1259.07,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So brand positioning, their content marketing strategy, organic SEO, paid programs they''re running, and social media, Spring health, very Strong brand, a 9 out of 10 on the metrics that we''ve established.","index":269,"end_time":1283.93,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1272.73,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And again we go into the detail of that in our research document.","index":270,"end_time":1286.57,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1283.93,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Their content plan is very strong.","index":271,"end_time":1288.89,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1287.45,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Everywhere else.","index":272,"end_time":1289.61,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1288.89,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"They, they Fall a bit flat.","index":273,"end_time":1291.21,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1289.61,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"They don''t run much from a paid ads perspective.","index":274,"end_time":1293.53,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1291.21,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"They don''t do much on their organic social media and they don''t have much of a presence for keywords organically to their website.","index":275,"end_time":1301.03,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1294.09,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"They tend to operate in a cheaper cost per click for Google Ads is mainly the space that they operate in for paid advertising.","index":276,"end_time":1309.91,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1302.63,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And then they also have a very large YouTube video library.","index":277,"end_time":1313.35,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1309.91,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So always good to see what the competition is doing.","index":278,"end_time":1316.55,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1313.91,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I think we learn as much about what we shouldn''t do as what we should do.","index":279,"end_time":1320.47,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1316.95,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And so, you know, one of the plans, Joe, that we''ll roll out is for a content series.","index":280,"end_time":1325.19,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1321.03,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I think that you started to enjoy that a bit more in the last few months with Autobyte.","index":281,"end_time":1329.26,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1325.19,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And I think that we have a very interesting proposition of how we can pivot and pitch that and make episodes for treatment centers and episodes for employers and episodes for employees bringing on possible guests and just having natural conversations about the state of the union.","index":282,"end_time":1344.61,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1329.41,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"With these offerings that currently exist out in the market, which is very slim to none.","index":283,"end_time":1348.45,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1344.61,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"The next one we looked at was lira.","index":284,"end_time":1354.45,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1352.69,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So they target very, very enterprise based companies, 2500 or more employees.","index":285,"end_time":1360.21,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1354.85,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"TYP.","index":286,"end_time":1360.53,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1360.21,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"They do a lot more from a brand and social media and paid perspective than Spring Health.","index":287,"end_time":1368.27,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1361.63,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So they, they have a much larger budget.","index":288,"end_time":1371.87,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1369.95,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"They do a lot of thought leadership out in the market as well from a content perspective, but a lot of like evidence and statistical based content as well.","index":289,"end_time":1381.79,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1372.51,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And their YouTube is, is, it only has 800 subscribers, but they do have, you know, quite a bit of videos on there and have a pretty strong market presence.","index":290,"end_time":1391.63,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1383.15,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So it seems like YouTube has been a pretty popular space, could even be a really strong space for us to advertise as well, you know, developing a video showing this type of solution.","index":291,"end_time":1401.37,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1392.49,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Their LinkedIn is massive, over 268,000 followers, which is almost double what Spring Health has.","index":292,"end_time":1409.69,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1402.49,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And all of their content there is about thought leadership and their product promotion.","index":293,"end_time":1414.57,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1410.17,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I can see reading.","index":294,"end_time":1419.46,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1418.74,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So if you want me to take a minute.","index":295,"end_time":1420.66,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1419.46,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, they didn''t really focus on the mental health the same way that Spring did, did they?","index":296,"end_time":1428.18,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1420.98,"speaker_name":"Joe Ragno"},{"text":"No, not, not as like directly.","index":297,"end_time":1430.58,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1428.5,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Right.","index":298,"end_time":1431.62,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1431.22,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"They were a bit more generalized but still like a thought leadership positioning of all of the, you know, offerings that they have.","index":299,"end_time":1437.86,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1431.7,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Right.","index":300,"end_time":1438.66,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1438.26,"speaker_name":"Joe Ragno"},{"text":"Okay.","index":301,"end_time":1439.38,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1438.82,"speaker_name":"Joe Ragno"},{"text":"Then looking at another one that you provided was Pelago.","index":302,"end_time":1445.04,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1441.86,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Very, very minimal market presence for Pelago.","index":303,"end_time":1449.27,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1446.63,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Not a very strong brand.","index":304,"end_time":1450.87,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1449.67,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Almost no social media presence, no paid advertising programs, Very, very small content marketing, you know, strategy that we were able to, to kind of seek out.","index":305,"end_time":1460.95,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1451.11,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"They do A little bit of SEO, but not very strong, very limited social media, so not many followers across all their channels.","index":306,"end_time":1468.91,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1462.15,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"For any channels that they even have in existence, domain authority is pretty low.","index":307,"end_time":1473,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1468.91,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And their SEO score, you know, just shows that they''re really not gunning for anything from an organic search perspective.","index":308,"end_time":1478.28,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1473,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"They just kind of exist in the market as it is right now.","index":309,"end_time":1480.84,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1478.28,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"They do have a glossary content strategy on their website, which is able to bring in some traffic.","index":310,"end_time":1487.84,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1482.52,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So something that has been pretty strong that we''ve been seeing in the market shift, meaning a glossary of, like, if you know how people are searching on chat, GBT versus Google, they''re doing a much larger prompt, asking multiple questions in one search.","index":311,"end_time":1499.56,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1487.84,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Glossaries are very helpful as a return of information there because you''re giving so much information on one page for all the different people that could possibly be searching there.","index":312,"end_time":1508.9,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1499.8,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"They do focus much more on the substance use than anything else.","index":313,"end_time":1513.94,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1510.42,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":314,"end_time":1517.22,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1516.74,"speaker_name":"Joe Ragno"},{"text":"And from the research I did on them, and correct me if I''m wrong with what you saw, but they, like, they''re the first stop.","index":315,"end_time":1525.58,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1517.38,"speaker_name":"Joe Ragno"},{"text":"It''s not like you can just go wherever you want.","index":316,"end_time":1527.7,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1525.58,"speaker_name":"Joe Ragno"},{"text":"Like, you have to go through them first.","index":317,"end_time":1529.62,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1527.7,"speaker_name":"Joe Ragno"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":318,"end_time":1530.22,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1529.78,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Or the gatekeeper.","index":319,"end_time":1531.12,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1530.22,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Right.","index":320,"end_time":1532.55,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1532.31,"speaker_name":"Joe Ragno"},{"text":"And then if they''re.","index":321,"end_time":1534.23,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1532.55,"speaker_name":"Joe Ragno"},{"text":"I guess if what they''re trying to do fails, then they recommend you to somewhere else.","index":322,"end_time":1540.87,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1535.19,"speaker_name":"Joe Ragno"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":323,"end_time":1541.35,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1540.87,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yep, 100%.","index":324,"end_time":1542.87,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1541.43,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay.","index":325,"end_time":1544.23,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1543.59,"speaker_name":"Joe Ragno"},{"text":"And then we have Treatment Navigator.","index":326,"end_time":1547.11,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1545.03,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We have an empty dartboard here, an empty, empty target here.","index":327,"end_time":1550.87,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1547.51,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So obviously no.","index":328,"end_time":1552.51,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1551.43,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"No presence that.","index":329,"end_time":1553.35,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1552.51,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"That has been established yet.","index":330,"end_time":1554.63,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1553.35,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"But from all of our conversations, we are certainly carving out an area that''s missing right now in.","index":331,"end_time":1561.91,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1555.59,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So, you know, we have a lot of conversation.","index":332,"end_time":1565.25,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1563.57,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"From everything that you''ve told us over the past couple of meetings, if anything is changing, you know, if you want to change your pricing or if you want to change, like a focus or anything, please just let us know and we''ll update all of our core documentation.","index":333,"end_time":1575.49,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1565.25,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"But there''s a lot of opportunities from an SEO perspective, a campaign perspective across several different channels, and really a branding and messaging and content perspective of there''s no one in the space doing exactly what Treatment Navigator was built to provide.","index":334,"end_time":1591.09,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1576.29,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And I think we have a very strong chance to prove that to treatment centers as we onboard them into the platform and then ultimately switch to an employer focus.","index":335,"end_time":1598.89,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1591.93,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Great.","index":336,"end_time":1601.05,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1600.65,"speaker_name":"Joe Ragno"},{"text":"Awesome.","index":337,"end_time":1604.41,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1603.85,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Any questions on anything from the competitive analysis before we get into the.","index":338,"end_time":1607.97,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1604.65,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"The actual roadmap?","index":339,"end_time":1609.05,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1607.97,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"No, I think I''m good.","index":340,"end_time":1612.17,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1611.05,"speaker_name":"Joe Ragno"},{"text":"Awesome.","index":341,"end_time":1613.49,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1612.89,"speaker_name":"Joe Ragno"},{"text":"Tim, anything from your end?","index":342,"end_time":1614.73,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1613.49,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"No, so far, so good.","index":343,"end_time":1616.81,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1615.53,"speaker_name":"timot"},{"text":"Awesome.","index":344,"end_time":1618.2,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1617.72,"speaker_name":"Joe Ragno"},{"text":"All right, so we set up our roadmaps based on objectives and key results.","index":345,"end_time":1623.4,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1619.4,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Just so we always are following our smart goals.","index":346,"end_time":1626.56,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1623.4,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Smart goals here were a bit.","index":347,"end_time":1628.52,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1626.56,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"It wasn''t really tied to a number of the goals that I''m laying out for this first quarter.","index":348,"end_time":1633.88,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1630.36,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So I''ll get into that a little bit here.","index":349,"end_time":1636.64,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1635.08,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So we really need to establish a foundation, as I said at the beginning, you know, pouring the concrete, having everything kind of baked in.","index":350,"end_time":1642.94,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1636.64,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So we need to establish a website, we need to get some sales enablement materials stood up and we need to get a campaign stood up.","index":351,"end_time":1651.41,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1643.81,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So really the most important part of this beginning venture here is to get all of those pieces in place.","index":352,"end_time":1660.69,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1652.13,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And so what I''ve laid out here is getting the website live, making sure.","index":353,"end_time":1664.85,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1660.93,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And I know we talked in our last meeting about whether we use tim seat or whether we just hook up through an API.","index":354,"end_time":1670.61,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1664.85,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So we don''t even need a seat.","index":355,"end_time":1671.81,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1670.61,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"But just understanding however you want Salesforce set up and making sure our campaigns map properly to that.","index":356,"end_time":1676.89,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1672.41,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And then we talked about getting a treatment center in every state as being a goal.","index":357,"end_time":1682.73,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1677.45,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I think that there''s a few that we should focus on.","index":358,"end_time":1684.89,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1682.73,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I think we have several states along the east coast that have a lot more options for treatment centers.","index":359,"end_time":1690.57,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1684.89,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"New Jersey, Maryland, Pennsylvania and then California will be a massive target as well, and a few other states that are littered in there.","index":360,"end_time":1698.11,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1690.73,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Then shifting our focus to the employer side of things once we have that network built.","index":361,"end_time":1704.02,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1698.82,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And what I put as the source of truth here would be Salesforce, as you mentioned, that''s.","index":362,"end_time":1708.42,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1704.5,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Well, understandably.","index":363,"end_time":1710.18,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1708.58,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So that''s the CRM of choice here.","index":364,"end_time":1711.78,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1710.18,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Right.","index":365,"end_time":1713.62,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1713.22,"speaker_name":"Joe Ragno"},{"text":"So in Q1 and Q2, we''re building the.","index":366,"end_time":1716.02,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1714.26,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Building the basics.","index":367,"end_time":1717.1,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1716.26,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So putting together the website, the campaign plans, and in Q2, launching those campaigns and then continuing to optimize as we go, changing target audience from treatment centers to employers.","index":368,"end_time":1729.28,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1717.1,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And then based on the data that we see of how are they interacting with the website, how are they interacting with content, what do we need to change to improve conversions?","index":369,"end_time":1737.56,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1729.28,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Great.","index":370,"end_time":1740.359,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1739.96,"speaker_name":"Joe Ragno"},{"text":"So laying out our quarterly initiatives.","index":371,"end_time":1744.44,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1742.28,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So we''re going to draft, design and develop.","index":372,"end_time":1746.92,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1744.44,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I don''t know why I put HubSpot in here.","index":373,"end_time":1749.48,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1747.4,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"This is not a HubSpot website.","index":374,"end_time":1750.76,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1749.48,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"It draft, design and develop a three page website, implement, you know, basic tracking and everything like that so that we understand, you know, exactly who''s viewing the website and where they''re coming from.","index":375,"end_time":1761.79,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1750.91,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Then launching Thought Leadership Content Engine.","index":376,"end_time":1764.99,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1762.43,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I really think you started to enjoy this a lot more towards the latter half of 2025.","index":377,"end_time":1770.51,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1765.47,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Correct me if I''m wrong, but I think that there''s a strong Opportunity here to not take much of your time, you know, maybe 30 minutes a week or every other week to record some videos or even if we land a guest as a prospect or someone that runs a treatment center, you know, we can have a lot of interesting conversations and syndicate those across several different channels.","index":378,"end_time":1788.11,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1770.75,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"One of the names that I was thinking was like the Agnostic Advisor, but I''m still kind of going through different name ideas for that content engine series and what we could do there, Agnostic Advisor kind of stood out to me because you''re not like promoting any one specific resource to them.","index":379,"end_time":1807.32,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1791.55,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So kind of thinking through those ideas still.","index":380,"end_time":1810.92,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1808.84,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"That makes sense.","index":381,"end_time":1812.12,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1811.24,"speaker_name":"Joe Ragno"},{"text":"And then I, I think it''ll be pretty important also to establish some level of social media presence via LinkedIn and possibly MeTa, I think could be a good channel as well.","index":382,"end_time":1823.24,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1812.92,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay, after that.","index":383,"end_time":1825.24,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1824.2,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I''m sorry, go ahead.","index":384,"end_time":1826.12,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1825.24,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"No, no, I was just saying.","index":385,"end_time":1827.24,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1826.28,"speaker_name":"Joe Ragno"},{"text":"Okay.","index":386,"end_time":1827.56,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1827.24,"speaker_name":"Joe Ragno"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":387,"end_time":1827.88,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1827.56,"speaker_name":"Joe Ragno"},{"text":"And then after that, getting the treatment center outreach campaign launched.","index":388,"end_time":1833,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1828.44,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So building a list.","index":389,"end_time":1834.68,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1833,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"500,000 qualified treatment centers across the state.","index":390,"end_time":1838.26,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1835.22,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So you can see some of the ones that I was listing previously.","index":391,"end_time":1840.46,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1838.26,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"California, Florida, Texas, New York, New Jersey, Maryland and Pennsylvania, based on our research, have the most treatment centers and are the most open to these styles of conversations based on policies and legislature.","index":392,"end_time":1852.3,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1840.46,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"They also favor these types of solutions over some other states.","index":393,"end_time":1855.54,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1852.3,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So reaching out to chief operating officers, admissions directors, everything like that, the people who are really feeling the pain and want to see that that''s how the business grow as well.","index":394,"end_time":1865.06,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1856.66,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And then launching that via LinkedIn and email outreach as well as some advertising programs.","index":395,"end_time":1870.66,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1865.62,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And then as you and Tim are having conversations with these treatment centers, building some sales enablement materials so that you can go in with a slide deck or a one pager.","index":396,"end_time":1879.86,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1870.98,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I know that you mentioned in your message last week they kind of needed a one pager.","index":397,"end_time":1884.26,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1879.86,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"It''s.","index":398,"end_time":1884.74,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1884.26,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I think, Joe, we''ve had this conversation before.","index":399,"end_time":1887.38,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1885.7,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I mean, people are doing so much research on their own now before they even have a conversation.","index":400,"end_time":1891.81,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1887.38,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"They are, they''re about 75 to 80% made up in their mind of if they''re considering you or even need you or, or you''re maybe the perfect fit for them before they talk to you.","index":401,"end_time":1902.81,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1891.81,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So we need to have some documentation that we can provide or that they can easily access on the website and some other channels to entice them to have that conversation.","index":402,"end_time":1912.09,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1903.21,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Oftentimes they need to get some buy in from the rest of their staff before they can can even move forward with having that conversation.","index":403,"end_time":1918.58,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1912.33,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Do we have this in the budget?","index":404,"end_time":1919.86,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1918.58,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Are we dealing with any of these issues.","index":405,"end_time":1922.02,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1920.42,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Are we able to provide this as a solution to our team?","index":406,"end_time":1924.66,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1922.26,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Right, yeah, that was kind of what I gathered from the people that I had talked to.","index":407,"end_time":1929.54,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1925.38,"speaker_name":"Joe Ragno"},{"text":"Nobody said no.","index":408,"end_time":1931.86,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1930.9,"speaker_name":"Joe Ragno"},{"text":"They were just like, hey, we need more information.","index":409,"end_time":1933.46,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1931.86,"speaker_name":"Joe Ragno"},{"text":"Right?","index":410,"end_time":1934.18,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1933.78,"speaker_name":"Joe Ragno"},{"text":"Awesome.","index":411,"end_time":1937.14,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1936.5,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I don''t think we''ve shown you what we''ve rebuilt from our ABM campaign architecture, so this is really exciting.","index":412,"end_time":1945.31,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1938.02,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"It''s something that Tristan and I worked on very heavily in Q4.","index":413,"end_time":1948.91,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1945.63,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We have layered in a bunch of new tools, so I''ll just do a quick overview here.","index":414,"end_time":1953.95,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1949.47,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Starting still with Clay for our contact list and data enrichment using Smart lead and Heyreach for email and LinkedIn outreach, having the ad layer on top.","index":415,"end_time":1962.91,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1954.51,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"But now we also utilize RB2B and factors for website de anonymization.","index":416,"end_time":1967.55,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1963.07,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So in the US we can use RB2B and that will actually de anonymize on a person level basis.","index":417,"end_time":1973.19,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1967.79,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So when someone views the website, we get a slack message from RB2B.","index":418,"end_time":1977.66,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1974.14,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"This is their LinkedIn profile, this is their position, this is their current job.","index":419,"end_time":1981.66,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1978.38,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"If for any reason anything ever switches outside of the US Factors would be the solution there because it is GDRP compliant and only does account level de anonymization.","index":420,"end_time":1993.58,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1983.02,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Still a very useful tool to have in this stack because Factors not only de anonymizes website traffic, but it connects directly to LinkedIn via an API.","index":421,"end_time":2003.42,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1994.06,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And what LinkedIn doesn''t tell you, they''ll tell you, hey, you got this many clicks, they won''t tell you who actually saw your ad.","index":422,"end_time":2009.9,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2004.06,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Factors is able to de anonymize the accounts that have seen your ad.","index":423,"end_time":2013.22,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2010.06,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So we know, are we getting some, you know, some depth, some reach with certain companies, treatment centers, employers, etc.","index":424,"end_time":2020.14,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2013.22,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"From there you''re very familiar with N8N.","index":425,"end_time":2023.66,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2021.42,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We built a very robust N8N logic process with four different main webhooks that are just collecting information, storing them into Supabase and then we''re able to export that into a very clean report.","index":426,"end_time":2037.47,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2023.9,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So we''re able to see we sent this many emails this week, we sent this many messages.","index":427,"end_time":2041.79,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2037.47,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Here are the accounts that have been interacting the most with the messaging we''ve been sending out, browsing the website the most, etc.","index":428,"end_time":2049.23,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2042.43,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And then from there we''re able to make tweaks based on that data so we can say, hey, you know, this company has been browsing the website a lot, they haven''t responded to a message.","index":429,"end_time":2058.47,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2049.31,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So maybe we develop a really personalized 2, 3 email sequence to them or develop a one pager specifically with, you know, them in Mind really able to use those data points to know how we can get someone across the finish line in their decision.","index":430,"end_time":2071.649,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2058.47,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And then everything reported back in Databox as well.","index":431,"end_time":2075.329,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2072.609,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I know this is a lot, but I''m sure you''re following all the technology pieces here.","index":432,"end_time":2082.849,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2079.329,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, I think the RB2B and factors and N8N are like the newer pieces of this.","index":433,"end_time":2089.329,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2083.409,"speaker_name":"Joe Ragno"},{"text":"Well, Supabase too.","index":434,"end_time":2091.299,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2089.969,"speaker_name":"Joe Ragno"},{"text":"The rest I think we had.","index":435,"end_time":2094.85,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2092.89,"speaker_name":"Joe Ragno"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":436,"end_time":2095.29,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2094.85,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Last year.","index":437,"end_time":2095.81,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2095.37,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, absolutely.","index":438,"end_time":2097.45,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2095.81,"speaker_name":"Joe Ragno"},{"text":"Awesome.","index":439,"end_time":2098.77,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2098.25,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And then what I have next is the points plan.","index":440,"end_time":2101.29,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2098.77,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Before I hop into this, just want to give a space for any questions, any points that you guys wanted to talk through that we haven''t gone through so far?","index":441,"end_time":2108.09,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2101.29,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"No.","index":442,"end_time":2109.69,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":2109.29,"speaker_name":"timot"},{"text":"Awesome.","index":443,"end_time":2111.77,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2111.13,"speaker_name":"Joe Ragno"},{"text":"All right, well then hopping into the points plan, so we have some points to play with each month.","index":444,"end_time":2118.74,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2112.57,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"You guys get 40 points plus an additional 30 each month.","index":445,"end_time":2121.86,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2118.9,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So in the first one, again, really need to build the foundation.","index":446,"end_time":2125.7,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2122.82,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We need to build a logo, establish brand guidelines, have like our messaging rules, things like that.","index":447,"end_time":2131.22,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2125.7,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I wanted to also develop.","index":448,"end_time":2132.9,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2131.86,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I have slide deck or presentation.","index":449,"end_time":2134.94,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2133.46,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"If we want to switch that to one pager, we absolutely can.","index":450,"end_time":2137.34,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2134.94,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Just based on the conversation that you had last week and the message you sent over, felt like that was a pretty important thing for us to stand up quickly and be able to get out to the market and then developing the website.","index":451,"end_time":2148.44,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2137.34,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So that''s what month one would look like.","index":452,"end_time":2153.16,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2151.4,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We are considering January month one.","index":453,"end_time":2155.2,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2153.48,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So this will bleed a little bit.","index":454,"end_time":2156.68,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2155.2,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We''re not going to have everything here stood up by January 31st or 30th.","index":455,"end_time":2161.56,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2156.68,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Right.","index":456,"end_time":2162.44,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2162.04,"speaker_name":"Joe Ragno"},{"text":"But bleeding into a little bit of month two, we''ll continue that momentum after that.","index":457,"end_time":2169.8,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2163.32,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We''ll develop the ABM plan document and then all the assets needed for it.","index":458,"end_time":2173.32,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2169.8,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So the image ad creative, the emails, the paid media, we need to set up some accounts and we''ll help you with all of that.","index":459,"end_time":2180.62,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2173.32,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Then actually setting up all of the infrastructure that I just showed for ABM, managing the website and then with RB2B and factors and everything that''ll all go into the tech stack.","index":460,"end_time":2190.06,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2181.18,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And then finally shifting a little bit more towards the content plan.","index":461,"end_time":2196.98,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2193.26,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So we have ABM running.","index":462,"end_time":2198.38,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2196.98,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Let''s stand up this content series, develop the branding for that.","index":463,"end_time":2202.3,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2198.38,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Establish, you know, is Joe the host every time or Joe and Tim switching?","index":464,"end_time":2206.78,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2203.5,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Is it kind of a.","index":465,"end_time":2207.9,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2206.78,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Maybe we hop on and we interview you and we just cut ourselves out of the video.","index":466,"end_time":2212.06,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2208.46,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"There''s a bunch of different flavors that we can bake into that.","index":467,"end_time":2214.5,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2212.3,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So we''re coming up with exactly what that plan is and then just managing the campaigns and then, you know, as we transition into the next quarter we would, excuse me, develop new campaigns if we, you know, are moving and progressing really well with signing up treatment centers onto the platform, maybe shifting over towards the employer focus.","index":468,"end_time":2232.66,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2214.5,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"But we''ll need to establish some data, some baseline metrics before we can make a decision like that.","index":469,"end_time":2237.71,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2232.66,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Any questions around what I''ve laid out for the first three months?","index":470,"end_time":2242.27,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2239.87,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, it looks like there''s so in one month one and month three, it looks like there''s like a five point difference.","index":471,"end_time":2248.55,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2243.23,"speaker_name":"Joe Ragno"},{"text":"In month two it looks like there''s a 15 point difference.","index":472,"end_time":2250.87,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2248.55,"speaker_name":"Joe Ragno"},{"text":"Are we just assuming that we''re going to be taking some of those from future months or how are we looking at that?","index":473,"end_time":2257.39,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2250.87,"speaker_name":"Joe Ragno"},{"text":"Yeah, so you actually, for the three months you get.","index":474,"end_time":2260.35,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2257.55,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So you get 40 points per month plus 30 points per month.","index":475,"end_time":2263.59,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2260.83,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So 70 points each month, which is 210.","index":476,"end_time":2267.73,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2263.59,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And this barely puts you over.","index":477,"end_time":2270.69,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2268.85,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"But these are pieces we feel are very important and then you know, in working with us.","index":478,"end_time":2276.05,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2271.33,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So if we''re not standing up a brand new campaign in a month, we kind of go into like maintenance of that campaign so the cost can come back down and we can get back to net zero.","index":479,"end_time":2282.61,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2276.05,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"What''s the, what''s the question?","index":480,"end_time":2284.85,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2283.65,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"Where''s the question stemming from, Joe?","index":481,"end_time":2287.17,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2285.33,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"Yeah, no, it''s just there''s a, there''s a point difference.","index":482,"end_time":2289.53,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2287.41,"speaker_name":"Joe Ragno"},{"text":"So I don''t know if there''s a difference meaning like you need more financial buy in from me for these couple of months or if we''re just going.","index":483,"end_time":2295.77,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2289.53,"speaker_name":"Joe Ragno"},{"text":"To say okay, that, that, that where I thought the question.","index":484,"end_time":2298.59,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2295.77,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"No, you''re the, this is all, it''s all within scope.","index":485,"end_time":2301.87,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2298.67,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"Okay, so what do you have 75 here?","index":486,"end_time":2305.67,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2302.27,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"What''s next month, Colin?","index":487,"end_time":2306.75,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2305.67,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"Again?","index":488,"end_time":2309.39,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2308.99,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"75.","index":489,"end_time":2310.27,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2309.63,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"Yeah, so we''re over a little bit.","index":490,"end_time":2311.47,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2310.27,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"So we''ll, we''re basically borrowing from some, some future months in the idea that we''ll have to go down a little bit in months four through six.","index":491,"end_time":2320.67,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2311.47,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"We''re almost always front heavy because we need to write plans and stand things up.","index":492,"end_time":2328.76,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2320.91,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"And you also have, we also have to do a website and a brand guidelines document.","index":493,"end_time":2334.28,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2329.4,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"Right?","index":494,"end_time":2334.76,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2334.44,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, that''s, that''s just what I was verifying.","index":495,"end_time":2336.32,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2334.76,"speaker_name":"Joe Ragno"},{"text":"That we were just kind of pulling from future months.","index":496,"end_time":2338.6,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2336.32,"speaker_name":"Joe Ragno"},{"text":"That''s correct.","index":497,"end_time":2340.08,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2339.48,"speaker_name":"Joe Ragno"},{"text":"And requiring additional capital.","index":498,"end_time":2341.4,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2340.08,"speaker_name":"Joe Ragno"},{"text":"Okay, you got it.","index":499,"end_time":2343.56,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2341.48,"speaker_name":"Joe Ragno"},{"text":"All right, well that is the entire roadmap presentation and points plan.","index":500,"end_time":2349.4,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2345.48,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So opening up the floor to any questions or comments.","index":501,"end_time":2352.54,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2349.48,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, I don''t have a ton.","index":502,"end_time":2355.9,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2353.42,"speaker_name":"Joe Ragno"},{"text":"I did ask the majority of it, but I guess what was your impression of the competitive landscape when you were going through what our competitors do Versus we do versus what we do.","index":503,"end_time":2367.38,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2355.9,"speaker_name":"Joe Ragno"},{"text":"I mean, I know you''re going to be providing me that documentation.","index":504,"end_time":2370.02,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2367.38,"speaker_name":"Joe Ragno"},{"text":"It is quite lengthy, but just like a Cliff Notes version if you have one of your impression of, like I said, the competitive landscape here.","index":505,"end_time":2377.93,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2370.02,"speaker_name":"Joe Ragno"},{"text":"Here.","index":506,"end_time":2378.32,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2378.08,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":507,"end_time":2378.96,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2378.48,"speaker_name":"Joe Ragno"},{"text":"To be honest, Joe, I was a little nervous at your first conversation with Justin of like, Justin, there''s no one doing this in the market and we have a real opportunity here doing research.","index":508,"end_time":2388.24,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2379.12,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I see what you see.","index":509,"end_time":2389.92,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2388.8,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So do I think it''s going to be the easiest thing ever?","index":510,"end_time":2392.88,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2390.08,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"No, but I think that this is a, a gap in need in the, in the market space and your competitors, or even like pseudo competitors, because they''re not direct, are not really doing much from a marketing perspective.","index":511,"end_time":2407.19,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2392.96,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We see like Spring Health has a strong brand and Lear has a strong, you know, content marketing plan.","index":512,"end_time":2412.79,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2407.19,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Other than that, like, no one is actually hitting the full, like every channel.","index":513,"end_time":2417.71,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2413.35,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"They''re not actually syndicating across.","index":514,"end_time":2419.11,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2417.71,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"They don''t have a full strategy that''s bleeding into every area of marketing that they should.","index":515,"end_time":2423.59,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2419.11,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And I think that they, between the competitors, some of them are a little too broad as like, we do this, then we have Plago, that''s like kind of that gatekeeper that we talked about.","index":516,"end_time":2435.1,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2424.63,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And then we have Spring Health that''s, they seem to be growing very quickly as well.","index":517,"end_time":2439.9,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2435.18,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Lira also only focusing on enterprise.","index":518,"end_time":2442.54,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2440.06,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So there''s a lot of like gaps in the market space that Treatment Navigator can fit directly into, build, you know, some share of the market and then start to reach up towards those enterprise level companies.","index":519,"end_time":2453.98,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2442.54,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, I guess because my concern was last time we didn''t see much if any competition.","index":520,"end_time":2460.97,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2454.54,"speaker_name":"Joe Ragno"},{"text":"And you know that, that''s great if, if you have a ton of money to make, people care about something.","index":521,"end_time":2468.57,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2461.13,"speaker_name":"Joe Ragno"},{"text":"But that was kind of the, oh, crap.","index":522,"end_time":2473.45,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2470.09,"speaker_name":"Joe Ragno"},{"text":"I think as we got further down, it''s like, well, maybe now there''s a reason why there''s no competition.","index":523,"end_time":2478.89,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2473.61,"speaker_name":"Joe Ragno"},{"text":"Yeah, I see it a little bit differently here because I think that they''re, there''s pseudo competition.","index":524,"end_time":2484.33,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2479.29,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Right.","index":525,"end_time":2484.53,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2484.33,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Like, it''s not the exact offering that Treatment Navigator is making.","index":526,"end_time":2488.49,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2484.53,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I think Treatment Navigators has found that gap in what employers and employees are seeking and treatment centers.","index":527,"end_time":2495.69,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2488.81,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"No one''s going to turn down leads.","index":528,"end_time":2497.25,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2495.69,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I mean, these are qualified leads.","index":529,"end_time":2498.69,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2497.25,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Why would they ever say no?","index":530,"end_time":2500.33,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2498.69,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So I think it''s carved out a true, like, need in the space.","index":531,"end_time":2504.49,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2501.05,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay.","index":532,"end_time":2505.69,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2505.13,"speaker_name":"Joe Ragno"},{"text":"That was my big questions.","index":533,"end_time":2511.45,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2510.09,"speaker_name":"Joe Ragno"},{"text":"I don''t know if Tim has anything.","index":534,"end_time":2513.46,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2511.45,"speaker_name":"Joe Ragno"},{"text":"Yeah, no, I''m okay.","index":535,"end_time":2517.34,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":2514.98,"speaker_name":"timot"},{"text":"I, I, you asked a question.","index":536,"end_time":2519.78,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":2517.34,"speaker_name":"timot"},{"text":"I, I had.","index":537,"end_time":2520.98,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":2519.86,"speaker_name":"timot"},{"text":"So we''re good.","index":538,"end_time":2522.1,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":2520.98,"speaker_name":"timot"},{"text":"And Cleared it up.","index":539,"end_time":2523.3,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2522.18,"speaker_name":"Joe Ragno"},{"text":"Awesome.","index":540,"end_time":2525.14,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2524.5,"speaker_name":"Joe Ragno"},{"text":"Awesome.","index":541,"end_time":2526.02,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2525.46,"speaker_name":"Joe Ragno"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":542,"end_time":2526.54,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2526.18,"speaker_name":"Joe Ragno"},{"text":"I think the biggest thing is that we want to get you website.","index":543,"end_time":2530.66,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2526.54,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"You gotta.","index":544,"end_time":2531.46,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2530.82,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"Gotta exist, gotta have the website, gotta have the brand.","index":545,"end_time":2534.18,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2531.46,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"And then I think was it in month one, Colin, that you''re also putting together some sort of deck?","index":546,"end_time":2537.74,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2534.18,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"Yeah, yeah.","index":547,"end_time":2539.89,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2538.69,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So then the ability to sell, I mean, or to at least talk about your product, I mean that is action item one here.","index":548,"end_time":2547.73,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2539.89,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"You need to come off real.","index":549,"end_time":2551.01,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2547.73,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"Right.","index":550,"end_time":2552.45,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2552.05,"speaker_name":"Joe Ragno"},{"text":"I guess that does bring up another question then.","index":551,"end_time":2555.57,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2553.41,"speaker_name":"Joe Ragno"},{"text":"So I know you guys have utilized Lovable for some of the tech offerings that you''ve created.","index":552,"end_time":2565.41,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2555.81,"speaker_name":"Joe Ragno"},{"text":"How do you kind of pair that with the website?","index":553,"end_time":2569.49,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2567.57,"speaker_name":"Joe Ragno"},{"text":"Is that something where you kind of just have a website separately where somebody clicks on a button and they navigate to that page?","index":554,"end_time":2576.45,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2569.65,"speaker_name":"Joe Ragno"},{"text":"What is the thought around navigating that?","index":555,"end_time":2581.89,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2577.33,"speaker_name":"Joe Ragno"},{"text":"Because that''s.","index":556,"end_time":2582.77,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2581.97,"speaker_name":"Joe Ragno"},{"text":"I''m using Lovable as well for the foundation of this.","index":557,"end_time":2586.37,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2582.93,"speaker_name":"Joe Ragno"},{"text":"So is it worth me connecting?","index":558,"end_time":2589.49,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2586.53,"speaker_name":"Joe Ragno"},{"text":"You know, I think I found TreatmentNavigator app was a good domain.","index":559,"end_time":2597.63,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2590.69,"speaker_name":"Joe Ragno"},{"text":"And it.","index":560,"end_time":2599.95,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2599.47,"speaker_name":"Joe Ragno"},{"text":"Was only like 20 bucks for the domain, so I think I could grab that.","index":561,"end_time":2602.95,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2599.95,"speaker_name":"Joe Ragno"},{"text":"But like, is that something where it''s worth just grabbing that, connecting it on the.","index":562,"end_time":2607.07,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2602.95,"speaker_name":"Joe Ragno"},{"text":"The lovable side and then kind of building the website off of that or kind of keeping them separate?","index":563,"end_time":2612.83,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2607.629,"speaker_name":"Joe Ragno"},{"text":"Yeah, so I think that''s a great domain.","index":564,"end_time":2615.63,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2613.23,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So we''re gonna have Lovable as the front end like user interface and then build a database for the back end.","index":565,"end_time":2621.31,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2616.51,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We''ve done this for a few sites, so we ever even want to get into blog posts, it''s very easy to build that, that query of like I want it to be this and then create a custom post on the website content perspective.","index":566,"end_time":2632.81,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2621.63,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So it''s all going to be built in this backend database so that we have a very lightweight website for you to utilize.","index":567,"end_time":2638.65,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2632.81,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I''m not sure if we''re going to use Supabase or exactly what we''re going to use for it, but I know that we''ve, we''ve built a few websites with, with the backend database there.","index":568,"end_time":2646.33,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2638.97,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay.","index":569,"end_time":2647.37,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2646.81,"speaker_name":"Joe Ragno"},{"text":"Awesome.","index":570,"end_time":2652.58,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2652.18,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Any other questions?","index":571,"end_time":2654.02,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2652.66,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"No, I think I''m good for now.","index":572,"end_time":2657.38,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2655.38,"speaker_name":"Joe Ragno"},{"text":"All right, well, I''m very excited to get started here, Joe.","index":573,"end_time":2660.98,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2657.78,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Like I said, I.","index":574,"end_time":2662.02,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2661.14,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"The research component really made me even more excited than I was from our conversations where I was already excited.","index":575,"end_time":2667.7,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2662.18,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"But I love pouring this initial foundation as well.","index":576,"end_time":2671.46,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2668.26,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Building a company, having the go to market strategy and then getting out there and seeing what the data tells us and where we need to make an upgrade.","index":577,"end_time":2677.19,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2671.46,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Pivot.","index":578,"end_time":2677.74,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2677.26,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Sounds good to me.","index":579,"end_time":2679.58,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2678.62,"speaker_name":"Joe Ragno"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":580,"end_time":2680.3,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2679.82,"speaker_name":"Joe Ragno"},{"text":"All right, so Colin, next step, weekly meeting and let''s get.","index":581,"end_time":2684.02,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2680.62,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"Let''s get going on the website plan and the brand guidelines document.","index":582,"end_time":2688.7,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2684.02,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":583,"end_time":2689.82,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2689.34,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Joe, do you want me to send over an availability link or do you want to lock in our weekly meeting right now?","index":584,"end_time":2694.7,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2689.98,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Send over an availability link.","index":585,"end_time":2697.26,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2695.5,"speaker_name":"Joe Ragno"},{"text":"Just because I''m not sure what Tim''s avail availability is going to look like in conjunction with mine, so.","index":586,"end_time":2703.98,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2697.58,"speaker_name":"Joe Ragno"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":587,"end_time":2704.22,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2703.98,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":588,"end_time":2704.61,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2704.29,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"But I would hopefully, if we can find some common ground on a time that works for you guys as well, like to, you know, set a.","index":589,"end_time":2714.37,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2707.09,"speaker_name":"Joe Ragno"},{"text":"Like how we had before, where it was like Fridays at noon or something like that.","index":590,"end_time":2717.97,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2714.69,"speaker_name":"Joe Ragno"},{"text":"Yeah, whatever works for you guys.","index":591,"end_time":2719.65,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2718.13,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Cool.","index":592,"end_time":2720.69,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2720.21,"speaker_name":"Joe Ragno"},{"text":"All right, guys, we''ll send that over.","index":593,"end_time":2723.41,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2721.09,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"Let''s get it going.","index":594,"end_time":2724.77,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2723.89,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"Sounds good.","index":595,"end_time":2726.13,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2725.57,"speaker_name":"Joe Ragno"},{"text":"Thanks, Justin.","index":596,"end_time":2726.81,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2726.13,"speaker_name":"Joe Ragno"},{"text":"Thanks, Colin.","index":597,"end_time":2727.41,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2726.81,"speaker_name":"Joe Ragno"},{"text":"Thanks.","index":598,"end_time":2727.81,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2727.41,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Thank you.","index":599,"end_time":2728.61,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2728.05,"speaker_name":"Joe Ragno"},{"text":"Take care.","index":600,"end_time":2730.53,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":2729.97,"speaker_name":"timot"},{"text":"Bye.","index":601,"end_time":2731.29,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2730.85,"speaker_name":"Joe Ragno"},{"text":"Bye, Tim.","index":602,"end_time":2731.81,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2731.29,"speaker_name":"Joe Ragno"}],"dateString":"2026-01-21T14:30:00.000Z","host_email":"colin.costigan@marketersindemand.com","meeting_link":"https://us02web.zoom.us/j/89661160528?pwd=KQASOzvolzWNcOxmA0hA2mfi1J6peZ.1","participants":["nathalie.mintjens@marketersindemand.com,dan.renyi@marketersindemand.com,tristan.pelligrino@marketersindemand.com,justin.brown@marketersindemand.com,tim@autobytes.io,colin.costigan@marketersindemand.com,joe@autobytes.io","nathalie.mintjens@marketersindemand.com","dan.renyi@marketersindemand.com","tristan.pelligrino@marketersindemand.com","justin.brown@marketersindemand.com","tim@autobytes.io","joe@autobytes.io"],"transcript_url":"https://app.fireflies.ai/view/01KEYJNFJ5A480TR8EEP8XGTVE","organizer_email":"colin.costigan@marketersindemand.com"}'::jsonb,
    '{"label":"positive","confidence":0.94,"bullets":["Outlined four target customer segments, confirmed persona alignment and opportunity with employer and provider focus.","Shared 140-page industry analysis covering SEO, paid, and competitive positioning across key market players.","Proposed Q1 roadmap includes brand guidelines, three-page site, one-pager, and ABM campaign foundation.","Clarified Treatment Navigator’s positioning as a unique middle-layer solution bridging treatment centers and employers.","Confirmed use of robust ABM tech stack, including RB2B, Factors, and Supabase for outreach and optimization."],"highlights":[{"quote":"We are certainly carving out an area that''s missing right now.","speaker":"Colin Costigan"},{"quote":"This looks awesome. This is better than anything I could ever thought of.","speaker":"Joe Ragno"},{"quote":"Do I think it''s going to be the easiest thing ever? No... but this is a gap in the market.","speaker":"Colin Costigan"}],"topics":["launch","strategy","delivery","competitive","ABM","targeting"],"model":"openai/gpt-4-1106-preview","version":1,"generated_at":"2026-01-21T00:00:00Z"}'::jsonb,
    '{"fireflies_summary":{"notes":"## **Target Market Definition and Segmentation**\n\nThe team finalized three target market segments to focus initial outreach and platform growth efforts effectively (03:50).\n\n- **Behavioral health and substance use treatment centers** were identified as the primary onboarding target, with firms generating between **$2 million and $30 million in revenue** and employing **25 to 500 people** (08:11).\n    - These centers typically hold titles like Chief Operating Officer or Admissions Director, facing challenges such as poor lead flow and underutilized bed capacity.\n    - Onboarding these centers first ensures there is a robust network for employers and employees to engage with once outreach begins.\n    - Joe Ragno confirmed alignment with this segment based on his existing network and outreach efforts.\n    - Integration opportunities with EMR systems like Kaipu were noted to enhance platform value.\n\n- **Mid-market employers** represent the second segment, targeting industries such as manufacturing, construction, healthcare, and hospitality, with revenue between **$20 million and $500 million** and employee counts from **100 to 1,000** (11:58).\n    - These employers may bolt Treatment Navigator onto existing Employee Assistance Programs (EAPs), emphasizing recruiting, retention, and employee wellbeing.\n    - The focus is on executive HR roles such as Chief People Officer and HR managers, who need scalable mental health and addiction solutions.\n    - This wide net ensures no early market share is missed, with plans to build credibility through early proof points from smaller companies.\n\n- The third segment targets **fast-growing technology, SaaS, and professional services companies** with revenues ranging from **$100 million to $2 billion** and employee headcounts between **1,000 and 5,000** (13:41).\n    - These companies require quick deployment of affordable, comprehensive mental health solutions to support rapid recruiting.\n    - Outreach will focus on CHRO-level executives who demand volume discounts and smooth onboarding.\n    - Joe Ragno confirmed readiness to offer volume-based pricing to accommodate this segment''s needs.\n  \n- Additionally, insurance brokerages, benefits consulting, and human capital firms were segmented separately to tailor messaging and proof points, distinguishing them from EAP providers (14:45).\n\n## **Brand Positioning and Messaging Framework**\n\nThe team developed a brand story positioning both treatment centers and employers as heroes, emphasizing the platform’s role in simplifying access to mental health and substance use treatment (16:19).\n\n- Treatment centers are positioned as mission-driven heroes receiving qualified leads without traditional advertising pressure, enhancing bed utilization and patient intake efficiency.\n- Employers are portrayed as champions providing quick, anonymous access to treatment options for employees, reducing administrative burdens and compliance risks.\n- Joe Ragno advised shifting messaging focus from substance use to broader mental health to avoid advertising restrictions and expand appeal (20:01).\n- The brand story is designed to be dynamic and evolve as product development and marketing campaigns progress, ensuring ongoing alignment with market feedback.\n- Colin emphasized that this foundational messaging will drive subsequent website content, sales materials, and outreach campaigns.\n\n## **Competitive Landscape and Market Opportunity**\n\nThe competitive analysis revealed a fragmented market with no direct competitor fully addressing the niche Treatment Navigator targets, offering a strong opportunity for differentiation (20:56).\n\n- Spring Health boasts a strong brand with a **9 out of 10 score** in key marketing categories but lacks paid advertising and organic social presence outside of YouTube (22:09).\n    - Their focus is more on substance use and mental health combined, with a large YouTube library but limited paid media.\n- Lira targets enterprise clients with **over 268,000 LinkedIn followers**, emphasizing thought leadership and paid social campaigns but less direct mental health messaging (23:38).\n- Pelago shows minimal presence, low domain authority, and limited SEO or social media activity, acting as a gatekeeper with a referral-first model (24:58).\n- Treatment Navigator currently has no presence but fills a clear market gap by combining targeted lead generation for treatment centers with streamlined employer engagement.\n- Colin reassured Joe that while competitors exist, none fully cover the market needs Treatment Navigator addresses, particularly at the mid-market and employer integration level (39:39).\n\n## **Roadmap and Quarterly Priorities**\n\nThe immediate focus is on building a solid foundation with website launch, sales materials, and campaign infrastructure in the first two quarters (26:59).\n\n- A **three-page website** will be drafted, designed, and developed with tracking to monitor visitor behavior and engagement (29:02).\n- Sales enablement materials, including a **one-pager or slide deck**, will be created promptly to support outreach and address prospects’ self-education needs (31:20).\n- The team plans to launch a **content series** named tentatively \"Agnostic Advisor,\" producing video episodes featuring conversations with treatment centers, employers, and industry guests (29:02).\n- Social media presence will be established primarily on LinkedIn and potentially Meta platforms to build brand awareness and engagement (30:12).\n- Treatment center outreach campaigns will target **500,000 qualified centers across key states** like California, Florida, Texas, New York, New Jersey, Maryland, and Pennsylvania, focusing on COOs and admissions directors (30:28).\n- ABM campaign architecture will leverage advanced tools such as **RB2B and Factors** for website visitor de-anonymization and lead enrichment, integrated with N8N workflows and Supabase databases to generate actionable reports (33:14).\n- Metrics and engagement data will inform ongoing campaign optimization, with baseline data collected to time shifts from treatment centers to employer focus (28:34).\n\n## **Technology Stack and Process Enhancements**\n\nThe marketing tech stack is enhanced with new tools to improve lead identification, data enrichment, and campaign management, enabling precise targeting and reporting (33:14).\n\n- RB2B and Factors tools provide granular de-anonymization of website visitors on a person or account level, improving lead qualification and outreach accuracy.\n- N8N automates data collection and processing, storing interactions in Supabase for clean reporting and campaign adjustments.\n- Slack integrations alert the team in real-time about high-value visitors, enabling timely personalized follow-ups.\n- Colin explained the website will integrate with Lovable as the front end UI, backed by a database (potentially Supabase), to maintain a lightweight and scalable platform supporting blog posts and custom content (43:00).\n- The system architecture supports easy content updates and future integrations, ensuring agility as marketing and product strategies evolve.\n\n## **Budgeting, Resource Allocation, and Meeting Cadence**\n\nThe team agreed to front-load effort and budget in the first quarter to establish brand and infrastructure, borrowing points from future months to cover initial scope (35:12).\n\n- **Monthly points** total **70 points** (40 base plus 30 additional), with **210 points over three months** allocated primarily toward website, brand guidelines, campaign plans, and content production.\n- Colin clarified that heavier investment in initial months will be balanced by maintenance phases in later months to manage budget and effort.\n- Joe confirmed no additional capital is required beyond this scope, easing financial planning (37:37).\n- Weekly meetings will be scheduled to maintain momentum, with Colin to send availability links to coordinate times accommodating Joe and Tim’s schedules (44:40).\n- Justin emphasized that the website launch and sales collateral are the highest priority immediate actions to establish market presence and support sales conversations (42:06).","outline":null,"keywords":["Treatment Navigator","Marketing Roadmap","Target Market","Competitive Analysis","Account-Based Marketing","Brand Storytelling"],"overview":"- **Target Market Focus:** Three segments identified: behavioral health centers, mid-market employers, and fast-growing tech firms for outreach.\n\n- **Market Segment Details:** Treatment centers; $2-$30M revenue, 25-500 employees. Mid-markets; $20-$500M revenue, 100-1,000 employees. Tech firms; $100M-$2B revenue, 1,000-5,000 employees.\n\n- **Brand Messaging Strategy:** Position treatment centers as heroes simplifying mental health access, while employers champion employee wellbeing and compliance.\n\n- **Competitive Analysis Insight:** Fragmented market with no direct competitor fully addressing Treatment Navigator''s niche, highlighting strong differentiation opportunity.\n\n- **Quarterly Priorities:** Focus on website, sales materials, and outreach campaigns in Q1, targeting 500,000 qualified treatment centers across key states. \n\n- **Tech Enhancements:** New tools for lead identification and data management to improve outreach and campaign reporting, integrating real-time alerts for high-value visitors.","action_items":"\n**Colin Costigan**\nSend full 140-page marketing research document and roadmap presentation to Joe for review (07:23)\nShare availability link to schedule weekly meetings coordinating between all parties (44:49)\nBegin drafting, designing, and developing three-page website including basic tracking (35:00)\nDevelop brand guidelines including logo, messaging framework, and sales enablement materials (slide deck or one-pager) (35:00)\nBuild ABM plan document with full campaign assets (image creatives, email